The core product is a software platform that connects to smart or conventional trainers, measuring power output and cadence to simulate real-world cycling conditions. Users can explore virtual environments, join group rides, participate in races, and follow structured workouts. Zwift also offers mobile and TV apps for controlling the experience and tracking progress across devices.

Targeting competitive cyclists and fitness enthusiasts, Zwift has grown significantly, with over 550,000 accounts reported as of early 2018. The company has attracted substantial investment to enhance its platform and expand into esports and broader fitness markets. Zwift merges fitness, gaming, and social interaction, creating a community-driven experience in indoor training.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/246.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'zwift', null), ('51', 'Lightricks', 'Lightricks UK Limited', 'https://lightricks.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lightricks/', 'Lightricks is an AI-first technology company founded in 2013 by a group of entrepreneurs, including four Ph.D. students from Hebrew University. Based in Jerusalem, Israel, Lightricks specializes in developing advanced photo and video editing software that empowers individual creators and businesses to bring their ideas to life.

The company offers a suite of popular mobile applications, including Facetune for photo retouching, Photoleap for creative photo editing, and Videoleap for video editing. Other applications like Filtertune, Beatleap, Artleap, Lightleap, and Boosted cater to a wide range of creative needs. Lightricks employs a freemium business model, allowing users to access its apps for free with optional premium features available through in-app purchases or subscriptions. With nearly 700 million downloads and over 30 million monthly active users, Lightricks has established a strong market presence.

In addition to its editing tools, Lightricks operates Popular Pays, an influencer marketing platform that connects creators with brands. The company has raised approximately $335 million in funding and is valued at around $1.8 billion, employing over 600 people and generating estimated annual revenues of about $236 million.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/230.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'module', null), ('52', 'AnyVan', 'AnyVan Ltd', 'https://www.anyvan.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/anyvan/', 'AnyVan is a UK-based online marketplace founded in 2009 by Angus Elphinstone and Ben Goor. The company specializes in large-item delivery, removals, vehicle transport, and storage services. It connects customers with transport partners who bid for jobs along their existing routes, optimizing vehicle capacity and reducing delivery costs by about 40%. AnyVan operates across the UK and several European countries, including Germany, Ireland, Spain, France, and Italy.

The company has developed a technology platform that uses algorithms to enhance logistics efficiency and minimize environmental impact. AnyVan is committed to sustainability, achieving carbon-neutral status for all transport moves and actively reducing CO2 emissions. They also support charitable initiatives through their Magic Van service, which provides free deliveries for nominated charities. With a focus on innovation and customer experience, AnyVan continues to grow its tech team to tackle complex logistics challenges.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '3', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/381.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/anyvan', null), ('53', 'Ben', 'Thanks Ben Ltd', 'https://www.thanksben.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/thanksben/', 'Thanks Ben Ltd, based in London, is a private limited company founded in November 2019. The company offers an innovative platform for managing global, flexible employee benefits. Its mission is to simplify the complexities of employee benefits and unlock value in benefits spending.

The platform centralizes and automates the administration of various employee benefits, allowing companies to consolidate options like pensions, health and life insurance, and wellbeing budgets into one flexible system. Employees can personalize their benefits by allocating budgets and choosing from a wide range of options across mental, physical, social, and financial wellbeing categories. Key features include streamlined benefit enrollment, flexible spending allowances, communication tools for decision support, and transparent reporting through total reward statements.

Ben targets global companies looking to enhance employee engagement and wellbeing with tailored benefits programs. The company is rapidly growing, with a dedicated team focused on creating a better benefits ecosystem that meets diverse employee needs.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '7', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/19.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/ben', null), ('54', 'Everun', 'Everun Limited', 'https://everun.ltd/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/everun/', 'Everun is a Chinese manufacturer and exporter based in Qingdao, specializing in mini and medium-sized wheel loaders ranging from 0.6 to 5 tons. The company also offers a diverse range of machinery, including excavators, forklifts, skid steer loaders, bulldozers, road rollers, trailers, telescopic loaders, and backhoes. Established in 2007, Everun has built a strong global presence, with its products operating in over 160 countries through a wide distributor network.

The company places a strong emphasis on research and development, with teams in both China and Europe focused on enhancing product design based on customer feedback. Everun''s equipment is designed for safety, efficiency, and operator comfort, meeting international standards such as CE certification and safety regulations like ROPS and FOPS. With a commitment to quality and customer service, Everun supports its clients through a comprehensive service network, including after-sales support and spare parts delivery. The company serves customers in agriculture, construction, and industrial sectors, particularly in Europe and Oceania.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1078.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('55', 'Financial House', 'Financial House Limited', 'https://www.financialhouse.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/financialhouse/', 'Financial House is a fintech company based in London, UK, specializing in credit card and transaction processing services. With around 409 employees, the company focuses on providing multi-currency payment solutions that are efficient and compliant with global security standards. Financial House operates as a private limited company and serves clients in over 90 countries.

The company offers a range of services, including the issuance of branded prepaid, gift, and debit cards as a principal member of Visa, Mastercard, and UnionPay International. Its PCI-DSS Level 1 certified platform features a single API that allows UK businesses to securely accept global payments. Financial House also provides access to key payment systems like SEPA, Faster Payments, BACS, and CHAPS, along with a comprehensive dashboard for transaction monitoring. Additionally, the company offers expert legal and compliance services to help clients navigate regulatory requirements in the UK.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1209.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('56', 'Civica', 'Civica UK Limited', 'https://www.civica.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/civica/', 'Civica is an international software company based in London, UK, specializing in cloud-based solutions for the public sector. With regional offices in Australia, Singapore, and North America, Civica supports over 5,000 public bodies and serves more than 100 million citizens globally. The company focuses on digital transformation by modernizing legacy systems through innovative software, data management, and automation.

Civica offers a wide range of software and IT services tailored to various public sector domains, including local government administration, social housing management, and health services. Their solutions encompass cloud platforms, specialist systems, and managed services designed to enhance operational efficiency and service delivery. Civica''s software supports critical public services such as education, financial management, and public safety, benefiting over 2.5 million professionals in the public sector. Recognized as a leader in GovTech, Civica is committed to helping organizations deliver essential services effectively.', 'The company cannot sponsor Graduate roles. Their policy regarding other roles is unclear.', '3', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1263.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'civica-uk-ltd-1', null), ('57', 'UK Research & Innovation (UKRI)', 'UK Research and Innovation', 'https://www.ukri.org/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/uk-research-innovation/', 'UK Research and Innovation (UKRI) is a non-departmental public body of the UK Government, established on April 1, 2018. Headquartered in Swindon, Wiltshire, UKRI is sponsored by the Department for Science, Innovation and Technology. Its mission is to invest in research and innovation to enhance lives, stimulate economic growth, and create jobs and high-quality public services throughout the UK.

UKRI brings together nine organizations, including seven research councils and Innovate UK, to support a wide range of research and development initiatives. It invests between £7 billion and £8 billion annually in various sectors, including biodiversity, quantum computing, space exploration, and healthcare. UKRI also provides funding for postgraduate researchers and universities, and runs programs to assist businesses in bringing innovations to market. Its partnerships span universities, research organizations, businesses, charities, and government agencies, all aimed at advancing scientific knowledge and addressing societal challenges.', 'The organisation is a public body and can sponsor visas on a case-by-case basis. We have excluded any that definitely cannot be.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/770.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('58', 'biomodal', 'Cambridge Epigenetix Ltd', 'https://biomodal.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/biomodal/', 'biomodal is a life-sciences technology and analytics company founded in 2012, based in the UK. The company specializes in developing advanced multiomics research tools that integrate genetic and epigenetic information from a single sample. Their flagship product, the duet multiomics solution, allows researchers to extract detailed epigenetic information from low input DNA libraries without the need for complex bioinformatics or harsh chemical treatments.

The duet solution distinguishes between standard DNA bases and modified cytosine bases, which are crucial for research in cancer, neurodegenerative diseases, and aging. biomodal employs a single-base-resolution, phased sequencing approach that combines genetic and epigenetic data in one workflow, enhancing the accuracy and depth of biological insights. This technology is designed to simplify multiomic analysis, making it a valuable resource for life scientists and clinical developers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1116.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'biomodal', null), ('59', 'Amplifi Capital', 'AMPLIFI CAPITAL (U.K.) LIMITED', 'https://www.amplificapital.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/amplifi-capital-u-k-ltd/', 'Amplifi Capital (U.K.) Limited is a consumer lending platform established in 2013 and operational since 2015. The company focuses on providing unsecured personal loans to near prime consumers in the UK who may struggle to access credit from traditional banks. Amplifi Capital aims to create a fairer financial community by supporting community-oriented financial institutions such as Credit Unions and Community Development Finance Institutions (CDFIs).

The company offers a fintech ecosystem centered around its proprietary platform, Gojoko, designed specifically for Credit Unions. This platform integrates various software providers and utilizes in-house technology to automate essential processes like credit checks and identity verification. Amplifi Capital serves approximately 120,000 customers, with a loan book of around £450 million and a total loan amount disbursed of about £850 million. The company is headquartered in London and is committed to ethical lending practices while empowering both borrowers and community financial institutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1150.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'ampcap', null), ('62', 'Silverfin', 'Silverfin Software Ltd', 'https://silverfin.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/silverfin/', 'Silverfin is a cloud-based accounting software company that provides a platform tailored for accountancy firms. Founded by accountants and software experts, Silverfin''s platform enhances efficiency, accuracy, and profitability in compliance and reporting services. It integrates various functions, including working papers, accounts production, corporation tax, and management reporting into a customizable cloud environment.

The platform automates core accounting workflows, allowing accountants to prepare financial statements, complete tax computations, and generate management reports more quickly and accurately. It supports real-time data integration from clients'' bookkeeping systems and over 50 leading financial software sources, ensuring data consistency. Silverfin''s offerings include automated working papers, customizable financial statements, management reports, tax computations, and a secure data hub for collaboration. The platform is designed for accountancy firms and finance teams in growing companies, helping them improve client service and streamline operations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/399.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('64', 'Zencargo', 'Worldwide Freight Logistics Ltd', 'https://www.zencargo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zencargo/', 'Zencargo is a London-based freight forwarder and logistics provider founded in 2016. The company focuses on modernizing the freight forwarding industry by using technology, including machine learning, to enhance supply chain operations and reduce costs. Zencargo offers a technology platform that allows customers to book, manage, and track international shipments across sea, air, and road transport modes. This platform provides real-time data and analytics, enabling businesses to make informed supply chain decisions.

The services provided by Zencargo include ocean, air, and rail freight forwarding, as well as trucking and cargo insurance. The platform promotes collaboration among shippers and partners by storing supply chain data in the cloud, which improves operational efficiency. Zencargo serves a diverse range of clients, from large FTSE 100 companies to startups, helping them modernize their supply chains and enhance visibility. With over 250 employees and significant funding, Zencargo is committed to driving change in the logistics sector through data, revenue optimization, and sustainability.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/555.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('66', 'Expensify', 'Expensify Limited', 'https://www.expensify.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/expensify/', 'Expensify, Inc. is a software company founded in 2008 by CEO David Barrett, specializing in expense management solutions for personal and business use. Its flagship product is an all-in-one app that helps over 15 million users globally track expenses, manage corporate cards, send invoices, pay bills, and book travel. The platform automates receipt scanning and expense tracking, making it user-friendly and suitable for individuals, small businesses, teams, and accounting professionals.

The company also offers the Expensify Card, enhancing its expense management capabilities. Expensify focuses on improving the employee experience with expense reporting, encouraging timely use and compliance. Additionally, Expensify.org, a charitable initiative launched in 2020, provides free access to the app for tracking volunteer expenses, promoting transparency in charitable giving. With a distributed workforce across various cities, Expensify has raised multiple rounds of venture capital and went public in November 2021 under the ticker EXFY.', 'The company can offer visa sponsorship and relocation assistance.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1220.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'expensify', null), ('67', 'Mimica', 'Mimica Automation Ltd', 'https://www.mimica.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mimica-automation/', 'Mimica is an AI-driven enterprise software company that specializes in task mining and process intelligence. Their technology captures user interactions, such as clicks and keystrokes, to create detailed process maps that highlight inefficiencies and automation opportunities. This approach provides organizations with enhanced visibility into their workflows, helping them achieve their digital transformation goals.

Mimica''s flagship product, Miner, automatically records and analyzes user activity to generate comprehensive process maps. Their Mapper tool converts interaction data into accurate process flowcharts and documentation, while the platform also offers automation roadmaps that prioritize workflows for improvement. With features like continuous monitoring and compliance with security protocols, Mimica supports large enterprises in sectors such as finance, insurance, and technology. The company is recognized as a leader in Digital Interaction Intelligence and has helped clients save millions in productivity through its innovative solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '8', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/141.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/mimica', null), ('68', 'Ravelin', 'Ravelin Technology Limited', 'https://www.ravelin.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ravelin-technology/', 'Ravelin Technology Ltd. is a private limited company based in London, England, founded in 2014. It specializes in AI-native fraud prevention and payments optimization solutions aimed at securing online commerce. Ravelin is recognized as a leading platform in fraud prevention, leveraging artificial intelligence to analyze historical data and detect patterns indicative of fraudulent activity.

The company offers a comprehensive fraud prediction and prevention platform that addresses various fraud vectors, including payment fraud detection, account takeover prevention, and marketplace fraud protection. Its technology provides real-time risk assessment and decision-making support, enabling merchants to accept more legitimate payments while minimizing false declines. Ravelin serves ambitious online merchants and global brands that require robust fraud prevention to protect their digital transactions. 

In early 2025, Ravelin was acquired by Worldpay International Group Ltd., enhancing its strategic value within the payments and fraud prevention ecosystem. This acquisition positions Ravelin to scale and integrate with extensive payment processing infrastructure, supporting omni-commerce globally.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/95.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'ravelin', null), ('69', 'ZILO', 'ZILO Technology Limited', 'https://www.zilo.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zilo-technology/', 'ZILO™ is a private limited company based in the UK, specializing in innovative software solutions for the global asset and wealth management sectors. Founded in 2023, with a related entity established in 2020, ZILO operates from its London office. The company focuses on delivering cloud-native software services that adapt to changing market conditions and regulatory environments.

ZILO™ offers a unified global software platform that consolidates Transfer Agency services, aiming to reduce costs and complexity for asset and wealth management firms. Their solutions are designed for high reliability, boasting over 99.9% uptime, and scalable performance to handle varying volumes of processes. The team at ZILO™ consists of experts in software, operations, and product development, bringing extensive industry knowledge to their clients.

With a commitment to being a long-term partner, ZILO™ emphasizes core values that guide its organizational culture and business success. The company is dedicated to providing future-ready software solutions that create sustainable value for its clients in the financial services industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1151.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('70', 'Sciensus', 'Sciensus Pharma Services Limited', 'https://www.sciensus.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sciensus/', 'Sciensus is a global life sciences company based in London, specializing in patient access, engagement, and insight solutions within the European healthcare ecosystem. With over 30 years of experience, Sciensus supports more than 300,000 patients annually, collaborating with over 4,000 hospitals, pharmacies, and clinics, including every NHS trust in the UK. The company focuses on chronic and long-term conditions, rare diseases, and cancer, combining advanced digital platforms with personalized clinical support.

Sciensus offers a range of services, including clinical trials support, early access and market access programs, aseptic compounding, and supply chain logistics. Their approach integrates technology with skilled patient care, employing over 500 licensed clinical staff to ensure holistic patient support. The company also utilizes proprietary patient apps and digital platforms to capture millions of patient interactions, providing valuable insights that help optimize treatment outcomes. Sciensus partners with pharmaceutical and biotech companies, healthcare providers, and patients to enhance medication access and improve health outcomes across Europe.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/138.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'sciensus', null), ('71', 'Chip', 'Chip Financial Ltd', 'https://www.getchip.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/get-chip/', 'Chip is a UK-based fintech company founded in 2016, headquartered in London. The company focuses on helping users build, manage, and grow their long-term wealth through automated savings and investment solutions. With a team of around 150 employees, Chip has become one of the fastest-growing tech companies in Britain, serving over 300,000 active customers and managing assets exceeding £6 billion.

