The platform offers a range of tools that cover the entire employee lifecycle. This includes HR management for centralized employee data and compliance, automated payroll processing tailored to local regulations, recruitment tools for managing hiring processes, and employee benefits administration to enhance engagement. Additionally, it features scheduling and time management capabilities to track attendance and manage workforce scheduling. Employment Hero is designed to be intuitive and affordable, supporting SMBs in managing their teams efficiently and compliantly.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/148.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'employmenthero', null), ('99', 'Fidel API', 'Fidel Limited', 'https://fidelapi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fidel-api/', 'Fidel API is a UK-based fintech company that offers a secure platform for businesses to connect with users'' bank cards and capture purchase data in real time through an API. This service enables businesses to create personalized user interactions across various sectors, including retail, hospitality, and e-commerce. 

The core offering is a software intermediary platform that links business applications to major card networks globally. It allows for real-time payment event data capture, facilitating programmable experiences based on card transactions. Fidel API prioritizes security and privacy by using card number tokenization to protect sensitive information.

Fidel API provides a range of developer-friendly tools, including a management dashboard, webhooks for notifications, and detailed documentation to support integration. The company serves businesses looking to enhance user engagement and operational efficiency through real-time payment data. Founded in January 2022, Fidel API is registered in the UK and has a diverse team of over 40 employees from more than 10 countries.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/334.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('100', 'YouGov', 'YouGov Plc', 'https://yougov.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/yougov/', 'YouGov is an England-based market research and data analytics firm that offers solutions such as audience intelligence and campaign activation for businesses.', 'The company can sponsor, but typically don''t tend to since they are usually able to find suitable applicants who don''t require a visa.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1166.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'yougov', null), ('101', 'Bark', 'Bark.com Global Limited', 'https://www.bark.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bark-com/about/', 'Bark.com is a London-based web services marketplace founded in November 2014 by Andrew Michael and Kai Feller. The platform connects customers with local service providers across a wide range of professional services, making the booking and hiring process easier. Bark.com features a digital marketplace that uses proprietary automation technology to match users with professionals in over a thousand service categories, including home improvement, tutoring, event planning, and business services.

With approximately 180,000 active service providers, Bark.com facilitates connections between over 7.3 million buyers and sellers annually. The company operates in eleven markets, including the UK, Australia, Canada, and the United States, and has expanded its presence globally since launching in new regions in 2020. Bark.com is privately held and is recognized as one of the fastest-growing private tech companies, ranking 64th in the 2023 Sunday Times 100 list.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1103.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'teamtailor', 'www', null), ('102', 'Kingfisher', 'Kingfisher plc', 'https://www.kingfisher.com/en/index.html', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kingfisher/', 'Kingfisher plc is a British multinational retail company based in London, specializing in home improvement and DIY products and services. With over 1,300 stores across nine European countries, it is a prominent player in the home improvement sector and is listed on the London Stock Exchange as part of the FTSE 100 Index.

Founded in 1982, Kingfisher has evolved into a focused retailer through key acquisitions, including B&Q, Castorama, Brico Dépôt, and Screwfix. The company offers a wide range of products, including home appliances, tools, hardware, home furnishings, garden supplies, and building materials. It serves both general DIY customers and trade professionals through distinct retail banners, catering to various market segments, including price-conscious consumers through its discount formats. Kingfisher leverages its scale for global sourcing and product development, enhancing customer experience and operational efficiency.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1016.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('103', 'Gousto', 'SCA Investments', 'https://www.gousto.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gousto/', 'Gousto is a UK-based food company founded in 2012, known for pioneering the recipe box delivery service in the UK. Headquartered in London, Gousto aims to transform how people shop and cook by providing convenient and sustainable meal solutions. The company serves customers in the United Kingdom and Ireland, offering a wide range of meal options that are easy to prepare and designed to reduce food waste.

Gousto delivers recipe boxes containing perfectly measured fresh ingredients and easy-to-follow recipe cards, enabling customers to cook exciting meals from scratch. With over 60 recipes available weekly, Gousto provides more variety than any other recipe box service in the UK. The company is committed to sustainability, reducing plastic use in packaging and helping customers lower their carbon footprint. Gousto also collaborates with brands like Pots & Co and Runna to enhance its product offerings and engage customers further. As a certified B Corporation, Gousto reflects its dedication to social and environmental responsibility.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '7', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/44.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'Gousto1', null), ('104', 'Airtable', 'Formagrid UK Limited', 'https://airtable.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/airtable', 'Airtable is a cloud collaboration company based in San Francisco, founded in 2012. It offers a platform that merges the simplicity of spreadsheets with the functionality of databases, allowing users to create customized applications and organize data without needing extensive coding skills. The platform supports various field types and enables users to link tables, sort, filter, and publish views.

Airtable serves a wide range of customers, from individual creators to large enterprises, including notable companies like Airbnb and Tesla. The platform features multiple views such as grid, calendar, and kanban, and integrates with over 450 apps, enhancing its versatility. In recent years, Airtable has introduced AI-driven tools to streamline app creation and management, further solidifying its position in the market. With a strong annual growth rate and a focus on enterprise clients, Airtable continues to expand its offerings and user base.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1147.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'airtable', null), ('105', 'Arrival', 'Arrival UK Limited', 'https://arrival.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/arrival/', 'Arrival is a British electric vehicle manufacturer founded in 2015 by Denis Sverdlov. The company focuses on producing lightweight electric vans, buses, and taxis, emphasizing sustainability and cost efficiency. Arrival operates with a unique manufacturing model based on "microfactories," which are small, flexible production facilities designed to localize vehicle assembly and reduce environmental impact.

Headquartered in Howald, Luxembourg, Arrival has significant operations in the UK, the US, and various locations across Europe and North America. The company has attracted major investments from Hyundai, Kia, and BlackRock. Its product lineup includes electric vans for delivery services, electric buses for public transport, and electric taxis for ride-hailing services. Arrival integrates advanced technology into its vehicles, utilizing BlackBerry QNX software to support sophisticated driver-assistance systems. Notable customers include UPS, which placed a substantial order for electric vans, and Royal Mail, which has trialed Arrival''s vehicles for fleet electrification.', 'The company entered administration in Feb 2024.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1222.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('106', 'Ecologi', 'Ecologi Action Ltd', 'https://ecologi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ecologihq/', 'Ecologi is a UK-based climate action platform and Certified B Corporation, founded in 2019 and headquartered in Bristol and the London Borough of Enfield. The company is dedicated to inspiring businesses to accelerate global climate action. With a vision of cultivating a thriving Earth for both people and the planet, Ecologi enables businesses to measure, reduce, and offset their carbon emissions while restoring natural habitats.

Ecologi offers a range of climate action tools and services for businesses at every stage of their net-zero journey. These include carbon footprint measurement, emission reduction guidance, climate impact funding for various projects, and impact reporting. The platform supports over 24,000 businesses and 40,000 members worldwide, helping them make measurable progress toward their climate goals. Recognized for its governance and environmental performance, Ecologi has funded over 87 million trees and avoided or removed more than 3.4 million tonnes of CO2e.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/215.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('107', 'SeedLegals', 'SeedLegals Ltd', 'https://seedlegals.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/seedlegals/', 'SeedLegals is a London-based legaltech company founded in 2016 by Anthony Rose and Laurent Laffy. The company focuses on legal automation for startups and small businesses, aiming to make legal processes more affordable and efficient. SeedLegals has established itself as a significant player in the UK startup ecosystem, known for closing more funding rounds than any other organization in the region.

The company offers a range of tools and services designed to streamline legal and financial processes. These include automated legal documentation for funding rounds, customizable templates for various legal agreements, cap table management, and assistance with tax incentive claims. SeedLegals also provides tools to simplify talent acquisition, making it easier for startups to manage hiring and equity incentives. The platform is tailored to support businesses throughout their lifecycle, from incorporation to growth and exit.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/89.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workable', 'seedlegals', null), ('108', 'QuantSpark', 'QuantSpark Limited', 'https://www.quantspark.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quantspark/', 'QuantSpark is a UK-based data analytics and AI-driven company focused on enhancing business operations through advanced analytics and software solutions. They aim to improve commercial decision-making and operational models by combining technology with strategic insights. Their services cater to various sectors, including retail, private equity, asset management, and public services.

The company offers a range of AI and analytics services, such as advanced analytics consulting, data strategy, predictive modeling, and the development of data-driven products. Notable proprietary products include Meeting IQ, which provides actionable insights from business conversations, ContractCube for analyzing contracts to identify revenue leakage, and RetailCube, which optimizes retail space allocation. QuantSpark promotes a collaborative work environment and emphasizes a human-centered approach to AI, ensuring their solutions are adaptive and future-ready.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '1', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/169.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('111', 'Peppy', 'Peppy Health Limited', 'https://peppy.health/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/getpeppy/', 'Peppy is a digital health company focused on providing personalized support for underserved healthcare areas, particularly in gender-specific and inclusive health issues like menopause, fertility, pregnancy, early parenthood, men''s health, and LGBTQ+ health. Founded by Mridula Pore, Evan Harris, and Max Landry, Peppy aims to empower individuals by breaking down stigma around sensitive health topics and offering accessible expert guidance.

The company operates through a digital health app that connects employees with real human experts via private chats, consultations, live events, and a library of educational resources. Key services include virtual consultations, on-demand resources, and multi-part health courses, all available at no cost to employees. Peppy serves a diverse range of clients, including employers in various sectors, and supports over one million employees globally, with a strong presence in the UK, Ireland, and the United States.

Peppy''s mission is to enhance employee wellbeing, productivity, and engagement, helping organizations become employers of choice. As a certified B Corporation, Peppy delivers innovative solutions that address health issues often overlooked in traditional healthcare, providing inclusive and stigma-free support for all individuals.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/419.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'peppy', null), ('112', 'HiBob', 'Hi Bob (UK) Limited', 'https://www.hibob.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hibob/', 'HiBob is a cloud-based human resource management platform founded in 2015 in Tel Aviv and now headquartered in London. The company aims to transform organizational operations in the modern workplace with its innovative HR platform, Bob. This platform simplifies and automates complex HR processes for fast-growing, globally distributed businesses.

HiBob''s offerings include a comprehensive human capital management system that covers core HR functions such as employee data management, onboarding, and performance management. The company has expanded its capabilities with payroll solutions following the acquisition of Pento, and it features an anonymous reporting tool called "Your Voice" to enhance workplace transparency. Additionally, HiBob incorporates AI-powered financial management tools and supports global HR compliance and workforce management, making it suitable for mid-sized companies with international operations. With significant venture capital funding and recognition in major publications, HiBob is positioned as a leader in HR technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/579.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'hibob', null), ('113', 'Creditspring', 'Inclusive Finance Limited', 'https://www.creditspring.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/creditspring/', 'Creditspring is a UK-based fintech company founded in 2016, focused on providing affordable and transparent credit through a subscription model. As a regulated lender, it aims to offer a smarter alternative to traditional credit products like overdrafts and payday loans. Customers pay a fixed monthly fee to access credit, eliminating interest charges and hidden fees, which promotes financial control and resilience.

Members can access up to two interest-free loans per year, with amounts ranging from £200 to £1,200, depending on their membership tier. Loan repayment terms are fixed at six months, and the company also offers tools like a Benefits Finder to help members identify unclaimed government benefits. Creditspring primarily serves UK consumers who are financially vulnerable and seek clear, affordable borrowing solutions. 

In 2024, Creditspring provided over £200 million in financial support, marking a significant increase from the previous year. The company became profitable in Q3 2024, with revenue exceeding £33 million. With a dedicated team and strong advisory support, Creditspring is committed to responsible lending and innovation in the financial sector.', 'They can sponsor visas depending on the role and other (unclear) circumstances. They have a number of people on visas at the moment (as of 25 Oct 2023).', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/168.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'creditspring', null), ('114', 'Snyk', 'Snyk Limited', 'https://snyk.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/snyk/', 'Snyk is a developer-oriented cybersecurity company founded in 2015, with headquarters in Boston and roots in Tel Aviv and London. The company focuses on empowering developers to build secure software by integrating security into the development process. Snyk adopts a "developer-first" and "shift-left" approach, emphasizing early detection and remediation of vulnerabilities during software creation.

Snyk offers a range of security solutions, including tools for open-source security, code security, container security, and infrastructure as code (IaC) security. The platform scans for vulnerabilities in open-source dependencies and custom code, ensuring that security is addressed from the start. Snyk also maintains a comprehensive vulnerability database and incorporates AI-driven static analysis to enhance detection capabilities. 

Targeting software developers and DevOps teams, Snyk supports organizations of all sizes in embedding security into their continuous integration and delivery pipelines. With over 1,300 employees and a multi-billion dollar valuation, Snyk has made a significant impact in the DevSecOps and developer security market.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/247.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('115', 'SPOKE', 'Respoke Limited', 'https://spoke-london.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/respoke-ltd---spoke/', 'SPOKE is a London-based apparel company that specializes in custom-finished men''s trousers and apparel, providing a nearly bespoke fit. Founded in 2013, the company addresses the issue of poorly fitting menswear by offering a wide range of sizes and custom finishing options. Their core promise is "Ridiculously Well Fit, or your money back," highlighting their commitment to delivering perfectly fitting garments.

SPOKE''s product line includes custom-made legwear such as chinos and selvedge denim trousers, designed for men who are dissatisfied with typical high street options. The company operates primarily through its e-commerce platform, allowing customers to enjoy a personalized fit experience. They partner with sustainably run factories across Europe, the Near East, and Asia to produce high-quality garments, ensuring both style and comfort for their customers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/126.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('116', 'Sourceful', 'Sourceful Ltd', 'https://www.sourceful.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sourceful-com/', 'Sourceful is a UK-based company founded in June 2020 that focuses on digital sourcing and sustainable packaging solutions for environmentally conscious brands. The company operates a real-time platform that enhances transparency and efficiency in the packaging supply chain, helping businesses minimize their environmental impact while optimizing operations.

Sourceful offers a marketplace connecting businesses with over 40 vetted suppliers in the UK and China, specializing in eco-friendly packaging and components. The platform features a universal sustainability standard that evaluates the environmental impact of sourcing decisions, including greenhouse gas emissions throughout the product lifecycle. Notable product innovations include the HydroTec Paper Pouch, which significantly reduces plastic use and carbon emissions compared to traditional options.

The company serves a diverse range of sectors, including food and beverage, fashion, healthcare, and online marketplaces. Sourceful has raised over $32 million in funding from prominent investors and has been recognized for its contributions to digital procurement technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/191.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('117', 'BEL Engineering', 'British Engines (UK) Limited', 'https://www.belengineering.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bel-engineering-uk-/', 'BEL Engineering (UK) is a precision engineering company founded in 2012, based in Newcastle upon Tyne. The company specializes in project-managed CNC machining, catering to high-quality subcontract machining needs in the UK and European markets. It produces components ranging from 3mm in diameter to 50 tonnes in weight, serving various sectors including civil nuclear, defence, aerospace, marine, and oil & gas.

The company offers turnkey project solutions that encompass the entire process from design and material sourcing to manufacturing, assembly, testing, and delivery. BEL Engineering is equipped with advanced machining capabilities, including five-axis machining for large components. It holds several key certifications, including AS9100 and ISO 9001, reflecting its commitment to quality and safety standards.

As part of the British Engines Group, BEL Engineering benefits from shared best practices and an extensive supply chain. The company prioritizes employee development and wellbeing, providing various benefits and training programs. With a turnover of approximately £15-17 million and a workforce of over 150 staff, BEL Engineering is well-positioned in the precision engineering sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1093.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'bel', null), ('118', 'ExodusPoint', 'ExodusPoint Capital Management UK, LLP', 'https://www.exoduspoint.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/exoduspoint/', 'ExodusPoint Capital Management, LP is an investment management firm based in New York City, specializing in global multi-strategy hedge funds. Founded in 2017 by Michael Gelband and Hyung Lee, the firm launched in 2018 with $8.5 billion in external capital, making it the largest hedge fund launch in history. As of early 2024, ExodusPoint manages approximately $12 billion in assets and employs around 646 professionals across offices in North America, Europe, and Asia.

The firm utilizes a multi-strategy investment approach that includes macro strategies, fundamental equity strategies, statistical arbitrage, and quantitative/event arbitrage. This approach combines quantitative models, fundamental research, and systematic trading to identify market inefficiencies and generate superior risk-adjusted returns. ExodusPoint serves institutional investors seeking diversified hedge fund exposure through its sophisticated investment process and global reach.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/852.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'exoduspoint', null), ('119', 'Shieldpay', 'Shieldpay Ltd', 'https://www.shieldpay.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/shieldpay/', 'Shieldpay is a UK-based financial technology company that focuses on secure and transparent payment solutions for the legal and professional services sectors. Founded in 2016 by Peter Janes, the company simplifies complex transactions through its digital escrow services, which help mitigate payment risks and fraud.

The Shieldpay platform features three main capabilities: Verify, Hold, and Disburse. The Verify function automates identity and bank detail verification, ensuring compliance with regulatory standards. The Hold capability safeguards client funds in segregated accounts, acting as a digital escrow until transaction conditions are met. The Disburse feature allows for fast and transparent payment release once all parties are verified and authorized. Shieldpay''s technology is designed to reduce the administrative burden and risk associated with managing client money, particularly for law firms and professional services handling high-value or international transactions.

Recognized for its innovation, Shieldpay has received several industry awards and serves a customer base that includes top law firms and various professional services organizations. The company is committed to continuous innovation in the fintech and legal payments space.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/209.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'shieldpay', null), ('120', 'Ohme', 'Ohme Operations UK Limited', 'https://ohme-ev.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ohmeev/', 'Ohme is a UK-based company founded in 2017 that specializes in smart electric vehicle (EV) charging solutions. The company focuses on optimizing charging costs and minimizing environmental impact. Ohme operates in both the UK and Australia, providing a leading smart charging platform that integrates with off-peak EV tariffs from energy suppliers. This technology allows EV drivers to charge their vehicles during the most cost-effective and renewable energy-rich times.

Ohme''s product lineup includes smart home EV chargers like the Home Pro and the Ohme ePod. The ePod is a compact, untethered charger compatible with all EVs, featuring WiFi connectivity and smartphone app control. It supports Tesla integration and offers a 3-year warranty along with local customer support in Australia. The company is committed to quality and data protection, holding certifications such as ISO 9001 and ISO 27001. Ohme collaborates with major automotive manufacturers and supports initiatives for drivers with disabilities, aiming to accelerate the transition to clean energy through smarter and more affordable EV charging solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor, but strongly prefers to "recruit those with full eligibility to work in the UK already."', '1', '14', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/71.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('121', 'WPP', 'WPP Brands (UK) Limited', 'https://www.wpp.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wpp/', 'WPP plc is a prominent global communications services group based in London. Originally founded in 1971 as a manufacturer of wire shopping baskets, it transformed into a leading marketing services company after a change in ownership in 1985. WPP offers a wide range of services, including advertising, media investment management, public relations, branding, and consultancy, through a vast network of subsidiaries and agencies.

The company serves a prestigious client base, including over 300 Fortune Global 500 companies and more than half of the NASDAQ 100. With approximately 1,400 locations in over 100 countries and a workforce of over 100,000 professionals, WPP emphasizes technology and data-driven solutions. Its growth strategy has been fueled by acquisitions, enhancing its capabilities in digital transformation and integrated marketing. WPP has been recognized for its creative excellence, being named ''Creative Company of the Year'' at the Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity in 2024.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '64', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1165.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'wpp', null), ('122', 'Beamery', 'Beamery Ltd', 'https://beamery.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/beamery/', 'Beamery is a London-based software company founded in 2013 by brothers Abakar and Sultan Saidov, along with Michael Paterson. The company aims to transform recruitment by using predictive marketing, data science, and AI to treat candidates like customers. 

Beamery offers a Talent Operating System designed for enterprise recruiting teams. This platform includes a Recruitment CRM and Marketing Automation tools to attract, engage, and retain top talent. It helps organizations build relationships with passive candidates, reduces hiring cycles, and enhances the candidate experience. Key features include a Talent CRM for maintaining candidate relationships and a marketing engine for nurturing talent. The platform also connects skills and task intelligence with real-time workforce data, enabling efficient hiring and reskilling.

With nearly 300 employees and a valuation of $1 billion, Beamery has facilitated over 1 million hires in the past year. The company is recognized for its innovation in HR technology and is committed to sustainability and social responsibility, focusing on diversity and environmental management.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/26.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/beamery', null), ('123', 'About:Energy', 'About:Energy Limited', 'https://www.aboutenergy.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/about-energy/', 'About:Energy is a London-based private limited company founded in 2021. The company specializes in advanced battery data and software solutions aimed at enhancing product development across the battery supply chain. They utilize exclusive intellectual property licenses from UK universities to create high-precision battery simulation models and complex datasets that aid in decision-making for cell selection, lifetime, and performance prediction.

Their main offering includes customizable white-box battery models that provide detailed electrical and thermal parameters of lithium-ion cells. These models integrate with engineering tools like COMSOL and MathWorks, allowing teams to design and optimize battery systems efficiently. About:Energy addresses key engineering challenges such as cell selection, pack design, thermal management, warranty analysis, and Battery Management System (BMS) development. Their flagship platform, The Voltt, is used across various industries to support battery product development and promote sustainability throughout the supply chain. The company is committed to positioning the UK as a leader in battery data and technology innovation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1305.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'aboutenergyuk', null), ('124', 'Lunio', 'PPC Protect Limited', 'https://lunio.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lunio/', 'Lunio is an AI-powered ad tech company based in Manchester, United Kingdom. Founded in 2018, Lunio specializes in detecting and securing the validity of paid media traffic, helping advertisers avoid invalid and fraudulent clicks. The company, formerly known as PPC Protect, aims to provide performance marketers with reliable invalid traffic detection to enhance their advertising effectiveness and reduce wasted ad spend.

Lunio''s core offering is a machine learning algorithm that identifies suspicious activity and invalid traffic with high precision. This technology allows for real-time detection and automated solutions, enabling marketers to focus on genuine audiences. The platform also provides actionable insights, including custom audience creation and IP exclusion features, to maximize return on investment. Lunio serves performance marketers and advertisers, offering flexible pricing based on a fraction of ad spend and a 14-day free traffic audit to assess the impact of invalid traffic on campaigns. With a dedicated team and significant funding, Lunio is recognized as a leader in click fraud prevention.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/207.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'lunio', null), ('128', 'Relativity', 'Relativity Global LLC', 'https://relativity.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/relativityhq/', 'Relativity is a technology company that specializes in legal data management and e-discovery solutions for corporations, law firms, and government agencies. Founded in 2001, the company has established itself as a leader in providing software that helps organizations manage, analyze, and secure large volumes of data related to litigation, investigations, and compliance. Headquartered in Chicago, Relativity emphasizes security, innovation, and customer support.

The company''s flagship product, RelativityOne, is a secure, cloud-based e-discovery platform that integrates artificial intelligence and analytics to streamline the e-discovery process. It supports data ingestion from popular enterprise tools like Microsoft 365 and Google Workspace, enabling efficient workflows. Key features include AI-powered document review tools, high-speed data processing, and advanced security measures. Relativity also offers an on-premises product, Relativity Server, while focusing on its SaaS offerings for enhanced scalability and innovation. The company serves a diverse customer base, including corporate legal teams, law firms, and government agencies, helping them reduce costs and improve productivity.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/972.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workday', 'External_Career_Site', null), ('129', 'Speechmatics', 'Cantab Research Limited', 'https://www.speechmatics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/speechmatics/', 'Speechmatics is a technology company based in Cambridge, England, that specializes in automatic speech recognition (ASR) software. Founded in 2006 by Dr. Tony Robinson, the company focuses on converting spoken language into written text using advanced deep learning techniques. Speechmatics offers both cloud-based and on-premises solutions that are highly accurate and support multiple languages and dialects.

Their technology is utilized across various industries, enabling businesses to transcribe and analyze audio content from sources like TV, radio, phone calls, and meetings. Key innovations include language packs for Global English and Global Spanish, as well as their Autonomous Speech Recognition software, which leverages self-supervised deep learning models. Speechmatics serves a diverse customer base, processing millions of hours of transcription monthly in 34 languages. The company has received several accolades for its growth and innovation, highlighting its commitment to delivering effective speech-to-text solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '17', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/679.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'speechmatics', null), ('130', 'Multiverse', 'Multiverse Group Limited', 'https://www.multiverse.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/joinmultiverse/', 'Multiverse is a UK-based upskilling platform founded in 2016, specializing in AI and technology adoption. The company focuses on transforming the workforce by combining expert human coaching with AI-driven learning to address skills gaps in data, AI, and technology. Multiverse offers professional apprenticeships and personalized on-the-job learning programs aimed at enhancing productivity and preparing talent for future roles in the AI era.

As an end-to-end partner for organizations, Multiverse employs a proprietary learning framework called MAGE to assess business goals and current skill levels. This allows them to create tailored learning paths that ensure skills are effectively applied in the workplace. With over 22,000 learners trained globally and partnerships with more than 1,500 organizations, including Microsoft and Mars, Multiverse emphasizes equitable access to economic opportunities and career transformation through skills development. The company has raised significant funding, becoming the UK’s first EdTech unicorn, reflecting its rapid growth and innovative approach to workforce transformation.', 'Sponsorship is usually reserved for Director-level or "business-critical" roles, but what the latter means is unclear (we''ve seen sponsored Product Manager roles in the past).', '1', '41', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/multiverse', null), ('131', 'Via', 'Via Transportation UK Ltd', 'https://citymapper.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ridewithvia/', 'Citymapper is a British technology company that specializes in public transit and mapping services. Founded in 2011 by Azmat Yusuf, the company is based in London. Originally launched as "Busmapper" to provide bus timetables, it evolved into Citymapper in 2012, expanding to include various transportation modes such as trains, buses, ferries, walking, cycling, and driving.

The Citymapper app integrates data from multiple sources, offering real-time information on transport options between locations in supported cities. Users can select routes based on speed or safety, and the app provides real-time traffic updates and alerts for transit disruptions. Citymapper also offers a transport card called the Citymapper Pass, which serves as an alternative to traditional transit cards. With over 50 million users across more than 100 cities, Citymapper aims to simplify urban navigation and enhance mobility through its innovative solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/288.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'via', null), ('133', 'Lightspeed', 'Lightspeed POS UK Ltd', 'https://www.lightspeedhq.com/uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lightspeedcommerce/', 'Lightspeed Commerce Inc. is a technology company based in Montreal, founded in 2005 by Dax Dasilva. The company provides a cloud-based commerce platform aimed at empowering small and medium-sized businesses in various sectors, including retail, hospitality, and golf. Lightspeed''s mission is to streamline operations and enhance customer experiences through unified software solutions.

The company offers an integrated suite of products, including a retail platform for managing inventory and sales, an e-commerce platform for building online stores, and a restaurant POS tailored for hospitality businesses. Lightspeed also provides payment processing solutions, advanced analytics, customer loyalty programs, and financing options. With a global presence and over 21,000 businesses served, Lightspeed is recognized for its innovative approach to commerce technology, helping businesses unify their sales, inventory, and customer engagement processes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '19', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/929.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'lightspeedhq', null), ('134', 'Capital on Tap', 'New Wave Capital Ltd', 'https://www.capitalontap.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/capital-on-tap/', 'Capital on Tap is a financial technology company based in London, founded in 2012 by CEO David Luck. The company focuses on providing small businesses with easy access to funding through innovative technology. Its primary product is the Capital on Tap Business Credit Card, which offers flexible capital, higher credit limits of up to £50,000, and tailored rewards like points and cashback. The company has also evolved from offering fixed-term loans to providing monthly payment cycles and fee-free products.

Having lent over £4 billion to more than 200,000 small business customers by its 10th anniversary, Capital on Tap expanded into the United States in 2021. The company integrates with various accounting software and supports Apple Pay for added convenience. With a strong emphasis on customer support, Capital on Tap operates a 24/7 in-house support center in Cardiff, Wales, ensuring high-quality service for its customers in both the UK and US markets.', 'The company is open to sponsoring technical roles and senior roles (i.e. "Head of" or "Director").', '1', '44', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/234.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'capitalontap', null), ('135', 'WeWALK', 'WeWalk Limited', 'https://wewalk.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wewalk/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'WeWALK is a startup founded in 2020 that focuses on assistive technologies for the visually impaired. The company aims to empower individuals by enhancing their mobility and independence through innovative technology developed with input from the community. Their approach, known as “community customization,” ensures that products meet the real needs of users.

One of their key offerings is the WeWALK Smart Cane, an AI-integrated device that combines traditional cane features with advanced technology like ultrasonic sensors and voice control. This smart cane allows users to navigate safely and access smartphone functions directly. WeWALK also provides WeASSIST, a visual assistance service through their app, connecting users with trained agents for live support. Additionally, their AI Mobility Training program teaches effective cane usage techniques to boost users'' confidence and skills. WeWALK serves the visually impaired community in 59 countries and collaborates with organizations like Microsoft and the Royal National Institute of Blind People to enhance accessibility.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1306.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('136', 'GoCardless', 'GoCardless Limited', 'https://gocardless.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gocardless/', 'GoCardless is a London-based fintech company founded in 2011, specializing in bank payments with a focus on recurring payments and Direct Debit processing. The company offers a payment gateway platform that allows businesses to set up, manage, and automate payments, subscriptions, and invoices, making it easier to collect recurring payments directly from customers'' bank accounts.

Initially targeting small and medium-sized businesses, GoCardless has expanded its services internationally, operating in the UK, EU, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, and the United States. Its product suite includes Direct Debit payment processing, subscription management tools, invoice payment automation, and integration with Open Banking. GoCardless serves a diverse range of customers, from entrepreneurs to large enterprises, processing approximately $30 billion in transactions annually and supporting around 100,000 merchants globally.

The company has experienced significant growth, raising substantial funding and achieving a valuation of $2.1 billion in 2022. GoCardless aims to create a global bank-to-bank payments network, connecting Direct Debit systems across countries into a unified platform.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '12', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/339.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'gocardless', null), ('137', 'CheqUp', 'CheqUp Health Limited', 'https://chequp.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/chequp/', 'CheqUp is a UK-based health company founded in 2020 and headquartered in Basingstoke, Hampshire. The company specializes in medically supervised weight loss programs, at-home blood diagnostic testing, and COVID-19 testing services. CheqUp aims to enhance clients'' health through personalized weight management solutions and convenient health diagnostics.

The company offers evidence-based weight loss programs that combine medications with clinical oversight and one-on-one coaching from experienced medical professionals. CheqUp emphasizes sustainable weight loss by integrating medication with holistic lifestyle support, adhering to NHS guidelines. Additionally, it provides easy and fast at-home blood tests for health monitoring and has been recognized for its reliable COVID-19 testing services during the pandemic.

CheqUp serves individuals seeking effective weight loss solutions, including those facing challenges like yo-yo dieting and hormonal changes. It is an approved supplier of weight loss management services to the NHS and partners with WeightWatchers to enhance customer support. CheqUp is GPhC-licensed and NHS-approved, ensuring high standards of care and safety.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/974.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('138', 'Nomo Bank', 'Bank of London and The Middle East plc', 'https://www.nomobank.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/nomobank/', 'Nomo Bank is a UK-based, Sharia-compliant digital bank that launched in July 2021. It is recognized as the world’s first fully digital international Islamic bank, designed for customers with global lifestyles who seek ethical financial solutions. Nomo focuses on accessibility, security, and compliance with Islamic finance principles, offering services regulated in the UK with deposit protection up to £85,000.

Nomo Bank provides a range of services, including multi-currency accounts that allow customers to hold, spend, and send funds in six currencies. It also offers fixed-term deposits for wealth growth in GBP, USD, or EUR, and Sharia-compliant property finance for residential or rental property purchases in England and Wales. Customers can enjoy digital banking tools, including instant account setup via smartphone and 24/7 access to their accounts. Nomo primarily serves residents of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), particularly in Kuwait and the UAE, catering to expatriates and investors seeking UK transactional banking and international financial flexibility.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1096.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('139', 'Supersolid', 'Supersolid Limited', 'https://supersolid.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/supersolid/', 'Supersolid is a mobile games development company based in Central London, UK, founded in 2012 by Kenneth Fejer, Michelle Chuang, Tommy Chuang, and Ed Chin. The company has grown to a team of over 30 employees and is backed by notable investors like Index Ventures and Initial Capital.

Specializing in casual mobile games for smartphones and tablets, Supersolid has developed several popular titles that have collectively garnered over 50 million downloads. Some of their notable games include "Super Penguins," "Adventure Town," "Food Street," "Home Street," and "Snake Rivals." The company focuses on the full lifecycle of mobile game development, emphasizing game design, user experience, community engagement, and regular content updates to keep players engaged. Supersolid aims to create polished and intuitive gaming experiences that incorporate social and collaborative features, appealing to casual mobile gamers worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/506.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'supersolid', null), ('142', 'Hiya', 'Hiya Communications UK Limited', 'https://www.hiya.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hiyainc/', 'Hiya Inc. is a Seattle-based technology company that specializes in voice intelligence solutions aimed at enhancing phone call security and user experience. Founded in 2016 as a spin-off from Whitepages, Hiya serves over 500 million users worldwide and employs approximately 150 people. The company is known for its innovative caller ID, spam protection, and branded call services.

Hiya''s core offerings include advanced caller identification and network-level spam and fraud call blocking through its flagship app and integrated services. The Hiya Protect solution uses adaptive AI for spam-blocking, while Hiya Connect is a SaaS platform that helps businesses engage with customers through branded calls. The company partners with major mobile carriers and device manufacturers, including Samsung and AT&T, to deliver its services globally. Hiya''s leadership team brings a wealth of expertise in software, telecommunications, and product development, contributing to its recognition as a top startup employer and one of the fastest-growing tech companies in North America.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/351.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/hiya', null), ('143', 'Snowplow', 'Snowplow Analytics Limited', 'https://snowplow.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/snowplow/', 'Snowplow specializes in real-time customer data infrastructure, helping organizations collect, model, and manage structured behavioral data across various platforms. Their platform captures detailed event-level data with over 130 default properties per event, which can be tailored to meet specific business requirements. This enables businesses to gain deep insights into user journeys.

The core product, the Behavioral Data Platform (BDP), consolidates behavioral data from multiple sources into a clean format, facilitating fast querying without the need for data cleaning. Snowplow supports low-latency data streaming for real-time delivery of customer metrics, essential for product analytics and marketing attribution. The platform operates within the customer''s cloud environment, ensuring complete data ownership and compliance with privacy regulations. Additionally, it enables advanced analytics, AI integration, and personalized customer experiences through event streaming and activation features.

Snowplow targets product and marketing teams focused on optimizing customer experiences and understanding user engagement across channels. Their technology is designed for companies that need detailed, real-time behavioral data to enhance their operations and marketing strategies.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/404.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'lever', 'snowplow', null), ('144', 'King', 'Activision Europe Limited', 'https://www.king.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/king/', 'King.com Limited is a Swedish video game developer and publisher known for its social games, particularly the popular title *Candy Crush Saga*, launched in 2012. The company is headquartered in Stockholm and London, with incorporation in St. Julian''s, Malta. King operates under the freemium model, allowing players to enjoy games for free while offering in-app purchases.

As a subsidiary of Activision Blizzard since February 2016, King continues to function independently within the Microsoft Gaming division following Microsoft''s acquisition of Activision Blizzard in October 2023. The company focuses on developing and publishing engaging social and casual games for mobile and cross-platform users, appealing to a wide demographic of casual gamers globally. King employs around 2,000 people and is led by President Todd Green and Chairman Gerhard Florin.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '27', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/448.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', '10xbanking', null), ('145', 'Tortus', 'Tortus AI Ltd', 'https://tortus.ai', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tortus-ai/', 'TORTUS is a British healthcare technology company that specializes in an AI platform designed to enhance clinical workflows by automating clinical documentation. Its main product is an AI-powered assistant that integrates with Electronic Health Record (EHR) systems like EMIS, TPP (SystmOne), Epic, and Cerner. This assistant streamlines administrative tasks, allowing healthcare professionals to focus more on patient care.

The platform features advanced medical speech-to-text technology that transcribes patient consultations in real time. It automatically drafts medical notes, referral letters, and clinical codes, significantly reducing the documentation burden on clinicians. TORTUS also provides intelligent dictation and is developing capabilities for workflow automation, such as ordering tests and scheduling appointments under clinician supervision.

TORTUS prioritizes data privacy and compliance, operating under various certifications and registered as a medical device. Founded by NHS clinicians and machine learning scientists, it is deployed across NHS hospitals, general practices, and ambulance services in the UK, with a partnership with X-on Health to expand its AI assistant in primary care. The company''s mission is to reduce human error in medicine and improve clinician productivity and wellbeing.', 'Sponsorship can be offered as long as candidates are willing to relocate to London.', '1', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/487.png', 'false', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('146', 'WealthKernel', 'WealthKernel Limited', 'https://www.wealthkernel.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wealthkernel/', 'WealthKernel is a fintech company based in London, UK, founded in 2015. It specializes in API-driven investment infrastructure for digital wealth management services. The company provides a range of technology solutions that enable fintech firms, wealth managers, and trading apps to efficiently build and scale digital investing products without the need for extensive in-house infrastructure.

WealthKernel''s core services include client onboarding with tailored risk assessments, automatic KYC and AML checks, and trading infrastructure that supports thousands of fractional securities across various markets. The platform also offers portfolio management, custody services with tier 1 banking partners, and supports multiple UK tax wrappers and account types. WealthKernel''s business model is B2B, generating revenue through subscription, transaction, and asset management fees, and it emphasizes security and compliance with ISO 27001 certification. The company aims to democratize wealth management by providing flexible and scalable solutions for its clients.', 'The company is only willing to consider visa sponsorship for existing employees who have started working via alternative visa routes.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/798.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('147', 'Landytech', 'Landy Tech Limited', 'https://landytech.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/landytech/', 'Landytech is a financial technology company based in London, founded in 2018. It specializes in providing an investment management platform called the Sesame platform, designed for family offices, asset owners, managers, and advisors. The Sesame platform consolidates data from various sources, enabling efficient portfolio management and automating complex reporting tasks. It supports regulatory reporting requirements and features customizable reporting, analytics, and risk management tools.

With a team of around 100-150 employees, Landytech has raised over $18 million in funding and has received multiple awards for its innovative solutions. The company primarily serves single-family offices, multi-family offices, and fund managers across key markets in the UK, France, Switzerland, and Germany. Landytech is committed to enhancing transparency and efficiency in investment management, providing dedicated client support and tailored software development to meet client needs.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/97.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'landytech', null), ('149', 'Recycleye', 'Recycleye Ltd', 'https://recycleye.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/recycleye/', 'Recycleye is a London-based technology company founded in 2019, focusing on AI-driven waste sorting and recycling solutions. The company has developed an advanced AI-powered system that uses computer vision to identify and sort materials in waste streams with high precision. This system operates continuously and can process up to 33,000 items per robot during a 10-hour shift, providing detailed data that helps waste facility managers enhance recycling efficiency and purity.

The company offers a range of services, including AI-powered waste identification systems, data analytics for optimizing waste stream purity, and robotic sorting solutions. Recycleye collaborates with notable partners like Imperial College London and Microsoft to advance its technology. Its solutions are deployed in various countries, serving waste management companies and recycling facilities that seek to improve operational efficiency and meet the growing demand for high-quality recycled materials. Recycleye aims to bridge the gap between academic research and practical applications in the recycling industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/927.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workable', 'recycleye', null), ('151', 'Bondsmith', 'Bondsmith Savings Ltd', 'https://www.bondsmith.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bondsmith/', 'Bondsmith is a UK-based financial technology company that specializes in banking as a service (BaaS) and savings as a service platforms. Operating through Bondsmith Savings Ltd, which is authorized and regulated by the UK''s Financial Conduct Authority, the company aims to help businesses optimize cash management and enhance payment experiences. 

Bondsmith offers a platform that allows companies to integrate banking and payment services into their offerings without the need to develop their own infrastructure. Their flagship product, savings as a service, enables businesses to provide optimized savings solutions to their customers. With a focus on cash optimization, Bondsmith supports various companies and institutions looking to embed financial services into their products. The company has a strong presence in the fintech sector, catering to a diverse market of clients.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1231.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'bondsmith', null), ('152', 'KASKO', 'Kasko Ltd', 'https://www.kasko.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kasko-tech/', 'KASKO is an insurance technology company based in the United Kingdom, founded in 2015. It specializes in "insurance as a service" through a modular, no-/low-code digital insurance platform. This platform allows insurers, managing general agents (MGAs), and digital marketplaces to create and manage customized insurance products and workflows efficiently.

KASKO''s offerings include a digital insurance platform that supports the development of new or existing insurance products, technology services for insurers, and solutions for obtaining intermediary licenses across the EU and UK markets. The company also provides consulting and recruitment services tailored to the insurance technology sector. KASKO''s innovative plug-in technology enables online marketplaces to offer insurance at the point of sale, enhancing customer experience and creating new revenue opportunities. With a focus on digital transformation and automation, KASKO aims to reshape the insurance landscape in Europe.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1066.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('153', 'FabricNano', 'FabricNano Limited', 'https://fabricnano.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fabricnano/', 'FabricNano is a synthetic biology and cell-free biomanufacturing company based in London, founded in 2018. The company focuses on creating sustainable alternatives to traditional chemical manufacturing by developing innovative biocatalysts that utilize enzymes. This approach aims to reduce environmental impact and greenhouse gas emissions.

The technology involves immobilizing enzymes on various carrier materials, allowing them to function outside living cells. These durable biocatalysts can last from six months to a year, making them suitable for industrial applications. FabricNano''s enzyme-coated carriers can be integrated into existing manufacturing processes, enhancing efficiency and sustainability. The company also employs AI and machine learning to optimize enzyme performance.

FabricNano produces biocatalysts for the manufacture of commodity chemicals, including bio-plastics, bio-fuels, and certain antibiotics. Its solutions target industries looking to reduce reliance on fossil fuels. The company has attracted significant investment and formed strategic partnerships to promote the adoption of its technology among large-scale chemical manufacturers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/203.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'fabricnano', null), ('154', 'Phoelex', 'Phoelex Ltd', 'https://phoelex.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/phoelex/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Phoelex is a London-based technology company that specializes in developing modern optical transceivers for high-speed data transfer in data centers. Founded in late 2016 and incorporated in October 2015, Phoelex focuses on creating hardware solutions that efficiently convert and transmit large volumes of data, supporting applications like big data processing and analytics.

The company designs and manufactures optical transceivers that are essential for reliable data communication over optical fiber networks. These products cater to data centers and enterprises that require advanced networking equipment to manage significant data infrastructure needs. Phoelex has gained recognition in startup and venture capital circles, showcasing its innovative approach to optical transceiver technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/783.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'accq', null), ('155', 'AlphaSights', 'AlphaSights Ltd', 'https://www.alphasights.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/alphasights/', 'AlphaSights is a global information services company that connects clients with expert knowledge on demand. Founded in 2008 and headquartered in London, it operates in nine major cities worldwide, including New York, Dubai, and Tokyo. The company specializes in providing access to expert insights across various sectors, helping clients make informed decisions.

The primary service offered by AlphaSights is expert network services, which facilitate consultations between clients and vetted industry experts. In addition to expert calls and meetings, the company provides customized research projects and a content library called AlphaView, which offers curated expert insights. AlphaSights leverages modern technology and a dynamic database of experts to efficiently connect clients with the right resources.

AlphaSights serves a diverse range of professional clients, including management consulting firms, investment management, and corporate services, across sectors such as technology, healthcare, and financial services. The company is recognized for its high-performance culture and commitment to employee development, contributing to its rapid growth and strong presence in the expert network industry.', 'The company generally only sponsors "language-speaking roles" for candidates that speak another language.', '1', '35', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/241.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('157', 'Trustpilot', 'Trustpilot Ltd', 'https://uk.trustpilot.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/trustpilot/', 'Trustpilot is a global online review platform founded in 2007 in Copenhagen, Denmark, by Peter Holten Mühlmann. It serves as the world’s largest independent customer feedback platform, hosting over 300 million reviews and supporting more than 1.25 million businesses across over 100 countries. With 67 million monthly active users, Trustpilot connects consumers and businesses through authentic reviews, empowering consumers to make informed purchasing decisions.

The company operates on a freemium business model, offering free access to basic review services while providing premium features such as advanced analytics and personalized customer support for businesses. Trustpilot emphasizes integrity and trustworthiness by employing advanced fake review detection technology and community oversight to ensure the authenticity of reviews. With a market capitalization exceeding £1 billion, Trustpilot continues to grow, adding over 190,000 new reviews daily and employing over 1,000 people globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '43', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/252.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'trustpilot', null), ('158', 'Spliced', 'Spliced Inc.', 'https://www.splicedinc.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/splicedinc/', 'Spliced Inc. is a private limited company based in London, established on December 6, 2021. As a global, remote-first game development studio, it operates under the umbrella of NetEase, Inc., a prominent Chinese internet and game services provider. The company is dedicated to redefining gaming experiences through innovative gameplay and interaction.

The talented team at Spliced Inc. is currently working on a top-secret project that emphasizes advanced brand development and digital design. Their focus is on creating engaging gaming experiences that captivate players and foster excitement within the gaming community. With a reported turnover of approximately £9.4 million and an operating profit of £741.7k for the year ending December 2023, Spliced Inc. demonstrates strong growth and profitability in its early years.

Spliced Inc. aims to deliver high-quality gaming experiences to gamers and enthusiasts worldwide, positioning itself as a pioneering force in the gaming industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1208.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('159', 'Raycast', 'Raycast Technologies Ltd', 'https://www.raycast.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/raycastapp/', 'Raycast is a productivity software company founded in 2020 by Thomas Paul Mann and Petr Nikolaev, based in London, UK. It specializes in developing an application launcher and productivity tool primarily for macOS, with recent expansions to Windows and iOS. The Raycast App provides fast access to applications, files, and workflows through a keyboard-driven interface, designed to help users streamline their tasks.

The company also offers an Extensions Platform that supports an open API and a built-in store for open-source extensions. This allows users to enhance functionality with tools for GitHub management, Spotify control, and more. Raycast Pro, a subscription plan, unlocks advanced features like AI-powered enhancements and cloud sync. With a daily active user base of over 100,000, Raycast emphasizes community collaboration and user feedback in its development process. The company has secured significant venture capital funding to support its growth and platform expansion.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/41.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'raycast', null), ('160', 'Scaleup Finance', 'Scaleup Finance UK Limited', 'https://www.scaleup.finance/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/scaleup-finance/', 'Scaleup Finance is a fintech company based in Denmark, founded in 2021. With around 90 employees and global offices, it focuses on providing a financial management platform tailored for startups, scaleups, and small to medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). The platform simplifies financial operations through a subscription-based model that combines technology with expert financial services.

A key feature of Scaleup Finance is its access to a dedicated fractional Chief Financial Officer (CFO). This CFO partner assists clients with strategic financial decision-making, budgeting, forecasting, and reporting. The platform automates various financial management tasks, including bookkeeping, payments, payroll, and reporting, which helps reduce the administrative burden on finance teams. It also offers tailored financial insights and integrates with leading accounting and ERP systems for seamless data management.

Scaleup Finance currently serves over 250 clients globally, providing them with smarter financial management solutions that support business growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1071.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('161', 'Allica Bank', 'Allica Bank Limited', 'https://www.allica.bank/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/allicabank/', 'Allica Bank is a British challenger bank and fintech founded in 2019, with headquarters in London and Milton Keynes. The bank focuses on serving small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in the UK, particularly those with 5 to 250 employees. Allica Bank offers a range of financial products tailored to SMEs, including lending solutions, savings accounts, and business current accounts.

Since its launch, Allica Bank has lent over £3 billion to UK businesses, showcasing its rapid growth. The bank''s lending products support SME growth and are offered through Allica Financial Services Limited. It also provides regulated savings accounts protected under the UK’s Financial Services Compensation Scheme and business current accounts, which were introduced in January 2023. Additionally, Allica Bank offers specialist bridging loans through Allica Bridging Finance Limited.

Recognized for its innovation and growth, Allica Bank has received accolades such as being named the UK''s fastest-growing private company in The Sunday Times 100 in 2024. With a dedicated team of over 680 employees, Allica Bank is committed to empowering established UK businesses through technology and expert support.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1100.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'allicabank', null), ('162', 'Fora', 'Fora Space Limited', 'https://www.foraspace.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fora-space/', 'Fora is a tech-forward travel agency and platform based in New York City, founded in 2021. The company empowers individuals passionate about travel to become travel advisors, whether full-time or as a side business. It combines advanced technology, personalized training, and a supportive community to help entrepreneurs launch and grow their travel advisory businesses.

Fora offers a comprehensive "business-in-a-box" solution that includes an innovative booking platform, expert training programs, and tools for client management and marketing. Advisors benefit from exclusive partnerships with top travel brands, providing competitive rates and unique experiences. The company serves a diverse customer base, including new entrepreneurs and experienced travel professionals, and has rapidly expanded its network, boasting nearly 500 active travel advisors and a waitlist of over 30,000 eager to join.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/871.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workable', 'fora-space-limited', null), ('163', 'Baxter International', 'Baxter Healthcare Limited', 'https://baxter.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/baxter-healthcare/?WT.svl=www.baxter.com', 'Baxter International Inc. is a global healthcare company founded in 1931, originally as the Don Baxter Intravenous Products Corporation. Headquartered in the United States, Baxter has a rich history of innovation in medical products and therapies, focusing on saving lives and enhancing patient care worldwide.

The company operates in the medical products and healthcare services sector, emphasizing renal care, hospital products, and advanced medical devices. Baxter''s product portfolio includes intravenous (IV) solutions, renal care products, and a range of hospital products such as respiratory therapy devices and surgical equipment. Following its acquisition of Hillrom in 2021, Baxter has also expanded into connected care and digital health solutions, integrating medical devices with digital monitoring.

Baxter serves a diverse array of healthcare providers, including hospitals, clinics, and dialysis centers, as well as home care patients. Its products are utilized in critical care, renal care, and surgical settings, reflecting the company''s commitment to improving healthcare outcomes globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/443.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'baxter/baxter', null), ('164', 'CoMind', 'CoMind Technologies Limited', 'https://comind.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/comindtechnologies/', 'CoMind is a neurotechnology company that develops advanced non-invasive neuromonitoring devices and neural interfaces. The company aims to redefine brain measurement and treatment to enhance patient outcomes, particularly in neurology and brain disorders. CoMind provides healthcare providers with innovative technologies that facilitate access to critical neurophysiological signals.

Operating in the healthcare and medical devices market, CoMind generates revenue through the sale of its products to hospitals, clinics, and research institutions globally. The company collaborates closely with medical professionals to ensure the effective application and ongoing enhancement of its technologies. The team comprises experts in non-invasive neuroimaging, neuroscience, and biomedical engineering, led by experienced executives.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '8', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/59.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/comind', null), ('165', 'Wluper', 'Wluper Ltd', 'https://wluper.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wluper_/', 'Wluper is a London-based technology startup founded in 2016, specializing in advanced conversational artificial intelligence (AI). The company focuses on creating natural language understanding solutions that enhance workforce efficiency and productivity, particularly in industries like transport, construction, utilities, and field services. Wluper''s technology integrates seamlessly into existing applications to automate workflows, addressing challenges posed by legacy systems and manual processes.

Wluper offers a range of AI-powered products, including the TrueUnderstanding API, which enables applications to comprehend complex queries, and TrueDialogue, designed for goal-driven conversations. They also provide data generation and annotation services to support AI training. By concentrating on domain-specific expertise, Wluper''s solutions facilitate more effective interactions compared to general assistants, helping organizations streamline operations and improve safety in the field.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/524.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('169', 'Fastly', 'Fastly Limited', 'https://www.fastly.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fastly/', 'Fastly, Inc. is a technology company founded in 2011 and based in San Francisco, California. It specializes in an edge cloud platform that enhances digital experiences by processing applications close to end-users. This platform includes a programmable edge cloud solution, a configurable cache layer, and serverless compute products, allowing developers to improve performance and security.

Fastly offers a variety of services centered around edge computing and cloud security. These include an edge compute solution for low-latency applications, cloud security features like web application firewalls and DDoS protection, and a managed content delivery network (CDN) that caches content near users. The company also provides image optimization, video streaming, and live entertainment services, along with an AI Accelerator introduced in 2024.

Fastly serves diverse industries such as digital publishing, online retail, streaming media, and financial services, with operations in multiple countries including the United States, Australia, and the United Kingdom. The company focuses on a usage-based business model that emphasizes a programmable, software-defined network for enhanced security and performance.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/320.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'fastly', null), ('170', 'AI Forge', 'AIForge Ltd', 'https://www.aiforge.org/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/aiforge-incubator/', 'AI Forge operates in two distinct areas: automotive AI solutions and AI startup incubation. 

The automotive AI Forge specializes in developing advanced AI software for the automotive industry. It focuses on enhancing vehicle efficiency, safety, and user experience through customized AI technologies. Their offerings include AI-based driver assistance, autonomous driving solutions, and the integration of augmented reality and computer vision. The company collaborates with leading car manufacturers to deliver tailored solutions and has successfully deployed software in millions of vehicles worldwide.

The AI startup incubator, also named AI Forge, is based in London and Latin America. It runs a 12-week hybrid program designed to accelerate the growth of AI startups. Participants receive mentorship, funding, and access to resources such as financial modeling and market research. The incubator aims to help early-stage AI entrepreneurs develop their ideas into viable products while also supporting corporates and investors in sourcing innovative AI startups.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/902.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('171', 'Brandbassador', 'Brandbassador Ltd', 'https://www.brandbassador.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/brandbassador/', 'Brandbassador is a Sweden-based ambassador marketing platform that specializes in eCommerce. Founded by the team behind the clothing brand Onepiece, the company focuses on helping brands build communities and drive revenue through ambassador marketing. With over 1 million active ambassadors and more than 550 eCommerce clients, Brandbassador transforms customer advocates into brand promoters using gamified campaigns.

The platform offers a range of services, including ambassador management tools for recruitment and engagement, campaign automation for streamlined marketing workflows, and analytics for tracking sales and campaign effectiveness. It also features social commerce integration with its "MyShop" functionality, creating seamless shopping experiences driven by social media advocacy. Brandbassador is recognized for fostering long-term relationships with ambassadors, positioning itself as a leader in community-driven growth and social commerce innovation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/208.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('172', 'eMed', 'Babylon Healthcare Services Limited', 'https://www.emed.com/uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/emedhealthcareuk/', 'eMed Healthcare UK is a leader in digital healthcare technology, specializing in digital-first primary care and chronic care management. The company is dedicated to providing high-quality, accessible care through its comprehensive 24/7 primary care service. Users can easily access a variety of specialists, including GPs, nurses, pharmacists, physiotherapists, and mental health practitioners.

The services offered by eMed Healthcare UK include a wide range of primary care options, solutions for managing chronic conditions, and a clinician-led weight management program. The company operates the GP at Hand practice, which is the largest GP practice in the UK, on behalf of the NHS. In 2023, eMed Healthcare UK expanded its capabilities by acquiring Babylon Health, enhancing its digital healthcare offerings. With over 4.8 million ratings in the app store and a satisfaction rate exceeding 93% for consultations, eMed Healthcare UK is committed to empowering individuals in managing their health effectively.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/359.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('173', 'Satchel', 'Teachercentric Limited', 'https://www.teamsatchel.com/index.html', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/team-satchel/', 'Satchel is a UK-based educational technology company that specializes in innovative software solutions for schools. Founded over 10 years ago and headquartered in London, it serves more than 4,500 schools worldwide, including secondary schools and sixth forms. The company is recognized for its commitment to innovation and has received multiple awards, including Edtech Innovator of the Year in 2019.The flagship product, Satchel One, is a comprehensive learning platform used by one in three secondary schools in the UK. It integrates various features such as homework management, behavior tracking, and classroom resources into a single cloud-based platform. Team Satchel also offers a cloud Management Information System (MIS) that supports school leaders with data management and operational efficiency. Additionally, Satchel Classes provides live and on-demand classes to help students catch up on learning and develop essential skills. The company values innovation, empathy, and collaboration, aiming to enhance educational experiences for students, teachers, and school leaders.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/570.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'teamsatchel', null), ('174', 'MAGIC', 'Magic Tech Ltd ', 'https://magic.fit/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/magicfit2021/', 'MAGIC AI is a fitness technology company that enhances home workouts by integrating artificial intelligence with smart fitness equipment. Founded by Varun Bhanot, the company focuses on making high-quality personal training accessible through its AI-driven platform, which offers personalized workout plans and real-time feedback.

The flagship product, the MAGIC AI Fitness Smart Mirror, features ReflectAI® technology that tracks users'' movements, counts repetitions, and provides guidance during strength training. It recognizes over 400 exercises and offers a variety of classes led by more than 25 trainers, including celebrity athletes like Alastair Cook. Additionally, MAGIC AI offers adjustable dumbbells that complement the smart mirror, creating a comprehensive home gym experience.

MAGIC AI has received significant recognition, including $2.5 million in venture capital funding and awards such as the Technology Entrepreneur of the Year 2023. The company targets individuals seeking personalized fitness solutions at home, appealing to a wide range of users from beginners to advanced athletes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1303.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'magic-careers', null), ('175', 'TransitionZero', 'TransitionZero', 'https://www.transitionzero.org/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/transitionzero/', 'TransitionZero is a climate tech non-profit and data analytics company based in London. It focuses on accelerating the global transition to zero carbon by providing open-access energy system modeling data, software, and expert analysis. Founded by former Carbon Tracker employees, TransitionZero aims to support governments, NGOs, investors, and large companies, particularly in low-income countries, in planning and implementing clean and reliable energy systems.

The organization offers a range of services, including comprehensive open datasets, user-friendly modeling software, and expert analysis. Its notable projects include the Solar Asset Mapper, which covers solar farms across 182 countries, and various tools for tracking costs and carbon pricing. TransitionZero also provides training to build local expertise in energy system modeling and offers consulting services to help companies and investors transition away from fossil fuels and meet Net Zero goals. With a commitment to transparency and accessibility, TransitionZero seeks to empower decision-makers and promote effective energy transition planning worldwide.', 'They can only sponsor a limited number of visas and tend to reserve them for senior or specialist roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/485.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('176', 'Fleek', 'On Fleek Tech Ltd', 'https://www.joinfleek.com/home', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/joinfleek/', 'Fleek is a global online marketplace founded in November 2021 by Abhi and Sanket, aimed at transforming the vintage fashion wholesale supply chain. The company connects verified vintage wholesalers with retailers and resellers across multiple countries, including the UK, France, Germany, and the US. Fleek offers a curated selection of authentic vintage clothing, ensuring quality through rigorous inspections at supply hubs in Pakistan and India.

The platform features a global network of suppliers, a Buyer Protection Policy for secure transactions, and end-to-end logistics handling, including shipping and customs clearance. Flexible payment options, such as "Buy Now, Pay Later," enhance the buying experience. Additionally, Fleek includes an AI assistant named Fleeky, which helps buyers find suitable suppliers based on their needs. With over 300,000 customers, Fleek is recognized as a leading marketplace for verified vintage wholesalers, emphasizing trust and quality in the vintage fashion industry. The company has raised $20.4 million in funding, highlighting its growth potential.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '13', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1105.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('177', 'Orbital', 'Orbital Witness Limited', 'https://www.orbital.tech/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/orbitalwitness/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Orbital Tech is a technology consultancy and development firm that specializes in creating customized projects to meet business objectives and optimize resources. The company was formed from the merger of GLAO i.b.d., which has over 15 years of experience in business analysis, and Gonzalo Sánchez-Romero, who brings 20 years of expertise in internet infrastructure and technology management.

The firm offers a range of services, including needs analysis, talent integration, problem-solving, technology identification, consultation, and project management. Orbital Tech emphasizes a collaborative approach, working closely with clients to understand their challenges and deliver effective solutions. Their focus is on leveraging knowledge in business development, digitalization, and artificial intelligence to help businesses modernize and enhance their operational efficiency.', 'Sponsorship can be offered to "the right person".', '1', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/74.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/orbital', null), ('178', 'Verkada', 'Verkada Limited', 'https://www.verkada.com/uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/verkada/', 'Verkada is a technology company founded in 2016 by Stanford graduates, specializing in modernizing enterprise physical security. Headquartered in San Mateo, California, Verkada focuses on providing cloud-based software and Internet of Things (IoT) infrastructure to enhance safety in buildings.

The company offers a range of products, including cloud-managed video security cameras, access control systems, and environmental sensors. These solutions are designed to help organizations manage security and monitor environmental conditions effectively. All products are integrated through Verkada’s unified cloud platform, which provides real-time insights and facilitates immediate action to address security risks.

Verkada serves over 2,500 organizations globally, including 25 Fortune 500 companies across various sectors such as corporate offices, education, healthcare, retail, and government. The company aims to be the operating system for the world’s safest buildings, continuously innovating and expanding its offerings to meet the evolving needs of its customers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '17', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1005.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'verkada', null), ('179', 'Enreach', 'Enreach UK Limited', 'https://enreach.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/enreachuk/', 'Visit our parent page by searching ''Enreach UK''', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/906.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('180', 'Jaja', 'Jaja Finance Limited', 'https://jaja.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jaja-finance/', 'Jaja Finance is a UK-based fintech company founded in 2015 and headquartered in London. It specializes in digitally-led credit card products aimed at simplifying credit access and management. The company offers the Jaja Vanta Credit Card, which features a 34.9% APR representative (variable) and allows potential customers to check their likelihood of acceptance through an easy online application without impacting their credit score. Jaja Finance provides both digital and physical credit cards as part of its services.

The company''s mission is to become the leading digital lender in the UK by using high-quality financial data to make smarter lending decisions. Jaja partners with technology providers like Bud Financial to enhance credit risk assessment and improve the lending lifecycle. This collaboration allows Jaja to utilize advanced data enrichment techniques, promoting financial inclusion by serving underserved customers. Their services focus on a seamless application experience, ensuring data accuracy and relevance to approve more borrowers efficiently. Jaja Finance aims to deliver innovative credit solutions that are straightforward and accessible for UK consumers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1036.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'jajafinance', null), ('181', 'nudge Global', 'Nudge Global Limited', 'https://www.nudge-global.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/nudge-global-ltd/', 'nudge is a UK-based company founded in 2013, specializing in financial wellbeing solutions. Headquartered in London, it operates globally, focusing on enhancing individuals'' financial health through personalized education and behavioral insights. 

The company offers a financial wellbeing platform that features personalized nudges, engaging educational content, and intelligent money management tools. These services help users build better money habits, enhance their financial knowledge, and simplify budgeting and goal-setting. nudge supports employees and their families in 195 countries, providing a consistent experience with locally relevant financial education. 

nudge serves large multinational corporations, including SAP, Procter & Gamble, Meta, and Accenture. The platform is designed to improve employee financial health and increase the uptake of employee benefits. With around 36 employees and annual revenues of approximately $5.4 million, nudge is committed to empowering individuals to manage their financial commitments effectively.', null, '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1119.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'nudge', null), ('182', 'Gravity Sketch', 'Gravity Sketch Limited', 'https://www.gravitysketch.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gravitysketch/', 'Gravity Sketch is a 3D design platform based in London, United Kingdom. It enables cross-disciplinary teams to create, collaborate, and review designs in a virtual environment, moving beyond traditional 2D methods. The platform enhances the design process with real-time feedback and immersive presentations, improving clarity and understanding of design intent.

