The core product is a parametric flood insurance policy that provides broad and flexible coverage based on objective sensor data, rather than traditional loss assessments. This model reduces basis risk and speeds up claims processing, covering various financial losses from flooding, including business interruption. FloodFlash serves a diverse clientele, including commercial property owners, utilities, and high-profile organizations, positioning itself as an insurer for risks often considered uninsurable by traditional markets. The company is backed by A-rated Lloyd’s capacity, ensuring financial stability and reliability.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/431.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('211', 'Proximie', 'Proximie Limited', 'https://www.proximie.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/proximie/', 'Proximie is a digital medicine company founded in 2016 by Dr. Nadine Hachach-Haram. The company aims to transform surgical care by creating a "borderless operating room" using advanced mixed reality technology. This technology allows clinicians, proctors, and medical device personnel to be virtually present in operating rooms worldwide, facilitating real-time remote assistance, mentoring, and observation during surgical procedures.

The Proximie platform enables surgeons to collaborate during live surgeries, allowing for communication, annotation, and guidance from anywhere. It is designed to be user-friendly and accessible in various healthcare settings, making it particularly valuable in resource-limited environments. Proximie also produces educational content to enhance the accessibility of surgical knowledge. With a presence in over 500 hospitals across more than 50 countries, Proximie is dedicated to improving surgical outcomes and training through innovative technology and a commitment to democratizing surgical expertise.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/106.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('212', 'Qogita', 'Qogita UK Ltd', 'https://www.qogita.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/qogita/', 'Qogita is a London-based B2B wholesale marketplace focused on the health and beauty sector. Founded in 2021 by Danny and Yaniv Toledano, it connects wholesalers, manufacturers, and a wide range of buyers, including Amazon sellers and retail stores, across Europe and the UK. The platform features a vast catalog of over 500,000 products from more than 500 vetted suppliers and 10,000 brands, including well-known names like Maybelline and Dior.

The marketplace allows buyers to easily browse products, build orders through various methods, and enjoy competitive pricing with low minimum order values. Qogita''s technology streamlines the order process by automatically allocating orders to sellers based on key factors. It also provides tools for tracking, invoicing, and analytics to help buyers make informed procurement decisions. For sellers, Qogita offers access to new markets without listing fees and support for exporting. With a team of around 75 employees and buyers in 28 countries, Qogita aims to enhance wholesale procurement for small and medium-sized businesses.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/12.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'qogita', null), ('214', 'Choco', 'CHOCO COMMUNICATIONS UK LTD', 'https://choco.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/choco-app/', 'Choco is a technology company based in Berlin, Germany, founded in 2018. It offers an AI-powered digital platform that connects restaurants and food suppliers, aiming to enhance efficiency, reduce food waste, and promote sustainability in the food supply chain. By digitizing the traditionally manual ordering process, Choco simplifies operations for both restaurants and suppliers.

The platform features a user-friendly app for restaurants, allowing chefs and managers to place orders quickly and accurately. For food distributors and wholesalers, Choco provides an AI-driven system that captures orders from various channels and integrates them into existing ERP systems. This eliminates manual data entry and includes tools for sales and marketing, enabling distributors to analyze customer data and streamline their operations.

Choco operates in multiple markets, including the U.S., Germany, France, Spain, the UK, Austria, and Belgium, and has facilitated over $1.2 billion in goods traded through its platform. Its mission is to create a transparent and sustainable food distribution system, significantly reducing errors and food waste in the industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/314.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/choco', null), ('215', 'Build A Rocket Boy', 'Build A Rocket Boy Limited', 'https://www.buildarocketboy.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/buildarocketboy/', 'Build A Rocket Boy is a video game development studio based in Edinburgh, Scotland, founded in 2016. Originally named Royal Circus Games, the company rebranded in 2018. It was co-founded by Leslie Benzies, known for his work on the Grand Theft Auto series. The studio focuses on creating immersive open-world gaming experiences that prioritize interactivity and player creativity.

