Crestline offers a wide range of capital solutions tailored for middle-market companies, including senior secured debt, unitranche loans, second-lien debt, structured equity, and bespoke NAV finance solutions. The firm also invests in European middle-market companies and manages specialty finance programs and real estate lending strategies. Additionally, Crestline operates a multi-portfolio manager equity market-neutral hedge fund strategy and provides beta overlay and hedging solutions to institutional clients. Through its affiliate, CL Life, it offers annuity products aimed at capital protection. 

Crestline''s leadership includes Founder and CEO Mr. Bratton, who has extensive experience in alternative asset strategies. The firm is committed to delivering innovative investment solutions that provide sustainable income and continuity for its global clientele.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/843.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'crestline', null), ('229', 'trumpet', 'Trumpet Software Limited', 'https://www.sendtrumpet.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sendtrumpet/', 'Trumpet is a software company that specializes in digital sales rooms and customer onboarding software. Its platform enhances the revenue cycle for sales teams and their customers by centralizing sales processes into interactive, personalized, and trackable digital spaces known as "Pods." These Pods consolidate demos, documents, communications, and collaboration tools into one organized workspace.

The Trumpet platform supports account-based selling, post-demo follow-ups, and revenue intelligence. It integrates with various sales and CRM tools, making it suitable for small to medium-sized teams, particularly in industries like RevTech, SalesTech, and MarTech. Key features include customizable digital sales rooms, real-time collaboration tools, and analytics for tracking buyer engagement. The platform is designed to accelerate customer onboarding and improve alignment between sales teams and clients, ultimately enhancing the overall sales experience. Pricing starts at approximately £29 per year, with options for custom pricing based on organizational needs.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/925.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'trumpet', null), ('230', '6sense', '6sense Insights UK Ltd', 'https://6sense.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/6sense/', '6sense is a technology company based in San Francisco, California, founded in 2013. It specializes in AI-driven predictive analytics and account-based marketing solutions tailored for B2B sales and marketing teams. The company helps identify potential customers, predict their buying behavior, and automate personalized engagement to enhance sales efficiency and drive revenue growth.

The core offering of 6sense is a platform that aggregates various data signals to provide insights into customer intent. This platform allows sales and marketing teams to identify and prioritize accounts, automate outreach workflows, and execute personalized account-based marketing campaigns. It integrates seamlessly with existing sales and marketing technology stacks, enabling data-driven decision-making.

6sense serves over 2,000 customers across various industries, focusing on optimizing sales and marketing efforts through predictive analytics. The company is led by CEO Jason Zintak and has raised over $200 million in funding, reflecting its strong market position and growth potential.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/801.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', '6sense', null), ('232', 'Raylo', 'Raylo Group Limited', 'https://www.raylo.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/raylo/', 'Raylo is a UK-based technology company that specializes in device leasing, providing consumers with access to high-end tech products like smartphones and laptops through affordable monthly subscription plans starting from around £7.99. The company aims to make circular consumption mainstream by offering a sustainable alternative to traditional device ownership, extending the life of existing products and reducing electronic waste.

Raylo''s leasing model allows customers to access new or refurbished devices without the high upfront costs of purchasing. At the end of the lease term, customers can choose to upgrade to a new device, continue using their current device, or return it. The company emphasizes sustainability by refurbishing returned devices and using plant-based packaging and electric vehicles. Raylo has achieved B Corporation certification, reflecting its commitment to social and environmental performance. With significant funding secured, Raylo is focused on innovating in the tech subscription market while promoting environmental responsibility.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/412.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'raylo', null), ('233', 'Crowdcube', 'Crowdcube Limited', 'https://www.crowdcube.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/crowdcube-limited/', 'Crowdcube is a British equity crowdfunding platform founded in 2011 by Darren Westlake and Luke Lang, based in London. The company aims to democratize investment by allowing everyday people to invest in startups and growing businesses, breaking down traditional barriers to angel investing.

The platform serves as a digital marketplace where entrepreneurs can raise capital by offering equity stakes to a wide range of investors, from first-time investors to seasoned professionals. With over 1,300 funding deals completed, Crowdcube has raised more than £1.2 billion for various businesses, including well-known names like BrewDog and Monzo. The platform emphasizes community-backed funding, enabling entrepreneurs to gain support from their customers and enhance marketing efforts.

Crowdcube was the first equity crowdfunding platform in the UK and has worked closely with the Financial Conduct Authority to ensure regulatory compliance. With over 1.7 million members, it fosters a vibrant investment community and provides accessible opportunities for individuals to invest in innovative businesses.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/212.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('234', 'Carmoola', 'Carmoola Corporate Services Limited', 'https://www.carmoola.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carmoola/', 'Carmoola is a UK-based fintech company that specializes in innovative used car financing solutions. Founded in 2021, Carmoola aims to simplify the car buying experience by providing fast, flexible, and transparent financing options. The company operates as a credit granting finance house, focusing on consumer credit for car purchases. It offers instant budget and finance approvals within 60 seconds, allowing customers to know their borrowing limits before searching for a vehicle.

Carmoola''s core product is a virtual credit card for approved buyers, which can be used to purchase vehicles online or at dealerships. This approach eliminates traditional brokers and their fees, enabling consumers to save money and expand their vehicle options. The financing model is designed to be flexible, allowing customers to adjust payment terms and pause payments without penalties. Carmoola also provides a fully digital application process, instant finance approval, unlimited free car checks, and extensive customer support resources to help buyers make informed decisions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1187.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'carmoola-1', null), ('235', 'Alpha Data', 'Alpha Data Parallel Systems Ltd', 'https://www.alpha-data.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/alpha-data-parallel-systems-limited/', 'Alpha Data is a leading global supplier of high performance COTS reconfigurable computer platforms and support software.  Focusing on the strategic market areas of digital signal processing (DSP), imaging systems, communications, military and aerospace and high performance computing (HPC), Space FPGA prototyping, Alpha Data has established a global customer base and reputation for leading edge design.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/818.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'alphawave/jobs', null), ('236', 'Informa', 'Informa UK Limited', 'https://www.informa.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/informa/', 'Informa plc is a global leader in business intelligence, academic publishing, and events, established in 1998 from the merger of IBC Group plc and LLP Group plc. The company has a rich history, with roots in notable brands like Taylor & Francis, an academic publisher founded in 1734.

Informa operates through three main divisions: Informa Connect, which delivers specialist events and training; Informa Markets, which organizes large-scale exhibitions and trade shows; and Informa Tech, providing B2B digital services and intelligence. Its diverse product portfolio includes academic journals, business intelligence reports, live events, and digital services tailored for professional and specialist markets. Informa serves a global customer base that includes academic institutions, professionals, and businesses seeking specialized knowledge and networking opportunities. The company is committed to growth through strategic acquisitions and innovation in its offerings.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '15', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1102.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'InformaGroupPlc', null), ('238', 'Stream', 'Wagestream Ltd', 'https://stream.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wagestream/', 'Stream is a London-based financial wellbeing platform founded in 2018. The company aims to improve the financial health of frontline workers by addressing the "poverty premium," which refers to the higher costs that lower-income workers face for financial services. Wagestream partners with over 1,000 employers, including notable names like Asda, Next, and the NHS, to serve nearly 3 million employees globally.The core offering of Wagestream is an app that provides Earned Wage Access (EWA), allowing employees to access a portion of their earned wages before payday. This service is complemented by a range of financial wellbeing tools, including real-time pay tracking, savings features, financial education, interactive payslips, and discounts on shopping and bills. The platform operates on a B2B2C model, integrating securely with employers'' payroll and HR systems. Wagestream is committed to social impact, guided by a charter and an Impact Advisory Board, and conducts ongoing research to enhance financial wellbeing for users.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/214.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'stream', null), ('239', 'Criteo', 'Criteo Ltd', 'https://www.criteo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/criteo/', 'Criteo is a global technology company based in Paris, France, specializing in digital advertising and commerce media. Founded in 2005, it offers a Commerce Media Platform that connects brands, retailers, and publishers to create personalized advertising experiences across the internet. Criteo leverages exclusive commerce data and advanced artificial intelligence to enable targeted marketing campaigns that drive customer acquisition, retention, and monetization.

The company provides a range of services, including performance display advertising, demand-side and supply-side platforms, and retail media monetization solutions. Criteo supports enterprise brands, retailers, agencies, and media owners with customized online marketing strategies. Its tools are designed to optimize advertising spend and maximize return on investment. Criteo''s customer base includes thousands of global brands, such as Sephora, Macy’s, Fiat, and Pepsi, and it facilitates over $1 trillion in annual commerce transactions, reaching approximately 2.5 billion users worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/738.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'criteo', null), ('240', 'TypeDB', 'Vaticle Ltd', 'https://typedb.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/typedb/', 'TypeDB is an open-source distributed database management system designed to model, manage, and query complex, interconnected data. It features a user-defined type system and offers two editions: the TypeDB Community Edition and the proprietary TypeDB Cloud, which includes cloud-based management capabilities. The company behind TypeDB, TYPEDB LTD, is based in the United Kingdom and focuses on software development for business and domestic applications.

TypeDB utilizes a unique data and query model that moves away from traditional relational databases. It employs types, subtyping, and type dependencies, allowing for schema extensions and clearer data relationships. Its query language, TypeQL, is designed to be intuitive and efficient, enabling users to write concise queries. Key features include ACID compliance, static type-checking, a graphical user interface called TypeDB Studio, and a robust storage engine. TypeDB is particularly suited for applications in AI, cyber threat intelligence, and robotics, making it ideal for enterprises and researchers needing advanced data modeling and querying capabilities.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/75.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('241', 'Agreena', 'Agreena Technology Limited', 'https://agreena.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/agreena/', 'Agreena is a Denmark-based climate solutions company dedicated to promoting regenerative agriculture. It operates Europe’s leading soil carbon program, AgreenaCarbon, which is the first large-scale arable agriculture project registered under Verra''s Verified Carbon Standard. The company partners with thousands of farmers across 20 European markets, covering around 4.5 million hectares of arable land, to support the transition from traditional farming to regenerative practices that enhance soil carbon sequestration.

Agreena offers a range of services, including a carbon credit program that mints, verifies, and sells carbon credits from regenerative farming. The company utilizes advanced technology, such as AI and satellite imagery, for digital measurement, reporting, and verification of farming practices. Additionally, Agreena provides climate solutions for businesses, helping them meet sustainability goals and improve supply chain transparency. With a commitment to connecting people, nature, and technology, Agreena plays a significant role in advancing sustainable agriculture and climate change mitigation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1047.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'agreena', null), ('242', 'Prezzee', 'Prezzee UK Limited', 'https://www.prezzee.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/prezzee/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/966.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'prezzee', null), ('243', 'Continuum', 'Continuum Industries Ltd', 'https://www.continuum.industries/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/continuum-ind/', 'Continuum Industries is a private limited company based in Edinburgh, Scotland, founded in June 2018. The company specializes in software development for business and domestic applications, as well as research and experimental development in natural sciences and engineering. Its mission is to create a global solution for infrastructure planning that allows projects to be completed more quickly and with reduced risk.

The company offers an AI-powered platform called Optioneer, tailored for utilities and developers in the energy sector. This platform enhances infrastructure planning, site selection, and optioneering by optimizing project workflows and transforming complex data into clear visual narratives. Key features of Optioneer include significantly compressing project timelines, de-risking network planning, and facilitating the development of hydrogen and water networks. Continuum Industries serves over 30 organizations across the US and Europe, focusing on power, utility, and renewables companies that aim to improve their infrastructure development processes.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1202.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'lever', 'continuum', null), ('244', 'Flash Pack', 'Flash Pack Travel Ltd', 'https://www.flashpack.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-flash-pack/', 'Flash Pack is a London-based adventure travel company founded in 2014 by Radha Vyas and Lee Thompson. It specializes in curated group trips for solo travelers, primarily those in their 30s, 40s, and 50s. The company aims to foster meaningful friendships through immersive travel experiences designed for like-minded individuals.

Flash Pack offers a variety of guided group tours, typically limiting groups to 14-16 members to create a friendly atmosphere. Their trips blend backpacking and luxury travel, featuring unique experiences like yacht trips to secluded islands and glamping in converted Land Rovers on the Serengeti. Destinations include locations across Asia, Africa, Europe, and the Americas, with trip categories such as Beach Holidays, City Breaks, and Wildlife adventures. Each trip includes premium accommodations and a dedicated local Pack Leader to ensure a high-quality experience.', 'The company sponsors roles across Product and Engineering. Their priority is to find the right fit, and are happy to sponsor that person.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/183.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'app', null), ('245', 'Checkout.com', 'Checkout Ltd', 'https://checkout.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/checkout/', 'Checkout.com is a British multinational financial technology company that specializes in global digital payment processing. Founded in 2009 by Guillaume Pousaz, the company is headquartered in London and has become one of the most valuable fintech startups in Europe, with a valuation of $40 billion in 2022.

The company offers a unified payment processing platform that allows businesses to accept payments worldwide through a single integration. Its technology combines various payment components, including gateways, processors, and fraud detection, into one seamless API. Key features include in-country acquiring, support for local payment methods, real-time fraud monitoring, and comprehensive reporting tools. Checkout.com serves a diverse range of customers, including major enterprises like Netflix, Pizza Hut, and Uber Eats, with over 300 global enterprises using its services.

Checkout.com has experienced significant growth, particularly in the US market, and is expanding its capabilities in Canada and Brazil. The company has achieved profitability early on and continues to grow through strategic partnerships and acquisitions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor and are definitely able to sponsor visas for Ukrainian citizens.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/43.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'CheckoutCareers', null), ('246', 'Twine', 'Clowdy Ltd', 'https://www.twine.net/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/twine.is/', 'Twine is a UK-based online marketplace headquartered in Manchester, connecting creative freelancers with buyers seeking their services. The platform, which rebranded from Clowdy in 2016, allows freelancers such as musicians, designers, filmmakers, and animators to collaborate on projects while ensuring all contributors receive credit. With over 750,000 freelance experts from more than 190 countries, Twine supports a wide range of creative and technical fields, including software development, graphic design, animation, and video production.

In addition to its marketplace, Twine features an AI platform that enhances communication and feedback for sales and customer success teams. This AI captures insights from calls and routes customer intelligence to relevant teams, helping to streamline product and go-to-market strategies. Twine''s mission focuses on creating an operating system that connects data and people, addressing challenges in data centralization and fostering innovation and improved customer experiences.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/129.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('247', 'Atla AI', 'Atla AI Ltd', 'https://www.atla-ai.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/atla-ai/', 'Atla is a technology company that specializes in AI agent evaluation and improvement. Founded in 2018 as a spin-off from Aarhus University in Denmark, Atla focuses on transforming advanced AI research into practical tools for developers and organizations. The company emphasizes explainability, transparency, and accountability in AI systems, aiming to address root causes of failures.

Atla offers a comprehensive platform for agent observability and evaluation, which provides real-time visibility into AI agents'' processes. This platform automatically detects errors and identifies patterns of failure, helping teams reduce manual review time and accelerate debugging. Additionally, Atla features the Selene model, a large language model trained to evaluate AI responses, and an alignment platform that allows users to customize evaluation criteria for their specific needs. Their solutions are designed for AI developers and research teams looking to enhance the performance and reliability of AI agents in production environments.', 'The company is prepared to sponsor the right candidate.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/788.png', 'false', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('248', 'Monese', 'Monese Limited', 'https://monese.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/monese/', 'Monese is a UK-based digital challenger bank founded in 2013 by Norris Koppel. Headquartered in London, with offices in Tallinn, Berlin, and Lisbon, it focuses on providing mobile banking services for expatriates, immigrants, and refugees who may struggle to open traditional bank accounts. The company employs around 200 people and serves millions of customers across 31 countries, offering services in 14 languages.

Monese''s main product is a mobile app that allows users to quickly open a UK or European current account without needing a fixed address or credit history. The app supports personal and business accounts, instant account opening, and provides a Visa debit card for everyday transactions. Monese also offers premium accounts with additional benefits, international transfer services, and a Banking-as-a-Service platform launched in 2023 to enhance its infrastructure. The company emphasizes financial inclusion and collaborates with charities to support vulnerable groups, making banking accessible to those facing barriers in new countries.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/202.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('250', 'Finbourne', 'Finbourne Technology Limited', 'https://www.finbourne.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/finbourne/', 'FINBOURNE Technology is a leading fintech company based in London, specializing in investment management solutions and a cloud-native data management platform for the financial services industry. Founded in 2016, the company operates globally with six offices and a team of over 250 professionals. FINBOURNE aims to empower financial firms by enhancing their data and investment capabilities, allowing them to improve client services and adapt to market changes.

The company''s flagship product, LUSID, serves as an operational data store and portfolio management platform, providing a comprehensive view of financial data across various operational areas. Additionally, Luminesce is a data virtualization tool that simplifies data connectivity throughout the investment lifecycle. FINBOURNE''s solutions cater to a diverse range of clients, including asset managers, banking firms, and asset owners, helping them manage over $4.1 trillion in assets efficiently. With a focus on innovation and client success, FINBOURNE continues to expand its offerings and global presence.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/564.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'finbourne', null), ('252', 'ASOS', 'ASOS.com Ltd', 'https://www.asos.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/asos-com/', 'ASOS.com is a prominent global online fashion retailer based in London, founded in 2000. Initially launched as "As Seen On Screen," the company focused on clothing inspired by celebrity styles but has since expanded to offer a diverse range of fashion products. ASOS serves over 20 million active customers across more than 200 international markets, making it a key player in the fast fashion e-commerce sector.

The company features a variety of proprietary fashion lines, including ASOS DESIGN, ASOS EDITION, COLLUSION, Topshop, and Topman, catering to a wide array of styles and preferences. In addition to its own brands, ASOS showcases hundreds of partner brands, providing customers with a curated selection of the latest trends. The ASOS Marketplace platform allows boutiques and individual sellers to reach customers worldwide, further enhancing the product variety available. With a focus on making fashion accessible, ASOS empowers young adults, particularly those in their 20s, to express their individuality through trendy and affordable options.', 'Sponsorship can only be offered for very niche roles, and it''s quite unlikely they will offer sponsorship alongside the vast majority of their opportunities.', '1', '57', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/48.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'ASOS', null), ('253', 'MOO', 'MOO Print Limited', 'https://www.moo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/moo-com/', 'MOO is a UK-based online printing company founded in London in 2004 by Richard Moross. It specializes in high-quality print products, serving customers in over 200 countries, with a notable presence in the US and Europe. MOO has evolved from a small startup to a global business, focusing on both the commercial and consumer markets.

For businesses, MOO offers customizable products like business cards, letterheads, and stationery to help brands stand out. For consumers, the company provides personalized items such as stickers, gift cards, greeting cards, and MiniCards. MOO is recognized for its innovative approach to print design, encouraging users to create and customize their products through an easy-to-use online platform. The company is guided by core values that emphasize collaboration, customer focus, environmental responsibility, and great design.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/398.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'lever', 'moo', null), ('254', 'Personio', 'Personio Group SE (UK Branch)', 'https://www.personio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/personio/?originalSubdomain=de', 'Personio is a German software company founded in 2015 and based in Munich. It specializes in cloud-based human resources (HR) management solutions for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) with up to 2,000 employees. The company was established by a group of founders who met at the Technical University of Munich and the Center for Digital Technology & Management.

The core offering of Personio is an all-in-one HR software platform that simplifies and automates various HR processes, including recruitment, employee management, payroll, absence tracking, and compliance. This subscription-driven platform helps HR teams streamline workflows and enhance employee experiences. Personio''s software integrates with existing HR systems and covers a wide range of functions, making it particularly suited for SMEs that have historically lacked dedicated digital HR solutions.

As of 2025, Personio serves over 12,000 customers in around 70 countries, with a strong presence in Germany. The company has experienced rapid growth, employing about 2,000 people and operating in multiple cities, including Berlin, London, and New York. Personio has raised over $700 million in venture capital, positioning it as one of Germany''s most valuable unicorns.', 'The company can offer sponsorship for some roles, but there is no specific policy. They treat sponsorship on a case-by-case basis.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/56.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('255', 'Modulr', 'Modulr Finance Limited', 'https://www.modulrfinance.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/modulr-finance/', 'Modulr Finance is a UK-based fintech company that specializes in embedded payment solutions to automate and simplify business payment processes. Founded in 2015 and headquartered in London, Modulr operates a cloud-first platform that integrates payment capabilities directly into digital businesses'' products or systems. The company aims to create a world where all businesses are powered by embedded payments.

With over 400 employees across offices in London, Edinburgh, Amsterdam, and Mumbai, Modulr is regulated as an electronic money institution by the UK’s Financial Conduct Authority and the Dutch central bank. Their offerings include automated payment systems, open banking technology, card generation, and an embedded payments API. Modulr collaborates with various software providers to embed payments into existing platforms or create new payment-enabled products. Their services are designed for businesses looking to streamline payment workflows and enhance security while ensuring compliance with regulatory standards.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/233.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'modulrfinance', null), ('256', 'Ki Insurance', 'Brit Group Services Limited', 'https://ki-insurance.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ki-insurance/', 'Ki Insurance is a digital-first insurance company and Lloyd’s of London syndicate, founded in 2021 and based in London. The company specializes in providing instant underwriting and quotes for complex and specialty commercial insurance risks. By leveraging advanced machine learning and proprietary algorithms developed in collaboration with Google Cloud and University College London, Ki Insurance significantly reduces the traditional quoting process from days to seconds.

The company offers a digital platform tailored for insurance brokers, allowing them to obtain instant quotes from multiple capacity providers simultaneously. This platform features instant underwriting decisions, a comprehensive management system for tracking policies, and 24/7 broker support. Ki Insurance focuses on insuring complex risks, including offshore wind farms and specialized assets, ensuring a seamless digital experience for brokers in the Lloyd’s market. With strong financial backing and a commitment to innovation, Ki Insurance is redefining the commercial insurance landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1130.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'ki-insurance', null), ('257', 'Oncimmune', 'Oncimmune Holdings Plc', 'https://www.oncimmune.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oncimmune/', 'Oncimmune - An Alden Scientific Company is a prominent developer in immunodiagnostics, focusing on immuno-oncology, autoimmune diseases, and infectious diseases. The company aims to enhance the understanding of the immune system to create more effective and safer treatments, along with improved diagnostic methods.

With the world''s largest antigen libraries, containing over 9,000 human antigens and multi-species variants, Oncimmune supports innovative technologies for antibody and autoantibody biomarker discovery. Their advanced analytical platform is designed to identify antibody biomarker signatures, which are essential for early disease detection and precision medicine. The company employs an integrated strategy that encompasses operations, technical and research development, and commercial activities, ensuring it remains a leader in immunodiagnostic innovation.

Oncimmune''s services include the development of immunodiagnostic tests, access to extensive antigen libraries, and solutions for multi-omic research. Their technologies cater to pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies, clinical laboratories, healthcare providers, and research institutions focused on immune-related conditions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/482.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('258', 'Better.co.uk', 'Trussle Lab Ltd', 'https://better.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/betterdotuk/', 'Better.co.uk is a digital mortgage broker based in the UK, dedicated to making the mortgage process simpler, faster, and more affordable for its customers. Originally launched as Trussle in 2015, the company rebranded in 2023 after being acquired by Better, a US-based digital homeownership company. Better.co.uk operates online, utilizing technology to compare around 12,000 mortgage products from over 100 lenders to find optimal solutions for clients.

The company offers a variety of services, including residential mortgages, remortgaging, buy-to-let mortgages, and bridging loans. It also provides mortgage protection services and secured homeowner loans for various needs. Better.co.uk is authorized by the UK Financial Conduct Authority, ensuring compliance and consumer protection. With offices in London and Cardiff, the company employs over 200 staff, including software engineers who enhance its mortgage comparison platform. Better.co.uk has received a high Trustpilot rating and is recognized for its innovative approach in the property technology sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/476.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'lever', 'better', null), ('259', 'The London Interdisciplinary School (LIS)', 'London Interdisciplinary School', 'https://www.lis.ac.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/school/lis-london-interdisciplinary-school/', 'The London Interdisciplinary School (LIS) is a private higher education institution located in Whitechapel, East London, established in 2017. It is recognized as the first new UK university since the 1960s to receive degree-awarding powers from its inception. LIS emphasizes an interdisciplinary, problem-based approach to education, integrating insights from various fields such as neuroscience, law, philosophy, and mathematics to prepare students for real-world challenges.

LIS offers a variety of academic programs, including a Bachelor of Arts and Sciences (BASc) and a Master of Arts and Sciences (MASc) in Interdisciplinary Problems and Methods, as well as an MBA program. The school also provides professional courses tailored for individuals and organizations. Classes are designed to be interactive, focusing on group work and active learning, with smaller class sizes in advanced years. The institution aims to develop leaders who can navigate complex global issues by fostering a broad intellectual range that combines arts, sciences, and humanities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/940.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('260', 'Space Ape Games', 'Space Ape Games (UK) Ltd', 'https://spaceapegames.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/space-ape-games/', 'Space Ape Games is a mobile game development company based in London, UK, founded in 2012. The company specializes in creating high-quality mid-core and casual mobile games, emphasizing live operations and community engagement. Known for its innovative gameplay, Space Ape has developed popular titles such as *Beatstar - Touch Your Music*, *Transformers: Earth Wars*, *Rival Kingdoms*, and *Samurai Siege*.

