Their platform tracks carbon offset projects, retirements, and buyer activity, allowing users to assess project quality and analyze market trends. AlliedOffsets employs a proprietary algorithm to evaluate the credit quality of offset projects, helping clients ensure they purchase the correct volume of offsets and fostering trust in the market. The company serves a diverse clientele, including corporates, investors, project developers, traders, and researchers, providing tools that support informed decision-making and product development. AlliedOffsets is committed to increasing transparency and standardization in the voluntary carbon market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1023.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('287', 'Varnish Software', 'Varnish Software Limited', 'https://www.varnish-software.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/varnish-software/', 'Varnish Software is a technology company based in Stockholm, Sweden, that specializes in high-performance content delivery solutions. Founded in 2010, it evolved from the open-source Varnish Cache project, which was designed to accelerate HTTP content delivery for high-traffic websites. The company focuses on the development, support, and commercialization of Varnish Cache and related software products.

The core product, Varnish Cache, is a high-performance HTTP accelerator that enhances content delivery for dynamic websites and APIs. It operates as a reverse caching proxy, specifically targeting HTTP traffic. Varnish Software also provides commercial support and additional software products to optimize digital content delivery. Their technology is trusted by over 10 million websites globally, including major brands like Nikon, Sky, Emirates, and Tesla. The company emphasizes flexibility and speed in its caching technology, aiming to improve user experience by reducing server load and accelerating web page loading times.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/924.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('288', 'Acquia', 'Acquia Ltd', 'https://www.acquia.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/acquia/', 'Acquia is an open source software company founded in 2007 by Dries Buytaert, the creator of Drupal. It specializes in providing infrastructure, support, and services for enterprise users of Drupal and digital experience management. Acquia has developed into a prominent provider of digital experience platforms (DXP) and content management solutions, helping brands build, operate, and optimize their digital experiences.

The company offers a variety of services, including Acquia Cloud for managed hosting, a comprehensive Digital Experience Platform that integrates content management and marketing tools, and a Customer Data Platform that utilizes machine learning for personalized communication. Acquia also provides digital asset management and product information management solutions, along with a visual website builder called Cohesion. With a focus on large enterprises, Acquia''s solutions are designed to enhance content management and customer engagement across multiple channels and devices. The company employs over 1,200 people and is recognized as one of the largest open source companies globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/355.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'acquia', null), ('289', 'Element', 'New Vector Limited', 'https://element.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/element-hq/', 'Element is a technology company founded in 2017 by the creators of the Matrix protocol, which focuses on secure, decentralized communication. The company aims to promote freedom in communication by allowing users to choose their hosting options within a global, open network governed by the Matrix.org Foundation.

