The firm provides a wide array of legal services, including corporate law, litigation and dispute resolution, taxation advisory, intellectual property disputes, and banking and financial services law. White & Case is particularly recognized for its expertise in complex cross-border transactions and disputes, catering to a diverse clientele that includes sovereign states and various industries.

With a focus on global collaboration, White & Case fosters a culture that values language skills and cross-border problem-solving. The firm has a rich history of involvement in significant financial and legal developments, reinforcing its reputation as a leader in the international legal landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/769.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'breezy', 'white', null), ('343', 'Tide', 'Tide Platform Limited', 'https://www.tide.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tide-banking/', 'Tide is a UK-based financial technology company founded in 2015 by George Bevis and Eileen Burbidge. It operates as a digital-only business financial platform aimed at small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). Tide offers a variety of financial products and services, including business bank accounts, loans, automated bookkeeping, and invoicing tools, all accessible through mobile apps for iOS and Android. The company has gained recognition for simplifying business banking and financial management, serving over 1.5 million small businesses worldwide.

Headquartered in London, Tide was one of the first digital-only firms in the UK to receive a banking license. It has played a significant role in supporting SMEs, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic, by lending over £50 million through the Bounce Back Loan Scheme. Tide is committed to innovation and customer-centric solutions, making it one of the fastest-growing fintech companies in the UK, with a focus on helping business owners save time and money.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/311.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'tide', null), ('345', 'Demandbase', 'Demandbase Limited', 'https://www.demandbase.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/demandbase/', 'Demandbase is a San Francisco-based company founded in 2006 by Chris Golec. It specializes in account-based marketing (ABM) solutions for B2B companies. The company focuses on helping businesses identify, reach, and convert high-value accounts online by utilizing AI and validated B2B data. Demandbase''s platform supports every stage of the buyer’s journey, enabling companies to optimize their marketing and sales efforts.

Recognized as a leader in the digital B2B marketing space, Demandbase offers a comprehensive ABM platform that integrates AI with sales and marketing data. This platform connects various advertising exchanges, content management systems, marketing automation tools, and CRM systems, facilitating seamless coordination across marketing and sales activities. Demandbase''s solutions encompass account-based advertising, website personalization, and real-time identification technology, all aimed at maximizing revenue by focusing on the most promising accounts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/845.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'demandbase', null), ('347', 'Minor Figures', 'Minor Figures Limited', 'https://minorfigures.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/minor-figures/', 'Minor Figures is a London-based coffee company founded in 2014 by a group of friends and baristas passionate about sustainability and enhancing coffee experiences. Initially focused on specialty coffee, the company has become a leader in the alternative milk market, particularly known for its barista-style oat milk designed to improve coffee quality.

The company offers a range of oat milk products, including original, light, and organic versions, as well as nitrogen-infused ready-to-drink beverages like cold brew coffee, chai, and mocha. Minor Figures emphasizes sustainability, operating as a carbon-neutral B-Corp and actively working to reduce its carbon footprint through various initiatives. With a presence in over 25 countries, including the UK, Australia, and the Asia-Pacific region, Minor Figures targets plant-based consumers and coffee enthusiasts seeking high-quality, innovative coffee solutions.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/60.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'minorfigures', null), ('348', 'LoveCrafts', 'LoveCrafts Group Limited', 'https://www.lovecrafts.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lovecrafts/', 'LoveCrafts is a global online community and marketplace for makers and crafters, focusing on knitting, crochet, sewing, cross stitch, embroidery, and quilting. Founded in 2012, the company was created to provide a centralized platform for craft enthusiasts to find materials and inspiration. Initially launched as LoveKnitting, it expanded to include LoveCrochet in 2015, and in 2019, both brands were unified under the LoveCrafts name.

The platform offers a wide range of products, including yarns, needles, patterns, and other crafting supplies. It features an independent pattern marketplace integrated with Ravelry, allowing designers to sell their patterns directly to users. LoveCrafts serves a diverse global customer base, promoting inclusivity and the joy of crafting across various cultures. The company combines commerce, content, and community, making it a vibrant destination for both hobbyists and professional makers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/787.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('350', 'University of the West of England Bristol (UWE Bristol)', 'University of the West of England', 'https://www.uwe.ac.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/school/university-of-the-west-of-england/', 'The University of the West of England (UWE Bristol) is a public university located in and around Bristol, UK. With roots dating back to 1595, it officially became a university in 1992, evolving from Bristol Polytechnic. UWE Bristol serves over 27,000 students and employs around 3,000 staff, attracting a diverse community from the UK and over 140 countries.

UWE Bristol offers more than 600 academic programs across fourteen departments, including undergraduate, postgraduate, professional, and short courses. The university emphasizes high teaching quality and strong industry partnerships, providing students with valuable real-world experience. UWE is also engaged in impactful research that advances various fields, contributing to the social and economic development of the Bristol region.

Recent developments include a £250 million investment in campus infrastructure, enhancing facilities for the Faculty of Business and Law, student accommodations, and a new Student Union building. UWE Bristol is committed to delivering a comprehensive educational experience while fostering employability and community engagement.', 'The university offers sponsorship alongside many of its roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/525.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'university', null), ('351', '3P Learning', '3P Learning Limited', 'https://www.3plearning.com/?', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/3p-learning/', '3P Learning is an Australian public company based in North Sydney, dedicated to developing online educational software and resources for schools and families around the world. Founded in 2003, the company creates engaging digital learning experiences in mathematics, literacy, spelling, and science.

The flagship products include Mathletics, an online mathematics platform widely used in primary schools, and Reading Eggs, a literacy software product. Additionally, 3P Learning offers Writing Legends, which focuses on improving writing skills. Their services support blended teaching approaches, featuring interactive games, ebooks, and comprehensive learning programs tailored to various student needs and learning styles.

With a customer base of over 17,000 schools and more than 5.5 million students across 179 countries, 3P Learning has a significant global presence. The company is publicly traded on the Australian Securities Exchange under the ticker symbol 3PL and employs around 390 people. Its leadership team is committed to innovation and expanding product offerings to enhance its market position in the educational software industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/764.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('352', 'Convene', 'Convene UK Holdings Limited', 'https://convene.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/convene-com/', 'Convene is a global lifestyle hospitality company based in New York City, founded in 2009. It specializes in designing and operating premium meeting, event, and flexible office spaces. As the largest dedicated provider of meeting and event venues in North America and the UK, Convene has nearly 40 locations across nine cities. Its portfolio includes brands like etc.venues, Club 75, and bespoke venues developed in partnership with other organizations.

The company combines hospitality and lifestyle experiences with commercial real estate, creating tailored spaces for corporate meetings and events. Convene offers premium venues for corporate gatherings, flexible coworking solutions, and virtual and hybrid event capabilities. It partners with leading real estate landlords to enhance building value and provide exceptional tenant experiences. Recognized as one of America’s 100 Most Promising Companies by Forbes, Convene caters to corporate clients and organizations seeking sophisticated venues that foster collaboration and impactful gatherings.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '23', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/840.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'convene', null), ('353', 'Super Payments', 'Super Payments Limited', 'https://www.superpayments.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/superpayments/', 'Super Payments is a UK-based fintech company founded in 2022 by Samir Desai CBE, known for co-founding Funding Circle. Headquartered in Bristol, the company aims to transform online payments by eliminating transaction fees for merchants and enhancing the shopping experience for consumers. Backed by notable investors like Accel and Union Square Ventures, Super Payments is focused on creating a payment network that benefits all users.

The company offers a fee-free payment processing platform that allows merchants to accept payments without incurring transaction fees. This model helps businesses save money and reinvest in growth. Super Payments supports various payment methods, including direct bank transfers, credit and debit cards, and digital wallets like Apple Pay and Google Pay. Customers using the platform receive automatic cash rewards, encouraging repeat purchases and fostering loyalty. Additionally, Super Payments utilizes AI technology to provide a fast and secure checkout experience and offers advertising solutions that connect shoppers with relevant offers during the payment process.', 'The company can offer sponsorship for "stellar" candidates.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/330.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/cytora.com', null), ('354', 'Easol', 'Easol Trading Limited', 'https://easol.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/easolhq/', 'Easol is an experience commerce platform founded in 2017 and based in London, England. It helps creators and businesses in the experience economy manage, market, and sell experiences directly from their own branded websites. The platform is designed to give users full control over their brand, customer relationships, and data, while avoiding marketplace commission fees.

Easol offers a range of services, including website building, a smart booking system, integrated payment processing, and marketing tools. Users can customize their websites, manage bookings with flexible options, and utilize automated communication and campaign management features. The platform also supports integration with external payment processors and marketing platforms, making it a comprehensive solution for experience creators such as travel companies, wellness retreats, event organizers, and adventure providers. 

Easol has experienced significant growth, raising approximately $29.6 million in funding and seeing a substantial increase in its customer base and transaction volume. The platform is recognized for its flexibility, stability, and responsive support team, helping businesses enhance their customer experience and marketing efficiency.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/403.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('355', '9fin', '9fin Limited', 'https://9fin.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/9fin/', '9fin is a London-based fintech company founded in 2016, specializing in AI-powered data and analytics for debt capital markets, including bonds, loans, and credit analysis. Its platform centralizes extensive market intelligence, combining various datasets with advanced analytics to support financial professionals in making informed decisions in dynamic environments.

The platform serves investment banks, asset managers, hedge funds, and law firms by providing real-time insights and predictive analytics. Key features include credit analysis tools, automated earnings call transcripts, covenant comparison, and distressed credit analysis. It also offers ESG data integration, AI-driven news aggregation, and powerful search functionality, enabling users to quickly access relevant information. With a proven track record of predicting market events, 9fin helps clients stay ahead in the competitive financial landscape. 

9fin''s client base includes nine of the top ten global investment banks and leading asset management firms, showcasing its significant presence in the industry. The company fosters a culture of responsibility and innovation, encouraging diverse perspectives and quick decision-making among its employees.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '23', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/125.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', '9fin', null), ('356', 'Freetrade', 'Freetrade Limited', 'https://freetrade.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/freetrade/', 'Freetrade is a UK-based fintech company founded in 2016 by Adam Dodds and Davide Fioranelli. It offers a mobile and web trading platform designed for retail investors in the UK, allowing users to trade equities and ETFs listed in the UK, US, and Europe without commission fees. The platform supports tax-efficient accounts like ISAs and SIPPs, and operates on a subscription-based revenue model, including a premium service called Freetrade Plus that provides additional investment options.

Freetrade enables commission-free trading of stocks, ETFs, mutual funds, and UK government bonds. It also offers fractional share trading for US securities and currency exchange services. The user-friendly platform includes features like automated orders and portfolio diversification tools. With over 1.6 million users and 720,000 active customers managing £2.5 billion in assets, Freetrade has been recognized as the Best Online Trading Platform at the British Bank Awards for six consecutive years. In January 2025, Freetrade was acquired by IG Group for £160 million.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '16', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/877.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/freetrade', null), ('358', 'Moshi', 'Mind Candy Ltd', 'https://www.moshikids.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/moshikids/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Moshi Kids is a digital app company dedicated to creating healthy, calming, and educational experiences for children aged 10 and under. Their flagship product, the Moshi app, features a diverse library of bedtime stories, educational games, soothing sounds, meditations, and music. This app is designed to help children relax, improve sleep, and support social-emotional learning.

The Moshi app includes over 400 audio stories and tracks, along with more than 50 interactive games that promote engagement and skill-building. It offers short audio clips called "Moments" to help children manage their emotions and provides relaxing sounds and meditations to encourage mindfulness. Moshi Kids prioritizes a safe environment for children, incorporating parental controls to manage playtime and settings.

With over 8 billion minutes listened, the app is utilized in both home and educational settings, with many teachers noting its positive impact on children''s focus. Moshi Kids combines entertainment, education, and wellbeing, making it a valuable resource for child development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/539.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('360', 'KatKin', 'Anikin Ltd', 'https://www.katkin.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/katkin/', 'KatKin is a UK-based fresh cat food company founded in 2019 by siblings Nikki and Brett O’Farrell. The company focuses on improving feline health through nutrition by offering fresh, personalized cat meals and snacks made from 100% human-grade meat. Their products are gently steam-cooked and frozen to maintain nutrients, with no fillers, grains, or preservatives. KatKin operates primarily as a direct-to-consumer subscription service, delivering tailored meal boxes to customers every 28 days.

The meals are vet-formulated to meet the dietary needs of cats, featuring high protein content and a variety of flavors such as beef, chicken, turkey, duck, pork, lamb, and fish. KatKin uses a proprietary algorithm to create personalized meal plans based on each cat''s unique traits, ensuring optimal nutrition. The company emphasizes a science-driven approach, supported by an in-house team of vets and nutritionists who continuously enhance recipes and nutritional solutions. KatKin has rapidly grown its customer base, delivering over 50 million meals to more than 200,000 cats and has raised over $22 million in funding to support its growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1276.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'personio', 'katkin', null), ('361', 'WeWork', 'WeWork International Limited', 'https://www.wework.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wework/', 'WeWork is a U.S.-based company founded in 2010 by Adam Neumann and Miguel McKelvey. It specializes in providing flexible coworking spaces and office solutions for entrepreneurs, startups, freelancers, and larger enterprises around the world. WeWork began as an eco-friendly coworking concept in Brooklyn and quickly expanded, opening its first location in SoHo, Manhattan, in 2011. Today, it operates over 800 locations across 40 U.S. cities and 32 countries.

WeWork offers a variety of workspace solutions, including All Access Membership for open workspaces, On Demand options for hourly or daily use, dedicated desks, private offices, and customizable office suites. The company transforms buildings into modern office spaces, catering to a diverse clientele that includes startups, freelancers, and major corporations like Facebook and Microsoft. WeWork also promotes a community-centric work environment, fostering collaboration through initiatives like WeWork Labs, a startup incubator.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1161.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'wework', null), ('363', 'PagerDuty', 'PagerDuty Limited', 'https://www.pagerduty.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pagerduty/', 'PagerDuty is a technology company founded in 2009 that specializes in real-time incident management and operations performance software offered as a SaaS platform. The company helps businesses gain visibility and actionable intelligence throughout the incident lifecycle, enabling quick and efficient responses to critical disruptions in IT environments. This focus ensures exceptional customer experiences.

The platform integrates with various monitoring, collaboration, and development tools, facilitating seamless workflows for IT and DevOps teams. PagerDuty''s core offerings include incident response management, real-time visibility through centralized dashboards, and automation powered by machine learning to enhance incident resolution. The company serves over 25,000 organizations globally, including a significant portion of the Fortune 100, and has established a strong presence with over 1,000 employees and multiple offices worldwide. With more than $370 million in annual revenue, PagerDuty continues to innovate in digital operations management.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/957.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'pagerduty', null), ('364', 'Blis', 'Blis Global Ltd', 'https://blis.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/blisglobal/', 'Blis is a global advertising technology company that specializes in geo-powered, omnichannel advertising solutions with a strong emphasis on privacy. Founded in 2004 in the UK by CEO Greg Isbister, Blis operates in over 40 markets across five continents, serving major brands and media agencies.

The company provides a comprehensive platform that allows advertisers to plan, buy, and measure campaigns focused on real-world outcomes. Key services include audience planning using geography-based data, smart cookieless technology for audience segment purchasing, and innovative measurement solutions that assess the entire audience. A notable product is Audience Explorer, launched in 2021, which supports omnichannel campaigns and audience insights without using cookies or personal identifiers. In 2025, Blis introduced Blis AI, an AI-powered tool that enhances media planning by quickly generating audience recommendations.

Blis is dedicated to delivering effective advertising campaigns that respect consumer privacy, ensuring that users do not have to trade their personal data for internet services.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1217.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('366', 'MullenLowe UK', 'MullenLowe Group Limited', 'https://www.mullenlowe.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mullenlowe-uk/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'MullenLowe UK is a full-service advertising and marketing communications agency based in London. It operates as part of the global MullenLowe Group, which is owned by the Interpublic Group (IPG). Established in its current form in 2015, MullenLowe UK has a rich heritage from the merger of several historic agencies, including Lowe & Partners and Lintas.

The agency offers a wide range of services, including creative strategy, digital marketing, public relations, social influence marketing, sustainability consulting, media planning, and user experience solutions through its digital arm, MullenLowe Profero. MullenLowe UK focuses on delivering integrated marketing campaigns and brand experiences tailored to client needs, emphasizing creativity and strategic innovation to help brands thrive in a dynamic marketplace. With a strong global presence and a diverse portfolio of clients, the agency is recognized for its award-winning campaigns and commitment to impactful brand growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/895.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'mullenlowe', null), ('367', 'Mistral AI', 'Mistral AI UK Limited', 'https://mistral.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mistralai/', 'Mistral AI is a French artificial intelligence startup founded in 2023 and based in Paris. The company specializes in developing open-source and commercial large language models (LLMs) that are efficient, customizable, and cost-effective. Founded by three AI researchers with backgrounds at Google DeepMind and Meta, Mistral AI aims to provide an accessible alternative to existing AI solutions by openly releasing its models and encouraging community contributions.

Mistral AI offers a range of products, including large language models, the Le Chat AI Assistant for text and image generation, and an optical character recognition API called Mistral OCR. The company also provides the Mistral Agents API for enterprise AI deployment and Mistral Code, a coding assistant designed to enhance software development. Its models and services cater to various industries, including finance, healthcare, customer support, education, software development, and content creation. Mistral AI is recognized for its open, portable, and customizable AI models, fostering a collaborative ecosystem in the AI space.', null, '3', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/397.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'lever', 'mistral', null), ('368', 'Safi', 'Safi Technologies Ltd', 'https://www.safi.co', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/safi-co/', 'Safi is a technology-driven company that operates a digital platform for trading recyclables. It connects buyers and sellers globally, offering a transparent and streamlined solution for the procurement and sales process in the recyclables market. The platform utilizes AI to enhance quality control and pricing accuracy, making it easier for users to manage their transactions.

Safi provides several key features, including AI-powered matching of buyers and sellers, which allows sellers to upload photos of their recyclable materials for optimal pricing. The platform also includes AI-enhanced quality checks to ensure material quality, giving buyers confidence in their purchases. Additionally, Safi digitizes the entire order management process, covering document signing, transport arrangements, and shipment tracking with real-time updates. The extensive network of users includes procurement and purchase managers in the recycling industry, who benefit from the platform''s transparency and efficiency.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/22.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/safi', null), ('370', 'Bromcom', 'Bromcom Computers Plc', 'https://bromcom.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/britton-and-time-solicitors/', 'Bromcom Computers plc is a British technology company founded in 1986 and based in Bromley, England. It specializes in cloud-based Management Information Systems (MIS) and finance software for the education sector, including schools, colleges, local authorities, and multi-academy trusts (MATs). The company launched the UK''s first cloud MIS platform in 2011, integrating school management and finance functions into a single, user-friendly system.

Bromcom''s offerings include a comprehensive cloud MIS for managing student data, attendance, assessments, and reporting, as well as integrated finance software tailored for educational institutions. The Parent Portal, MyChildAtSchool.com, allows parents to access their child''s academic information online. Bromcom also hosts BromCommunity, an online forum for over 8,000 users to share best practices and support. The company serves over 4,800 schools across England, Northern Ireland, and Wales, emphasizing innovation and cloud technology to improve student outcomes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/459.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('372', 'Due', 'Due Ltd', 'https://www.opendue.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/due-network/', 'Due is a web-based invoicing and billing software solution designed to assist businesses of all sizes in automating invoice generation and payment management. The platform simplifies the billing process with tools for creating, customizing, and sending professional invoices. It supports multi-currency and multi-language options, making it ideal for international operations.

The core services of Due include customizable invoice creation, email and PDF invoice delivery, invoice history management, and payment processing. Users can apply discounts, set up recurring billing, and track time and expenses integrated with invoicing. The platform also offers automated payment reminders, reporting features, and team permissions for collaborative billing processes. Overall, Due provides a comprehensive suite of features to enhance financial transaction management and improve cash flow for organizations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/531.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('373', 'Taxfix', 'Positron Technologies Ltd', 'https://taxfix.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/taxfix-uk/', 'Taxfix UK (formerly TaxScouts) is a digital tax and accounting platform that simplifies tax filing for individuals and small businesses. Founded in London in 2017, it combines innovative technology with a network of over 150 accredited accountants. TaxScouts offers expert tax advice and filing solutions primarily in the UK, Spain, and Estonia. In 2024, it became part of the Taxfix Group, enhancing its reach and capabilities in the European market.The platform provides three main services: expert-assisted tax return filing, one-off tax advice consultations, and ongoing access to a dedicated pay-as-you-go tax accountant. TaxScouts also supports tax return filing for Limited (LTD) companies, catering to a diverse range of customer needs. The service emphasizes a fully online process that is fast, efficient, and transparent, with fixed pricing that covers all support and changes. TaxScouts aims to make tax filing straightforward and less intimidating, serving individual taxpayers and small business owners who value convenience and accuracy.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/463.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'teamtailor', 'taxfix', null), ('374', 'ustwo', 'ustwo Limited', 'https://ustwo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ustwo-/', 'ustwo is a digital product studio founded in December 2004 by childhood friends Matt "Mills" Miller and John "Sinx" Sinclair in Shoreditch, London. The company is majority employee-owned and has grown to over 300 employees globally. ustwo is known for its collaborative and inclusive culture, which values diversity, creativity, and trust, creating an environment where individuals can thrive.

The studio specializes in digital product design and development, crafting user-centered mobile apps, websites, and digital experiences. They also offer brand and innovation consulting, helping clients build impactful digital products. A notable achievement is their critically acclaimed mobile game *Monument Valley*, which has won multiple awards and sold over 26 million copies. ustwo collaborates with a range of prestigious clients, including Google, Apple, and Jaguar Land Rover, delivering innovative digital experiences that align with their values. As a certified B Corporation, ustwo is committed to social and environmental responsibility, integrating these principles into their business practices.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1002.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'hibob', 'https://ustwo.careers.hibob.com/api/job-ad', null), ('375', 'University of Greenwich', 'University of Greenwich', 'https://www.gre.ac.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/school/university-of-greenwich/', 'The University of Greenwich offers a wide range of apprenticeship programs through its Employability & Apprenticeships department. These programs include Intermediate, Advanced, Higher, and Degree apprenticeships, catering to various educational levels from GCSE to Master''s degrees. The initiative combines practical experience with academic education, allowing learners to pursue their career goals while providing employers with opportunities to recruit and upskill their workforce.

Support services are available for both learners and employers. Learners receive initial assessments and induction sessions to prepare for their apprenticeships. Employers benefit from tailored programs that enhance their talent pipeline and assist them in navigating the apprenticeship application process. Upon completion, learners earn qualifications and certificates, including an award from the University of Greenwich and an apprenticeship certificate from the Education and Skills Funding Agency. The university operates across three campuses in London and Kent, offering programs in sectors such as Health, Construction, Engineering, and Science.', 'The university offers sponsorship alongside many of its academic and technical roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/527.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'university', null), ('376', 'Holly', 'Job Protocol Labs Ltd', 'https://www.hollyhires.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hollyhires/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/926.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('379', 'Samsara', 'Samsara Neworks Limited', 'https://www.samsara.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/samsara/', 'Samsara is a technology company founded in 2015 by Sanjit Biswas and John Bicket, who previously co-founded Meraki. The company specializes in digitizing and optimizing physical operations for industrial businesses by integrating hardware, software, and cloud computing.

Samsara offers a Connected Operations Platform that combines IoT sensors, AI-powered dash cameras, GPS tracking, and cloud-based software. This platform provides real-time visibility and analytics for fleet management, equipment monitoring, and worksite operations. Key products include AI dash cameras that enhance safety, vehicle gateways, and sensors that monitor various operational variables, along with software solutions for route optimization and predictive maintenance.

With over 19,000 core customers, including small businesses and large enterprises across various industries, Samsara generates revenue through subscription-based services and hardware sales. The company has a global presence with offices in multiple countries and went public in December 2021, achieving significant annual recurring revenue milestones.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '41', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/978.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('380', 'ai.io', 'Project 23rd Century Limited', 'https://www.ai.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ai-io/', 'AI.io is a data science and engineering company based in New York City, founded in 2016. The company specializes in advanced artificial intelligence solutions that aim to enhance business operations and improve everyday life. AI.io focuses on creating explainable and trustworthy AI, providing evidence-based insights, managing bias, and supporting better decision-making to drive revenue growth.

The company develops white box enterprise AI solutions that prioritize transparency and explainability. Their offerings include AI-powered applications for various sectors, such as media and entertainment, financial services, healthcare, and travel. AI.io''s core technology, the PLATO platform, supports machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, computer vision, and cognitive AI capabilities. By emphasizing collaboration between humans and machines, AI.io seeks to augment human intelligence and improve process efficiency across diverse industries.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1233.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'ai', null), ('382', 'Omnipresent', 'Omnipresent Group Limited', 'https://omnipresent.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/omnipresentgroup/', 'Omnipresent, founded in 2019 and headquartered in London, specializes in global employment solutions for distributed teams. The company simplifies cross-border hiring by managing compliance, payroll, and administrative tasks, allowing businesses to build international teams without the need for local entities. With a total funding of $137.9 million, including a $120 million Series B round, Omnipresent operates in over 160 countries and is recognized as a leader in global employment services.

The company offers a range of services, including Employer of Record (EOR) solutions, payroll and benefits administration, compliance and tax management, and contractor management. Their OmniPlatform is a SaaS tool designed for onboarding, managing, and paying global employees, seamlessly integrating with existing HR systems. Omnipresent targets growing companies looking to expand internationally while prioritizing speed, cost-effectiveness, and compliance in their hiring processes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/305.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'omnipresent', null), ('383', 'VICE', 'Vice UK Ltd', 'https://www.vice.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/vice-media/', 'VICE Media is a global media and entertainment company founded in 1994 in Montreal, Canada. Originally starting as a punk magazine called *Voice of Montreal*, it evolved into a multi-platform corporation producing content across digital, television, film, and print. VICE News, a key part of VICE Media, focuses on current affairs and investigative journalism, delivering daily content through various channels.

VICE News creates a wide range of digital content, including articles, videos, and documentaries, available on its website and social media. It also produces television programming for networks like HBO and VICELAND, as well as documentaries that delve into global issues. The company maintains a print presence with its magazine, which covers alternative culture, politics, and lifestyle topics. VICE Media is recognized for its impactful journalism, having received numerous awards, including Peabody and Emmy Awards.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1041.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('384', 'Incredible', 'Incredible Technologies Limited', 'https://www.getincredible.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/incredibletechnologies/', 'We''re a credit repayment solution. We''re building a platform that tracks and automates credit card repayments, helping people on their way to better financial health.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/794.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('386', 'Goodlord', 'Oh Goodlord Ltd', 'https://www.goodlord.co', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/goodlord/', 'Goodlord is a UK-based technology company that provides an end-to-end digital platform for the lettings industry. The platform simplifies the rental process for letting agents, landlords, and tenants by automating and integrating various steps involved in lettings, such as referencing, compliance, rent collection, and tenant services. Goodlord aims to enhance the renting experience and is trusted by over 3,500 agencies across the UK, processing more than one million tenancies annually.

The comprehensive software solution consolidates up to 100 different tenancy steps into a single platform. Key features include tenant referencing services, tenancy management, compliance automation, and various insurance products. Goodlord also offers utility switching services and training support for agents. The platform is designed to improve efficiency, reduce manual tasks, and increase revenue for letting agents while ensuring compliance and enhancing tenant satisfaction.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '10', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/116.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/goodlord', null), ('387', 'Charlotte Tilbury', 'Islestarr Holdings Limited', 'https://www.charlottetilbury.com/uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/charlotte-tilbury-beauty-ltd/', 'Charlotte Tilbury Beauty is a luxury cosmetics, skincare, and fragrance company founded in 2013 by renowned British makeup artist Charlotte Tilbury. Headquartered in London, the brand has quickly gained global recognition for its high-performance products designed to enhance confidence and beauty. The product range includes makeup, skincare, and fragrances, with signature items like the ''Filmstar Bronze and Glow'' palette.

The company emphasizes a strong brand experience through retail partnerships and online platforms, launching in prestigious department stores such as Selfridges and expanding to the United States with retailers like Bergdorf Goodman and Sephora. Charlotte Tilbury Beauty is committed to empowering women, demonstrated by its initiatives and partnerships supporting female empowerment. Acquired by Puig in 2020, the brand has experienced significant growth, with revenues exceeding £310 million by 2022.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/160.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'charlotte-tilbury', null), ('388', 'University of Reading', 'University of Reading', 'https://www.reading.ac.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/school/university-of-reading/', 'The University of Reading is a public research university located in Reading, Berkshire, England. Established in 1892, it has a rich heritage that dates back to the 1860s with the founding of the Schools of Art and Science. The university gained full status in 1926 and has since evolved into a comprehensive institution known for its strong emphasis on research and teaching.

The university offers a wide range of academic programs across various disciplines, including arts and humanities, science and technology, agriculture, business, education, architecture, and music. It provides undergraduate, postgraduate, and research degrees, supported by extensive facilities and specialized research institutes. The University of Reading is committed to equality and inclusion, with a history of pioneering figures in academia.

As a research-intensive institution, the university produces significant scholarly outputs in fields such as environmental science, agriculture, and health. It serves a diverse student body, including domestic and international students, and engages with local and global communities through outreach and partnerships.', 'The university offers sponsorship alongside many of its roles and offers detailed information on the routes that can be taken for each role in their job descriptions.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/768.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'universityofreading', null), ('389', 'Oodle Car Finance', 'Oodle Financial Services Limited', 'https://www.oodlecarfinance.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oodlecarfinance/', 'Oodle Car Finance is a UK-based car finance company that aims to simplify the car financing experience through technology and customer-focused services. Founded around 2010, the company has grown rapidly and now employs over 450 people across offices in Oxford, Cardiff, London, and Manchester. Oodle positions itself as a modern lender, utilizing advanced technology and innovative credit underwriting to enhance decision-making speed and customer experience.

Oodle offers a range of car finance solutions, including loans and finance deals that make the car buying process more transparent. Customers can apply for pre-approval to gauge their borrowing capacity without affecting their credit file. The company also connects customers with a network of trusted car dealers, ensuring a smooth purchasing experience. With a strong reputation reflected in over 16,000 Trustpilot reviews, Oodle has helped more than 250,000 customers secure car finance. The company fosters a collaborative workplace culture, emphasizing employee well-being and career development.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for a small number of technical roles.', '1', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/262.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'oodlefinance', null), ('391', 'Chainalysis', 'Chainalysis UK Limited', 'https://www.chainalysis.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/chainalysis/', 'Chainalysis is a blockchain analysis company based in New York City, founded in 2014. It specializes in compliance, investigation, and intelligence software that analyzes blockchain public ledgers to track virtual currency transactions and combat illicit activities like money laundering and fraud. The company serves a wide range of clients, including government agencies, financial institutions, cryptocurrency businesses, and consumer brands.

The Chainalysis platform offers a comprehensive suite of tools, including Chainalysis Investigations for law enforcement, Chainalysis Intelligence for mapping real-world entities to blockchain addresses, and Crypto Compliance Services to help digital asset firms meet anti-money laundering regulations. Additionally, it provides Web3 Growth Insights to support strategic growth for decentralized projects. With a focus on transparency and security, Chainalysis has mapped over 1 billion blockchain addresses and supports more than 1,000 organizations across 70 countries.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/39.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'chainalysis-careers', null), ('392', 'OpenX', 'OpenX Limited', 'https://www.openx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/openx/', 'OpenX is an independent programmatic advertising technology company founded in 2008, based in Pasadena, California, with additional offices in New York, Tokyo, London, and Kraków. The company specializes in supply-side platform (SSP) services, helping premium publishers efficiently monetize their digital inventory while providing advertisers with high-quality audience reach through data-driven targeting and identity solutions.

OpenX operates a cloud-based ad exchange platform on the Google Cloud Platform, enhancing performance and scalability. The platform supports real-time bidding and programmatic transactions, ensuring efficient monetization for publishers and effective audience targeting for advertisers. Key offerings include advanced data and identity targeting solutions, as well as enhanced publisher management tools following strategic acquisitions. OpenX is committed to creating a fair advertising ecosystem, focusing on transparency, data-driven decision-making, and compliance with privacy regulations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/411.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'lever', 'openx', null), ('393', 'Adyen', 'Adyen UK Limited', 'https://www.adyen.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/adyen/', 'Adyen is a global payment company based in Amsterdam, founded in 2006. With over 4,300 employees across 23 countries, it operates as an acquiring bank and payment service provider. Adyen''s platform simplifies the payment lifecycle by integrating various functions such as gateway, processing, risk management, issuing, and acquiring into a single solution. This allows businesses to accept payments through e-commerce, mobile, and point-of-sale (POS) channels.

The company offers a range of services, including payment processing in multiple currencies, POS solutions, and tools for fraud detection. Adyen also provides a service for issuing virtual and physical cards, as well as a product designed for marketplaces to manage payments and payouts. With a strong global presence and acquiring licenses in numerous countries, Adyen supports large enterprises and merchants in achieving their payment needs efficiently. The company is publicly listed on Euronext Amsterdam since June 2018 and processes over €1.2 trillion in payment volume, establishing itself as a key player in the payments industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '8', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/281.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'adyen', null), ('395', 'BuzzFeed', 'BuzzFeed UK Limited', 'https://www.buzzfeed.com/uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/buzzfeed/', 'BuzzFeed, Inc. is a digital media company founded in 2006 and based in New York City. Initially focused on creating viral content, it has grown into a major platform that offers a mix of entertainment, news, and social media content. BuzzFeed produces a variety of digital formats, including articles, listicles, quizzes, videos, and interactive media, covering topics like pop culture, lifestyle, and food.

The company operates the BuzzFeed Community, which allows users to create and share their own content. BuzzFeed also has a video production arm, BuzzFeed Motion Pictures, and has expanded internationally with editions in several countries. Its business model is centered on digital advertising, partnering with brands to create sponsored content and utilizing e-commerce and affiliate marketing to diversify revenue. BuzzFeed attracts a wide audience interested in engaging and shareable content, making it a valuable platform for advertisers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/834.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'buzzfeed', null), ('396', 'Live Nation', 'Live Nation (Music) Ltd', 'https://www.livenation.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/live-nation/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '9', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/453.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'LNExternalSite', null), ('397', 'Avant Arte', 'Avante Arte Ltd', 'https://avantarte.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/avantarte', 'Avant Arte is a contemporary art platform founded in 2014 by Christian Luiten and Curtis Penning. Initially starting as a visual blog and Instagram page, it has grown into a significant online presence in the art world, boasting over 2.5 million followers. The company specializes in creating and selling high-quality limited editions in collaboration with leading contemporary artists. Their offerings include silkscreen prints, sculpture editions, and other art forms, all produced with a focus on quality and presentation.

Avant Arte aims to make art collecting accessible and engaging for both new and seasoned collectors. The platform provides a thoughtfully designed online experience that combines digital engagement with physical art ownership. Additionally, Avant Arte supports artists by creating opportunities for them to earn a living and by promoting underrepresented voices in the art community. Through partnerships with museums and cultural institutions, the company has raised significant funds and connected a diverse audience with contemporary art, fostering a supportive community for both artists and patrons.', null, '4', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/465.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('399', 'THIS', 'Plant Meat Ltd', 'https://this.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/thisisntmeat/', 'THIS™ is a UK-based company that specializes in 100% plant-based food products. Their offerings include a variety of meat alternatives, such as chicken pieces and bacon rashers, designed to replicate the taste and texture of traditional meat. The products are high in protein and made entirely from plants, catering to consumers who seek nutritious and flavorful meal options.

The company emphasizes sustainability and aims to provide a low environmental impact compared to meat-based alternatives. THIS™ products are available in major supermarkets across the UK and Northern Ireland, making them accessible to a wide audience. The brand targets consumers interested in healthy, sustainable, and indulgent plant-based foods, promoting better taste, health, and environmental responsibility.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/197.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('400', 'Graphcore', 'Graphcore Limited', 'https://www.graphcore.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/graphcore/', 'Graphcore is a British semiconductor company founded in 2016, based in Bristol, UK. The company specializes in developing advanced hardware accelerators tailored for artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning workloads. Its core product, the Intelligence Processing Unit (IPU), is designed to optimize AI-specific operations, enabling efficient and scalable computation for complex machine learning models.

Graphcore offers a variety of products based on IPU technology, including IPU chips, complete AI computing systems like the M2000, and scalable AI compute clusters such as IPU-POD₁₂₈ and IPU-POD₂₅₆. These products are aimed at cloud hyperscalers, scientific computing labs, and enterprises with large AI teams, particularly in sectors like financial services and pharmaceuticals. The company also provides a software stack to support developers in building and deploying AI models on their hardware.

