Retool''s offerings include a low-code development environment for creating internal applications such as dashboards and operational tools. The platform supports enterprise-grade features, including permissions and integrations, to enhance complex workflows. Retool serves a diverse range of clients, including notable companies like Brex, DoorDash, Amazon, and Allbirds. With a team of around 300 employees, Retool has achieved significant growth, reaching over $90 million in annual recurring revenue by 2023 and a valuation exceeding $3 billion.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1272.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('572', 'Isomorphic Labs', 'Isomorphic Labs Ltd', 'https://www.isomorphiclabs.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/isomorphic-labs/', 'Isomorphic Labs is a biotechnology company based in London, founded in 2021 as a subsidiary of Alphabet Inc. The company focuses on using advanced artificial intelligence to enhance drug discovery and development. It originated from DeepMind and utilizes the Nobel-winning AlphaFold technology to accurately predict protein structures, which helps identify new drug target pathways.

The company has developed an AI-driven drug discovery platform that predicts protein folding and molecular interactions, enabling efficient in-silico screening of compound libraries. Isomorphic Labs also released AlphaFold 3, a highly accurate AI model for predicting biological molecule structures, available for non-commercial research. The company collaborates with major pharmaceutical firms like Novartis and Eli Lilly to apply its technology in drug research, aiming to accelerate the identification of potential treatments across various disease areas. With a strong focus on innovation, Isomorphic Labs is committed to transforming the drug design process through its AI capabilities.', 'The company can offer sponsorship for roles based in the UK. Relocation support is also available.', '4', '29', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/295.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'isomorphiclabs', null), ('573', 'Thermulon', 'Thermulon Ltd', 'https://www.thermulon.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/thermulon/', 'Thermulon is a deep-tech advanced materials company founded in 2019, specializing in the production of silica-based aerogel insulation materials. Their innovative manufacturing process addresses traditional challenges in aerogel production, resulting in a highly insulating material with lower embodied carbon and improved scalability. The core product, a silica-based aerogel, is composed of 95-98% air, providing exceptional thermal insulation while being fire-safe and lightweight.

The company targets industries such as electric vehicles, construction, aerospace, and chemical manufacturing, offering advanced aerogel materials that enhance energy efficiency and contribute to climate impact mitigation. Thermulon operates from a custom-built laboratory in London and has a registered office in Stockton-On-Tees, United Kingdom. They are preparing to scale production and enter the market by the end of 2026, with an early adopter program available for customers interested in accessing their aerogel materials ahead of the full commercial launch. Thermulon aims to support the global Net Zero journey by providing affordable, scalable, and safe insulation solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/814.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('574', 'Taskrabbit', 'Taskrabbit Limited', 'https://www.taskrabbit.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/taskrabbit/', 'TaskRabbit is an online marketplace and task management platform founded in 2008 by Leah Busque in Boston. It connects individuals needing assistance with everyday tasks to skilled freelance workers known as "Taskers." Originally named RunMyErrand, the service began as an SMS-based platform and has since evolved into a website and mobile app that allows users to post a variety of tasks.

The services offered by TaskRabbit include furniture assembly, moving help, cleaning, handyman work, delivery, and personal assistance. The platform operates in over 45 markets across the United States, United Kingdom, and Canada, making it easy for customers to find local Taskers for their errands and home-related chores. TaskRabbit has completed millions of tasks, including assembling furniture, cleaning homes, and helping with moves. The company is particularly appealing to busy individuals and households, as well as businesses seeking flexible freelance labor.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/995.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'taskrabbit', null), ('575', 'Juro', 'Juro Online Limited', 'https://juro.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/juro/', 'Juro is a London-based technology company that specializes in AI-powered contract management solutions. Its integrated, browser-based platform streamlines the entire contract lifecycle for legal and business teams, allowing them to create, review, negotiate, approve, sign, and store contracts within a single workflow. The platform incorporates artificial intelligence to automate tasks such as drafting, reviewing, and managing contracts, ensuring compliance and legal oversight.

Juro serves over 6,000 companies globally, facilitating more than 2 million contracts across 85+ countries. The platform features tools for end-to-end contract lifecycle management, real-time collaboration, customizable workflows, and deep integration with popular business applications like Slack and Salesforce. Juro is also SOC 2 Type 2 compliant, emphasizing its commitment to data security and governance. With significant funding and a diverse customer base, Juro is positioned as a leader in the contract lifecycle management space.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for certain roles. The specific policy for each role is made clear in the job description.', '1', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/508.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('576', 'Workato', 'Workato UK Ltd', 'https://www.workato.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/workato/', 'Workato is a multinational software company based in Mountain View, California, founded in 2013. It specializes in a cloud-based enterprise automation platform that integrates applications, data, and systems. The platform leverages artificial intelligence to orchestrate workflows and automate business processes, making it accessible for both business and IT teams through a low-code/no-code interface.

The Workato Enterprise Automation Platform features a drag-and-drop interface, prebuilt connectors known as "recipes," and real-time monitoring. It supports the automation of complex business processes, including Employee Lifecycle Management and Lead Management. With a focus on security, governance, and scalability, Workato enables organizations to maintain compliance while streamlining operations. The company serves a diverse customer base, from small businesses to large enterprises, and has been recognized as a leader in integration platform as a service (iPaaS) by industry analysts. Workato operates on a subscription-based model and has expanded its global presence with offices in Dublin and Singapore.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1164.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'workato', null), ('578', 'Innovid', 'Innovid EU Ltd', 'https://www.innovid.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/innovid', 'Innovid is an American advertising technology company based in New York City, specializing in the distribution, management, and measurement of digital and connected TV (CTV) ads. Founded in 2007, Innovid initially focused on interactive video advertising and has since expanded its offerings to include display advertising and digital out-of-home (DOOH) advertising. The company has made strategic acquisitions, such as Herolens, Taykey, and TVSquared, to enhance its technology and market presence.

Innovid provides a range of services, including interactive video ads that engage viewers, advanced CTV ad solutions with dynamic ad insertion, and comprehensive measurement and attribution services. The company is recognized for its innovation in video advertising, holding patents for interactive video content and being the first to receive MRC accreditation for CTV industry standards. With a diverse global customer base and partnerships with major industry players, Innovid is positioned as a competitive alternative in the ad tech space, emphasizing innovation and scalable growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/866.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'innovid', null), ('579', 'Rooser', 'Rooser Limited', 'https://www.rooser.eu/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rooser/', 'Rooser is a company that operates a cloud-based seafood trading platform, connecting buyers and sellers in the seafood industry across multiple countries. The platform allows users to list and discover seafood stock in real time, negotiate pricing, coordinate logistics, manage payments, and handle claims, streamlining the supply chain for perishable seafood products.

Founded by an entrepreneur with a fishing background, Rooser developed its software to enhance the efficiency of seafood trading. The company offers a digital marketplace called Sea.Store, where various seafood products, including haddock, cod, and salmon, are traded. The platform supports order management, logistics coordination, and payment processing, making transactions more efficient and transparent. Rooser primarily serves wholesale buyers, retailers, and fishing businesses, with a strong focus on the French market, which accounts for the majority of its sales.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1207.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('581', 'Fairvue', 'Fairvue Partners Ltd', 'https://www.fairvuepartners.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fairvue-partners/', 'Fairvue is a strategic management consultancy dedicated to investor relations and the capital markets. We design and execute intentional IR programmes that raise visibility and optimise market valuation through corporate strategies that are cognisant of investors'' views.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/779.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('582', 'KAYAK', 'Kayak Software (UK) Limited', 'https://www.kayak.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kayak/', 'KAYAK searches hundreds of other travel sites at once to find the information you need to make the right decisions on flights, hotels & car hires.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/364.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/kayak', null), ('583', 'Garrison', 'Garrison Technology Limited', 'https://www.garrison.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/garrisontechnology/', 'Garrison Technology Ltd, now part of Everfox, specializes in cybersecurity solutions that focus on hardware-enforced security (hardsec) and software to protect government, critical infrastructure, and commercial enterprises from advanced cyber threats. Founded in 2014, Garrison has developed technologies aimed at providing nation-state level security, particularly for sensitive government missions and regulated industries.

The company''s flagship product, the Garrison ULTRA browser isolation platform, defends against phishing, ransomware, and other web-based risks by isolating web content in secure hardware environments. This technology utilizes field-programmable gate array (FPGA) hardware to combine physical security with software flexibility, delivering robust cybersecurity. Garrison''s solutions also include Trust Qualified Browsing (TQB) for secure remote web browsing, cross-domain solutions, and threat protection services, all integrated into Everfox’s broader cybersecurity offerings. Their technology is trusted by national governments and organizations that require high levels of security assurance against sophisticated cyber threats.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/65.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('584', 'Carl Friedrik', 'OPPERMANN LONDON LTD', 'https://www.carlfriedrik.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carl-friedrik/', 'Carl Friedrik is a Scandinavian luxury leather and travel goods company founded in London in 2012 by Swedish brothers Niklas and Mattis Oppermann. Named after their late grandfather, the brand aims to provide high-quality, minimalist leather accessories and travel products. Carl Friedrik combines Bauhaus and Scandinavian design principles with traditional craftsmanship to create functional and timeless items that emphasize durability and style.

The product range includes leather goods like laptop sleeves and bags made from premium vachetta leather, as well as elegant luggage crafted from durable materials such as aluminum and Makrolon polycarbonate. Notable products include the 72-hour Backpack, designed for hands-free travel with practical features. The company focuses on sustainability by producing long-lasting items and offers a lifetime guarantee along with a 100-day trial period. Carl Friedrik operates on a direct-to-consumer model and has seen significant growth, particularly with its luggage collection launched in 2019. The brand connects with modern professionals and travelers who appreciate intelligent design and quality craftsmanship.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/458.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'recruitee', 'carlfriedrik', null), ('585', 'Magpie', 'Magpie Creative Communications Limited', 'https://www.wearemagpie.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/magpie-comms/', 'Magpie is a creative behaviour change agency based in Leeds, dedicated to inspiring positive social impact through campaigns and communications. They focus on sectors such as health, education, arts, climate change, poverty reduction, equality, and wellbeing. Magpie collaborates with changemakers—organizations and individuals committed to creating positive change—using creativity, collaboration, and behavioural science to transform lives.

The agency offers a range of services that include developing empathetic campaigns, applying behavioural science insights, and engaging communities in co-production. Their team, led by Dr. Julie Van De Vyver, consists of behavioural science experts and experienced creatives who work together to design effective behaviour change strategies. Magpie also provides branding, social marketing, insight and marketing research, web design, and graphic design services to support their initiatives.

Magpie''s culture emphasizes trust, support, and diversity, fostering a collaborative environment for talented individuals with a social conscience. They position themselves as partners for those addressing societal challenges, aiming to create meaningful and sustainable solutions through their comprehensive approach.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1040.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('586', 'Judge.me', 'Judge.me Ltd', 'https://judge.me/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/judgeme/', 'Judge.me is a UK-based technology company that specializes in customer review solutions for e-commerce businesses. Trusted by approximately 450,000 to 500,000 online stores globally, it is a leading app on platforms like Shopify. Judge.me offers tools designed to help merchants increase sales, build customer loyalty, and enhance their online reputation through authentic user-generated content.

The company provides a comprehensive reviews platform with two pricing plans: a Forever Free plan and an Awesome plan at $15 per month, which unlocks premium features. Its product suite includes customizable reviews widgets, trust badges, user-generated content displays, and interactive review prompts. Judge.me integrates seamlessly with major e-commerce platforms such as Shopify, WooCommerce, and BigCommerce, and supports various marketing and customer service tools. The company serves a wide range of industries, helping businesses from small startups to established brands improve customer trust and engagement through effective review management.', 'Sponsorship can be offered to the "right fits".', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/797.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'judgeme', null), ('588', 'Moneyhub', 'Moneyclub Financial Technology Ltd', 'https://www.moneyhub.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/moneyhub-enterprise/', 'Moneyhub is a global financial technology company based in Bristol, UK, specializing in Open Banking, Open Finance, and Open Data solutions. The company offers an ISO 27001 certified software platform that enables businesses to aggregate financial data, generate insights, send notifications, and initiate payments within a regulated framework. 

Moneyhub''s services include an Open Data Platform that connects to thousands of financial institutions across 37 countries, data aggregation and analytics for actionable insights, secure payment initiation, and customizable white-label solutions. The company also provides personalized financial dashboards, exemplified by its partnership with Standard Life to create a comprehensive pensions dashboard. 

With a mission to enhance financial wellness for individuals and businesses, Moneyhub serves a diverse range of clients in finance, telecoms, and retail. The company values flexibility, diversity, and inclusion within its workforce, and has raised approximately $90.5 million to support its growth and innovation in the fintech sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1138.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'moneyhub', null), ('589', 'Perkbox', 'Perkbox Ltd', 'https://www.perkbox.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/perkbox/', 'Perkbox is a global employee engagement platform founded in 2015 by Saurav Chopra and Chieu Cao. It evolved from their earlier venture, Huddlebuy, which focused on group discounts for small businesses. Perkbox addresses the need for meaningful employee benefits by offering a self-serve platform that helps businesses attract, engage, and retain talent through improved employee happiness and company culture.

The platform provides a rewards and benefits system that allows organizations to connect with and celebrate their employees, regardless of location. Its services include personalized rewards, recognition programs, wellbeing support, and accessible benefits through a global mobile app. Perkbox supports diverse workforces with features like employee insights and medical benefits, empowering employees with choices in how they receive recognition and rewards. Trusted by over 4,000 businesses worldwide, Perkbox serves more than 500,000 employees and has a presence in international markets, including Australia.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/157.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'Perk', null), ('592', 'Entrepreneurs First (EF)', 'Entrepreneur First Operations Limited', 'https://joinef.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/entrepreneur-first/', 'Entrepreneurs First (EF) is a global talent investor founded in 2011 by Matt Clifford and Alice Bentinck, with offices in London, Paris, Bangalore, New York, and San Francisco. EF specializes in supporting exceptional individuals to become technology company founders through a unique approach known as talent investing. This method focuses on identifying and backing individuals with high potential, often before they have a cofounder or a concrete startup idea.

EF offers several programs, including the Founder in Residence Program, which provides an intensive entrepreneurial experience. Participants receive mentorship, access to a global network of advisors and venture capitalists, and initial funding support for their ventures. EF has helped create over 600 companies with a combined valuation exceeding $13 billion, spanning various sectors such as robotics, healthcare, AI, and manufacturing. The company aims to empower talented individuals, particularly those outside Silicon Valley, to pursue their entrepreneurial ambitions and make a global impact.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/553.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('594', 'Miro', 'Miro EMEA UK Ltd', 'https://miro.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mirohq/', 'Miro is a collaborative online platform and innovation workspace that supports distributed teams in planning, brainstorming, product development, and execution. Founded in 2011, Miro has evolved from a visual whiteboarding tool into a comprehensive workspace used by over 90 million users and more than 250,000 organizations globally, including notable companies like Nike, IKEA, and Deloitte.

The core product is a digital whiteboarding application that allows users to create interactive boards for various purposes, such as workshops, strategy mapping, and agile ceremonies. Miro offers features like real-time collaboration, over 300 customizable templates, and advanced diagramming tools. It supports the entire innovation lifecycle, helping teams develop strategies, design products, and manage processes collaboratively. Miro''s mission is to empower teams to dream, design, and build the future together, enhancing creativity and productivity across diverse industries.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/540.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'miro', null), ('595', 'Evident', 'Evident Insights Limited', 'https://evidentinsights.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/evidentinsights/', 'Evident is a London-based intelligence platform focused on benchmarking and tracking artificial intelligence (AI) adoption in the financial services sector, particularly among banks. Founded in June 2022, the company operates under Evident Insights Ltd and aims to provide data-driven insights that help financial institutions assess and enhance their AI maturity and competitiveness.

The core offering of Evident is the Evident AI Index, an annual benchmark that evaluates around 50 of the world''s largest banks on various aspects of AI adoption, including talent, innovation, leadership, and responsible practices. This index serves as a global standard for measuring AI maturity in banking. In addition to the index, Evident offers AI maturity assessments, insights reports on AI trends, symposiums and webinars for industry leaders, and a Monthly Dispatch for ongoing updates on AI activity in the sector. The platform primarily serves financial institutions, investors, and advisors interested in AI capabilities within the financial services industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9e8c3ab5-b938-4b5b-b300-e239333dd95d.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'evident', null), ('596', 'Outra', 'Outra Limited', 'https://www.outra.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/outra/', 'Outra is a UK-based company that specializes in advanced household data solutions. Founded as the data engine behind Hometrack, it was acquired by Zoopla in 2017 and has since launched its own platform. Outra leverages data science, machine learning, and artificial intelligence to predict consumer behaviors and trends.

The company offers a suite of data-centric tools that enhance customer insights and improve marketing effectiveness across various industries, including insurance, retail, finance, real estate, and home improvement. Their platform integrates over 60 data sources and analyzes more than 75 billion data points. Key capabilities include predicting when households are likely to move, tracking contract end dates, and identifying customers considering switching services. This allows businesses to target high-intent customers during critical decision-making moments, optimizing marketing spend and capturing leads effectively.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1152.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('597', 'Zinc', 'Zinc Work Ltd', 'https://zincwork.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zincwork/', 'Zinc is a technology company based in London, UK, that specializes in automated pre-screening and background checking software for HR and recruiting teams. Founded in 2017, Zinc aims to improve the efficiency and transparency of talent recruitment processes. The platform allows organizations to conduct background checks with a single click, supporting hiring processes worldwide.

Zinc offers a range of services, including comprehensive background screening, criminal record checks in over 190 countries, and employment history verification. The platform also provides specialized checks such as DBS checks, financial services register verification, and social media presence checks across major platforms. Additionally, it features self-certification checks that help recruiters gather detailed candidate information for compliance purposes.

Zinc primarily serves HR and recruitment teams across various industries, with a strong emphasis on financial services. The company offers tiered pricing plans and a free trial, making its services accessible to organizations of different sizes. With a dedicated team of around 41-50 employees, Zinc generates approximately $10.5 million in revenue.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/120.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'zinc', null), ('600', 'PhysicsX', 'PhysicsX Limited', 'https://www.physicsx.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/physicsx/', 'PhysicsX is a deep-tech company based in London, founded in 2019. It specializes in developing advanced machine learning and AI applications to enhance physics simulations for engineering and design. The company integrates AI-driven multiphysics inference with numerical simulation, which accelerates innovation throughout the product lifecycle. This enables rapid development and deployment of AI tools that optimize design, manufacturing, and operations in complex industrial environments.

The PhysicsX platform supports the full AI lifecycle, including simulation, data management, model training, and deployment as customizable applications. This empowers enterprises to create optimized products with reduced risk and faster development times. PhysicsX serves a variety of advanced industries, including Space, Aerospace, Medical Devices, Additive Manufacturing, Electric Vehicles, Motorsport, and Renewables. Their solutions contribute to improved product designs, reduced emissions, enhanced performance, and increased efficiency in various sectors. The company collaborates with major partners to innovate in aerodynamics simulation and vertical farming projects, drawing talent from diverse backgrounds to drive real-world impact.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '23', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/373.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'physicsx', null), ('601', 'STITCH Editing', 'Stitch Editing Limited', 'https://stitchediting.tv/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/stitch-editing/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'STITCH Editing is a private limited company founded in 2010, with offices in London and Los Angeles. It specializes in motion picture production, offering professional editing services for commercials, music promos, and short films. The company is known for its collaborative and creative environment, emphasizing high-quality craft and service.

In addition to editing, STITCH Editing launched Homespun, a platform dedicated to developing new talent and showcasing creative projects. The company has built a reputation for producing award-winning advertisements and music videos, supported by its high-spec facilities and the expertise of its founding partners, who are accomplished film editors. STITCH Editing actively shares its work and creative culture on social media and video platforms like Instagram and Vimeo.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/989.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'stitch', null), ('602', 'Amp X', 'Amp X Limited', 'https://ampx.energy/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/amp-x', 'Amp X is a digital energy platform company based in London, England, founded in 2019. It focuses on innovative grid software services that support the energy transition, particularly at the grid edge. The company''s platform fosters a decentralized and flexible smart energy ecosystem powered by clean energy, aiming to shape the future of the grid.

Amp X offers a range of interoperable solutions through its proprietary Asset Management Platform. One notable product is the Consumer Energy Management System, Alice, which helps households manage energy costs and reduce CO2 emissions. The platform also enhances grid flexibility by unlocking energy resources at the grid edge. Amp X engages in partnerships, such as with Plico to deploy a Virtual Power Plant in Western Australia and with Smartcar for smart charging management solutions for electric vehicle owners.

As part of Amp Energy, which has a strong background in renewable energy development, Amp X is positioned to grow its grid-edge technology business. The platform utilizes AI to optimize battery dispatch and provide essential grid services, contributing to grid stability and the integration of renewable energy sources.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1097.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'teamtailor', 'ampx', null), ('603', 'Intent HQ', 'Intent HQ Limited', 'https://intenthq.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/intenthq/', 'Intent HQ is a global AI and customer data analytics company based in London. It specializes in privacy-first marketing solutions that transform first-party customer and transactional data into actionable insights. The company’s patented Customer AI platform manages over 200 million customer profiles and processes billions of data points daily, enabling enterprises to predict customer behavior and create personalized interactions.

The core offerings include the Customer AI Platform, which helps businesses build detailed customer profiles for targeted marketing, and the Customer Intelligence Platform (CIP), designed for the telecommunications sector to convert user actions into actionable data. Intent HQ also features the xChange Marketplace for data insights and the Intent Edge mobile engagement solution, which provides predictive features while maintaining high privacy standards.

