Elekta''s core offerings include precision radiation therapy and radiosurgery solutions. Its flagship product, the Gamma Knife, uses focused gamma radiation for noninvasive treatment of brain tumors. The company also provides linear accelerators for radiotherapy, advanced multi-leaf collimators, and brachytherapy solutions. Elekta collaborates with healthcare providers worldwide to enhance patient outcomes through its innovative technologies.

With a strong presence in key markets such as the United States, Japan, China, and Europe, Elekta employs over 4,500 people globally. Its technologies are utilized by hospitals and cancer treatment centers, aiming to improve survival rates and quality of life for patients with cancer and brain disorders.', 'The company can offer sponsorship and relocation services to candidates from the EU who are willing to relocate to Crawley, UK.', '1', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/439.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'elekta/Elekta_Careers', null), ('645', 'Outsized Ventures', 'Outsized Ventures Limited', 'https://www.outsized.vc/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/outsizedventures/', 'Outsized Ventures is an early-stage venture capital firm based in London, established in 2018. The firm specializes in investing in high-growth technology and science startups, particularly those with disruptive potential in emerging markets and Europe. Outsized Ventures focuses on backing founders who are innovating to address significant challenges.

