In addition to its platform, GEEIQ offers tailored services for Premium and Enterprise subscribers, focusing on expert-led reporting and long-term strategy curation. This approach emphasizes measurable results in virtual spaces, helping brands effectively reach younger audiences who are more engaged in virtual environments than traditional social media. With a customer base of over 1,000 brands and around 40 employees, GEEIQ has secured $8.2 million in funding to support its growth in the evolving landscape of virtual marketing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/560.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'pinpoint', 'geeiq', null), ('741', 'Spotify', 'Spotify Limited', 'https://spotify.com/uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/spotify/', 'Spotify is a Swedish audio streaming company founded in 2006 by Daniel Ek and Martin Lorentzon. It launched to the public in 2008 and has grown to become the world''s most popular audio streaming service, boasting over 696 million users and 276 million subscribers across more than 180 markets as of 2024.

Spotify offers a wide range of audio content, including access to over 100 million music tracks, nearly 7 million podcasts, and around 350,000 audiobooks. The platform uses advanced algorithms to personalize music recommendations and playlists, enhancing user engagement. It also features synchronized lyrics, music reviews, and social messaging, along with family plans and partnerships with companies like Uber and PlayStation. Spotify''s mission is to support artists by providing them with a platform to earn a living from their work while allowing fans to discover and enjoy diverse audio content.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '39', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/542.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'lever', 'spotify', null), ('743', 'Shopify', 'Shopify UK Limited', 'https://www.shopify.com/uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/shopify/', 'Shopify is a prominent global e-commerce platform founded in 2006 in Ottawa, Canada, by Tobias Lütke, Daniel Weinand, and Scott Lake. The company was born from the founders'' experience with an online snowboarding equipment store, leading to the development of a unified platform that simplifies online store creation, payment processing, order management, and customer data handling.

Shopify provides a comprehensive suite of services that enables businesses to easily create and manage online stores. Its core offering is a cloud-based platform that allows merchants to build customizable storefronts without needing extensive technical skills. Key features include website templates, payment processing, inventory management, order tracking, and customer relationship management. The platform also supports third-party developers through an API and an App Store, enhancing its functionality.

Shopify caters to a diverse range of merchants, from individual entrepreneurs to large enterprises, and is known for its ease of use, flexibility, and scalability. The company is publicly traded on the New York Stock Exchange and Toronto Stock Exchange, with Tobias Lütke serving as CEO.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/791.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'shopify', null), ('744', 'Heroes', 'Heroes Technology Ltd', 'https://makeheroes.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/makeheroes/', 'Heroes is a multi-brand developer dedicated to supporting families from pregnancy through early childhood with award-winning products. The company focuses on improving the lives of families globally through operational excellence and a strong customer-centric approach. 

With expertise in Amazon, direct-to-consumer, and retail channels, Heroes effectively engages customers at every touchpoint. The company also has robust capabilities in international expansion, making its products available in stores and marketplaces worldwide. Heroes operates from locations in White Bear Lake, Minnesota, and Kowloon, Hong Kong, emphasizing quality and customer experience across various sales platforms.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/865.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('745', 'Residently', 'Residently Services (UK) Limited', 'https://residently.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/residently/', 'Residently is a London-based proptech company founded in 2017, with an additional office in New York. The company focuses on digitizing and simplifying the rental process for tenants, landlords, and agents through a centralized digital platform. This platform streamlines property viewings, lease management, payments, and communication.

Residently offers a mobile app that allows renters to search for properties, arrange viewings, submit references, pay deposits, and manage leases. It also provides add-on services such as broadband setup, furniture rental, cleaning, and contents insurance, all bookable through the platform. For landlords and property managers, Residently supplies tools to manage viewings, paperwork, maintenance requests, and tenant communications, enhancing efficiency and reducing costs.

