Dext provides a comprehensive platform that automates bookkeeping workflows and integrates with major accounting software. Its key product, Dext Prepare, automates the collection and processing of receipts, invoices, and bank statements. The platform supports over 700,000 businesses and 12,000 accounting firms worldwide, ensuring real-time data processing and secure data storage. Dext also offers tools for expense and invoice management, enabling efficient tracking and organization of costs, particularly for professional services firms. With a focus on innovation and user empowerment, Dext enhances productivity and financial insight through seamless integration and advanced automation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/94.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workable', 'dext', null), ('759', 'Accsys', 'Titan Wood Limited', 'https://www.accsysplc.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/accsys-technologies/', 'Accsys Technologies PLC is a London-based company that specializes in developing and producing high-performance wood products through innovative chemical modification technologies. Founded in 2005, the company uses a proprietary low-emission acetylation process to enhance the durability, stability, and sustainability of wood materials.

The main products include Accoya® wood, an acetylated softwood, and Tricoya® wood, an acetylated wood fiber used in wood-based panels. These products are designed to be resistant to rot, insects, and moisture, making them ideal for applications in construction, outdoor decking, cladding, and furniture. Accsys positions its offerings as environmentally friendly alternatives to traditional hardwoods and chemically treated timber, supporting sustainable forestry practices.

Accsys serves a global market, with significant sales in the UK, Ireland, Europe, the Americas, and the Asia-Pacific region. The company is led by CEO Jelena van Os, who has been in the role since June 2023.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/998.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('760', 'LivePerson', 'LivePerson (UK) Ltd', 'https://www.liveperson.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/liveperson/', 'LivePerson is an enterprise software company that specializes in conversational AI and digital customer engagement solutions. Founded in 1995 by Robert LoCascio, who continues to serve as CEO, the company has been a pioneer in online communication, introducing innovations such as web chat and asynchronous messaging. LivePerson''s mission is to enhance conversations between businesses and consumers, enabling brands to create seamless, personalized experiences across various digital and voice channels.

The company''s flagship product, the Conversational Cloud, integrates AI chatbots, messaging channels, and voice AI to facilitate natural conversations at scale. LivePerson also utilizes generative AI and large language models to automate customer interactions and provide real-time assistance. With over 18,000 brands as clients across industries like telecommunications, financial services, and retail, LivePerson supports more than one billion conversational interactions each month. The company is recognized for its innovative approach and commitment to responsible AI development, earning accolades such as the #1 Most Innovative AI Company in the World by Fast Company in 2022.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/880.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'liveperson', null), ('761', 'Teamtailor', 'Teamtailor Ltd', 'https://www.teamtailor.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/teamtailor/', 'No specific information found.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/175.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('762', 'Legl', 'The Justice Platform Ltd', 'https://legl.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/legl-uk/', 'Legl is a UK-based digital legal advisory and technology company that aims to make legal services more accessible and user-friendly for growing businesses and law firms. Founded to address the inefficiencies of traditional legal processes, Legl combines legal expertise with innovative technology, including AI and open banking, to enhance compliance, onboarding, payments, and client workflows.

The company offers a cloud-based SaaS platform featuring various tools such as payment plans for installment payments, secure direct account-to-account payments through open banking, customizable digital forms for onboarding and compliance, and instant access to international company reports. These solutions are designed to automate legal and financial processes, improve client experiences, and reduce risks for law firms and their clients.

Legl primarily serves law firms looking to modernize their operations and growing businesses in need of proactive legal advisory services. With a strong commitment to legal innovation, Legl continues to expand its market presence, supported by significant funding and a vision to enhance access to justice.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/193.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'legl', null), ('765', 'Goodnotes', 'Goodnotes Limited', 'https://www.goodnotes.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/goodnotes', 'GoodNotes is a digital note-taking company founded in 2011 by Steven Chan, with headquarters in Hong Kong and an office in London. The company develops the GoodNotes app, a digital paper platform designed for iPad and Apple Pencil users, and also available on iPhone and Mac. The app allows users to take handwritten notes, search handwritten text, and organize notes into a digital library, enhancing the traditional note-taking experience.

The GoodNotes app features advanced AI technologies, including handwriting recognition and an in-app assistant called "Ask GoodNotes." It also includes a digital stationery marketplace for customizable templates and educational modules tailored for subjects like mathematics. With over 24 million monthly active users, GoodNotes serves a diverse customer base, including students, educators, professionals, and creatives, and is recognized as a top-grossing productivity app in various markets. The company has grown to over 100 employees, focusing on innovation and user experience.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles. They also offer relocation support.', '1', '8', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1266.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'goodnotes', null), ('766', 'The Social Innovation Partnership (TSIP)', 'The Social Innovation Partnership Limited', 'https://www.tsip.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-social-innovation-partnership/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'The Social Innovation Partnership (TSIP) is a B Corporation certified social enterprise based in the United Kingdom. Founded in 2010, TSIP focuses on driving social change by empowering individuals and organizations to create positive impacts in their communities. The company combines consultancy services with community-led innovation initiatives to enhance social impact and promote fairer societies.

