With a commitment to clear communication and strong client relationships, Digital Marmalade has built a loyal client base, with 90% of their business coming from existing clients and referrals. The company is registered as Digital Marmalade Limited and operates with a small team of fewer than 50 employees.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1133.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('797', 'Dyson', 'Dyson Limited', 'https://dyson.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/dyson/', 'Dyson is a British technology company founded in 1991 by inventor James Dyson in Malmesbury, England. The company specializes in designing and manufacturing innovative household appliances, with a strong focus on vacuum cleaners. Dyson is known for its bagless vacuum technology that uses cyclonic separation to maintain suction power. The first model, the DC01, became the UK’s best-selling vacuum cleaner and set a new standard in the market.

In addition to vacuum cleaners, Dyson offers a range of products including air purifiers, hand dryers, hair dryers, humidifiers, and robotic cleaners. Notable products include the Airblade hand dryer, Air Multiplier bladeless fans, and the Supersonic hair dryer, which has gained popularity for its unique design. Dyson operates in over 100 countries, targeting consumers who appreciate high-performance and technologically advanced home appliances. The company invests significantly in research and development to enhance its technologies and expand its product offerings.', 'The company is able to offer sponsorship.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/446.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'dyson', null), ('800', 'Forage', 'Forage UK Operations Limited', 'https://www.theforage.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/theforage/', 'Forage is a global e-learning and career preparation company that provides free virtual job simulations designed by top employers. Founded in 2017 and headquartered in San Francisco, with additional offices in New York, London, and Sydney, Forage aims to bridge the gap between education and employment. The company is recognized as a Great Place to Work, reflecting high employee satisfaction.

Forage offers over 300 interactive, self-paced online projects that simulate real job tasks and environments. These simulations, created in partnership with leading companies like BCG, JP Morgan, and PwC, typically take 2-5 hours to complete. The platform helps students and early career professionals develop essential skills, significantly increasing their chances of securing employment. Additionally, Forage provides educators with free access to its library of job simulations, allowing them to enhance their curricula with project-based learning. The company collaborates with employers to improve recruitment outcomes by preskilling candidates, contributing to better hiring efficiency and employee retention.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1274.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'ryan/RyanCareers', null), ('801', 'Kao', 'Kao (UK) Limited', 'https://www.kao.com/emea/en/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kao-usa-inc-/', 'Kao Corporation is a global Japanese company founded in 1887, originally as a soap manufacturer. Over the years, it has grown into a leading multinational enterprise specializing in consumer products, chemicals, and personal care. The company operates in 26 countries and is publicly listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, reporting consolidated sales revenue of approximately ¥1.5 trillion.

Kao offers a diverse range of products, including beauty and personal care items like skincare, haircare, and cosmetics under well-known brands such as Bioré, Sofina, and John Frieda. It also produces household cleaning products, including detergents and disposable baby diapers like Merries. Additionally, Kao manufactures specialty chemicals and invests significantly in research and development to drive innovation in its product lines. The company targets a broad consumer base, catering to various demographics with its extensive portfolio.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/874.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'kao', null), ('802', 'Conduktor', 'Conduktor UK Limited', 'https://www.conduktor.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/conduktor/', 'Conduktor is a technology company focused on enterprise data management and operational data streaming, particularly utilizing Apache Kafka. Founded in 2019, with offices in New York, London, and Paris, Conduktor aims to simplify and optimize the management of real-time operational data for businesses globally.

The company offers a platform and tooling suite designed to manage Kafka infrastructure and operational data flows. Key features include a unified data platform that consolidates data silos, centralized governance for security and compliance, and tools for optimizing data flows. Conduktor also provides real-time data streaming capabilities, enabling businesses to leverage data for AI initiatives and critical operational processes.

Conduktor serves data-driven enterprises that rely on real-time data for decision-making. The company emphasizes collaboration, ownership, and innovation within its culture, aiming to empower teams to operate confidently in data-driven environments.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/422.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'lever', 'conduktor', null), ('803', 'KETS', 'KETS Quantum Security Ltd', 'https://kets-quantum.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kets-quantum/', 'KETS Quantum Security is a UK-based technology company that specializes in chip-scale quantum-safe security solutions. Founded in 2016, the company emerged from extensive research at the University of Bristol. KETS focuses on protecting critical infrastructure, telecommunications networks, industrial control systems, sensors, and connected vehicles using the unique properties of quantum mechanics and integrated photonics.

The company''s primary offering is a quantum key distribution (QKD) system implemented on compact silicon photonic chips. This technology enables secure encryption that is resistant to both classical and quantum cyber attacks, while maintaining ultra-low size, weight, and power consumption. KETS has developed a scalable QKD prototype in collaboration with BT, which is currently being tested for deployment in telecom networks. Their products also include chip-based quantum key distribution modules and miniaturized quantum transmitters for applications like drones and unmanned aerial vehicles.

KETS collaborates with major industry players and has received multiple awards for its innovative contributions to cybersecurity. The company is dedicated to securing high-value data and systems against emerging quantum threats across various sectors, including telecommunications, government, defense, and finance.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/532.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'cmcmarkets/CMC_Markets_Careers', null), ('805', 'OpenGamma', 'OpenGamma Limited', 'https://opengamma.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/opengamma/', 'OpenGamma is a fintech company founded in 2009, focused on creating an open platform for analytics and risk management in the financial services sector. With headquarters in London and New York, the company specializes in derivatives trading and treasury management. OpenGamma is recognized for its innovative approach to margin analytics and collateral management, aiming to modernize treasury operations in response to regulatory complexities and market volatility.

The company offers a derivatives margin analytics platform that automates collateral management processes, optimizes margin requirements, and enhances operational efficiencies. This platform integrates analytics throughout the treasury lifecycle, enabling clients to manage cash and collateral more effectively while lowering financial and operational risks. OpenGamma serves a sophisticated client base, including global investment banks, asset managers, and hedge funds, managing over $130 billion in initial margin for more than 60 leading clients worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/541.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'opengamma', null), ('806', 'Muddy Machines', 'Muddy Machines Ltd', 'https://www.muddymachines.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/muddymachines/', 'Muddy Machines is a UK-based agriculture technology robotics company founded in 2020 by Florian Richter and Christopher Chavasse. The company aims to address labor shortages in agriculture through robotic automation. Led by an experienced team, including a former Dyson robotics engineer, Muddy Machines focuses on creating lightweight, electrically powered, modular robots that can adapt to various crops without harming the soil.

Their flagship product, Sprout, is a robotic harvester designed for green asparagus, capable of autonomously navigating fields and harvesting for up to 16 hours a day. Additionally, they have developed a modular robotic drivetrain that can be retooled for different crops and a logistics robot named Squirrel, which transports harvested crops from workers to storage areas. Muddy Machines primarily serves growers in the UK horticulture sector, working closely with large producers to refine their solutions. The company has received multiple awards and secured over £2.5 million in funding to support its innovative efforts in sustainable farming.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1292.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'icims', 'hines', null), ('808', 'Context', 'Get Context Analytics Ltd', 'https://context.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/get-context-ai/', 'Context.ai is a product analytics company that focuses on evaluation and analytics services for applications utilizing Large Language Models (LLMs). Founded in 2023 by former Googlers Henry Scott-Green and Alex Gamble, the company aims to help businesses understand user behavior and measure product performance in LLM-powered applications.

The company offers a platform that provides insights into user interactions with LLM applications. Key services include tracking conversation topics, performance analysis, debugging conversations, brand risk monitoring, user retention analysis, and measuring the impact of new releases. Their flagship product features a dashboard that allows customers to analyze data generated by LLMs, helping them assess whether the content effectively addresses user queries. Notably, Cognosys has benefited from Context.ai''s services, gaining valuable insights into user interactions. 

In 2023, Context.ai raised $3.5 million in seed funding from GV and Theory Ventures. The co-founders have since joined OpenAI, and the company is winding down its operations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/922.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/context', null), ('814', 'Globacap', 'Globacap Technology Limited', 'https://globacap.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/globacap/', 'Globacap is a financial technology company based in London, with an office in New York, that focuses on digitizing and automating private capital markets. Founded in 2017, the company aims to enhance efficiency, transparency, and connectivity in private market transactions through its advanced technology platform. It primarily serves financial professionals, including asset managers, placement agents, registered investment advisors, and advisory firms.

The platform offers a range of services, such as investor aggregation and deal distribution, investment vehicle management, and customizable white-label solutions for capital markets intermediaries. It also automates regulatory processes to reduce operational overhead. By leveraging Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT), Globacap enhances liquidity and transaction flow, making private assets more accessible and efficient. The company has gained recognition as one of the UK’s fastest-growing tech firms and successfully raised $21 million in a Series B funding round to further its mission in the private capital markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1146.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'globacap', null), ('815', 'SumUp', 'SumUp Payments Limited', 'https://www.sumup.com/en-gb/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sumup/', 'SumUp is a global financial technology company founded in 2012, focused on empowering small businesses with accessible payment solutions. With a mission to simplify payment processing, SumUp serves over 4 million businesses worldwide, including street vendors, salons, and large sports stadiums. The company operates in 35 countries, including major markets in Europe, the Americas, and Australia.

SumUp offers a variety of products designed to support small merchants. Their offerings include portable card readers, point-of-sale systems, online payment solutions, and a financial services super app that provides a free business account. Additionally, SumUp provides a merchant cash advance to help small businesses access capital. The company emphasizes transparency in its pricing model, ensuring no hidden fees, making it easier for small merchants to thrive. With a commitment to inclusivity, SumUp continues to innovate and expand its services to meet the needs of underserved businesses.', 'The company offers visa and relocation support for some roles. We have excluded any that definitely cannot be.', '4', '174', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/269.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('818', 'Quantexa', 'Quantexa Ltd', 'https://www.quantexa.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quantexa/', 'Quantexa is a global data and analytics software company founded in 2016 and based in London. The company specializes in Decision Intelligence, a technology that connects and contextualizes both internal and external data. This approach empowers organizations to make trusted, evidence-based operational decisions. With over 700 employees across 15 locations, including major cities like New York, Sydney, and Tokyo, Quantexa is committed to driving innovation in decision-making.

The core offering is the Decision Intelligence Platform, which enhances operational performance by providing a connected view of data. This platform improves accuracy and speeds up analytical processes significantly compared to traditional methods. Quantexa also offers data management services, industry-specific solutions for sectors such as banking and insurance, and expert services to support platform adoption. The company fosters a collaborative community for customers and partners to share knowledge and best practices, positioning itself as a leader in the rapidly growing Decision Intelligence market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1020.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('819', 'Airfinity', 'Airfinity Limited', 'https://www.airfinity.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/airfinity-ltd/', 'Airfinity Ltd is a UK-based data and analytics company founded in 2015 and headquartered in London. The company specializes in predictive health intelligence and disease forecasting, providing real-time insights to inform strategic decisions that enhance global health and increase lifespan. Airfinity utilizes advanced data analytics, machine learning, and expert epidemiological analysis to monitor and forecast trends in infectious diseases and public health.

The company gained recognition during the COVID-19 pandemic by creating a dedicated data and analytics platform that became a trusted resource for decision-makers worldwide. Airfinity''s services include real-time disease outbreak tracking, pharmaceutical pipeline analytics, and biorisk surveillance for over 160 infectious diseases. They also launched a specialized platform for obesity data and analytics, focusing on breakthrough obesity drugs. Airfinity supports a diverse range of clients, including governments, pharmaceutical companies, financial institutions, and research organizations, by providing custom data-driven insights for effective decision-making.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1091.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('820', 'Foundry', 'The Foundry Visionmongers', 'https://www.foundry.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/foundryteam/', 'Foundry is a creative software company with nearly 30 years of experience, specializing in advanced software solutions for the Media and Entertainment industry. Based in London’s Soho district, the company has additional offices in the US, Canada, China, Japan, Australia, and Ireland. Foundry collaborates with major studios and post-production houses, including Industrial Light & Magic, DNEG, and Pixar.

The company offers a suite of industry-leading software tools such as Mari, Katana, Nuke, and Furnace. These tools have played a crucial role in the production of every VFX Academy Award-winning film over the past decade. Foundry is committed to advancing the art and technology of visual experience, providing powerful software for visual effects, animation, and post-production workflows. Its products are widely used by artists around the world to create high-quality digital content for entertainment media.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1043.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'foundry', null), ('821', 'Antavo', 'Antavo Limited', 'https://antavo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/antavo/', 'Antavo AI Loyalty Cloud provides AI-powered customer loyalty technology that enhances the loyalty program lifecycle for global enterprises. Founded in London by four Hungarian co-founders, Antavo serves various industries, including retail, food & beverage, quick service restaurants, travel, hospitality, and shopping malls.

The company offers a scalable, cloud-native loyalty platform built on Kubernetes architecture, ensuring high performance and low latency. Its API-centric, no-code platform allows for easy integration with systems like Shopify and Salesforce, enabling marketing teams to manage loyalty programs independently. Antavo''s AI capabilities include Timi AI, a digital loyalty expert that helps optimize loyalty programs, and tools like Planner and Optimizer, which assist in designing programs and analyzing loyalty data.

Antavo supports innovative loyalty mechanics, incorporating gamification elements to boost customer engagement. Its clientele includes notable brands such as KFC, Skims, and C&A, showcasing its strong presence across diverse sectors. Antavo is recognized by industry analysts and manages billions of customer loyalty data points annually, positioning it as a leader in loyalty technology.', 'Sponsorship cannot be offered.', '2', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/575.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'teamtailor', 'antavo', null), ('822', 'NewDay', 'NewDay Cards Limited', 'https://www.newday.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/newday/?trkInfo=clickedVertical:company,clickedEntityId:5022659,idx:3-1-4,tarId:1460464007298,tas:newday', 'NewDay is a prominent financial services company in the UK, specializing in consumer credit products. Established in 2000, NewDay serves approximately 5.8 million customers through various brands, including Aqua, Fluid, Marbles, and Bip, which is the UK’s first digital-only credit card. The company offers a wide range of credit solutions, such as revolving credit cards, Buy Now, Pay Later (BNPL) options, instalment finance, and white-label credit services for major retailers like John Lewis & Partners and Lloyds Banking Group.

NewDay operates through two main units: the Credit business, which manages its own and partner brands, and the Platform business, which focuses on digital finance solutions. Their modern technology platform supports responsible credit decisioning, allowing them to cater to a diverse customer base, including near-prime borrowers. Committed to responsible lending, NewDay is authorized and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) and adheres to the Lending Code. The company emphasizes values such as accountability and integrity while investing in employee development to foster a high-performance culture.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '18', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/933.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'newday/NewDay', null), ('823', 'Codat', 'Codat Limited', 'https://www.codat.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/codat-limited/', 'Codat is a technology company founded in 2017 that specializes in financial data connectivity solutions through a universal API tailored for small and medium-sized businesses (SMBs). The company aims to simplify and automate the integration of financial software with various platforms, allowing financial service companies, lenders, accountants, and fintech providers to access small business financial data more efficiently.

Codat offers a suite of APIs that automate data synchronization across different financial systems. Key products include APIs for syncing commerce, expenses, payroll, and payables data, as well as a Bank Feeds API and a Lending API. The platform supports integrations with major accounting software and ERP systems, enabling real-time transaction syncing and efficient financial data management. Codat also provides professional services and tiered customer support to assist clients in implementing their solutions.

With offices in London, New York, San Francisco, and Sydney, Codat serves a diverse clientele, including financial institutions and fintech companies, enhancing their ability to streamline operations and improve customer experiences through automated financial data access.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/554.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/codat', null), ('824', 'Mojo Mortgages', 'Zoopla Ltd', 'https://mojomortgages.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mojomortgages/', 'Mojo Mortgages is a UK-based online mortgage broker founded in 2016. The company combines innovative technology with expert in-house mortgage advisors to streamline the mortgage application process. Customers can quickly check their mortgage eligibility and see real-time deals within about 15 minutes. Mojo Mortgages manages the entire application process, ensuring a smooth experience for clients.

As a whole-of-market broker, Mojo Mortgages provides access to over 70 lenders, including high street banks and specialist mortgage providers. This extensive network allows them to offer tailored mortgage recommendations and exclusive products, contributing to a 95% success rate for applicants. The company has assisted thousands of individuals in securing mortgages and has engaged with over 55,000 people regarding their mortgage needs in 2024.

Mojo Mortgages is part of the Houseful group and was acquired by RVU in 2021. The company has received multiple awards for its innovation and service quality, reflecting its commitment to customer satisfaction.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1118.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'mojomortgages', null), ('825', 'Capital One', 'Capital One (Europe) Plc', 'https://www.capitalone.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/capital-one/', 'Learn how banking with Capital One can help you meet your financial goals.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/444.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'teamtailor', 'capitalone', null), ('826', 'Sky', 'Sky UK Limited', 'https://sky.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sky/?original_referer=https://duckduckgo.com/&originalSubdomain=uk', 'Sky is a prominent British broadcaster and telecommunications company based in Isleworth, Middlesex. As a subsidiary of Sky Group, owned by Comcast Corporation, it ranks among Europe''s largest media and entertainment companies by revenue and subscriber base. Founded in 1990 from the merger of Sky Television and British Satellite Broadcasting, Sky has become the UK''s largest pay-TV provider and a significant telecommunications operator.

Sky offers a wide range of services, including multi-channel television broadcasting through platforms like Sky Q and Sky Glass, as well as broadband internet services using DSL and fiber technologies. The company also provides fixed line and mobile telephony services, along with interactive offerings such as mobile TV and gaming. Sky serves millions of customers across various European countries, distributing its channels directly and licensing content to other operators. Committed to innovation and social responsibility, Sky actively promotes initiatives for internet access and carbon emission reductions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/440.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'sky', null), ('827', 'FreeAgent', 'FreeAgent Central Ltd', 'https://www.freeagent.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/freeagent/', 'FreeAgent is a cloud-based accounting software company founded in 2007 and headquartered in Edinburgh, Scotland. It was created to simplify bookkeeping and business administration for freelancers and small businesses. The platform is designed primarily for UK small businesses, landlords, and their accountants or bookkeepers, helping users manage their finances with ease.

FreeAgent offers a comprehensive suite of accounting tools, including expense management, invoicing, time tracking, and tax return submission. The software also features a dedicated mobile app for managing business tasks on the go and provides world-class customer support. With over 150,000 customers, FreeAgent enables users to maintain a clear financial overview and reduce the stress associated with tax and bookkeeping.

The company has expanded into the US market and was acquired by NatWest Group in 2018, continuing to operate independently. FreeAgent is recognized for its commitment to simplifying financial management for small businesses and freelancers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/557.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'pinpoint', 'app', null), ('828', 'Xelix', 'GSPV Limited', 'https://xelix.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/xelix./', 'Xelix is a fintech company founded in 2018 by Paul Roiter and Phil Watts, specializing in AI-powered solutions for enterprise Accounts Payable (AP) teams. The company offers a comprehensive platform designed to enhance controls, reduce fraud risk, and automate manual AP tasks. It integrates seamlessly with existing ERP and AP systems, providing a robust solution for managing complex invoice and vendor data.

The platform features five core modules: Statements for automating supplier statement reconciliation, Helpdesk for quickly resolving vendor queries using generative AI, Transactions to prevent payment errors and fraud, Vendors for optimizing vendor master data, and Reports for creating actionable procure-to-pay reports. Xelix processes over $200 billion in invoice flow annually, leveraging advanced AI technologies to analyze invoicing patterns and detect suspicious activities.

Xelix primarily serves enterprise customers in the UK and US, focusing on CFOs and AP teams in global organizations. Its solutions are designed to improve financial controls, enhance operational efficiency, and deliver measurable cost savings through sophisticated AI technology.', 'The company can offer sponsorship to the right candidate.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/515.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('829', 'Method', 'GlobalLogic UK Limited', 'https://www.method.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/methodinc/', 'Method is a global strategic design and engineering firm founded in 1999, with offices in New York City, Charlotte, Atlanta, Denver, and London. The company employs around 200 people and specializes in the intersection of brand, product, and service design. Method focuses on multidisciplinary design thinking to create adaptable and beautiful solutions, emphasizing quick adaptation to new technologies. As part of GlobalLogic and the Hitachi family, Method provides enterprise-scale design and engineering services from over 30 locations worldwide.

The firm offers a wide range of services throughout the product life cycle, including digital strategy, customer experience enhancement, e-commerce growth, and experience design. Method also specializes in technology and engineering, providing agile custom application development, AI and machine learning, and cloud engineering. Additionally, they support organizational enablement through agile transformation and design thinking coaching. Method collaborates with various industries, helping clients modernize technology and innovate product offerings.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/892.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'method', null), ('830', 'The Orchard', 'Sony Music Entertainment UK Limited', 'https://www.theorchard.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-orchard/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'The Orchard is a global music and entertainment company based in New York City, operating as a division of Sony Music Entertainment. Established in 1997, it serves independent artists, labels, and content creators in over 40 cities worldwide. The Orchard offers a range of services designed to empower clients in the music industry.

Their offerings include music distribution for both digital and physical formats, comprehensive marketing and advertising campaigns, and advanced rights management solutions. The Orchard also provides support for video services, royalty accounting, publishing administration, sync licensing, and data analysis. This combination of services helps clients effectively distribute, promote, and monetize their content.

The Orchard has a diverse clientele, including notable names like Double P Records, Top Dawg Entertainment, and Maverick City. The company fosters a supportive work environment and owns BalconyTV, an online music channel featuring acoustic performances.', 'The Orchard does not offer sponsorship often. They do so on a case-by-case basis for specific "hard-to-fill" roles like "VP and above" positions or tech candidates who qualify (it is unclear what qualification is here).', '1', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/231.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'theorchard', null), ('832', 'Darktrace', 'Darktrace Holdings Limited', 'https://darktrace.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/darktrace/', 'Darktrace is a leading cybersecurity company that specializes in AI-driven solutions to detect and respond to advanced cyber threats in real time. Founded in 2013 by experts from the University of Cambridge, Darktrace has developed innovative technologies that adapt to an organization''s unique digital environment. The company is headquartered in Cambridge, UK, and San Francisco, USA, with over 44 offices worldwide and a workforce of more than 2,200 employees.

The flagship product, the Enterprise Immune System, uses unsupervised machine learning to establish a "pattern of life" for users and devices, enabling it to identify anomalies and potential threats. Darktrace also offers Darktrace Antigena, which autonomously responds to cyber-attacks, and the Darktrace Cyber AI Analyst, which automates threat investigation. Additionally, Darktrace provides cloud-native security solutions and focuses on securing industrial networks. With over 10,000 customers across various industries, Darktrace is recognized for its innovation and commitment to responsible AI use in cybersecurity.', 'The company will only sponsor visas for certain roles. These will be assessed on a case-by-case basis. Applicants should ask at the time of application.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/349.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'DarktaceExternal', null), ('833', 'Tricentis', 'Tricentis UK Limited', 'https://www.tricentis.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tricentis/', 'Tricentis is a global software testing company founded in 2007 in Vienna, Austria, and now headquartered in Austin, Texas. The company specializes in enterprise continuous testing and quality engineering, offering an AI-powered, fully automated, and codeless testing platform. This platform is designed to enhance software quality assurance in complex enterprise environments.

Tricentis has evolved from a consulting business into a leader in test automation. Its flagship product, Tricentis Tosca, supports a wide range of testing needs, including risk-based testing, SAP testing, API testing, and load testing. The company serves over 3,000 customers worldwide, including nearly half of the Fortune 500, and has generated over $330 million in annual recurring revenue as of 2023. Tricentis emphasizes partnerships to enhance its market reach and help customers innovate faster while reducing costs and risks.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '22', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/898.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'workday', 'tricentis/Tricentis_Careers', null), ('834', 'Genius Sports', 'Genius Sports UK Ltd', 'https://www.geniussports.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/geniussports/', 'Genius Sports is a global sports technology company based in London, founded in 2001. Initially a betting data specialist, it has grown into one of the largest firms in the sports tech industry, employing around 2,600 people across 18 locations worldwide. The company aims to be the essential technology partner for sports leagues, teams, and brands, enhancing the sports ecosystem from live data capture to fan engagement.

Genius Sports offers a range of services, including real-time data capture and distribution, sports betting solutions, and performance analytics. Its GeniusIQ platform processes multiple real-time data feeds to support various applications in sports. The company also provides automated officiating tools, fan engagement solutions, and video streaming services. Notable partnerships include the NFL, Premier League, NBA, and major sportsbooks like Caesars and FanDuel, showcasing its role as a key player in modern sports entertainment and data integrity.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/263.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'geniussports', null), ('836', 'Moody''s', 'Moody''s Analytics UK Ltd', 'https://www.moodys.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/moodys-corporation/', 'Moody''s Corporation is a prominent provider of credit ratings, research, and risk analysis services, with a history dating back to 1909. Recognized as one of the "Big Three" credit rating agencies, Moody''s plays a crucial role in helping businesses and financial leaders make informed decisions.

The company offers a variety of services, including credit ratings for financial instruments like bonds and commercial paper, in-depth research and analysis across multiple sectors, and advanced data and analytics tools. Moody''s also provides risk management solutions that assist organizations in optimizing their risk processes. Its services are utilized by a diverse clientele, including financial institutions, investors, corporations, and government agencies, all seeking to navigate complex financial landscapes with confidence.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/522.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'moodys', null), ('837', 'Patchwork', 'LocumTap Ltd', 'https://patchwork.health/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/heypatchwork/', 'Patchwork Health is a UK-based health technology company founded in 2016 by NHS doctors Dr. Anas Nader and Dr. Jing Ouyang. The company aims to address healthcare staffing challenges faced by NHS hospitals. It focuses on improving workforce management for healthcare organizations, particularly NHS Trusts.

The company offers an end-to-end workforce planning and management platform designed by healthcare professionals. This platform includes a digital staff bank that connects organizations with clinicians to fill shifts, collaborative rostering tools for better scheduling, and data analytics to optimize staffing decisions. Patchwork Health also provides flexible working options for clinicians, enhancing staff satisfaction and retention. Trusted by over 200 healthcare organizations, including more than ten NHS Trusts, the platform has saved millions in staffing fees while ensuring adequate staffing levels to improve patient care.

Headquartered in London’s Leather Market, Patchwork Health is part of a vibrant healthtech ecosystem, fostering a collaborative culture focused on leveraging technology to enhance healthcare delivery and workforce management.', null, '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/188.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('839', 'Publicis Groupe', 'Publicis Limited', 'https://www.publicisgroupe.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/publicis-groupe/', 'Publicis Groupe is a French multinational advertising and public relations company, founded in 1926 and headquartered in Paris. As the largest advertising company in the world by revenue, it operates in over 100 countries with approximately 98,000 employees. The company has a strong presence in more than 202 cities globally and focuses on both traditional and digital advertising, emphasizing creativity, technology, and data-driven marketing.

