With headquarters in Boston and London, Sofar Sounds has hosted over 22,000 performances in more than 400 cities worldwide, including cultural hubs like Paris, New York City, and Los Angeles. The events feature three different artists or groups, with audience sizes typically ranging from 10 to 100 guests. The location and lineup are kept secret until shortly before the event, enhancing the element of surprise.

Sofar Sounds supports emerging and independent artists by providing them a platform to perform and connect with diverse audiences. The company also produces digital content, including live session recordings and podcasts, to broaden access to its music experiences. It fosters a global community of music lovers, emphasizing inclusivity and equality in the music industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/410.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'lever', 'sofarsounds', null), ('841', 'Makers', 'Makers Academy Limited', 'https://makers.tech/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/school/makers-academy/', 'Makers is a UK-based tech education and talent organization founded in 2013 by Evgeny Shadchnev and Rob Johnson. As Europe’s first coding bootcamp, it has grown into a comprehensive service aimed at equipping individuals and businesses with essential skills for the AI-driven economy. Makers is a certified B Corp, demonstrating its commitment to high standards of performance, accountability, and sustainable practices.

The company offers a variety of tech education programs, including software development, DevOps and cloud engineering, data engineering, test engineering, and data analytics. These programs are delivered through immersive bootcamp-style training, typically lasting 16 weeks, and focus on both technical skills and problem-solving abilities. Makers also provides apprenticeships and tailored upskilling programs for businesses, helping to build AI-confident tech teams.

