Ramp Network offers a range of products, including fiat-to-crypto on-ramps and crypto-to-fiat off-ramps, allowing users to convert between fiat currencies and cryptocurrencies easily. Their customizable widget can be integrated into partner applications, and they provide SDKs and developer tools for seamless implementation. The company emphasizes regulatory compliance, holding registrations with FINCEN in the U.S., FCA in the U.K., and the Central Bank of Ireland, ensuring adherence to global financial regulations. With support for over 150 countries and various payment methods, Ramp Network is committed to making cryptocurrency accessible worldwide. 

The company partners with notable names in the blockchain and Web3 space, including Axie Infinity, Brave Browser, and GameStop, highlighting its role in promoting mainstream adoption of Web3 technologies.', 'The company can only offer sponsorship for management-level roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/328.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'rampnetwork', null), ('853', 'Climate X', 'Climate X Ltd', 'https://www.climate-x.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/climate-x/', 'Climate X is a London-based company founded in 2020 that focuses on climate risk data and analytics. It provides insights primarily for the financial services and real estate sectors, aiming to enhance global economic stability by helping organizations understand and manage the physical risks associated with climate change.

The company offers a climate risk platform that integrates scientific data and econometric modeling. Its flagship product, Spectra, serves as a digital twin of the Earth, projecting the likelihood and impact of weather events on assets. This tool assists financial institutions and real estate firms in stress-testing portfolios and making informed decisions. Additionally, Climate X provides Adapt, a product for scenario-based resilience planning, and solutions for climate risk reporting that align with major regulatory frameworks.

With a team of 51 to 200 employees, Climate X is led by CEO and co-founder Lukky Ahmed. The company has gained significant funding and established partnerships with industry leaders, reinforcing its position in climate risk assessment and sustainability planning.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1137.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('854', 'YardLink', 'YardLink Ltd', 'https://yardlink.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/yardlink/', 'YardLink is a technology company based in London, UK, founded in 2016. It specializes in digital supply chain management for the construction industry. The company operates a B2B marketplace platform that connects construction procurement teams and contractors with a large network of trusted local plant hire companies and suppliers across the UK.

The YardLink platform simplifies the procurement process by allowing users to find, book, and pay for a variety of construction equipment, such as access towers and mini excavators, all through a single account. It offers real-time project-level equipment tracking and management tools, enabling customers to manage orders from multiple suppliers via an online dashboard. This centralized approach enhances efficiency and transparency in construction supply chains.

YardLink serves construction companies, contractors, and procurement teams, providing instant access to over 1,000 vetted suppliers. The platform supports both independent and national suppliers, ensuring broad product availability and competitive pricing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/777.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('856', 'Lifebit', 'Lifebit Biotech Ltd', 'https://www.lifebit.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lifebit-ai/', 'Lifebit is a precision medicine software company founded in 2017, headquartered in London, UK, with operations in Athens, Greece. The company specializes in AI-powered enterprise data platforms that securely manage, access, and analyze sensitive genomic and biomedical datasets for healthcare and life sciences organizations. 

Lifebit''s core innovation is its patented federated biomedical data platform, which allows researchers to conduct analyses on distributed datasets without moving or exposing sensitive data. This platform, known as Lifebit CloudOS or the federated DataLakehouse, integrates various functionalities, including a federated lakehouse for health data, a centralized research environment for governance and collaboration, AI-powered data harmonization, and workflow integration. Lifebit serves a diverse customer base, including pharmaceutical companies and research institutes, and has expanded its accessibility by launching on the Amazon Web Services (AWS) Marketplace. The company''s mission is to democratize access to complex omics data, enabling researchers to perform meaningful analyses while ensuring data privacy and security.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/105.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'lifebit', null), ('857', 'Amplitude', 'Amplitude Analytics Limited', 'https://amplitude.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/amplitude-analytics/', 'Amplitude is an enterprise software company based in San Francisco, California, specializing in product analytics and product intelligence platforms. The company helps businesses understand user behavior, enhance product experiences, and drive growth across various industries, including fintech, e-commerce, gaming, and media.

