The company provides comprehensive trade compliance coverage across numerous exchanges and brokerages worldwide. Key features include automated trade approvals based on company policies, real-time monitoring for potential violations, and streamlined reporting workflows. Aer Compliance serves a diverse customer base, including major funds and market makers, focusing on high-risk environments where compliance is essential. In November 2024, Aer Compliance was acquired by StarCompliance, enhancing its capabilities in cryptocurrency compliance technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/549.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('924', 'Asana', 'Asana Software UK Limited', 'https://www.asana.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/asana/', 'Asana, Inc. is a technology company founded in 2008 by Dustin Moskovitz and Justin Rosenstein. Headquartered in San Francisco, it has additional offices in Tokyo, Vancouver, Warsaw, and Singapore. Asana develops a project and work management platform that helps teams coordinate, track, and manage their work efficiently.

The core product, also named Asana, is a workflow and project management tool that allows organizations to break down projects into smaller tasks, assign responsibilities, and set deadlines. It aims to minimize time spent on meetings and searching for information, enabling users to focus on their core work. Asana is available as a web application and through native apps for iOS, Android, and desktop, supporting collaboration across devices. The platform integrates with tools like Gmail and is available in multiple languages.

Asana serves over 100,000 paying organizations worldwide, including notable customers such as eBay, Uber, and IBM. The company''s name reflects its mission to bring ease and focus to work processes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1258.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('925', 'Better Origin', 'Entomics Biosystems Limited', 'https://betterorigin.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/betterorigin/', 'Better Origin is a UK-based company founded in 2015 that focuses on transforming food waste into sustainable products through insect farming technology enhanced by artificial intelligence. The company aims to address food waste, reduce emissions, and improve animal welfare with its innovative insect farming solutions.

The flagship product is the X-Series, which includes modular, containerized insect farms that convert local organic waste into nutritious insect protein and oils. These fully automated units optimize conditions for insect growth and yield, primarily using Black Soldier Fly larvae. Better Origin also produces sustainable animal feed and organic fertilizers from the byproducts of the insect farming process. The company offers an end-to-end service model, managing the entire farming process for customers, who simply provide organic waste.

Better Origin serves food companies, farmers, and retailers looking for low-carbon alternatives to traditional animal feed. Their technology contributes to sustainable agriculture and addresses global challenges related to food waste and land scarcity. The company has raised significant funding to expand its operations and partnerships across Europe.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/162.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'better-origin', null), ('926', 'Artificial', 'Artificial Labs Limited', 'https://artificial.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/artificiallabs/', 'Artificial Labs is a London-based insurtech company that focuses on underwriting technology for the specialty insurance market. Founded in 2013, the company is headquartered in London and operates as a private limited company. 

The company offers a configurable digital platform tailored for complex specialty insurance placement and underwriting. Its Smart Placement Technology assists brokers in digitizing insurance placements and optimizing capacity management, while the Smart Underwriting Technology enables carriers to enhance their underwriting processes. The platform integrates data from various sources, providing users with actionable insights to improve decision-making. 

Artificial Labs collaborates with leading global brokers and carriers, including Chaucer, Convex, The Ardonagh Group, Lockton, and BMS, as well as new managing general agents like Augmented Underwriting. The company is recognized for its innovative technology solutions that support the future of specialty insurance.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1191.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('927', 'Wayflyer', 'Wayflyer UK Limited', 'https://www.wayflyer.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wayflyer/?originalSubdomain=ie', 'Wayflyer is a global revenue-based financing company founded in 2019 and headquartered in Dublin, Ireland, with offices in New York, London, and Sydney. The company specializes in providing fast and flexible funding solutions primarily for eCommerce and consumer packaged goods (CPG) brands. Wayflyer helps businesses overcome working capital challenges and scale effectively through its core service of revenue-based financing.

Wayflyer offers capital to online merchants in exchange for a percentage of their future revenue, aligning repayments with the cash flow patterns typical of eCommerce businesses. Funding amounts range from $10,000 to $20 million, catering to various business sizes and growth stages. The company delivers financing quickly, often within 24 hours, enabling merchants to invest in inventory, marketing, and other operational needs without diluting equity. Wayflyer utilizes technology solutions for seamless access to funds and maintains a high approval rate and customer satisfaction rate. Their customer base includes eCommerce startups and small to medium-sized online merchants across North America, Europe, and beyond.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '12', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/32.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/wayflyer', null), ('928', 'NetJets', 'NetJets Management Limited', 'https://www.netjets.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/netjets-europe/', 'NetJets Inc. is a leading American company in private aviation, established in 1964 and known for being the first private business jet charter and aircraft management company. Originally founded as Executive Jet Airways, it was rebranded as NetJets in 2002 after being acquired by Berkshire Hathaway in 1998. The company is recognized for inventing the fractional ownership model for private jets.

NetJets provides a variety of services focused on private jet travel. These include fractional ownership, where customers buy a share of a jet; flexible leasing options; jet card programs for prepaid flight access; on-demand charter services; and full-service aircraft management. The company also facilitates aircraft sales and offers VIP security and additional tailored aviation solutions. With the world’s largest private jet fleet, NetJets serves high-net-worth individuals, corporations, and other clients seeking reliable and luxurious air travel. Headquartered in Columbus, Ohio, it continues to lead the private aviation industry with its innovative approach and commitment to customer service.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/481.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'netjets', null), ('929', 'Immersive Gamebox', 'Immersive Group Gaming Ltd', 'https://www.immersivegamebox.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/immersivegamebox', 'Immersive Gamebox is an entertainment company that specializes in immersive, interactive group gaming experiences. It features proprietary "Gameboxes," which are smart, digital rooms designed for groups of two to six players. The company aims to transform location-based entertainment by offering social, controller-free games that utilize motion tracking, touch-sensitive walls, dynamic projection mapping, and surround sound, creating fully immersive experiences without the need for headsets.

Founded to enhance group entertainment, Immersive Gamebox operates in multiple countries and has engaged over one million players, accumulating more than 50 million minutes of gameplay. The company has received over 25,000 five-star reviews on Tripadvisor, ranking it among the top attractions worldwide. Its games cater to a wide audience, from children to adults, and are designed to be easy to pick up and enjoyable for all skill levels, making them ideal for family outings, friends'' gatherings, date nights, and corporate events.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1289.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'immersive', null), ('930', 'Unify', 'Deep Ivy Ltd', 'https://unify.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/letsunifyai/', 'Unify AI Business Corporation, founded in 2023 by Austin Hughes and Connor Heggie, is an AI-native company that specializes in performance management for sales teams. Their primary offering is a Go-To-Market (GTM) platform that consolidates data from various sources, such as CRMs and data warehouses, into a unified data graph. This integration helps sales teams identify high-potential prospects, automate account research, and personalize outreach messaging.

The platform is designed to support smaller and fast-growing sales teams, particularly in AI and tech startups. It automates repetitive outbound sales tasks and provides relevant context for personalized interactions. Key features include AI-driven sales automation, intent signal integration, and multi-channel outreach capabilities. Unify serves a diverse client base, including notable startups like Perplexity and SoFi, helping them enhance their sales pipelines through improved targeting and automation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1139.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'lever', 'unify', null), ('932', 'Credit Benchmark', 'Credit Benchmark Limited', 'https://www.creditbenchmark.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/credit-benchmark/', 'Credit Benchmark is a British financial data and analytics company founded in 2013. It specializes in providing Credit Consensus Ratings and Analytics, which are derived from the aggregated internal credit risk views of over 40 leading global financial institutions, including many Global Systemically Important Banks (GSIBs). The company’s unique Credit Consensus model aggregates one million monthly rating observations to produce an independent measure of credit risk, serving as an alternative to traditional rating agencies.

The company offers a range of products and services, including entity-level credit risk data for over 80,000 obligors, updated regularly. It provides descriptive analytics that show the variability of credit views and security-level rating assessments in partnership with Bloomberg for approximately 130,000 bonds and loans. Credit Benchmark delivers its data through various platforms, including web applications, Excel add-ins, and APIs, making it accessible to a wide array of clients in the financial sector, such as banks, asset managers, and corporates. Headquartered in London, Credit Benchmark emphasizes transparency and the collective insights of credit analysts to enhance credit risk assessment.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/502.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'creditbenchmark', null), ('933', 'Plum Guide ', 'Plu&m Limited', 'https://www.plumguide.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/plum-guide/', 'Plum Guide is a global vacation rental company founded in 2015 and based in London, with additional offices in New York and Hong Kong. It specializes in curating a selective collection of short-term rental properties, including vacation homes and Airbnbs, across over 500 destinations in 29 countries. The platform features more than 30,000 rigorously vetted homes, making it one of the largest curated collections worldwide.

The company employs a unique, technology-driven curation process that combines an AI-powered algorithm with expert human review. Each property undergoes the "Plum Test," a comprehensive assessment of over 150 features, ensuring high standards for comfort and style. Plum Guide also offers a B2B service, Plum Guide ForBusiness, providing its curation technology to online booking platforms and hotel groups. The company targets discerning travelers seeking reliable and stylish vacation homes, and it has received industry recognition for its innovation and service quality.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/517.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'breezy', 'plum', null), ('934', 'Abound', 'Fintern Limited', 'https://www.getabound.com/', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/getabound?trk=public_jobs_topcard-org-name', 'Abound is a UK-based fintech company that specializes in providing low-cost, fair, and flexible personal loans. Founded by Michelle and Gerald, Abound aims to improve personal lending by using a comprehensive approach to credit assessment, particularly for individuals without established credit scores. The company operates as a B2C SaaS platform and is headquartered in London.

Abound offers personal loans up to £10,000 with repayment terms ranging from 12 to 60 months. Their application process is designed to be fast and transparent, allowing customers to receive personalized quotes without impacting their credit score. By evaluating a borrower’s full financial picture, including income and spending habits, Abound provides affordable interest rates and flexible repayment options, with a representative APR of 25.8%. The company focuses on increasing access to affordable loans and helping consumers build better financial lives.', 'The company is able to offer sponsorship for "selective" roles. It is unclear which roles are included in that definition.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1198.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/abound', null), ('935', 'Zempler Bank', 'Advanced Payment Solutions Ltd', 'https://www.zemplerbank.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cashplus/', 'Zempler Bank is a fully regulated UK challenger bank that transitioned from a prepaid card operator, originally known as Cashplus, to a fully authorized bank in July 2024. Founded by CEO Rich Wagner, the bank aims to simplify banking for individuals and small businesses that are often overlooked by traditional banks.

Zempler Bank offers a variety of services, including digital business accounts for sole traders and small to medium-sized enterprises, personal current accounts, and credit products such as credit cards. Their business accounts feature tools for invoice creation, digital receipt management, and cash flow tracking, with integration options for popular accounting software. Personal banking customers can benefit from overdrafts and Creditbuilder products to enhance their credit history.

The bank is dedicated to economic sustainability and customer support, focusing on providing straightforward banking solutions. With a commitment to innovation, Zempler Bank continues to expand its offerings to better serve its customer base in the UK.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/414.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('936', 'Navan', 'Navan Labs UK Limited', 'https://navan.com/uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/navan', 'Navan is a technology company based in Palo Alto, California, specializing in corporate travel and expense management. Founded in 2015, Navan provides an integrated platform that simplifies business travel booking, expense reporting, and corporate card program integration for enterprises around the world. The company has expanded its presence to over 50 global offices, including locations in Europe and India.

Navan offers several key products, including Navan Travel, an AI-powered booking platform that personalizes travel options based on company policies and traveler preferences. Navan Expense automates expense reporting and reimbursement processes, making it easier for employees and finance teams. Additionally, Navan Connect integrates corporate payment cards with the travel and expense platform, allowing for seamless management of expenses. With a focus on user-friendly experiences and compliance, Navan serves a diverse range of clients, including major corporations like Unilever, Wayfair, and Zoom.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/254.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('937', 'Progression', 'Make and Grow Ltd', 'https://progression.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/progressionhq/?originalSubdomain=uk', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/513.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('938', 'Paddle', 'Paddle.com Market Ltd', 'https://www.paddle.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/paddle/', 'Paddle is a London-based technology company founded in 2012, specializing in a unified platform for Software as a Service (SaaS) businesses. The platform integrates various functions, including billing, payment processing, subscription management, revenue recovery, analytics, and customer support. This comprehensive solution helps software companies streamline their operations, allowing them to focus on product development and customer success.

Operating globally, Paddle serves over 3,000 software customers across more than 200 markets and 245 countries and territories. The company targets SaaS companies, developers, small and medium-sized businesses, and product managers, with a strong presence in regions like Australia/New Zealand and Western Europe. Paddle emphasizes localization in payment methods and checkout experiences to enhance conversion rates in diverse international markets.

A key feature of Paddle is its role as a Merchant of Record, managing global payment processing, fraud management, and compliance with international sales tax regulations. This model allows clients to offload complex payment and regulatory tasks, enabling them to concentrate on their core business. Paddle operates on a transaction-based fee model, aligning its success with that of its customers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '18', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/29.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/paddle', null), ('939', 'IG Group', 'IG Group Holdings Plc', 'https://www.iggroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/iggroup/', 'IG Group is a prominent global provider of online trading services, founded in 1974 by Stuart Wheeler. Initially known as IG Index, the company pioneered spread betting, allowing investors to speculate on gold prices without owning the commodity. Headquartered in London, IG Group operates in Europe and the USA, offering access to around 19,000 financial markets.

The company provides a diverse range of financial products and services, including spread betting, CFDs (Contracts for Difference), forex trading, stock trading, and options and futures. IG Group is recognized for its user-friendly trading platforms, which include web-based and mobile applications equipped with real-time market data and analysis tools. With a market value of £3.4 billion as of 2024, IG Group serves a wide client base of retail and institutional traders, earning multiple awards for its services and platforms.', 'They "don''t tend to consider candidates who are overseas for roles in other countries unless they are currently working for or have worked for IG".', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/437.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'ig/EXT_IG', null), ('940', 'ComplyAdvantage', 'IVXS UK Limited', 'https://complyadvantage.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/complyadvantage/', 'ComplyAdvantage is a SaaS-based risk intelligence company that specializes in AI-driven solutions for financial crime and anti-money laundering (AML) risk detection. Its platform, ComplyAdvantage Mesh, integrates global intelligence to help financial institutions and enterprises effectively manage financial crime risks.

The company offers a comprehensive suite of services that includes customer and company screening, ongoing monitoring, transaction monitoring, and access to extensive sanctions and watchlists. ComplyAdvantage utilizes artificial intelligence throughout the financial crime risk management lifecycle, enhancing accuracy and reducing false positives. This approach is essential for organizations in the financial services sector, including banks and fintech firms, as they navigate regulatory compliance.

With a leadership team experienced in AI, fintech, and compliance, ComplyAdvantage is recognized as a category leader in its field. The company supports its clients in proactively detecting and managing financial crime risks, ensuring they meet global regulatory standards efficiently.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/267.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('941', 'Pixie', 'UsePixie Software UK Ltd', 'https://www.usepixie.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/usepixie/', 'Pixie is a London-based company that offers practice management software specifically designed for accounting and bookkeeping firms. Its platform simplifies and automates workflows, enabling firms to manage clients, deadlines, team tasks, and communications in one place.

The software features workflow automation to reduce administrative tasks, client data centralization for secure file sharing and record management, and access to pre-built templates from a global community. It also provides flexible reporting for visibility into work progress and dedicated support, including an account manager for onboarding and workflow optimization. Pixie uses a flat fee pricing model for firms, making it scalable for businesses of all sizes.

Targeting accounting and bookkeeping firms, Pixie aims to streamline compliance and improve efficiency. The company, incorporated in December 2020, focuses on delivering a user-friendly solution that helps firms save time and grow effectively.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/121.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('942', 'Connectd', 'LinkExec Ltd', 'https://www.connectd.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/connectd-co/', 'Connectd is a fintech and business services company based in London, United Kingdom. Founded by Roei Samuel, it operates a data-driven community network platform that connects entrepreneurs, startups, investors, non-executive directors, board advisors, and mentors. The platform aims to facilitate growth opportunities and funding by leveraging innovative technology and smart matching algorithms.

Connectd''s core offering includes a technology platform that ingests data from various sources to create comprehensive profiles for startups and investors. This enables smart matching technology that pairs startups with compatible investors and advisors based on industry relevance and progress metrics. The platform also features progress reporting tools for founders, enhancing transparency with investors, and fosters peer-to-peer learning and networking opportunities. Connectd primarily serves startups seeking investment and mentorship, as well as investors looking for strategic opportunities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/790.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('943', 'NatWest', 'NatWest Group plc', 'https://www.natwestgroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/natwest-group/', null, 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/698.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'natwestgroup/NatWest_Careers', null), ('944', 'Turo', 'TuroUK Ltd', 'https://turo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/turo/', 'Turo is a peer-to-peer car-sharing company founded in 2009, originally launched as RelayRides in Boston. It operates an online marketplace that connects private car owners with travelers and local renters, providing an alternative to traditional car rental services. Headquartered in San Francisco, Turo expanded nationwide across the U.S. by 2012 and later entered the Canadian market in 2016.

The core service of Turo allows car owners to list their vehicles for rent, while travelers can book cars directly through the platform. Turo offers a diverse range of vehicles, from economy to luxury, catering to various customer needs for daily transportation and travel. The platform emphasizes convenience and affordability, appealing to adventure-seekers and those who prefer peer-to-peer sharing models. Turo has experienced significant growth and has raised substantial venture capital, reaching over $1 billion in cumulative global gross revenue.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1264.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('945', 'ThoughtRiver', 'ThoughtRiver Ltd', 'https://thoughtriver.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/thoughtriver/', 'ThoughtRiver is a legal technology company based in Cambridge, UK, that specializes in AI-driven contract review solutions. Founded by Tim Pullan, the company aims to automate and streamline the contract review process for legal teams facing high volumes of complex contracts. Its flagship product, Lexible®, utilizes advanced natural language processing and machine learning to analyze contracts, extract critical information, and highlight risks with high accuracy and speed.

In addition to Lexible®, ThoughtRiver offers a range of AI-powered contract review services, including Purely NDA, a user-friendly solution for reviewing and negotiating Non-Disclosure Agreements. The platform is designed to enhance efficiency for both legal and non-legal users, making the contract review process quicker for organizations of all sizes. ThoughtRiver''s technology is recognized for its speed and accuracy, completing contract reviews in minutes with over 90% accuracy, and is backed by robust data protection measures. The company serves a diverse customer base, including large enterprises like PwC and Singtel, while also supporting local businesses in Cambridge.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/516.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('946', 'Impala', 'Impala Travel Technology Ltd', 'https://impala.travel/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/impala-travel/', 'Impala is a corporate travel technology company based in the UK, founded in 2022 and headquartered in London. The company specializes in reducing corporate travel expenses by up to 30% through data-driven negotiation and tailored travel solutions. Impala focuses on optimizing costs across accommodations, airline and ground transport, and group travel events, helping businesses turn travel into a strategic advantage.

The company utilizes deep analysis of historical travel data and industry insights to create customized travel programs for its clients. Impala''s services include accommodation negotiation and management, airline and ground transport negotiation, and group travel planning. They also offer the Impala Events app for managing large group events, ensuring favorable deals on hotels, venues, and meals. With a commitment to continuous improvement, Impala integrates seamlessly with existing booking systems to enhance compliance and traveler satisfaction.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/530.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'impala', null), ('947', 'Zoe', 'Zoe Limited', 'https://zoe.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/joinzoe/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'ZOE encompasses several distinct companies across different industries. 

ZOE Energy Storage is a global provider of integrated energy storage products and solutions, headquartered in Shanghai, China. It specializes in energy storage systems, particularly the Z BOX series, which is certified for safety and quality worldwide. The company offers services such as research and development, certification, and virtual power plant operations, and is expanding its presence in North and South America, Europe, and the Middle East.

