The company aims to elevate creative expression through data, establishing a global standard for creative analytics. Major brands like Nestlé, Bayer, and Mars have utilized CreativeX''s platform to achieve measurable improvements in ad performance and marketing effectiveness. The platform allows marketers to define standards of creative excellence and measure their assets against these benchmarks, ultimately boosting audience understanding and marketing impact.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '3', '7', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/300.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'creativex', null), ('977', 'Amnesty International', 'Amnesty International, International Secretariat', 'https://www.amnesty.org/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/amnesty-international/', 'Amnesty International is a prominent international non-governmental organization founded in London in 1961 by Peter Benenson. The organization is dedicated to the protection and promotion of human rights as outlined in the Universal Declaration of Human Rights. Operating independently of governments and political ideologies, Amnesty International campaigns for human rights globally.

The core mission of Amnesty International includes publicizing and combating violations of fundamental human rights, such as freedom of speech and protection against torture. Its activities encompass systematic research and documentation of human rights abuses, advocacy to influence public opinion and government actions, and raising awareness through publications and grassroots activism. The organization also supports victims by working for the release of political prisoners and providing assistance to affected individuals and their families.

With a network of national sections in over 50 countries and a membership of more than ten million, Amnesty International plays a significant role in shaping international human rights law and policy. Its emblematic logo, a burning candle wrapped in barbed wire, symbolizes hope and resistance against oppression.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/903.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'amnestyinternational', null), ('978', 'Coalition', 'Coalition Risk Solutions Ltd', 'https://www.coalitioninc.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/coalitioninc/', 'Coalition, Inc. is a San Francisco-based cyber insurtech company founded in 2017. The company specializes in integrating cybersecurity technology with insurance to effectively manage cyber risks. Coalition''s mission is to provide comprehensive solutions for small and midsize enterprises, which often face significant cyber threats without adequate protection.

One of Coalition''s key offerings is Active Insurance, which combines cyber insurance coverage with cybersecurity tools. This product includes risk assessments, incident prevention measures, and a dedicated incident response team available 24/7. The insurance coverage addresses various cyber risks, such as network breaches, ransomware, and privacy liability. Coalition''s solutions are designed to make cybersecurity and insurance accessible to businesses of all sizes, particularly those that are under-resourced.

With a focus on a culture-first approach and a leadership team experienced in cybersecurity and insurance, Coalition is recognized as one of the fastest-growing cyber insurance providers in the U.S. and Canada. The company is also expanding globally through strategic partnerships to enhance its offerings and market reach.', 'Sponsorship cannot be offered currently.', '2', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/826.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'coalition', null), ('979', 'Zenobe', 'Zenobe Energy Limited', 'https://www.zenobe.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zenobe-energy-ltd/', 'Zenobē is a global leader in battery storage and fleet electrification, founded in 2017 and based in London, United Kingdom. The company focuses on facilitating the transition to zero-carbon power and transport systems through innovative battery solutions. Zenobē operates in regions including Europe, Australia, New Zealand, and North America, with offices in New York and Naperville.

The company offers a range of services centered on energy storage and fleet electrification. Zenobē provides large-scale battery storage systems that connect to the electricity grid, enhancing the use of renewable energy. They also specialize in turnkey fleet electrification solutions, which include charging infrastructure and vehicle-battery managed services. Additionally, Zenobē refurbishes batteries for second-life applications, extending their usability and reducing waste. As a leading owner and operator of electric buses in Australia and New Zealand, Zenobē is also expanding its offerings to light commercial vehicles and trucks.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/186.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'zenobe', null), ('980', 'Toyota Connected', 'Toyota Connected Europe Limited', 'https://toyotaconnected.eu/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/toyota-connected-europe/', 'Toyota Connected Europe (TCEU) is a technology-driven mobility solutions company established in 2018, based in London. As part of Toyota''s global expansion of connected services, TCEU focuses on developing innovative mobility products tailored to the European market. The company operates with an emphasis on data science, engineering, and design, and collaborates closely with Toyota Motor Europe, retailers, and distributors.

TCEU offers a range of services, including a Mobility Services Platform (MSPF) that supports ride-sharing, car-sharing, and remote delivery solutions. It also provides fleet management solutions for businesses, governments, and consumers, along with data-driven technologies aimed at enhancing safety and sustainability in mobility. The company utilizes large-scale mobility data to improve user experiences and engineers scalable platforms for connected vehicles and services. TCEU is committed to advancing Toyota''s vision for connected and sustainable mobility in Europe.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/936.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'toyotaconnected', null), ('981', 'Trainline', 'Trainline.com Ltd', 'https://www.thetrainline.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/trainline/', 'Trainline is a British technology company that specializes in digital rail and coach ticketing services throughout Europe. Founded in 1997, it has developed into a leading online platform for purchasing train and coach tickets, railcards, and related travel products. The company operates a global digital platform that facilitates online and mobile sales, payments, and ticketing solutions.

Trainline serves a diverse customer base, including individual consumers, small and medium enterprises, large corporate clients, public sector partners, travel management companies, and travel agents. Its offerings include online booking for all UK rail carriers and major coach operators, expense management tools for corporate travel, and integrated rail booking solutions with corporate travel management platforms. The company has offices in London, Paris, and Edinburgh, reflecting its extensive reach across Europe.

Trainline went public on the London Stock Exchange in 2019 and reported revenues of £158 million in 2020. The company continues to focus on enhancing its technology and diversifying its services to support recovery and growth in the travel sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '30', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/46.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('982', 'Logically', 'TheLogically Ltd', 'https://www.logically.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/joinlogically/', 'Logically is a British multinational technology company founded in 2017, focused on combating misinformation and disinformation through advanced artificial intelligence and expert human analysis. With offices in the UK, US, and India, the company aims to enhance civic discourse and protect democratic processes by providing access to trustworthy information.

