The company operates on a collective insurance model, where customers contribute monthly based on the actual cost of claims from the entire community. This approach fosters shared responsibility and aligns the interests of both insurer and insured. Laka offers bicycle insurance, coverage for cycling accessories, and a no depreciation policy, ensuring customers receive the full value of their claims. Their services include a fully digital claims process and flexible subscription options, allowing customers to adjust their coverage as needed.

Laka primarily serves cyclists and users of e-bikes and cargo bikes, appealing to those who value a fair, usage-based insurance system. The company has gained recognition as an award-winning provider in the green mobility sector and has raised $10.4 million in Series B funding to support its growth.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/112.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'laka', null), ('1018', 'LHV', 'LHV Bank Limited', 'https://lhv.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lhvbank/', 'LHV Bank, founded in 1999 and headquartered in Tallinn, Estonia, is a prominent financial institution that transitioned from an investment union to a full-service universal bank in 2009. As a subsidiary of AS LHV Group, which is publicly traded on the Nasdaq Tallinn Stock Exchange, LHV Bank offers a wide range of financial services to private individuals, small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), and institutional investors.

