The company offers a range of complete and digestible meals for dogs, including low-carbon recipes and Europe’s first complete vegetarian fresh dog meal. In 2024, Butternut Box expanded its offerings to include fresh cat food under the brand Marro. Committed to sustainability, Butternut Box is a certified B Corporation, reflecting its dedication to environmental and social responsibility. The company operates a manufacturing facility in the UK and is expanding its production capacity in Poland, serving multiple markets across Europe. For every new customer, Butternut Box donates a meal to a dog in need, reinforcing its commitment to social impact.', 'The company rarely sponsors, and usually do only for hard-to-fill tech roles. We have excluded any that definitely cannot be.', '3', '14', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/251.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'butternutbox', null), ('1064', 'Optimove', 'Optimove UK Ltd', 'https://www.optimove.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/optimove/', 'Optimove is a privately held company that specializes in Relationship Marketing software as a service (SaaS). Founded in 2009 and based in Tel Aviv, Israel, it has additional offices in London and New York City. The company employs over 500 people and serves more than 1,200 brands across various industries, including retail, eCommerce, travel, gaming, and financial services.

