The company operates a sophisticated SaaS platform that automates balance sheet optimization for financial institutions, including banks and institutional investors. Capitolis offers solutions such as Tear Ups/Compressions to reduce capital requirements, Novations for efficient position transfers, and the Ionic platform for creating new investment opportunities. Additionally, it features a Capital Marketplace that connects banks with institutional investors, facilitating the origination and distribution of financial products. Capitolis also provides Portfolio Optimization solutions to help clients manage regulatory concerns and enhance financial efficiency.

With a strong client base that includes major global banks like Barclays, Citi, and Morgan Stanley, Capitolis is recognized for its innovative approach and has been listed among CNBC''s World''s Top Fintech Companies for three consecutive years.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/287.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'embed', null), ('1066', 'SigTech', 'SIG Technologies Limited', 'https://sigtech.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sigtechltd/', 'SigTech is a technology company that specializes in creating custom AI agents for financial institutions, including asset managers and banks. Their main product, MAGIC (Multi-Agent Generative Investment Copilots), automates complex workflows in capital markets, significantly reducing the time required for tasks that typically take analysts a full day to complete, down to about 15 minutes. These AI agents are tailored for each client, utilizing real case studies and inductive learning, while ensuring regulatory compliance through a human-in-the-loop design.

The company focuses on enhancing various financial workflows such as deal sourcing, commercial loan underwriting, market research synthesis, investor relations reporting, and compliance checking. SigTech aims to transform analysts into AI-augmented experts, improving productivity and compliance across the board. Their clients primarily consist of financial institutions seeking automation and AI-driven solutions to boost operational efficiency in capital markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/348.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1067', 'Masabi', 'Masabi Limited', 'https://www.masabi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/masabi/', 'Masabi Ltd. is a British technology company founded in 2001 and based in London, with additional offices in New York, Boston, Denver, and Cluj. The company specializes in fare collection services for public transport systems globally, utilizing a Fare Payments-as-a-Service (FPaaS) model to provide scalable and cost-effective ticketing solutions.

Masabi''s flagship product, the Justride Platform, supports various ticketing methods, including mobile apps, smart cards, and contactless payments. The Justride SDK allows integration of Masabi''s technology into third-party applications, enhancing user access to transit services. Additionally, the Justride Validator facilitates contactless tap-and-ride ticketing, making it accessible for transit operators of all sizes. Masabi serves over 60 clients worldwide, including major transit authorities in cities like Boston, London, and New York, and has been recognized for its innovative contributions to fare collection.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/14.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'masabi', null), ('1068', 'Atlassian', 'Atlassian (UK) Operations Limited', 'https://www.atlassian.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/atlassian/', 'Atlassian is a global software company founded in 2002 in Sydney, Australia, by Mike Cannon-Brookes and Scott Farquhar. Initially starting as a bootstrapped startup, it has grown into a significant player in software development and team collaboration, now publicly traded on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol "TEAM."

The company specializes in software tools that enhance project management, software development, and team collaboration. Its flagship product, Jira, is widely used for project and issue tracking. Other key offerings include Confluence, a team collaboration platform, Trello, a visual project management application, and Opsgenie, an incident management platform. Atlassian also features the Atlassian Marketplace, which provides a variety of third-party apps and integrations to enhance its products'' functionality. The company focuses on supporting agile development and improving productivity for teams across various industries.', 'The company can offer sponsorship and evaluates whether to on a case-by-case basis.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/490.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'lever', 'atlassian', null), ('1069', 'TransferRoom', 'Transferroom Ltd', 'https://www.transferroom.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/transferroom-ltd/', 'TransferRoom is a UK-based online marketplace that enhances the professional football transfer market by connecting over 800 clubs and more than 550 agencies worldwide. The platform facilitates direct communication and transactions, allowing users to engage without intermediaries. With over 7,500 successful deals and a revenue of approximately $5.9 million, TransferRoom employs around 80 people.

The platform provides live market intelligence, player availability, pricing, and contract data to football clubs, agents, and players. It helps club executives reduce costs and improve cash flow by offering direct access to decision-makers and reliable market insights. Players can compare their statistics and monitor their market value, while agents and clubs benefit from a network that enables quick feedback and better decision-making. TransferRoom''s core product integrates essential data and communication tools to streamline the transfer process and empower users in the competitive football landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/201.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'teamtailor', 'transferroom', null), ('1070', 'Illuminet', 'Illuminet Solutions Limited', 'https://illuminet.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/illuminet/', 'Illuminet is a global business efficiency company based in Poole, England, specializing in IT transformation, automation, and artificial intelligence services. Founded in 2009, the company has a team of around 118 employees and has successfully completed over 500 projects across 66 countries. Illuminet offers a wide range of services, including technology consultancy, IT architecture, data sciences, software engineering, and cloud engineering.

