Overall, Touchlab Limited is committed to advancing robotic systems through innovative haptic solutions, primarily serving clients in the United Kingdom.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2507c749-b0ab-4a81-95a4-5561453df63d.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1161', 'TeamSportz', 'TeamSportz Group Ltd', 'https://www.teamsportz.pro/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/teamsportz/', 'TeamSportz is an innovative sports AI platform that enables athletes, teams and sport academies to improve their performance and understanding of the game whilst enhancing health and wellbeing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ec0100c0-bb61-4ca1-a568-b790be8d4081.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1162', 'Veremark', 'Veremark Ltd', 'https://www.veremark.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/veremark/', 'Veremark is a global background screening and verification company based in London, England. Founded in 2018, it operates in over 180 countries, providing a wide range of pre-employment checks and background screening services. Veremark''s mission is to help organizations make faster and more informed hiring decisions through reliable and transparent solutions.

The company offers over 40 types of background checks, including employment history verification, education verification, criminal record checks, identity verification, and social media screening. A notable product is Verepass, a digital credential platform that allows candidates to retain verified background check results for future job applications. Veremark''s services are designed to support various industries, including fintech, technology, HR, and professional services, catering to businesses of all sizes from startups to large enterprises. The company emphasizes compliance with global data protection regulations and integrates seamlessly with existing HR workflows.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '10', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/39e90faf-8669-4e67-9307-7dbc772d787e.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'veremark', null), ('1163', 'Pollinate', 'Pollinate International Limited', 'https://www.pollinate.global/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pollinateint/', 'Pollinate is a London-based fintech company founded in 2017. It specializes in providing a white-label, cloud-based digital experience platform for banks, aimed at enhancing services for small and medium-sized businesses (SMBs). The company partners with leading banks globally, including NatWest Group, National Australia Bank, Truist, Fiserv, and Mastercard, operating on a B2B model to build a global network.

The core product is a platform that integrates with banks'' existing systems, offering SMB clients a unified dashboard for managing various business functions. Key features include merchant services, payment processing, digital onboarding, loyalty programs, marketing tools, and business insights from transaction data. This platform empowers SMBs with access to services typically available only to larger corporations. Pollinate generates revenue by offering this platform-as-a-service (PaaS) to financial institutions, providing them with a competitive edge in the market. The company also has operations in North America, with an office in Charlotte, North Carolina.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/571ac6d6-d6ce-4fff-b31e-d1d439c6ed97.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1164', 'Sprout', 'Sprout.ai Limited', 'https://sprout.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sproutai/', 'Sprout.ai is an artificial intelligence company based in London, founded in 2018. It specializes in AI-driven claims automation and fraud detection specifically for the insurance industry. The company has raised $20.12 million in funding and operates globally, with a team across three continents and nine countries.

The Sprout.ai platform includes four main components: extraction of data using patented OCR technology, enrichment of claims with contextual data, policy checking through natural language processing, and decisioning with AI models that provide real-time recommendations. The platform is designed to reduce claim settlement times significantly, addressing the needs of customers who require faster resolutions. Sprout.ai''s technology is configurable for various insurance lines and integrates seamlessly with existing insurer tools, enhancing operational efficiency and customer satisfaction.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e9637643-56df-4113-b6f8-77febb0371a0.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'sprout', null), ('1165', 'SymTerra', 'Keamore Limited', 'https://www.symterra.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/symterra/', 'SymTerra is a UK-based technology startup founded in March 2021 by Sarah Crawley and John Ryan. With over 25 years of combined experience in construction site management and project management, they created a digital communication platform tailored for the construction industry. This platform addresses communication challenges by enabling easy and intuitive collaboration among multiple contractors on the same project.

The core offering of SymTerra is an integrated communication platform that allows clients, contractors, and subcontractors to document work through images and videos, share information instantly, and manage supply chains and documentation digitally. It acts as a Building Information Modelling (BIM) pipeline, enhancing project management and communication while reducing delays and rework costs. SymTerra has grown to a team of 15 employees and has built a client portfolio managing over £5 billion worth of construction and infrastructure projects, including notable clients like Thames Water, MTR, and Balfour Beatty.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2351f0bd-8a32-49b7-bc7e-04f4b14a5122.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1166', 'Concrete4Change', 'Concrete4Change Ltd', 'https://www.concrete4change.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/concrete4change-ltd/', 'Concrete4Change is a research and development company dedicated to decarbonizing the cement and concrete industry. Founded by Dr. Michael Wise and Dr. Sid Pourfalah, the company focuses on developing technology that permanently sequesters CO2 into concrete, significantly reducing its environmental impact. Their innovative approach captures CO2 from flue gas emissions and combines it with calcium waste to create a reactive calcium carbonate additive. This additive allows concrete manufacturers to reduce cement content by up to 20%, resulting in stronger, lower-cost concrete with lower embodied carbon emissions.

The company collaborates with concrete manufacturers and industry stakeholders to pilot and scale their technology, ensuring practical adoption in the construction sector. Concrete4Change is transitioning to a product sales model that emphasizes cost reduction and performance benefits for concrete producers. Their culture promotes merit, excellence, and continuous learning, positioning them as a key player in advancing sustainable concrete solutions globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/337c9529-e1e6-4f6b-af46-9d0c5a0029c0.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1168', 'KeyNest', 'KeyNest Services Limited', 'https://keynest.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/keynest/', 'KeyNest is a key management company founded in 2016 by Marc and Florian, two Airbnb hosts. The company aims to simplify and secure key exchange and storage for property managers, Airbnb hosts, estate agents, and other clients across multiple countries. KeyNest operates a network of over 34,000 partner locations, known as KeyNest Points, throughout the UK and Europe. These locations include newsagents, cafés, taxi offices, and automated lockers, providing flexible and convenient access to keys.

KeyNest offers two main services: KeyNest Points, which securely hold keys for short-term rental hosts and property managers, and KeyNest Cloud, a smart key tracking system designed for estate agents and property managers. The cloud-based platform provides a centralized dashboard for real-time tracking of keys, enhancing accountability and organization. KeyNest integrates with leading Property Management Software and is the official Host Assist partner of Airbnb in the UK, allowing seamless key management for users. The company is recognized in the property and short-term rental industry and has received several awards for its innovative solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/58442a28-9c99-4850-af13-c767ad012857.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1169', 'Jiva.ai', 'Jiva.ai Limited', 'https://jiva.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jiva-ai-ltd/', 'Jiva.ai is a zero-code AI platform founded in 2019 and based in the United Kingdom. The company aims to democratize artificial intelligence by making advanced AI and data science accessible to users without coding skills. Its intuitive drag-and-drop interface allows for rapid development, testing, and deployment of AI solutions.

The platform supports various data types, including imaging, video, text, audio, and structured data, enabling users to generate multimodal insights. Jiva.ai utilizes generative AI, machine learning, and agentic AI techniques to help businesses create tailored AI agents and solutions. It serves multiple industries, with a significant focus on healthcare, where it partners with organizations like GE Healthcare and the NHS to develop AI-driven diagnostic tools and predictive models. Jiva.ai also caters to sectors such as finance, logistics, and retail, assisting organizations of all sizes in turning data into actionable intelligence.

Key features include zero-code AI development, next-generation AutoML for model training, multimodal AI capabilities, and strong data security measures. Jiva.ai operates as a Software as a Service (SaaS) platform, making it scalable and accessible for diverse business needs.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a6c17d69-3562-4854-848e-9886b91c2f94.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1170', 'Cera', 'Cera Care Limited', 'https://ceracare.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ceracare/', 'Allied Healthcare, now part of Cera, specializes in home-based healthcare services in the UK and Germany. As a key component of Cera, which is recognized as the largest HealthTech company in the UK, Allied Healthcare contributes to delivering approximately 2 million home healthcare visits each month. Cera, founded in 2015, has grown significantly, serving around 30 million people with a workforce of 10,000 employees.

The services offered include in-home care for older and vulnerable patients, telehealth solutions, and medication management through technology. Cera''s AI-driven tools help predict health deteriorations, enabling proactive care and reducing hospitalizations. The company primarily serves government entities, including NHS partnerships, as well as private insurers and individual patients. Cera has experienced remarkable growth, ranking in Deloitte’s Fast 50 for three consecutive years.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/52d27819-6dcf-4754-b0cd-f38909c66b41.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1171', 'Kidly', 'Kidly Ltd', 'https://www.kidly.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kidly/', 'KIDLY is an online lifestyle store dedicated to children aged 0-5 years. Founded in 2016 by James Hart, the company is based in Leavesden, England. KIDLY offers a curated selection of quality, sustainable clothing, homewares, and toys, featuring its own KIDLY Label alongside products from other children''s brands. The focus is on providing stylish and practical items for parents and caregivers.

The company primarily targets parents and caregivers seeking high-quality, sustainable products for young children. KIDLY serves the e-commerce industry, providing a platform for customers to purchase a variety of children''s lifestyle products.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d2208795-fa09-4cba-9ac9-a70afc89c378.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1172', 'The Cheeky Panda', 'The Cheeky Panda Ltd', 'https://uk.cheekypanda.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-cheeky-panda/', 'The Cheeky Panda is a company based in London, UK, that specializes in sustainable products made from bamboo, the fastest-growing plant in the world. Founded in 2016 by Julie and Chris, the company became a certified B Corporation in July 2019, highlighting its commitment to environmental and social responsibility.

The Cheeky Panda offers a variety of bamboo-based products, including toilet paper, straws, and items for beauty and babies. Their mission focuses on reducing carbon emissions, minimizing plastic use, and saving trees through sustainable practices. The company operates in over 25 countries, targeting environmentally conscious consumers. They also engage customers with referral programs and loyalty rewards, such as "Panda points" for discounts on future purchases.

In addition to its product offerings, The Cheeky Panda partners with The World Land Trust to support conservation efforts, habitat restoration, and reforestation projects. This partnership reflects their dedication to creating a sustainable future for generations to come.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2cb0c3fb-8b96-4b6e-aa3f-9ef349410b55.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1173', 'Genflow', 'Genflow Ltd', 'https://genflow.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/genflow/', 'Genflow is a global creator company based in London, founded in 2016 by Shan Hanif. The company specializes in helping content creators monetize their audiences and build their brands. It offers a range of services, including design, production, distribution, content creation, marketing, and creator management, positioning itself as a leader in the creator economy.

With an audience-first approach, Genflow collaborates with creators who collectively reach over 250 million people worldwide. The company supports creators in launching and scaling their product brands by providing in-house design, product development, and e-commerce store management. Genflow also operates the Genflow Creators Agency, which manages talent and facilitates partnerships with major global brands like Google, Nike, and Kylie Cosmetics. 

With offices in London, Beverly Hills, New York, and Dubai, Genflow reflects a strong global presence and a commitment to empowering creators in their business endeavors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/552818cb-b776-4687-baa3-d04537591b44.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'breezy', 'genflow', null), ('1174', 'Creoate', 'Creoate Limited', 'https://www.creoate.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/creoate/', 'CREOATE is a UK-based wholesale marketplace founded in 2020, designed to empower independent retailers and brands. It connects over 50,000 retailers across 10 countries, making it the largest B2B marketplace in the UK. The platform focuses on unique and sustainable products, offering a wide range of categories including homeware, gifting, fashion, and food. Retailers can filter products based on values such as eco-friendliness and minority ownership.

Co-founded by Ashley Horn and Fahad Khan, CREOATE aims to address challenges faced by independent retailers, such as limited financing and sourcing difficulties. The platform provides better payment terms, efficient logistics, and AI-driven tools for sales forecasting and inventory management. By facilitating direct trade between brands and retailers, CREOATE simplifies international wholesale transactions and supports small businesses in navigating the retail landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0837c467-a0da-43da-98b8-6e38cc59e339.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'breezy', 'creoate', null), ('1175', 'Rap Fame', 'Rap Tech Studios Ltd', 'https://rapfame.app/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rap-tech-studios-ltd-rap-fame-app/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1c390f7b-6553-4e7c-9118-e960258c7751.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1176', 'Dragonfly AI', 'Dragonfly Technology Solutions Limited', 'https://dragonflyai.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/dragonflyai-co/', 'Dragonfly AI is a London-based technology company founded in 2018, specializing in predictive analytics for optimizing creative content. The company utilizes neuroscience and artificial intelligence to analyze how audiences engage with visual content, helping clients enhance the effectiveness of their designs. Their technology is based on extensive visual neuroscience research conducted in collaboration with Queen Mary University of London.

The core offering is a visual analytics platform that provides real-time attention heatmaps and predictive reports, allowing clients to optimize their creative content across various formats. Dragonfly AI also offers a mobile app, a Chrome extension for real-time website testing, and an advanced studio experience called Studio 2.0 for testing multiple creative variants. Additionally, they provide a developer API for seamless integration and consulting services to help clients interpret data and implement insights effectively. The company serves notable clients in consumer packaged goods and digital marketing, helping them streamline creative processes and enhance their marketing strategies.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/61be01b4-8fd6-42fe-a571-7d22da93d221.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1177', 'Sauce Shop', 'Lacehouse Kitchen Limited', 'https://www.sauceshop.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sauceshop/', 'Sauce Shop is a UK-based company founded in 2014 in Nottingham by Pam and James. The company specializes in crafting high-quality, natural sauces made in small batches. Their diverse product range includes hot sauces, BBQ sauces, ketchups, mayonnaises, cooking sauces, and seasonings, featuring over 30 distinct flavors. Sauce Shop emphasizes the use of real, fresh ingredients, avoiding artificial additives and added water to create intense flavors.

Starting from a home kitchen, Sauce Shop has grown into one of the UK’s largest sauce producers, producing over 60,000 bottles per week. The company is committed to sustainability, using 100% recyclable glass packaging sourced within the UK. Their products have received significant recognition, including 39 Great Taste Awards since 2016. Sauce Shop''s sauces are available nationwide in major UK supermarkets and appeal to cooking enthusiasts seeking bold, natural flavors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7e4deac1-3044-40fb-9fe0-dcde6bda3c0f.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1178', 'Picnic', 'Picnic Media Limited', 'https://www.picnic.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/picnic-io/', 'Picnic is a grocery delivery company based in Amersfoort, the Netherlands. Founded in 2015, it combines modern technology with the traditional concept of the milkman to deliver fresh groceries directly to customers'' homes. The company operates a fleet of small electric vehicles, focusing on sustainability by minimizing CO2 emissions and reducing inner-city traffic congestion.

With over 1,000,000 customers in the Netherlands and an expansion into Germany, Picnic has invested in automated fulfillment centers to enhance its delivery capabilities. The company offers a wide range of fresh groceries, including everyday essentials and household items, catering primarily to families and individuals seeking a convenient and eco-friendly grocery delivery service.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9b1643bf-6bd2-4622-8fa7-b1b31176f4c0.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1179', 'myenergi', 'Myenergi Ltd', 'https://www.myenergi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/myenergi-ltd/', 'GivEnergy is a leading provider of residential battery storage systems in the UK, focused on empowering energy freedom through accessible energy management solutions. Founded in 2018 and based in Bangor, UK, the company designs and manufactures a range of products, including inverters, battery systems, electric vehicle chargers, and energy management software. These products create an integrated ecosystem that helps customers manage their energy use, store energy from various sources, and optimize consumption.

GivEnergy serves residential households, commercial businesses, and community low-carbon housing projects, with scalable solutions to meet diverse energy storage needs. The company has achieved over 5,000 installations per month, enabling customers to significantly reduce energy costs and carbon emissions. GivEnergy is committed to environmental responsibility, operating its headquarters on renewable energy and supporting community initiatives like the GivEnergy 850 Learning Lab, which encourages underprivileged students to pursue careers in net zero technologies. With rapid growth and plans for a new manufacturing facility, GivEnergy is positioned as a key player in the renewable energy sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/be3eacd4-0840-4be0-998a-68c3ef237483.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1180', 'Uhubs', 'Upskillhubs Ltd', 'https://www.uhubs.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/uhubs/', 'Uhubs is a company founded in 2019, dedicated to addressing the global skills crisis in sales. Co-founded by Ash Ali, an experienced entrepreneur in B2B sales and marketing, and Matt, who has a background in EY, Uhubs aims to provide scalable, tech-enabled solutions for sales capability assessments. The company is registered as UHUB LTD in Milton Keynes, UK.

Uhubs offers a platform designed to assess and enhance sales team capabilities. Their services include sales capability assessments, customized solutions for improving sales performance, and process optimization to define and replicate best practices. The platform integrates seamlessly with CRM systems, providing businesses with tools to evaluate skills and visualize progress while demonstrating the return on investment of their initiatives. The pricing model is flexible, scaling based on team size and the number of assessments needed, making it suitable for businesses of all sizes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c6c67314-88bf-400a-9e96-6b50928badbd.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1181', 'AeroCloud', 'AeroCloud Systems Limited', 'https://aerocloudsystems.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/aerocloud-systems/', 'AeroCloud is a cloud-native airport management technology company that offers intelligent and scalable solutions tailored for airports of all sizes. Founded to modernize airport operations, AeroCloud utilizes advanced AI, machine learning, and computer vision to provide real-time insights and automation, enhancing operational efficiency and passenger experience.

Since entering the US market in 2017, AeroCloud has partnered with over 70 airports globally, including major hubs like London Luton and Minneapolis St Paul. Their key offerings include the Intelligent Airport Operations System, which integrates various airport functions for improved performance, and passenger processing solutions that enhance throughput and flexibility. AeroCloud Optic is a notable innovation, providing comprehensive monitoring of passenger flow from kerb to gate.

AeroCloud emphasizes a collaborative partnership with its clients, focusing on responsive support and co-creation. Their modular platform allows airports to choose components that fit their needs, making it adaptable and cost-effective. With a commitment to innovation and operational success, AeroCloud is positioned as a leader in the airport management technology space.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3b88ad64-1884-400f-9e2d-77441aaa939d.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1182', 'Tumelo', 'Tumelo Ltd', 'https://www.tumelo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tumelo/', 'Tumelo is a global fintech company that focuses on enhancing transparency and engagement in shareholder voting. Founded at Cambridge University by Will Goodwin, Georgia Stewart, and Ben King, Tumelo aims to empower investors by providing clear visibility into the companies they own and enabling effective exercise of their voting rights.

The company''s main product, ProxySphere, is a pass-through voting platform designed for both institutional and retail investors. It offers a modern interface that allows users to choose from various voting policies or vote on individual proposals. ProxySphere is flexible and includes features like proposal-theme filtering, which helps investors focus on important issues such as climate change and corporate governance. Tumelo''s mission is to ensure that all investors can utilize their voting power, fostering a more transparent and responsible investment ecosystem. 

Tumelo serves a range of clients, including major financial institutions like Legal & General Investment Management and Fidelity International. The company is recognized for its innovative approach to shareholder voting and has received media attention from outlets such as The Times, Forbes, and Bloomberg. Tumelo also prioritizes security, holding ISO 27001 accreditation and implementing robust security practices.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/42ee26d9-44e8-4946-858b-b89aa846418c.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'tumelo', null), ('1183', 'The Francis Crick Institute', 'The Francis Crick Institute Limited', 'https://www.crick.ac.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-francis-crick-institute/', 'The Francis Crick Institute is a prominent biomedical research center located in London. Established in 2010 and officially opened in 2016, it was formed through a partnership involving the Medical Research Council, Cancer Research UK, the Wellcome Trust, University College London, King''s College London, and Imperial College London. Named after the renowned scientist Francis Crick, the institute aims to enhance the understanding of human biology and disease through integrated research across various scientific disciplines.

The institute conducts extensive biomedical research across more than 20 topics, including biochemistry and tumor biology. Its state-of-the-art facility, completed in 2016, promotes collaboration among scientists from diverse fields. The Francis Crick Institute also provides research collaborations, training, and career development opportunities for scientists, serving a wide range of stakeholders, including academic researchers and clinical scientists.', 'Sponsorship can be offered on case-by-case basis.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/80c8e2ef-4372-4121-bd93-1140d775011f.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1184', 'National Grid', 'National Grid plc', 'https://www.nationalgrid.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/national-grid/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0dbbea6a-0aed-49e4-96ca-57521ab9e03b.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'national', null), ('1185', 'Medivet', 'Medivet Group Limited', 'https://www.medivetgroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/medivet-group-limited/', 'Medivet is a prominent veterinary care provider established in 1987, primarily operating in the UK, Germany, Spain, and France. With over 500 branches and 27 24-hour veterinary centers, Medivet serves a community of more than 1,500 veterinarians through a unique co-ownership model. This allows vets to become equity partners in their clinics while enjoying clinical freedom and extensive support from the network.

The company offers a wide range of small animal veterinary services, including routine care, advanced surgeries, and diagnostic technologies. Medivet employs a "hub and spoke" system, enabling local clinics to access specialist expertise and treatments through its nationwide network. Additionally, Medivet provides comprehensive laboratory services, supported by a team of expert pathologists. The company also features a Healthcare Plan designed to help pet owners manage the costs of essential pet healthcare, allowing clients to save an average of £225 annually.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dc652857-2b12-42a1-a479-3192eb3043d1.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'medivet/MedivetCareers', null), ('1186', 'Hikvision', 'Hikvision UK Limited', 'https://www.hikvision.com/uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hikvision-uk-&-ireland/', 'Hikvision, officially known as Hangzhou Hikvision Digital Technology Co., Ltd., is a prominent global provider of video surveillance products and integrated security solutions. Founded in 2001 in Hangzhou, China, the company is publicly traded on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. Hikvision specializes in developing, manufacturing, and marketing advanced video surveillance equipment, including network cameras, digital video recorders (DVRs), network video recorders (NVRs), and video management software.

The company has expanded its offerings to include AI-powered Internet of Things (AIoT) technologies, enhancing its video surveillance capabilities with intelligent features. Hikvision serves various sectors such as smart cities, transportation, education, healthcare, retail, and government security. With operations in over 170 countries and regions, Hikvision emphasizes research and development, investing over 7% of its annual revenue into innovation. In 2023, the company reported revenues of approximately $10.5 billion, showcasing its strong position in the global video surveillance industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/08981012-9056-4de6-ab0b-9b392d7f38dc.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1187', 'Oxa', 'Oxa Autonomy Limited', 'https://oxa.tech/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oxauniversalautonomy/', 'Oxa is a UK-based company that specializes in autonomous vehicle software, enabling vehicles to operate autonomously anywhere and at any time through their Universal Autonomy™ concept. Founded by Paul Newman and Ingmar Posner, Oxa has grown from the Oxford University RobotCar UK project into a global leader with over 400 employees.

The company offers an autonomy software platform that supports self-driving technology across various industries, focusing on commercial and industrial applications. Their solutions include virtual testing environments, vehicle-driving software, and cloud-based management tools, tailored for sectors such as airports, retirement communities, ports, and mining. Oxa has a strong track record of innovation, including the first commercial deployment of their Oxa Driver software and Europe''s first zero-occupancy autonomous vehicle journey on public roads. 

With significant funding, including a $140 million Series C round in 2023, Oxa is committed to advancing safety and operational efficiency in the deployment of autonomous vehicles. Their comprehensive platform and services make them a trusted partner for businesses looking to integrate self-driving technology into their operations.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3d136388-c5be-43a8-8bdb-20b18d04e5aa.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'oxa', null), ('1188', 'Orbex', 'Orbital Express Launch Limited', 'https://orbex.space/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/orbital-express-launch-limited/', 'Orbex, officially known as Orbital Express Launch Ltd., is a UK-based aerospace company founded in 2015. Headquartered in Forres, Scotland, with additional facilities in Denmark and subsidiaries in Germany, Orbex specializes in low-cost, sustainable orbital launch services for the small satellite industry. The company is recognized as one of Europe’s leading private launch service providers.

The flagship product, Orbex Prime, is a micro-launch vehicle designed for small satellite launches. It utilizes renewable bio-propane fuel, significantly reducing the carbon footprint compared to traditional rocket fuels. The rocket features innovative technologies such as 3D-printed engines and carbon fiber structures, enhancing both performance and sustainability. Orbex emphasizes environmental responsibility by minimizing space debris and maximizing reusability.

Orbex offers a flexible core launch service with supporting services to simplify the launch process for customers. The company plans to operate primarily from the Sutherland Space Hub in northern Scotland, a carbon-neutral spaceport, and may expand to other locations in the future. Orbex serves small satellite operators seeking reliable and environmentally conscious launch solutions, supported by funding from public and private sectors.', 'The company can offer sponsorship and relocation support for the majority of its roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/37ef6ac8-b929-4aba-a851-94cb18c87bd9.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1189', 'NavLive', 'NavLive Limited', 'https://www.navlive.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/navlive/', 'NavLive helps architects, developers, and construction firms to win clients faster with instant 2D/3D building models, RICS-grade 1:100 surveys, and direct Scan-to-BIM integration. 

