With NavLive, you start faster, deliver sooner, and win more contracts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/aa097f82-0232-43a7-9e9e-1936727f8b1f.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1190', 'Studio Gobo', 'Keywords Studios plc', 'https://www.studiogobo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/studio-gobo/', 'Studio Gobo is a UK-based interactive design and game development studio founded in 2011 by four industry veterans. Headquartered in Brighton, East Sussex, with additional locations in Hove and Zurich, the company has grown to around 110-125 employees and generates approximately $20 million in revenue.

The studio specializes in AAA character-action game development and co-development support for high-profile video game projects. They emphasize a collaborative, team-based approach that values creativity, equality, and transparency. Studio Gobo has worked on notable titles such as LEGO Horizon Adventures, Hogwarts Legacy, and For Honor, collaborating with major publishers like Sony Interactive Entertainment and Guerrilla Games. Their services include game development, interactive design, and research and innovation through a dedicated lab in Zurich.', 'For successful candidates, the company will pay for visa costs and provide a relocation allowance.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8ad3649b-225f-4051-b8c5-43317077cb41.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'breezy', 'studio', null), ('1191', 'LabGenius', 'LabGenius Ltd', 'https://labgeni.us/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/labgenius/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8f486fa3-f562-4d52-9308-6f2f3885f31e.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1192', 'Flagstone', 'Flagstone Group Limited', 'https://www.flagstoneim.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/flagstone-group-ltd/', 'Flagstone is a UK-based financial technology company that offers a high-interest cash deposit savings platform. It aims to help individuals, businesses, and charities manage, protect, and grow their cash savings efficiently. Users can access and open savings accounts from over 60 UK banks through a single application, benefiting from exclusive and market-leading interest rates. The platform is available to UK savers aged 18 and over, with a minimum deposit of £10,000, and also caters to international clients, including corporates, funds, and trusts.

Flagstone provides several key services, including savings account aggregation, which allows users to spread deposits across multiple accounts to maximize interest earnings. The platform also helps users maximize protection under the UK’s Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS), ensuring eligible cash deposits are protected up to £85,000 per client, per banking group. With features like a cash deposits calculator and easy online management, Flagstone simplifies the savings process while maintaining a focus on security and efficiency.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8ae6449d-fc7c-4bae-abca-74c6849544ce.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'flagstone', null), ('1193', 'm3ter', 'M3ter Limited', 'https://www.m3ter.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/m3ter/', 'm3ter is a technology company that specializes in usage-based billing software for mid-size to large B2B software companies. Founded in 2020 by John Griffin and Griffin Parry, the company focuses on automating and optimizing billing and revenue accounting workflows. Their platform simplifies complex pricing models, helping software scale-ups eliminate billing errors and reduce compliance risks.

The core offering is a usage-based billing platform that includes metering, rating infrastructure, and integration capabilities with systems like Salesforce and SAP. This platform allows companies to configure and automate billing for various pricing models, including subscription and metered usage. m3ter''s software automates the entire quote-to-cash process, enabling rapid product rollouts and providing near real-time visibility into customer usage and billing data.

m3ter serves software scale-ups and technology companies with complex pricing needs, supporting their transition to usage-based pricing models. Notable clients include Onfido, Sift, and ClickHouse, which have all benefited from improved revenue recovery, shortened billing cycles, and enhanced customer self-service options.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ed8cfa92-ba79-44cc-8fbd-a841161c9ac8.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1194', 'Puraffinity', 'Puraffinity Limited', 'https://www.puraffinity.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/puraffinity/', 'Puraffinity is a green technology company founded in 2015 as a spinout from Imperial College London. The company specializes in designing and manufacturing advanced adsorbent materials aimed at removing PFAS (per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances) from water. Puraffinity provides sustainable water treatment solutions that address environmental challenges related to PFAS contamination across various sectors, including residential, commercial, industrial, municipal, and environmental services.

The flagship product, Puratech, features a novel adsorbent media designed with tailored molecular groups that enhance its ability to selectively trap and remove a wide range of PFAS compounds from water. This innovative approach offers improved efficiency compared to traditional technologies like granular activated carbon and ion exchange. Puraffinity aims to provide PFAS-free water to 1 billion people by 2030, focusing on regulatory compliance and minimal environmental impact. The company operates from London, UK, and is currently in the Series A funding stage, led by CEO Vincent Caillaud and a dedicated executive team.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bf79a8bc-ac89-4403-8faf-94174a5c1e5f.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1195', 'Seatfrog', 'Seatfrog Ops Limited', 'https://seatfrog.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/seatfrog/', 'Seatfrog is a London-based technology company founded in 2016 by Iain Griffin and Dirk Stewart. The company aims to enhance the train travel experience by making premium seating more accessible and affordable through its innovative mobile app platform. This app allows standard ticket holders to bid on or purchase upgrades to first-class seats in real time, often at lower prices than standard first-class fares.

The platform integrates seamlessly with train operators'' systems, providing live inventory updates and dynamic bidding until the train''s departure. It also enables users to switch and purchase train tickets while offering real-time notifications about available upgrades and seat availability across over 2,400 destinations. Seatfrog''s technology benefits both passengers and rail operators, increasing premium seat occupancy and generating additional revenue. The app is available on iOS and Android, catering to travelers looking for comfort and flexibility in their journeys.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1089ce29-738b-400f-8bbe-6258df52a94e.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1196', 'Natter', 'Tenth Chapter Limited', 'https://www.trynatter.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lets-natter/', 'Natter is a UK-based technology company that offers a virtual conversation platform designed to enhance communication in hybrid and remote work settings. Founded by former executives from Uber, BBC, and Google, Natter aims to create inclusive interactions by replicating the informal "watercooler conversation" experience. The platform connects employees across various locations and levels, facilitating timed video discussions known as "natters."

Natter''s core product is a web-based tool that uses intelligent matching algorithms to pair employees with peers and leaders they may not typically engage with. This promotes diversity and inclusion within organizations. The platform also employs advanced data analytics to gather and analyze conversation data in real time, providing actionable insights and engagement metrics quickly. Natter prioritizes security and privacy, ensuring confidential feedback through robust measures like AES-256 encryption and GDPR compliance. 

The company has partnered with notable organizations such as University College London, WeWork, Kraft Heinz, and World Remit, reflecting its commitment to improving employee engagement and inclusivity in the evolving workplace landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/161e30cf-d68e-4c7e-9900-a988eb31c36f.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1197', 'Infinitopes', 'Infinitopes Limited', 'https://www.infinitopes.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/infinitopes/', 'Infinitopes is an integrated cancer biotechnology company based in Oxford, United Kingdom. Founded in 2021 as a spinout from the University of Oxford, the company focuses on developing next-generation immune medicines aimed at improving the lives of cancer patients. Their innovative approach targets cancer metastases through precision immunotherapy, utilizing their proprietary Precision Immunomics™ technology for unbiased identification of tumor-specific antigens.

The company’s core product pipeline includes precision cancer vaccines designed to prevent the recurrence of life-threatening metastases. Infinitopes combines advanced antigen discovery with effective vaccine vector technologies to stimulate durable T-cell immune responses. They are currently advancing a Phase I/IIa clinical trial for early-stage oesophageal cancer, marking a significant step in validating their vaccine candidates. Infinitopes collaborates with various partners in oncology and immunology, including academic institutions and funding bodies, to enhance cancer care and patient outcomes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/739f7856-3867-49e4-a5eb-9836bc928e47.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1198', 'Nomios', 'Nomios UK&I Limited', 'https://www.nomios.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/nomios-uk-i/', 'Nomios UK&I is a cybersecurity and cloud network specialist based in Basingstoke, UK, with an additional office in Dublin, Ireland. As part of the Nomios Group, the company focuses on designing, securing, and managing digital infrastructures for organizations of all sizes. They emphasize enterprise-grade security and network integrity, serving as a trusted partner for businesses undergoing digital transformation.

The company offers a range of services, including cybersecurity solutions that implement advanced security architectures, cloud networking to support secure connectivity, and managed services for 24/7 monitoring and incident response. Their professional services provide strategic consulting and tailored project rollouts. Nomios UK&I collaborates with over 40 vendors, including Palo Alto Networks and Cisco, to deliver integrated, vendor-agnostic solutions. With a global client base of over 2,000, they cater to highly regulated industries that require complex network and security solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '7', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3890f0a7-8b15-4242-8ded-d9b695905965.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'nomios', null), ('1199', 'Acurable', 'Acurable Ltd', 'https://acurable.com/en-us', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/acurable/', 'Acurable is a medical technology company founded in 2016 and based in London, with an additional office in Seville, Spain. The company specializes in developing wearable medical devices for home use, focusing on non-invasive, continuous monitoring and diagnostics for respiratory conditions, particularly sleep apnea.

The flagship product line, AcuPebble®, utilizes patented wearable acoustic sensor technology to capture physiological signals from the body. These signals are processed using advanced algorithms to provide diagnostic outputs. Acurable''s AcuPebble SA100 device is designed for the automated diagnosis of obstructive sleep apnea in adults, while the AcuPebble RE100 is intended for continuous monitoring in research settings. The devices have received regulatory approvals, including the CE mark for Europe and FDA 510(k) clearance for the USA.

Acurable''s research and development are conducted at its headquarters within the Imperial College White City Incubator, fostering a collaborative environment focused on scientific innovation. The company aims to enhance healthcare accessibility and patient-centric solutions through earlier detection and better management of chronic conditions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3b8becc8-0dbc-4a68-9e01-72046811bf19.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1200', 'Disperse', 'Disperse.io Ltd', 'https://www.disperse.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/disperse-io/', 'Disperse is a London-based technology company that specializes in artificial intelligence solutions for the construction industry. The company focuses on enhancing construction project delivery by providing a building productivity platform that automates progress tracking and issue detection on construction sites. This platform utilizes a combination of human expertise and AI, including 360-degree imaging and computer vision, to capture and analyze visual data in real time.

Disperse offers services such as site scanning and data capture, progress tracking for various construction components, and issue detection to help teams manage risks effectively. Their platform supports both 2D drawings and Building Information Modeling (BIM) workflows, catering to customers at different stages of digital maturity. Additionally, Disperse provides standardized reports through an intuitive user interface, facilitating better communication among project stakeholders.

With a team distributed across London, Oxford, Sarajevo, and Yerevan, Disperse is committed to innovating in construction technology. Their platform is currently in use on major construction projects in London and New York City, serving a diverse range of clients in the building sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c1ae0626-2ca0-4446-9771-3d7bda2f5eb3.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'breezyhr', 'disperse', null), ('1202', 'Eleven Therapeutics', 'Eleven Therapeutics (UK) Ltd', 'https://eleventx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/eleventx/', 'Eleven Therapeutics is a biotechnology company founded in 2020 that specializes in developing RNA-based therapeutics. The company combines advanced RNA biology, synthetic chemistry, and artificial intelligence to create a programmable approach to drug discovery. With collaborative hubs in Cambridge (UK), Boston (US), and Tel Aviv (Israel), Eleven Therapeutics leverages global scientific talent and partnerships with leading institutions, including the Vaccine Research Center at NIAID and Cambridge University.

The company focuses on creating precise therapeutics that target disease-causing genes, particularly in the area of respiratory diseases. Their innovative discovery engine utilizes DNA synthesis, high-throughput sequencing, and AI-driven algorithms to optimize RNA therapeutics for safety and effectiveness. Eleven Therapeutics is developing RNA interference (RNAi) therapeutics, including preclinical candidates like an intranasal siRNA targeting SARS-CoV-2. The team consists of diverse entrepreneur-scientists dedicated to advancing RNA therapeutics and addressing significant unmet medical needs.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4e735ff6-be57-4561-b42a-117b6e79ff3b.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'eleventx', null), ('1203', 'Zapp', 'Quick Commerce Limited', 'https://www.justzapp.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zappquickcommerce/', 'Zapp is a premium convenience delivery company based in London, UK, founded in 2020. It operates an instant grocery and convenience delivery app that serves hundreds of thousands of customers in the city. Zapp focuses on enhancing everyday life by providing rapid access to a curated selection of products, including daily essentials, luxury items, and pharmacy products.

The company utilizes advanced technology to anticipate customer needs, ensuring relevant products are available at the right time and place. Zapp offers 24/7 delivery, emphasizing speed and convenience for its premium, high-demand clientele. With plans for future expansion, Zapp aims to build an efficient on-demand supply chain in one of the world''s largest megacities. The company has raised over $300 million in funding, supported by notable investors, and is committed to innovation in the convenience retail market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '21', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ca04b9df-9ef3-414c-aebf-6713b1e65b53.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1204', 'Qatalog', 'Qatalog Ltd', 'https://qatalog.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/qatalog/', 'Qatalog is an AI-powered platform that focuses on improving knowledge management and process automation within organizations. Its mission is to simplify work by providing easy access to company knowledge and automating routine tasks. The platform integrates with various business tools and data sources, offering insights and automation to boost productivity.

Key features of Qatalog include a unified search bar for real-time information access, a permission-aware AI engine for secure data handling, and a centralized information hub for project-specific documents and updates. The platform also includes a goals feature that helps teams track progress and maintain transparency. Qatalog is designed to be versatile, catering to businesses looking to enhance their internal workflows and collaboration.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/75ea885d-b757-47a5-80d8-008c48abb457.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1205', 'Koru Kids', 'Koru Kids Ltd', 'https://www.korukids.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/korukids/', 'Koru Kids is a UK-based childcare company founded in 2016 by Rachel Carrell, with its headquarters in London. The company specializes in providing flexible, high-quality childcare solutions through vetted nannies and nanny shares, catering to the needs of busy modern families.

Koru Kids connects families with experienced, background-checked nannies for tailored childcare arrangements. Their services include nannies available for specific days and times, with pricing based on experience levels. The service fee covers various costs, including taxes, public liability insurance, and an initial setup fee for enhanced DBS checks and regulatory registrations. The company aims to simplify the childcare search process, making it easier for families to find nurturing care that prioritizes children''s emotional wellbeing and development.

With a team of around 60 employees and over $13 million in funding, Koru Kids serves families across London and the UK, offering flexible and trustworthy childcare alternatives to traditional nurseries. Their mission is to support families by enabling parents to pursue their careers while ensuring children receive attentive, quality care.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/98a5837d-cdaf-40a9-9c7b-a6aafed77dac.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'korukids', null), ('1206', 'Fat Llama', 'Fat Llama Limited', 'https://fatllama.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fatllamahq/', 'Fat Llama is a London-based peer-to-peer rental marketplace founded in 2016. The platform allows individuals to rent out items they own but do not use daily, as well as rent items they need temporarily. It offers a wide range of products, including power tools, cameras, and DJ equipment, promoting sustainable consumption through the sharing economy. Users can list items for free and retain 80% of the rental price, while Fat Llama manages insurance, payments, and user verification to ensure a secure rental experience.

The company was established by Chaz Englander, Rosie Dallas, and Owen Turner-Major, inspired by their own challenges in renting single-use items. In 2022, Fat Llama merged with Hygglo, expanding its reach beyond the UK. The platform serves both individuals and businesses, helping them monetize underutilized possessions or access items temporarily. Fat Llama has raised over $12 million in funding from notable investors and is led by CEO Ola Degerfors, focusing on product growth and customer success.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/881c1e6d-c66e-4f7c-a0a0-ff63169a84aa.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1207', 'Rekki', 'Rekki Ltd', 'https://rekki.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rekkiapp/', 'REKKI is a technology company focused on improving wholesale operations in the food and hospitality industry. Founded in 2016 by experienced restaurateurs and chefs, REKKI offers a mobile app and digital platform that connects restaurants with local suppliers, streamlining the ordering process and supply chain management.

The platform supports over 1,300 suppliers globally, enabling foodservice businesses to source ingredients efficiently. REKKI''s solutions integrate with more than 50 ERP and accounting systems, making it easy for clients to adopt and enhance their operations. With teams based in London, New York, Amsterdam, and Lisbon, REKKI combines industry expertise with technology to address the unique challenges faced by chefs and suppliers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6d42f29b-5982-4389-bddb-ad646798a947.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1208', 'Habito', 'Hey Habito Ltd', 'https://www.habito.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/habito-/', 'Habito is a UK-based FinTech company that specializes in digital mortgage services. Founded in 2016 and headquartered in Reading, it operates as an online mortgage broker and lender. Habito simplifies the home-buying process by offering a comprehensive platform that integrates mortgage advice, application, legal work, and property surveys into a seamless online experience.

The company provides free mortgage advice and a fully digital application process, earning revenue through commissions from lenders. Its offerings include Habito Plus, a full-service home-buying package, and Habito One, a unique mortgage product with long-term fixed-rate deals. Habito also offers a Mortgage in Principle service to strengthen buyers'' offers and specialized buy-to-let mortgage products for rental property investors. With a focus on technology, Habito uses advanced digital tools to analyze thousands of mortgage products in real-time, ensuring customers find the best deals efficiently. The company is dedicated to delivering a supportive customer experience, guided by qualified mortgage brokers and case managers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4e950058-862e-4127-919a-e41031673df3.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'habito', null), ('1209', 'lendinvest', 'Lendinvest Ltd', 'https://www.lendinvest.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lendinvest/', 'LendInvest is a prominent UK-based asset management platform that specializes in property finance. Founded to innovate the traditional property finance market, the company utilizes technology to deliver faster and more reliable financial solutions. LendInvest is publicly traded on the Alternative Investment Market (AIM) of the London Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol LINV.

The company offers a variety of mortgage products, including short-term mortgages for quick capital access, development mortgages for financing construction projects, and buy-to-let mortgages for landlords and property investors. LendInvest''s platform simplifies the mortgage application process, making it efficient for intermediaries, landlords, and developers to access capital. With significant funds under management and a focus on sustainability, LendInvest is committed to promoting responsible financial practices.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/98b157cb-d334-43ca-9841-52caa7e6fe7f.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1210', 'Digimarc', 'Evrythng Ltd', 'https://www.digimarc.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/digimarc/', 'Digimarc Corporation, founded in 1995 and based in Beaverton, Oregon, specializes in enterprise software and services focused on digital identification technologies. The company is known for its pioneering work in digital watermarking and serialized QR codes, which enhance product authenticity, prevent counterfeiting, and improve supply chain traceability across various industries, including apparel, consumer packaged goods, health and beauty, and automotive.

The company offers several key products, including its digital watermarking technology, which embeds invisible codes into images and packaging, and the Digimarc Barcode, an invisible barcode that enhances scanning efficiency without affecting product aesthetics. Additionally, Digimarc provides a digital product cloud platform for real-time digital identities and secure personal identification products through its subsidiary, Digimarc ID Systems, LLC. With a mission to create a more secure and interconnected world, Digimarc aims to improve sustainability and efficiency in supply chains while enhancing customer experiences.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8377448e-dcf7-4495-a298-a6c2fce8d366.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'lever', 'digimarc', null), ('1211', 'Freenow', 'Transopco UK Ltd', 'https://www.free-now.com/uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/freenow/', 'FREENOW is a prominent European mobility platform based in Hamburg, Germany. Founded in 2009 as mytaxi, it has evolved into a multi-mobility service provider operating in over 180 cities across nine European countries. FREENOW connects passengers with licensed taxi drivers and offers a variety of services, including private hire vehicles, carsharing, car rentals, e-scooters, e-bikes, and e-mopeds, all accessible through a single app.

With a customer base of over 14 million passengers and a network of more than 100,000 drivers, FREENOW is one of the largest mobility platforms in Europe. The company focuses on providing reliable, accessible, and sustainable urban transport solutions. It aims to modernize the taxi industry and promote the electrification of its vehicle fleet, investing over €100 million in sustainability initiatives. FREENOW collaborates with cities and communities to enhance urban mobility and reduce reliance on private cars.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f60e97d0-2df3-4a63-820f-1135dd72c5e1.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'freenow', null), ('1212', 'Pharmacy2U', 'Pharmacy2U Limited', 'https://www.pharmacy2u.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pharmacy2u/', 'Pharmacy2U Ltd is a British online pharmacy founded in 1999 by pharmacist Daniel Lee, based in Thorpe Park, Leeds. The company specializes in managing NHS repeat prescriptions and private prescriptions, delivering medications directly to patients'' homes through its in-house developed technology platform.

Pharmacy2U offers electronic management and dispensing of prescriptions, allowing patients to request repeat prescriptions online. It was a pioneer in the electronic transfer of prescriptions in the UK, integrating with numerous GP surgeries to facilitate this service. The company serves NHS patients needing repeat prescriptions and private customers looking for convenient online pharmacy services, emphasizing accessibility and technology in prescription management and delivery. 

Currently, Pharmacy2U is owned by private equity firm EPIC Investment Partners and continues to operate as an active private limited company.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/398b7eb1-dba2-431d-bc78-250016382eeb.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1213', 'Atticus', 'Assemble Technologies UK Ltd', 'https://www.atticus.tech/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/atticustech/', 'Atticus is a global technology company that specializes in fact-checking and verification software for critical documents. Their platform enhances collaboration and efficiency for teams working on regulated documents, including legal and financial disclosures. Atticus serves clients in the legal, corporate, and financial sectors, such as law firms, corporate governance professionals, and financial institutions.

The software automates the verification workflow, improving accuracy and reducing the time spent on fact-checking. Atticus supports a wide range of document types, including prospectuses, pleadings, and statutory reports. The company has raised approximately A$10.8 million in funding, with investments from notable firms like Blackbird Ventures and Skip Capital.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9dc3934f-de25-4906-b8a9-56775d1778c4.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'hibob', 'https://atticus.careers.hibob.com/api/job-ad', null), ('1215', 'Adzuna', 'Adzuna Limited', 'https://www.adzuna.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/adzuna/', 'Adzuna is a private company founded in April 2011 and based in London, UK. It operates as an internet-based job search engine that aggregates job advertisements from various sources, including large job boards and employer websites, into a single database. Adzuna aims to enhance the job search experience for users by providing a faster and more transparent way to find fulfilling employment.

The platform serves tens of millions of users monthly across 16 countries, including the UK, US, and Australia. Adzuna offers several tools, such as ValueMyCV, which helps users assess their CV''s market value, and an AI interview tool called "Prepper," designed to assist job seekers in preparing for interviews. Additionally, Adzuna provides salary statistics and labor market insights to help users make informed career decisions. The company also supports employers and recruiters with advertising and recruitment solutions, particularly following its acquisitions of Getwork and Seiza, which have expanded its capabilities in enterprise job search and social media recruitment.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0dd67af7-482c-42c6-a4be-9a5ff58655d3.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'adzuna', null), ('1216', 'WNS', 'WNS Global Services (UK)', 'https://www.wns.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wns-global-services/', 'WNS (Holdings) Limited is a global leader in business transformation and Business Process Management (BPM), based in Mumbai, India. The company serves over 700 clients across more than 10 industries, employing over 62,000 people in delivery centers located in countries such as India, the Philippines, Poland, Romania, South Africa, the UK, and the US.

WNS offers a wide range of BPM solutions that integrate industry expertise with AI-powered platforms and advanced analytics. Their core services include customer experience management, finance and accounting outsourcing, human resource solutions, procurement, research and analytics, governance, risk and compliance, supply chain management, and technology-enabled business transformation. The company focuses on various sectors, including banking, insurance, healthcare, retail, manufacturing, and life sciences, partnering with clients to enhance operations and drive digital transformation. 

With a client-centric approach, WNS combines traditional Business Process Outsourcing (BPO) and Knowledge Process Outsourcing (KPO) services to support both operational efficiency and strategic decision-making. The company is dedicated to helping clients innovate and adapt in a dynamic business landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4a3899c3-7c33-4f19-8c7e-2edc94166be1.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'wns', null), ('1217', 'Captify', 'Captify Technologies Ltd', 'https://www.captifytechnologies.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/captify/', 'Captify is a digital media and advertising technology company based in London, UK, founded in 2011. The company specializes in Search Intelligence and Search Retargeting, utilizing real-time search data from over 1 billion daily searches across more than 2 billion devices worldwide. Captify''s proprietary machine learning technology transforms raw search behavior into actionable insights, enabling brands to understand consumer intent and optimize their marketing strategies.

The company offers a Search Intelligence Platform that supports various aspects of digital marketing without relying on third-party cookies. Key features include real-time audience targeting, programmatic advertising activation, and unique measurement solutions. Captify serves over 800 global brands and partners with more than 150 media agencies, providing data-driven audience strategies that enhance marketing effectiveness. With a strong focus on consumer insights, Captify is recognized as a leader in the ad tech industry, receiving multiple accolades for its innovative solutions.', 'Sponsorship cannot be offered.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/856cda51-9deb-4d7a-a9cc-833029694f04.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'captify', null), ('1218', 'Avantia', 'Avantia Law Limited', 'https://www.avantialaw.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/avantialaw/', 'Avantia Law is a global law firm founded between 2018 and 2019, with its headquarters in London and a presence in New York. The firm specializes in AI-driven legal solutions tailored for asset managers. Avantia combines senior legal expertise with proprietary technology to enhance contract management, compliance, and limited partner transfer workflows.

The firm offers a range of services, including contract management, compliance solutions, and streamlined LP transfers. Its in-house developed Ava AI platform, launched in January 2025, automates various legal processes, providing features like real-time progress tracking and compliance summaries. Avantia serves over 100 clients worldwide, focusing on large asset managers who need scalable solutions for fund operations and compliance.

Avantia operates as a fully regulated law firm, distinguishing itself from traditional legal tech vendors. Its hybrid model integrates the efficiency of alternative legal service providers with the oversight of experienced lawyers, enabling the firm to handle both high-volume administrative tasks and complex transactions effectively.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/03c60b96-2f76-4aee-8c6f-0664010a704a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'avantialaw', null), ('1219', 'BioCorteX', 'BioCorteX Ltd', 'https://biocortex.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/biocortex/', 'BioCorteX is a London-based private limited company focused on digital health and biotech/pharma, specializing in in-silico drug development for oncology research. Founded in March 2021, the company utilizes advanced computational modeling to enhance and streamline drug development, particularly for therapeutics transitioning from Asian markets to the global stage.

The company''s key innovation is its proprietary platform, Carbon Mirror™, which emulates biological interactions using Carbon Knowledge, a comprehensive microbiome knowledge graph. This platform allows for the modeling of complex interactions between patients, their microbiomes, and treatments, enabling predictions of individual responses to therapies. BioCorteX addresses the variability in drug efficacy caused by differences in microbiome composition, aiming to develop tailored therapeutics that improve clinical outcomes.

BioCorteX serves pharmaceutical and biotech companies involved in oncology drug development, as well as clinicians seeking personalized treatment strategies. Their technology supports global drug development efforts, particularly in expanding therapeutics from Asian markets for worldwide use.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dab0479e-2652-4e28-8223-e8535f66bed6.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1220', 'Cogna', 'Cogna Ltd', 'https://www.cogna.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wearecogna/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d2ae4bc0-4322-4941-a1b9-c67211a35fd3.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'cogna', null), ('1221', 'Kitt', 'Kitt Technology Ltd', 'https://www.kittoffices.com/en/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kittoffices/', 'Kitt is a UK-based company founded in 2018 that specializes in end-to-end office space solutions. It offers services such as finding, designing, building, and managing office environments tailored to client needs. Kitt operates as a managed office operator and office outfitter, partnering with landlords to create customizable, tech-enabled workspaces.

The company focuses on delivering high-quality, managed office spaces that combine flexibility with premium service standards. Kitt has completed over 200 transactions and transacted more than 150,000 square feet of office space in 2024 alone. Its services include ready-to-go managed offices, bespoke design and build services, and automated office management functions. Kitt also utilizes a proprietary technology platform to streamline office search and management, enhancing the tenant experience. The company serves a diverse range of clients, including well-known brands like Flo Health, Oatly, Nested, and PZ Cussons Beauty.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4ba5bbdc-74d3-4bd3-8fb0-5daa83f0ce15.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'kitt', null), ('1222', 'Roli', 'ROLI Ltd', 'https://roli.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/roli/', 'ROLI is a London-based music technology company founded in 2009 by Roland Lamb and Corey Harrower. The company focuses on inventing and developing music-making devices and software that enhance how people create, learn, and interact with music. ROLI''s mission is to democratize music creation, making it accessible to everyone, regardless of skill level.

The company offers a range of innovative products, including the Seaboard Series, which features pressure-sensitive keyboards for expressive control. Their LUMI system combines hardware and software to make piano learning engaging and interactive. ROLI Blocks are modular devices that work with the NOISE app, allowing users to create music with tactile control. Additionally, ROLI develops software like the NOISE app and Equator, a synthesizer optimized for their hardware. ROLI also provides a unique learning platform that integrates pedagogy to inspire music education for all levels.

ROLI serves a diverse customer base, including professional musicians, producers, and beginners, and aims to foster a vibrant community of music creators worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9c995742-efda-44f8-864d-26cc7895d0ac.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'roli', null), ('1223', 'MultiOmic', 'Multiomic Health Limited', 'https://multiomic.health/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/multiomic-health/', 'Multiomic Health is an AI-enabled drug discovery company based in London, England, focused on precision medicine for conditions related to metabolic syndrome. Founded on March 5, 2021, the company aims to develop innovative treatments for diseases such as type 2 diabetes, chronic kidney disease, atherosclerosis, and non-alcoholic fatty liver disease.

The company employs a unique approach that combines deep patient datasets, AI-driven data science, and experimental biology to identify molecular-level disease drivers in specific patient subpopulations. Their MOHSAIC platform integrates multiomics analysis with computational systems biology and laboratory experiments to create novel therapeutic concepts. Multiomic Health collaborates with research institutions, healthcare providers, and health tech companies to access de-identified patient data and samples, advancing its drug discovery pipeline and companion diagnostics.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/228894b5-beeb-41fb-af13-cc4e90efcf63.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1224', 'Ochre Bio', 'Ochre Bio Limited', 'https://www.ochre-bio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ochre-bio/', 'Ochre Bio is a biotechnology company based in Oxford, UK, focused on developing RNA-based medicines for chronic liver diseases, including fatty liver disease and other metabolic disorders. Founded in 2019, the company utilizes advanced genomics, spatial sequencing, AI, and high-throughput screening to identify disease-causing genes and create targeted RNA therapeutics, particularly small interfering RNAs (siRNAs) for liver cells.

The company''s innovative Human Discovery Platform integrates extensive human liver datasets and patient disease atlases to identify new drug targets. Complementing this is the Human Validation Platform, which employs AI and human liver models to validate therapeutic candidates. Ochre Bio produces its RNA therapies in-house, significantly speeding up the research and development process. The company aims to develop genomic medicines that can rejuvenate diseased livers and reduce the need for liver transplants.

Ochre Bio collaborates with pharmaceutical companies, research institutions, and healthcare providers to advance RNA therapeutics in hepatology. The company has secured significant investments, including a $1.3 billion partnership with Boehringer Ingelheim to develop RNA medicines for liver diseases.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d7edb650-c35c-47cb-adb0-6e07c3ea8fbb.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'ochrebio', null), ('1225', 'PACT', 'Hide Biotech Ltd', 'https://pact.earth/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pactearth/', 'PACT is a company focused on designing and manufacturing innovative biomaterials from natural earth resources, including collagen, herbal extracts, oils, and minerals. Their flagship product, Oval, is a patented biomaterial made primarily from cosmetic-grade collagen, offering a sustainable alternative to plastic and traditional leather. Oval is crafted for creative collaboration, providing an elegant and adaptable skin that reduces environmental impact, particularly in high-end applications like cosmetics, skincare, and pharmaceuticals.

Founded in November 2019 and registered as PACT EARTH LTD in the UK, the company emphasizes sustainability and harmony with nature. Their process transforms collagen into supple skins enriched with natural ingredients, combining scientific innovation with artisanal craftsmanship. PACT serves clients in the creative industries and luxury sectors, providing sustainable and traceable materials for product development in fashion, cosmetics, and pharmaceuticals. The team includes scientists, engineers, and creatives dedicated to pioneering materials that benefit the biosphere.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/79343c4c-2fe3-47df-bfd0-0ef541e6cfc4.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'pact', null), ('1226', 'PillSorted', 'PillSorted Ltd', 'https://www.pillsorted.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pillsorted/', 'PillSorted is a UK-based digital pharmacy company founded in 2019 by pharmacist Zeinab Ardeshir. The company focuses on enhancing the pharmacy experience for patients managing multiple medications through personalized, technology-driven services. PillSorted integrates with the NHS healthcare system to provide efficient prescription management and delivery.

The company offers a range of services, including digital consultations with pharmacists, free home delivery of NHS prescriptions, and medication management tools like easy-to-read medicine charts. PillSorted also coordinates with general practitioners to streamline prescription processes and supports care homes with specialized services. With a commitment to preventative healthcare, PillSorted aims to reduce the burden on NHS staff while improving patient support. Based in Cambridge, the company has raised $6 million in funding to expand its services across London and the UK.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5cb3eb9f-208c-4ad1-9c95-a5b85c399ed3.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'breezy', 'pillsorted', null), ('1227', 'QuantrolOx', 'QuantrolOx Ltd', 'https://quantrolox.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quantrolox', 'QuantrolOx is an Anglo-Finnish company founded in 2021, with headquarters in Oxford, UK, and operations in Espoo, Finland. The company specializes in automated machine learning-based control software for quantum technologies, focusing on tuning, stabilizing, and optimizing qubits in quantum computers. Its core product, the QX Software Suite, includes QXTR for automated tuning and optimization, and QXCR for automated characterization of quantum processors.

QuantrolOx''s software is designed for quantum scientists and developers, enabling them to achieve stable platforms for experimentation while effectively utilizing quantum infrastructure. The company operates in the B2B sector, offering its software as a SaaS subscription model. It collaborates closely with quantum hardware builders to ensure deep integration with quantum machines, enhancing performance for its customers, primarily researchers and companies in the quantum computing field. QuantrolOx is recognized for its innovative Quantum EDGE software, which automates qubit and quantum processor fine-tuning.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/68552c0b-90d2-4925-b304-5281b67e2b04.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1228', 'Skin Analytics', 'Skin Analytics Ltd', 'https://skin-analytics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/skin-analytics/', 'Skin Analytics is a UK-based company founded in 2012 that specializes in AI-powered medical technology for skin cancer detection and management. The company has developed an artificial intelligence as a medical device (AIaMD) called DERM, which analyzes high-resolution dermoscopic images to identify various types of skin lesions. This technology enables remote dermatologist-quality assessments, improving access to early detection and supporting healthcare systems globally.

The core service of Skin Analytics is its AI-supported teledermatology platform, designed to integrate into skin cancer care pathways. The platform collaborates with the UK’s National Health Service (NHS) to create sustainable skin cancer pathways, utilizing machine learning and computer vision to provide clinical decision support tools for dermatologists and general practitioners. The company operates on a subscription-based software-as-a-service (SaaS) model, targeting hospitals and healthcare providers to enhance early skin cancer detection and optimize patient outcomes.

Led by CEO Neil Daly, CTO Jim Holmes, and Medical Director Dan, Skin Analytics combines expertise in various fields to drive innovation in dermatology. The company has raised approximately $6.6 million in funding and employs around 30 people from its headquarters in London.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/baa9320d-ccdb-4e27-beb6-9611bdf5d230.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1229', 'Universal Quantum', 'Universal Quantum Technologies Limited', 'https://universalquantum.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/universal-quantum/', 'Universal Quantum Ltd. is a UK-based company founded in 2018 as a spin-off from the University of Sussex. The company specializes in building utility-scale, fully scalable quantum computers using trapped ion technology and standard silicon-chip processing techniques. With a team of leading scientists and engineers, Universal Quantum is dedicated to creating a robust and modular quantum computing blueprint aimed at addressing significant global challenges.

Headquartered in Brighton, East Sussex, with an additional presence in Hamburg, Germany, Universal Quantum operates in the fields of computer manufacturing, IT consultancy, and research in natural sciences and engineering. The company focuses on developing scalable quantum computers and engages in information technology consultancy and experimental research related to quantum computing. They also promote knowledge sharing through podcasts, blogs, and other media to enhance understanding and collaboration in the quantum technology space.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/efda7513-fb45-4045-8e09-861d3055c975.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'teamtailor', 'universalquantum', null), ('1230', 'Vitesse', 'Vitesse PSP Ltd', 'https://www.vitesse.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/vitesse-psp/', 'Vitesse is a fintech company that specializes in integrated treasury and payment solutions for insurance carriers and claim administrators. The company focuses on transforming insurance payments and has grown significantly, processing billions in payments annually. Vitesse offers technology-driven solutions that enhance control, transparency, and efficiency in managing funds and liquidity.

The company provides integrated treasury solutions that unify banking networks with advanced technology, as well as payment solutions that facilitate faster claims payments. Notably, its Faster Claims Payment product, developed in partnership with Lloyd''s of London, won the ''Claims Initiative of the Year'' award in 2023. Vitesse has received regulatory approval from the New York Department of Financial Services, supporting its expansion in the U.S. market.

Vitesse primarily serves the insurance industry and has established partnerships with major players, including Lloyd’s of London. The company is recognized as one of Britain’s fastest-growing private companies and is listed among CNBC Statista’s World''s 300 Top Fintech Companies.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4f0566b6-e515-4993-b312-782a8aa7422b.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1231', 'StableLogic', 'StableLogic Ltd', 'https://stablelogic.com/en-gb/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/stablelogic/', 'StableLogic is an independent technology consultancy based in London, specializing in customer experience, software development, cloud services, and network solutions. Founded in 1999, the company offers a range of end-to-end services, including expert consultancy, custom software development, and strategic technology guidance. Their cloud services, as an AWS Advanced Tier and Public Sector Partner, include cloud readiness assessments, migration strategies, and security enhancements.

The company serves a diverse clientele, including public sector organizations, financial services, and global multinationals, with offices in the UK, Australia, and the US. StableLogic emphasizes core values such as integrity, quality, and innovation, focusing on delivering tailored solutions that meet complex technology and business needs. With a team of over 120 employees, StableLogic is committed to helping medium to large organizations achieve operational excellence and growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/064b3912-4a73-42c2-8045-c6f1fd5349ee.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1232', 'Adsum', 'Adsum Technologies Ltd', 'https://www.adsum-works.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/adsum-finance/', 'Adsum is a tax and compliance technology firm dedicated to simplifying tax management for accountants and businesses. Founded by a team of entrepreneurs, accountants, and technologists, Adsum aims to enhance transparency and agility in tax workflows. The company believes that managing taxes should be straightforward, allowing professionals to focus on growth rather than repetitive tasks.

Adsum offers innovative software tools designed to automate tax-related processes and provide real-time data insights. Their key products include OpenTax, a comprehensive dashboard that gives accountants oversight of various client tax obligations, and InstantVAT, which accelerates VAT refunds to improve cash flow. These solutions are tailored to meet the needs of accountants and businesses looking to optimize their tax management and compliance efforts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/fb43de7b-7a12-4fc4-981a-8dfc26061786.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1233', 'btrt', 'BTRT Ltd', 'https://www.btrt.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/btrt-product/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a6393b33-6671-4c27-96d8-a02b7b61bba6.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1235', 'Huboo', 'Huboo Technologies Ltd', 'https://www.huboo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/huboo-fulfilment/', 'Huboo is an eCommerce fulfilment company based in Bristol, specializing in end-to-end fulfilment solutions. They aim to support small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) by providing a seamless and scalable service that allows these businesses to compete globally. Huboo''s comprehensive offerings include inventory management, picking, packing, and shipping products worldwide through a global courier network.

The company operates multiple fulfilment centres across Europe and utilizes an integrated software platform for real-time management of inventory, warehouse operations, order processing, shipping, and returns. Their proprietary technology combines various systems, including inventory and warehouse management, order management, and reporting, allowing for custom integrations and tailored processes. This technology enhances efficiency and scalability for eCommerce businesses, enabling them to focus on growth while Huboo manages logistics.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ce13d38d-5ce5-4f1f-b273-6e45ad1ed306.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'huboo', null), ('1237', 'Kleene.ai', 'Minoro Ltd', 'https://kleene.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kleeneai/', 'Kleene.ai is a UK-based software company founded in 2017 and headquartered in London. It specializes in business intelligence and data management solutions, offering a no-code platform for data transformation and modeling. This platform enables organizations to efficiently consolidate, transform, and visualize their data without the need for extensive data engineering resources.

The core product is an all-in-one ELT (Extract, Load, Transform) solution that allows businesses to quickly build and maintain data pipelines. With over 600 pre-built data integrations, Kleene.ai helps clients aggregate data from various SaaS applications into a single source of truth, facilitating reliable insights with minimal technical expertise. The company also provides data consulting services to support clients in accelerating their data projects and enhancing their data maturity.

Kleene.ai aims to democratize knowledge by simplifying data centralization, making it accessible for businesses to leverage their data effectively. Its platform supports teams across multiple departments, including sales, marketing, and product development, by improving deal visibility and customer insights.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c909b899-70de-4e48-a6fe-f33f7ad72a19.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1239', 'Opteran', 'Opteran Technologies Ltd', 'https://opteran.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/opteran/', 'Opteran Technologies Limited is a UK-based deep-tech company founded in 2020. It specializes in developing neuromorphic, bio-inspired software and hardware for robots and autonomous machines. The company draws on over eight years of research into honeybee and insect brains to create "Natural Intelligence," a unique approach to machine autonomy that mimics biological processes.

Opteran offers a range of vision-based, edge-compute products designed for real-time, low-power navigation and decision-making. Key products include Opteran See, which provides panoramic vision using two low-cost cameras; Opteran Sense, which enables state estimation and collision avoidance; and Opteran Mind, a neuromorphic software model that allows for GPS-free navigation in complex environments. The technology is applicable in various sectors, including defense, industrial robotics, agriculture, and infrastructure inspection, addressing challenges like depth perception and obstacle avoidance.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/92d444e6-c17a-4e2e-bc76-7d6ee3ad6aa5.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1240', 'Ori', 'Ori Industries 1 Ltd', 'https://www.ori.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ori-global-cloud/', 'Ori Industries is a technology company that specializes in AI infrastructure. They offer an end-to-end platform designed to help teams efficiently train, fine-tune, deploy, and scale machine learning models. Their solution supports the entire AI lifecycle, from prototype to production, while ensuring security and compliance.

The platform provides deployment flexibility, allowing customers to run AI workloads on Ori’s cloud, their own cloud, or in hybrid environments. Ori Industries emphasizes expert support and has a strong focus on security and governance, making it suitable for enterprises with complex AI projects. Their infrastructure is optimized for high performance and reliability, catering to industries that require robust and compliant AI solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/21d0ed26-b0dd-4cb7-853e-a16915ca5f44.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1242', 'Sentify', 'Sentify Ltd', 'https://getsentify.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sentify-ai/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1bc4eff7-ed50-477c-a761-4902c8695eb0.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1243', 'Sphere', 'Sphere Innovations Limited', 'https://sphere.buzz/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sphere-innovations-ltd/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bb996162-6f56-4953-89d6-ab9ba42e6662.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'sphere', null), ('1244', 'Supercede', 'Supercede Technology Ltd', 'https://supercede.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/supercedehq/', 'Supercede is a UK-based SaaS platform and e-trading ecosystem tailored for the reinsurance industry, established in 2019. It connects cedents, brokers, and reinsurers in a single digital environment, streamlining the entire reinsurance deal process. The platform enhances data preparation, risk sharing, and deal execution across the global reinsurance value chain.

The company offers two main products: Packs and Deals. Packs help cedents and brokers create organized submissions for reinsurers, improving data quality and reducing manual effort. Deals allows brokers and reinsurers to trade reinsurance risks globally, providing instant access to essential information and enhancing market reach. Supercede''s web-based platform features advanced capabilities, including an “exhibit-first” view for easy navigation and specialized AI for efficient data processing.

Supercede prioritizes security and independence, employing enterprise-grade security protocols certified to ISO 27001 standards. The platform serves a global clientele, including industry leaders like Markel, Generali, Lockton Re, Hiscox, and Convex, representing over 140 companies and facilitating nearly 50 different reinsurance risks.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/753eae6b-4327-4238-8a39-caeb528cb729.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'supercede', null), ('1245', 'Medtronic', 'Medtronic Limited', 'https://www.medtronic.com/uk-en/index.html', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/medtronic/', 'Medtronic is a global leader in medical technology, founded in 1949 in Minneapolis, Minnesota, by Earl Bakken and Palmer Hermundslie. Initially a medical equipment repair shop, the company quickly became known for its innovations, including the first battery-powered external pacemaker in 1957. Medtronic''s mission is to alleviate pain, restore health, and extend life through high-quality medical technologies.

The company develops a wide range of medical devices and therapies across several areas. In cardiac and vascular care, it offers implantable pacemakers and defibrillators. Medtronic also specializes in neurological therapies, diabetes management devices, and minimally invasive surgical technologies. Additionally, it has made advancements in remote monitoring and digital health, enhancing patient care through secure data transfer. With operations in over 160 countries and approximately 84,000 employees, Medtronic impacts the lives of more than 70 million people annually, serving hospitals and healthcare providers worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '14', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3d77d6b3-33be-488e-a974-c3fb5ef13c34.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'medtronic/MedtronicCareers', null), ('1246', 'Triptease', 'Triptease Limited', 'https://www.triptease.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/triptease/', 'Triptease is a SaaS company founded in 2015, with offices in London, New York, and Singapore. It specializes in providing digital tools and a data-driven platform that helps hotels increase direct bookings and revenue while reducing reliance on online travel agencies (OTAs). The company serves over 10,000 hotels worldwide, including major brands like Best Western and Virgin Hotels, as well as many independent properties.

The Triptease platform offers a range of features designed to enhance the customer journey from acquisition to conversion. Key tools include Parity Monitoring for real-time price alerts, a Price Check Widget for displaying competitive rates, and targeted messaging to boost conversion rates. The platform also provides insights and analytics to help hotels understand guest behavior and optimize their marketing strategies. Additionally, Triptease organizes the Direct Booking Summit, an event that educates hoteliers on effective distribution strategies.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/700a2a51-3b8c-4266-96c5-776deba8b4d6.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1247', 'Papaya', 'Papaya Technologies Ltd', 'https://papayadash.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/papayadash/', 'Papaya Dash is a London-based fleet management technology company founded in 2022. It specializes in solutions for electric and commercial vehicle operations, focusing on streamlining fleet management through automation and real-time insights. With a team of 24 employees, the company aims to enhance fleet uptime and reduce inefficiencies in manual processes.

The company offers a unified fleet management platform that centralizes vehicle sourcing, maintenance tracking, and communication among stakeholders. Key features include automated workflows and real-time operational visibility. Additionally, Papaya Dash provides an EV marketplace that connects fleet operators with electric vehicle suppliers and service providers, helping to optimize costs and mitigate supply chain risks. Their data analytics services deliver insights on fleet performance and operational efficiency.

Papaya Dash is committed to sustainability and supports the transition to electric vehicles. The company has successfully improved fleet management processes for 98% of its customers. With $3.5 million in seed funding, it continues to grow and innovate in the fleet management sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5e9c0fae-8b58-4402-ba52-1a4db3d9fbdb.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'papaya', null), ('1248', 'Matta', 'Matta Labs Ltd', 'https://www.matta.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mattaai/', 'Matta is a technology company dedicated to developing industrial artificial intelligence (AI) aimed at enhancing manufacturing processes. The team consists of engineers, scientists, and builders who focus on creating foundational AI models specifically designed for manufacturing environments.

The company''s primary offering includes manufacturing foundation models that help factories become more intelligent and responsive. These models are likely to improve operational efficiency, predictive maintenance, and automation within manufacturing workflows. Matta emphasizes integrating AI deeply into production processes to optimize decision-making and overall productivity.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8dd56c30-f751-43c3-b9ff-85c0191805d3.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1249', 'Screenloop', 'Screenloop Ltd', 'https://www.screenloop.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/screenloop/', 'Screenloop is a UK-based private limited company founded in 2021, specializing in AI-native applicant tracking software and interview intelligence solutions. Headquartered in London, the company focuses on helping in-house Talent Acquisition teams at startups, SMEs, and growing companies hire more efficiently and fairly. Screenloop aims to reduce unconscious bias in hiring through automation and AI technology.

The company offers an all-in-one Talent Operations Platform that integrates various AI-powered tools to streamline recruitment workflows. Key features include an applicant tracking system that manages candidate pipelines, interview scheduling, and evaluation, as well as interview intelligence tools that analyze interview data. Additionally, Screenloop provides an AI Notetaker that generates notes during interviews, robust security features for sensitive data, and a dedicated support team to assist customers. 

Screenloop primarily serves dynamic businesses looking to modernize their talent acquisition processes while promoting a supportive work culture that encourages remote and hybrid work.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bd8624ae-c9f3-4a12-aed5-267f55e7d574.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1251', 'Virtex', 'Virtex Entertainment Limited', 'https://www.virtexstadium.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/virtexstadium/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0fa6dd37-acd2-4845-a701-71b41c4010c5.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1252', 'CoSyne Therapeutics', 'CoSyne Therapeutics', 'https://www.cosyne.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cosyne-therapeutics/', 'CoSyne Therapeutics is a private limited company founded in 2021 and based in London, UK, with experimental labs in Cambridge. The company specializes in AI-driven drug discovery, focusing on developing precision medicines for brain diseases. By utilizing a unique approach called Polymathic AI, CoSyne combines proprietary data with custom-built biology and chemistry models to enhance drug discovery processes.

The company offers drug discovery services that integrate AI, biology, and chemistry to create innovative pharmaceuticals for neurological conditions. Their Polymathic AI platform allows for the rapid identification of drug candidates and precision targeting of genetic vulnerabilities in brain diseases. CoSyne Therapeutics serves the biopharmaceutical and healthcare sectors, aiming to benefit patients with complex neurological disorders through advanced therapeutic solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/57bb1e6e-4c4a-41e6-a21c-e2d646bca069.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1253', 'Nuntius Therapeutics', 'Nuntius Therapeutics Limited', 'https://www.nuntiustx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/nuntius-therapeutics/', 'Nuntius Therapeutics is a private biotechnology company based in London, UK, founded in 2021. The company focuses on developing cell-specific genetic medicines using advanced nanocarrier technology. It specializes in creating programmable and non-immunogenic nanocarriers designed to deliver mRNA, DNA, and CRISPR therapies to targeted tissues beyond the liver, addressing limitations of traditional delivery methods.

The core technology of Nuntius involves dendrimer lipid nanocarriers, which can be manufactured cost-effectively at scale. These nanocarriers aim to reduce immunogenicity risks and enable targeting of hard-to-reach tissues, expanding the therapeutic potential of gene therapies. Nuntius is advancing a pipeline of treatments primarily targeting cancer, lung diseases, and neurodegenerative diseases, with a notable focus on a cancer immunotherapy currently in preclinical development. The company utilizes machine learning models to optimize the selection of nanocarrier candidates, enhancing therapeutic efficacy.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4ad8f2a7-ef13-40b5-8c02-9d2103e647c9.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1254', 'Zaptic', 'Juliand Digital Ltd', 'https://zaptic.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zaptic/', 'Zaptic is a UK-based technology company founded in 2015, focused on enhancing the lives of frontline workers through a connected worker platform. This platform is designed to digitize and optimize work processes in industrial and retail environments, improving safety, productivity, and continuous learning.

The company offers a cloud-based, no-code task mobility platform that allows businesses in manufacturing, consumer goods, retail, and services to quickly create and deploy digital workflows, forms, and dashboards. Key features include paperless daily management systems, context-specific issue resolution, continuous learning management, and real-time access to critical information. Zaptic''s platform also incorporates advanced analytics and gamification to motivate workers and improve performance.

Zaptic''s solutions are utilized by notable clients such as Carlsberg and Danone, showcasing its effectiveness in large-scale operations. The company emphasizes transparency, autonomy, and simplicity, aiming to empower workers and drive sustainable operational excellence across various sectors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e7b6c1ba-7537-4a8e-b839-2d10f0bbee20.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'teamtailor', 'zaptic', null), ('1256', 'Sonos', 'Sonos Experience Ltd', 'https://www.sonos.com/en-gb/home', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sonos-inc-/', 'Sonos, Inc. is a consumer electronics company based in Santa Barbara, California, founded in 2002. It specializes in designing, developing, manufacturing, and selling wireless audio products globally. Sonos is known for pioneering whole-home wireless audio systems, allowing users to stream music and audio content seamlessly across multiple rooms.

The product lineup includes wireless speakers, soundbars, headphones, and accessories, all recognized for their high-quality sound and easy setup. Sonos products integrate well with popular streaming services like Spotify and Apple Music. The company targets consumers who appreciate high-quality, wireless home audio solutions, including music enthusiasts and smart home users. 

Sonos went public in August 2018 and trades on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol SONO. With over 1,700 employees, the company reported revenues around $1.5 billion and continues to innovate in the wireless audio technology space.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/27640a3e-9181-4153-abf6-fc71d1eb4594.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'sonos', null), ('1257', 'COPA90', 'COPA90 Limited', 'https://www.copa90.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/copa90/', 'COPA90 is a London-based football media company founded in 2012. Initially launched as a YouTube channel by Bigballs Media, it focuses on fan culture and stories beyond traditional match coverage. The company has grown into a multi-platform media business with over 8.5 million followers, producing documentaries, interviews, and original programming that connect football fans with the sport in engaging ways.

