SSE has a diverse energy portfolio, with a strong emphasis on renewable sources, particularly wind power. It owns and operates various power stations, including hydroelectric, wind farms, and gas-fired facilities. The company manages extensive electricity networks in Scotland and parts of England, ensuring reliable energy delivery to millions of customers. SSE also supplies electricity and gas to residential and business clients across Great Britain and Wales, offering tailored energy tariffs and efficiency services. With a commitment to sustainability, SSE is a key player in the UK and Irish energy markets, dedicated to providing reliable and sustainable energy solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5a414aa7-6113-4ed0-8f31-1996d7ccc0da.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'sse', null), ('1299', 'HarbourVest', 'HarbourVest Partners (UK) Limited', 'https://www.harbourvest.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/harbourvest-partners/', 'HarbourVest Partners is an independent global private markets firm with over 42 years of experience. Founded in 1982, it has grown from a Boston-based startup to a significant player with a presence in Asia, Europe, and the Americas. The firm specializes in various private market investments, including private equity funds, secondary investments, direct investments, real assets, and credit programs.

With more than $143 billion in assets under management, HarbourVest has established a strong network, supporting over 30,000 portfolio companies and holding over 900 advisory seats. The firm operates from 14 global offices, including major cities like Boston, London, Hong Kong, Tokyo, and Sydney. HarbourVest focuses on building long-term relationships with institutional investors, such as pension funds and family offices, providing them with diversified exposure to private markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2d13f105-802e-4af0-9a8d-0049975860ee.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'HVP', null), ('1300', 'Outlier Ventures', 'Outlier Ventures Operations Ltd', 'https://outlierventures.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/outlierventures/', 'Outlier Ventures is a prominent venture capital firm and accelerator based in Greater London, specializing in Web3 technologies. Founded in 2014, it is recognized as the leading Web3 accelerator by investment volume, partnering with around 200 top Web3 founders each year. The firm focuses on early-stage blockchain projects and startups that contribute to the decentralized Web3 ecosystem, including areas like decentralized finance (DeFi), non-fungible tokens (NFTs), and blockchain infrastructure.

The company offers a wide range of services, including capital investment, technical expertise, and access to a global network of over 1,000 Web3 founders and venture capitalists. Its accelerator programs, such as Base Camp and Ascent, provide structured support for startups to launch token networks and scale their projects. Outlier Ventures also collaborates with leading corporations to identify and nurture innovative startups, helping to shape the future of the internet. The firm is dedicated to fostering an open and decentralized Web3.0, emphasizing user control over data and digital identities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/57402024-ab44-4ec8-b17d-04c81b48e865.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/cryptio', null), ('1301', 'Kanjo', 'Kanjo Health Ltd', 'https://www.mykanjo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kanjohealth/', 'Kanjo Health is a technology-driven healthcare company based in London, UK, focused on mental health support tools for children. Founded in 2021, the company aims to enhance understanding and support for children''s mental health through innovative solutions.

The Kanjo Health platform is designed to build social, emotional, and cognitive skills in children. It provides valuable insights into children''s well-being, assisting parents and clinicians in addressing mental health needs. The platform utilizes AI-driven insights and triaging tools to improve the accuracy of diagnosing conditions such as ADHD and Autism, thereby enhancing clinical evaluations and reducing misdiagnosis rates. 

Co-founded by Sophia Parvizi-Wayne and Deepthi Upalla, Kanjo Health has garnered support from the Abu Dhabi Investment Office and partnered with the Abu Dhabi Government. The company has raised $100,000 in funding and has established a user base of thousands of parents utilizing its platform.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7c1e3546-fcb2-4c91-9f09-39c3e60c140a.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1302', 'Unfabled', 'Unfabled Ltd.', 'https://unfabled.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/unfabled/', 'Unfabled is a UK-based personalized health and wellness company dedicated to addressing the gender health gap by focusing on menstrual and hormonal health throughout all life stages. Founded in 2021 and headquartered in London, Unfabled offers a consumer platform that curates trusted, sustainable health and wellness products tailored to women''s specific health needs, including menstrual cramps, endometriosis, menopause, pregnancy, postpartum care, sexual wellness, fertility, and conditions like PCOS.

The company features a dual business model, providing a consumer-facing platform that delivers personalized wellness product recommendations based on users'' health and lifestyle data. Unfabled also operates a B2B data platform that collects and analyzes health data to offer insights for healthcare providers and businesses. With a significant social media presence, particularly on TikTok, Unfabled engages with its community to identify unmet needs and emerging trends. The company aims to redefine women''s health by offering personalized, sustainable solutions and leveraging data to enhance care across all stages of a woman''s hormonal journey.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/90a9a2ee-1cc4-4017-8897-b4666304cece.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1303', 'Kaedim', 'Kaedim', 'https://www.kaedim3d.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kaedim/', 'Kaedim is a technology company that specializes in AI-powered 3D content creation, primarily for the gaming industry and other sectors that require 3D assets. Founded in 2020 by Konstantina Psoma, Kaedim aims to enhance the transition from 2D digital content to immersive 3D environments. The company achieves this by streamlining the 3D asset creation process through advanced AI solutions combined with human artistic expertise.

Kaedim offers an AI-driven platform that converts 2D images into production-ready 3D assets, significantly speeding up the process—up to 10 times faster than traditional methods. Their unique "human-in-the-loop" approach ensures high-quality and scalable production. The platform supports various industries, including commerce, architecture, product design, and animation. Kaedim also features a marketplace with over 10,000 3D assets available for developers and creators, catering to hundreds of game developers and over 250 enterprise clients, including AAA game studios and film production companies.', 'The company can offer visa sponsorship for candidates who are already based in the UK, including recent graduates.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/21d49c0f-2f4c-4018-ba45-8ebd9b087d15.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1305', 'Change.org', 'Change.org Worldwide Limited', 'https://www.change.org/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/change-org/', 'Change.org is a for-profit public benefit company founded in 2007 by Ben Rattray and Mark Dimas. It serves as a global platform for social change, allowing individuals to create and support activist petitions on various social, political, and environmental issues. With over 200 million users in 196 countries, the platform empowers people to mobilize supporters and engage decision makers at all levels.

The core service of Change.org is its open petition platform, where users can start petitions for free and gather signatures to influence change. The company also offers campaign support through coaching and small teams of campaigners to help maximize the impact of petitions. Users can promote their petitions to reach wider audiences, with various payment options available. Change.org emphasizes its mission to empower individuals and organizations to drive social and political change while maintaining transparency and social impact as key values.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/024696d2-7aec-46e5-a216-9ad20763dd8d.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/change', null), ('1306', 'Emma', 'Emma Technologies LTD', 'https://emma-app.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/emma-technologies-ltd/', 'Emma is a London-based personal finance management company founded in 2017. Officially registered as EMMA TECHNOLOGIES LTD, its mission is to empower users to take control of their financial future through tools that simplify money management and promote healthy financial habits.

Emma offers a mobile app that helps users track spending, manage subscriptions, budget effectively, and grow savings. The app provides a comprehensive overview of financial activities, including spending tracking, subscription management, and budgeting tools. Users can also access cashback offers from various brands and explore additional services like rent reporting and investment opportunities. Emma is registered with the UK Financial Conduct Authority, ensuring compliance and security in payment services.

With over $7.3 million in funding and more than one million users, Emma continues to expand its offerings to help individuals save money and build wealth. The company is located in London and employs between 11 and 50 people.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a41dd133-8b55-4f22-89c3-e25ea48759f5.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1307', 'CellVoyant', 'CellVoyant Technologies Limited', 'https://cellvoyant.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cellvoyant/', 'CellVoyant is an AI-first biotechnology company based in Bristol, UK, established in 2021. The company focuses on developing innovative stem cell-based therapies for chronic diseases. It utilizes advanced artificial intelligence, live cell imaging, and machine learning to enhance stem cell differentiation, facilitating the scalable manufacturing of various cell and tissue types.

The core technology platform of CellVoyant integrates label-free imaging and computer vision with Bayesian Neural Networks for time series analysis. This allows for non-invasive identification and control of cell states without genetic modification. Their main products—FateView, FateCast, and FateSim—enable the autonomous management of cell manufacturing processes by quantifying biological factors to guide cells toward desired outcomes.

CellVoyant''s technology is rooted in research from the Carazo Salas lab at the University of Bristol and targets the biotechnology and cell and gene therapy sectors. The company aims to advance cell and tissue manufacturing science, making it practical and scalable for researchers and therapeutic developers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4ef68181-0ac3-4dc2-b6fc-83db72f042a6.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1308', 'Ori Biotech', 'OriBiotech Ltd', 'https://oribiotech.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oribiotech-ltd/', 'Ori Biotech is a biotechnology company that specializes in cell and gene therapy manufacturing technology. Founded in 2015 and based in London and New Jersey, the company focuses on automating and accelerating the production of advanced therapies. This approach aims to make treatments more scalable, affordable, and accessible to patients worldwide, particularly for cancer and rare genetic diseases.

The core offering of Ori Biotech is the IRO® platform, a proprietary manufacturing system that fully automates, digitizes, and standardizes the production of cell and gene therapies. This platform integrates hardware, software, data, and analytical tools to enhance the manufacturing process, increasing throughput and reproducibility while reducing costs. Ori Biotech serves therapy developers, contract manufacturers, and academic researchers, providing tools that streamline development and manufacturing workflows.

The company has secured over $100 million in funding to expand its team and accelerate the commercialization of its platform. Ori Biotech also runs the Lightspeed Early Access Program (LEAP), allowing select partners to access the platform prior to its full market launch.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5a2f6538-b5d1-4898-97dc-558aa3e72750.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1309', 'Mesh-AI', 'MESH AI LIMITED', 'https://www.mesh-ai.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wearemesh-ai/', 'Mesh-AI is a global consultancy based in Poole, England, that focuses on using data, machine learning, and artificial intelligence to address complex business challenges. Founded in 2021, the company specializes in serving highly regulated sectors, particularly Financial Services and Energy & Utilities. Mesh-AI combines a team of technical consultants, data scientists, engineers, and industry specialists to deliver production-ready AI and data solutions quickly, often achieving results in weeks.

The company offers a range of services, including the development of scalable AI and data systems, enterprise data strategy design, and enhancing AI and machine learning capabilities for organizations. Mesh-AI partners with leading cloud providers like AWS and Microsoft to ensure rapid and compliant solution delivery. Its unique "Mesh Model" aligns cross-functional teams to drive measurable business outcomes across transformation projects, emphasizing speed and compliance in AI deployment.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/669394d0-826f-403b-9d15-43b8a1f9dba2.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1310', 'Storfund', 'Storfund', 'https://storfund.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/storfund/', 'Storfund is a financial technology company based in London, founded in 2018. It specializes in payment solutions for online marketplace sellers, allowing them to access their sales revenue immediately upon shipping their products. This approach helps sellers avoid the delays associated with traditional payment cycles.

The company''s main service, Daily Advance, is an embedded financing solution that enables faster payouts for marketplace sellers. This service integrates directly within various marketplaces, eliminating the need for sellers to manually request payments or submit sales data. Storfund guarantees on-time payments and offers unlimited funding that scales with the seller''s business. It also provides access to competitive foreign exchange rates and allows sellers to cancel the service at any time.

Storfund partners with a global network of online marketplaces, including a recent integration with Mirakl’s Connect platform, which supports over 400 marketplaces worldwide. The company targets ecommerce sellers on platforms like Amazon, TikTok Shop, and Back Market, helping them manage cash flow challenges and facilitating their growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dcbc3ec5-a713-4d6a-b1b3-a73be510cb0a.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1311', 'Unibuddy', 'Unibuddy Limited', 'https://unibuddy.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/unibuddy/', 'Unibuddy is an education technology company based in London, UK, founded in 2015 by Kimeshan Naidoo and Diego Fanara. The company specializes in a student engagement platform that connects prospective and current students with student ambassadors and alumni from higher education institutions around the world. This platform offers a personal and authentic way for students to explore university life, courses, and accommodation.

The core product, Chat, allows for one-to-one messaging, group chats, and video calls, providing real-time insights into university experiences. In 2022, Unibuddy introduced Community, which fosters connections among students with shared interests. The platform is integrated into university websites and is also utilized by UCAS, enhancing the recruitment process for over 600 partner institutions globally, including notable universities like the University of Cambridge and NYU. Unibuddy has facilitated over one million messages between students, supporting informed decision-making in the higher education journey.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b9e8e1c5-c9c0-4ef0-8970-cc45c4f8eba7.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'teamtailor', 'unibuddy', null), ('1312', 'Flo', 'Flo Health UK Limited', 'https://flo.health/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/flohealth/', 'Flo Health Inc. is a digital health company dedicated to female reproductive health, founded in 2015 or 2016. It is known for the Flo app, which is the most popular women’s health app globally, boasting over 380 million downloads and 73 million monthly active users. The company is headquartered in Wilmington, Delaware, and has a significant international presence.

The Flo app offers a range of features, including cycle and ovulation tracking, pregnancy and postpartum guidance, menopause support, and a privacy-focused Anonymous Mode. It also provides community features for users to discuss health concerns. Flo collaborates with medical experts and organizations like the UNFPA to enhance global female health initiatives. The app serves women and individuals who menstruate, with a strong user base in the U.S. and availability in over 190 countries. Flo''s mission is to empower users with data-driven insights and expert resources to improve female health.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '18', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/42908a1a-8d68-416a-a696-2ad4a349b6ce.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'flo', null), ('1313', 'BenevolentAI', 'BenevolentAI Ltd', 'https://www.benevolent.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/benevolentai/', 'BenevolentAI is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company based in London, UK, with additional offices in New York City and wet-lab facilities in Cambridge, UK. Founded in 2013, the company focuses on using artificial intelligence to enhance the discovery and development of new medicines for complex and untreated diseases. Their goal is to improve traditional drug development processes by reducing time and costs while increasing clinical success rates.

Central to BenevolentAI''s operations is the Benevolent Platform™, an AI-driven system that integrates a biomedical Knowledge Graph with advanced machine learning. This platform processes data from over 85 sources, enabling the identification of new biological targets and the design of drug molecules. BenevolentAI operates two main business units: BenevolentBio, which focuses on human health, and BenevolentTech, which expands AI applications in biosciences. The company collaborates with major pharmaceutical firms and charitable organizations to develop innovative medicines and address high unmet medical needs in areas like neurodegeneration, oncology, and rare diseases.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c10f940f-15c8-4e16-a93c-dd342fdea3a7.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1314', 'Paysend', 'Paysend Group Ltd', 'https://paysend.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/paysend/', 'Paysend is a global fintech company founded in the UK in 2017, specializing in cross-border money transfers through its digital payments network. It has grown from a startup focused on card-to-card transfers to a significant player in global payments, serving over 11 million consumers and numerous enterprise clients in more than 170 countries.

The company offers a range of services, including Paysend Consumer, which allows individuals to send and receive money instantly in over 170 countries. Paysend Enterprise provides a B2B solution for secure global payouts via a single API integration. Additionally, Paysend features a multicurrency account for managing multiple currencies, virtual cards for business payments, and is developing instant settlement accounts to enhance operational efficiency. With partnerships with major card networks like Mastercard and Visa, Paysend aims to simplify and reduce the costs of international transactions while promoting financial inclusion for both banked and unbanked populations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4cece14f-417b-4fe6-ab85-c1758001dbbc.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1315', 'Elvie', 'CHIARO TECHNOLOGY LTD', 'https://www.elvie.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/elvie/', 'Elvie is a London-based femtech company founded in 2013 by Tania Boler and Alexander Asseily. The company focuses on developing innovative connected technology products that enhance women’s health and well-being, particularly during the postpartum period. Elvie aims to support women through significant life experiences, such as pelvic floor health recovery and breastfeeding.

Elvie''s product lineup includes the Elvie Trainer, a compact pelvic floor trainer that pairs with a training app, and the Elvie Pump, a silent, wearable breast pump designed for discreet use. Other products include the Elvie Curve and Elvie Catch, which address milk leakage during pumping, and the Elvie Stride, an ultra-quiet breast pump targeted at the US market. Elvie sells its products online and through distributors in Europe, China, and the United States, with a strong emphasis on meeting the needs of new mothers and women seeking convenient solutions for pelvic floor training and breastfeeding.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7ebe281e-6709-4151-a639-f7e73915948c.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'willow-blossom', null), ('1316', 'Haiper', 'Haiper Limited', 'https://haiper.ai/home', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/haiperai/', 'Haiper is an AI-powered video generation and creation platform based in King''s Cross, London. The company specializes in enabling users to create high-quality, photorealistic 3D content, images, and videos using artificial intelligence technology. Haiper''s platform is designed to be accessible to individuals and businesses, including those with limited technical skills, by utilizing AI models that function on smartphones and other devices.

The platform offers a variety of tools for multimedia content creation, including text-to-image and text-to-video generation, image-to-video animation, video enhancement, and style transformation for videos. These features empower users to produce engaging content for social media and other digital channels without needing advanced technical expertise or expensive hardware. Haiper serves a diverse customer base, including individual creators, social media influencers, publishers, and professionals in the multimedia and entertainment industries. The company emphasizes community-driven development, encouraging user feedback to enhance its AI models responsibly.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3f668dcd-57b7-426d-99cd-6daeefcd9852.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1317', 'YOOBIC', 'Yoobic Limited', 'https://yoobic.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/yoobic/', 'YOOBIC is a digital workplace platform founded in 2014 by brothers Fabrice, Avi, and Gilles Haïat. The company focuses on enhancing the efficiency of frontline teams through improved communication, training, and task management. With over 350 global clients, including well-known brands like Boots, Burgerfi, and Lacoste, YOOBIC has established itself as a key player in the industry. The company is headquartered in New York City and operates five offices worldwide, employing around 200 people.

The core offering of YOOBIC is a mobile-first platform designed specifically for frontline employees. It features a social media-style newsfeed for communication, mobile learning modules for training, and digitized task management tools to streamline operations. The platform also includes advanced analytics and AI capabilities, supporting over 200 integrations with popular systems like Salesforce and Microsoft. YOOBIC aims to improve employee engagement and operational efficiency, particularly in retail and frontline operations, by addressing common challenges faced by these teams.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/62a189af-113a-41cd-a997-8475254ce66c.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1318', 'CarbonChain', 'CarbonChain.io Limited', 'https://www.carbonchain.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carbonchain-io/', 'CarbonChain is an AI-powered carbon accounting platform founded in 2019 and based in London, UK. The company focuses on measuring, reporting, and reducing greenhouse gas emissions in supply chains, particularly in industries that contribute significantly to global emissions, such as metals and mining, agriculture, manufacturing, oil and gas, and logistics. CarbonChain aims to support businesses and financial institutions in their transition to a net-zero economy by 2050.

The company offers a SaaS platform that automates carbon emissions accounting across supply chains. Key services include carbon footprinting, supply chain decarbonization tools, climate-related financial reporting, and a carbon risk rating methodology. These services provide detailed emissions data and actionable insights, helping clients manage ESG risks and comply with environmental regulations. CarbonChain''s technology is utilized by various sectors, including manufacturers, banks, commodities traders, and insurers, enhancing emissions transparency and risk management.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/73d0acc2-5f50-4d40-81ef-9d65aa39d4c2.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'carbonchain', null), ('1320', 'ev.energy', 'EV DOT ENERGY LIMITED', 'https://www.ev.energy/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/evdotenergy/', 'ev.energy is a technology company based in London, UK, founded in 2018. The company focuses on integrating electric vehicle (EV) charging with the energy grid to promote decarbonization in transport and energy. It specializes in smart charging software solutions that optimize charging schedules, benefiting EV owners, utilities, and businesses by reducing costs and carbon emissions.

The company operates internationally, particularly in Europe and North America, and has formed partnerships with various energy companies and charging station operators. Its smart charging platform utilizes advanced algorithms and machine learning to personalize charging schedules, enhance grid stability, and support renewable energy integration. Notably, ev.energy''s ChargeWise Initiative, funded by the California Energy Commission, aims to deploy smart charging solutions at scale, connecting over 200,000 vehicles and facilitating millions of charging sessions globally.

Driven by a commitment to sustainability, ev.energy seeks to make EV charging more efficient and environmentally friendly while supporting the transition to a low-carbon economy.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c7a3e336-9414-4c53-82c5-4ce12e10fc31.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'ev', null), ('1321', 'TransferGo', 'TransferGo Ltd', 'https://www.transfergo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/transfergo/', 'TransferGo is a London-based fintech company founded in 2012, specializing in international money transfers. It primarily serves migrant workers who send remittances to their families abroad. The company operates a digital remittance platform that offers fast, transparent, and cost-effective cross-border payments through online and mobile applications, avoiding traditional bank fees.

The core service of TransferGo is its account-to-account money transfer system, allowing senders to fund transfers from their local bank accounts, with recipients receiving funds directly into their bank accounts in over 160 countries. Transfers are often completed within 30 minutes, making it one of the fastest remittance services in Europe. TransferGo has expanded its offerings to include real-time payment capabilities and business payment solutions, catering to both individual and business clients.

