Kriya, formerly known as MarketFinance, provides flexible finance solutions through an online platform, helping businesses access working capital efficiently. Since its inception in 2011, it has advanced over £2.6 billion to companies across multiple sectors. Additionally, Kriya offers a web-based business process management system that automates and manages workflows with features like drag-and-drop design and analytics dashboards. Kriya Medical Devices manufactures medical devices in molecular diagnostics, biochemistry, and diabetes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c8aab197-8414-4db0-8395-2c7cdfa5f940.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'kriya', null), ('1325', 'Relation Therapeutics', 'Relation Therapeutics Limited', 'https://www.relationrx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/relation-therapeutics/', 'Relation Therapeutics is a London-based TechBio company founded in 2019. The company specializes in AI-driven drug discovery, focusing on complex diseases such as osteoporosis, neurodegeneration, and metabolic disorders. Led by Dame Emma Walmsley, Relation Therapeutics emphasizes interdisciplinary collaboration and has raised a total of $61.3 million in funding.

The company combines machine learning, human genetics, and immune system research to explore relationships between genes, proteins, and drugs. Its methodology includes integrating active learning into drug discovery workflows and generating proprietary datasets through rapid lab experiments. This approach aims to identify biological targets and drug candidates for polygenic diseases that traditional methods may overlook. While specific drug candidates are not publicly disclosed, the pipeline likely includes small-molecule therapeutics or biologics derived from its AI platform insights.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8100703e-253a-48e4-8083-ac48fc169533.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/relationrx', null), ('1326', 'iProov', 'IPROOV LTD', 'https://www.iproov.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/iproov/', 'iProov is a leader in biometric face authentication and liveness detection technology, established in 2011. The company focuses on solving the challenge of online identity verification with its patented Genuine Presence Assurance™ technology. This ensures that the individual authenticating is real and present, effectively protecting against sophisticated fraud.

