Cytora offers a configurable platform that allows commercial insurers to digitize, evaluate, and route risks through automated workflows. This platform integrates various data sources and utilizes AI-driven analytics to transform unstructured risk information into structured, decision-ready data. Key features include the ability to automate workflows from new business submissions to claims, and the latest version, Cytora Platform 3.0, employs agentic LLMs for complex risk digitization with a focus on explainability and iterative improvement. The company collaborates with partners like Duck Creek Technologies to further enhance underwriting productivity and decision quality. 

Cytora is recognized for its contributions to the insurance technology sector, serving major clients such as QBE and AXA XL, and has received accolades for its innovative solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '8', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/52c4340e-4b42-4d24-807f-83184f9de841.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'ashby', 'cytora.com', null), ('1330', 'Modo Energy', 'Modo Energy', 'https://modoenergy.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/modo-energy/', 'Modo Energy is a software-as-a-service (SaaS) company founded in 2019, based in Camden, London. It specializes in data analytics and decision-support tools for owners, operators, and investors in renewable energy, particularly focusing on grid-scale battery energy storage systems (BESS). The company operates in both the United Kingdom and the United States.

Modo Energy''s platform offers a suite of integrated tools that assist users in navigating the energy market. Key services include performance benchmarking of battery storage assets, revenue and price forecasting, real-time data tailored for battery storage, and in-depth market research. The software is utilized by a diverse range of customers, including asset owners, investors, operators, and industry consultants, helping them optimize performance and make informed decisions.

Recognized as a trusted authority in the UK battery storage market, Modo Energy manages approximately 90% of Britain''s grid-scale battery capacity. The company is certified as a B Corporation, reflecting its commitment to environmental and social impact, particularly in supporting the transition to net zero emissions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9dacda5c-742f-49fb-b3cc-96ab0e4176e9.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'modoenergy', null), ('1331', 'PrimaryBid', 'PRIMARYBID LIMITED', 'https://www.primarybid.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/primarybid/', 'PrimaryBid is a UK-based fintech company that operates a fully digitized, FCA-regulated online platform. It connects retail investors directly with publicly listed companies seeking to raise capital. Founded by former investment bankers, PrimaryBid aims to make capital markets more inclusive and accessible to everyday investors.

The company''s technology platform allows individual investors to participate in capital raises, such as equity offerings, at discounted prices. This service was traditionally available only to institutional investors. PrimaryBid''s platform facilitates direct investment into public companies and is built in partnership with the London Stock Exchange, ensuring regulatory compliance and smooth integration with capital market operations.

PrimaryBid focuses on enabling retail participation in equity capital markets through a user-friendly digital interface. It provides access to initial public offerings (IPOs), follow-on equity offerings, and other capital raising events. By serving both retail investors and publicly listed companies, PrimaryBid promotes fairer and more inclusive capital markets. The company has garnered significant investment from various venture capital firms, reflecting confidence in its mission and growth potential.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6f2e646b-9055-46f7-86f5-2881c618438d.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1332', 'Skyports', 'Skyports Infrastructure Limited (UK)', 'https://skyports.net/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/skyports/', 'Skyports Infrastructure is a prominent player in the Advanced Air Mobility (AAM) sector, established in 2018. The company focuses on developing and operating vertiports, which are specialized landing infrastructures for electric vertical takeoff and landing (eVTOL) aircraft. These vertiports are essential for the emerging electric air taxi industry, enabling safe and efficient urban air transport.

Skyports offers various services, including vertiport development, operational management, and drone services. They design and build vertiports that adhere to industry best practices, ensuring optimal performance for eVTOL operations. Additionally, Skyports manages the operational aspects of these facilities and utilizes drone technology to enhance logistics and data capture across multiple sectors.

The company collaborates with key partners in the AAM industry, including Joby Aviation, Volocopter, Wisk, and Groupe ADP, to advance the integration of vertiports and eVTOL technology. Skyports operates globally, with notable locations in London, Paris, and Singapore, where they test and demonstrate innovative solutions for urban air mobility.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/555c27e5-c419-4c8e-91c4-43649b5b8ca0.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1333', 'Brilliant Planet', 'Brilliant Planet Limited', 'https://www.brilliantplanet.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/brilliantplanet/', 'Brilliant Planet is a climate technology company founded in 2013, based in London, UK, with operations in Morocco and Oman. The company focuses on scalable and affordable solutions to climate change by utilizing microalgae for carbon sequestration. Their innovative process allows for the cultivation of large quantities of microalgae on coastal desert land without the need for fresh water, significantly enhancing carbon capture capabilities compared to traditional forests.

The company offers a carbon removal service through open-air pond systems that sequester carbon dioxide at a gigaton scale. This technology is designed for industrial efficiency and targets sectors such as ocean conservation and climate change mitigation. Brilliant Planet markets its carbon removal credits to corporations and organizations aiming to achieve climate goals, with notable clients including global technology firms. The company has successfully raised $12 million in Series A funding to support its scaling efforts and aligns its operations with sustainable development goals.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/07db8ad9-74df-446c-a4a0-22fd5c187999.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'lever', 'brilliant', null), ('1334', 'MAIHEM', 'Maihem Ltd', 'https://www.maihem.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/maihem/', null, 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e3047034-3c4b-4688-8fef-c993ea0ef91d.png', 'false', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/maihem', null), ('1335', 'Homebox', 'Homebox Ltd', 'https://www.homebox.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/homeboxhq/', 'Homebox is a UK-based company that specializes in simplifying utility management for renters and property professionals. Founded in 2012 and headquartered in Coventry, West Midlands, Homebox offers a service that consolidates all household utility bills into a single monthly payment, making it easier for tenants to manage their expenses. The company also allows housemates to pay their individual shares of the bills, reducing disputes and confusion.

For property professionals, including letting agents and landlords, Homebox streamlines utility administration by automating notifications to suppliers about tenancy changes and managing utilities during vacant periods. The company employs between 51 and 200 people and focuses on delivering technology-driven solutions with a strong emphasis on customer service. Homebox serves thousands of tenants, letting agents, landlords, and Build to Rent operators across the UK, positioning itself as a facilitator of easier home moves and utility management.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a25feae9-5249-46dc-b0aa-91e0d94dac1e.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'homebox', null), ('1336', 'Starling Bank', 'Starling Bank Limited', 'https://www.starlingbank.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/starlingbank/', 'Starling Bank is a UK-based digital challenger bank founded in 2014 by Anne Boden. As Britain’s first fully digital bank, it operates without physical branches, providing services exclusively through its mobile app. Starling received its banking license in 2016 and has established itself as a significant player in the fintech sector, recognized for its customer-centric solutions and transparency.

