The platform features a no-code/low-code environment that empowers clients to customize workflows and manage product innovation independently. FintechOS integrates AI capabilities to enhance processes like underwriting and customer personalization. It also supports customer onboarding with automated, multi-channel journeys and streamlines back-office operations, ensuring seamless integration with existing systems. With an Ecosystem Hub that includes over 150 pre-integrated third-party services, FintechOS helps financial institutions leverage external innovations to enhance their offerings. The company serves a diverse range of clients, including major brands like Groupe Société Générale and Deloitte.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2efb1f94-a3c8-423a-a37e-1fa088b6d551.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'fintechos', null), ('1338', 'SurrealDB', 'SurrealDB Ltd', 'https://surrealdb.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/surrealdb/', 'SurrealDB is a multi-model database platform that integrates relational, document, graph, and vector databases into one cohesive system. This design simplifies application development by reducing the need to manage multiple databases and backend services, which helps lower complexity and development time. SurrealDB supports various data models and query patterns, allowing developers to work flexibly without committing to a single data model.

The platform offers a serverless cloud database and an embedded database library, making it suitable for a range of applications from edge devices to large-scale distributed clusters. Key features include real-time data synchronization, a powerful query language called SurrealQL, and built-in security measures. SurrealDB caters to developers, small and medium enterprises, and large organizations, providing tailored support and resources to enhance their data management capabilities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a03fa8d9-d4e6-469d-babe-4395a62119b2.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1339', 'Tripledot Studios', 'Tripledot Studios Limited', 'https://tripledotstudios.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tripledot-studios/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Tripledot Studios is a mobile game development company founded in 2017 by experienced professionals from King, Facebook, Product Madness, and Peak Games. Based in London, with an office in Minsk, the company has grown to employ over 90 people and is recognized as one of the top independent mobile game developers worldwide.

The company specializes in designing, developing, and publishing casual mobile games that appeal to a broad audience. Tripledot''s games are characterized by their simplicity and accessibility, with a focus on player retention through regular updates and new features. With over 25 million daily active users, Tripledot has achieved significant financial success, nearing $2 billion in annual gross revenues. In 2025, the company expanded its portfolio by acquiring AppLovin’s mobile games studio portfolio, further enhancing its offerings in the mobile gaming market.

Tripledot Studios values collaboration, creativity, and innovation, using data-driven insights to inform its game development process. The company has received industry recognition, including the “Best Developer” award at the Pocket Gamer Mobile Games Awards 2023, and has been featured on the Financial Times FT1000 list for its rapid growth.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a29184d0-5f0e-45a3-847d-d3717cc962ac.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'tripledotstudios', null), ('1340', 'Carbon Clean', 'CARBON CLEAN SOLUTIONS Limited', 'https://www.carbonclean.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carbon-clean-solutions-pvt.-ltd./?msgConversationId=6654065484306137088&msgOverlay=true', 'Carbon Clean is a leader in advanced carbon capture technology, dedicated to reducing industrial carbon emissions and facilitating the transition to net zero. Founded in 2009 and based in London, with additional offices in India, Spain, and the United States, the company has over 15 years of experience in designing and operating industrial carbon capture systems. Their mission is to capture 1 billion tonnes of industrial CO₂ emissions through scalable and cost-effective solutions that integrate seamlessly with existing operations.

The company provides a range of services and products, including proprietary solvents, tailored engineering design, modular carbon capture units, and end-to-end systems for carbon capture plants. Carbon Clean''s technologies, such as CycloneCC™ and CaptureX™, are designed for hard-to-abate industries like cement, steel, and energy-from-waste. With a strong focus on innovation and customer impact, Carbon Clean has successfully removed over 1.9 million metric tonnes of carbon from 49 facilities worldwide, supporting clients in their decarbonization efforts and contributing to the circular carbon economy.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/27d32bfe-e47e-4331-a23e-798c042ceece.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'carbon', null), ('1342', 'Fnality', 'Fnality International Limited ', 'https://www.fnality.org/home', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fnality-international/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7f261bdf_ea75_48a5_bed1_a3673192302d.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1344', 'Otta', 'Otta Technology Limited', 'https://otta.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/otta-hq', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1796ce71_0a12_4099_8797_42a4c587bedc.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1345', 'Fintech Farm ', 'FINTECH FARM LTD', 'https://www.fintech-farm.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fintech-farm1', 'Fintech Farm is a London-based fintech startup that focuses on creating and operating digital banks, or neobanks, primarily in emerging markets. Founded on March 19, 2021, by Dmytro Dubilet, Nick Bezkrovnyy, and Alexander Vityaz, the company leverages their extensive experience in the fintech sector to drive innovation in digital banking.

The company offers a range of services to assist traditional banks in establishing neobanks. This includes mobile app development, a complete technology stack for digital banking operations, advanced credit engines, and data-driven strategies for customer acquisition and retention. Fintech Farm has successfully launched neobanks in several countries, including Azerbaijan, Vietnam, India, Kyrgyzstan, and Uzbekistan, providing essential financial services to underserved populations. Their mission is to enhance financial inclusion and promote digital banking adoption in these markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/25a5284e_675f_49ce_978e_f3edbc12bd5f.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1346', 'Napier AI', 'Napier Technologies Limited', 'https://www.napier.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/napier/', 'Napier AI is a London-based compliance technology company founded in 2015. It specializes in Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and financial crime compliance solutions, utilizing big data, machine learning, and artificial intelligence. The company aims to turn compliance into a competitive advantage for financial institutions and related organizations.

Napier AI offers a unified, scalable platform that integrates various compliance tools into a single dashboard. This platform supports both on-premise and cloud deployments, making it suitable for organizations of all sizes. Key features include AI-driven decision-making for transaction monitoring and sanctions screening, a sandbox testing environment for compliance rule testing, and customizable dashboards for quick identification of suspicious activities. The company adheres to high security standards, ensuring robust data protection.

The product suite is designed for risk and compliance professionals, IT teams, and financial crime specialists across sectors like banking and asset management. Napier AI emphasizes continuous innovation with regular platform updates and provides dedicated customer support to enhance user experience.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d16c91c6_5fb2_4e6d_9733_0aedbf92c824.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'napier', null), ('1347', 'Archax', 'Archax Limited', 'https://archax.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/archaxex/', 'Archax is a London-based digital securities exchange, custodian, and brokerage firm that focuses on institutional investors in the digital asset market. As the first digital securities exchange regulated by the UK Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), Archax provides a compliant and transparent platform that connects traditional capital markets with blockchain technology.

The company offers a range of services, including a digital securities exchange for trading security tokens and cryptocurrencies, brokerage services for efficient trade execution, and custodial services for securely holding digital assets. Archax supports trading of major cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and Ethereum, as well as tokenized real-world assets, enhancing investment opportunities for institutions. With features like a user-friendly web interface, full API connectivity, and 24/7 market availability, Archax is designed to meet the needs of asset managers, hedge funds, family offices, and other professional investors looking to engage in the digital asset space.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c400ee1d_726c_4534_a93a_874a2815a087.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1348', 'Charm Therapeutics', 'Charm Therapeutics Limited', 'https://charmtx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/charm-therapeutics/', 'CHARM Therapeutics is a biotechnology company based in London, UK, founded in 2021. The company specializes in discovering and developing innovative medicines using advanced 3D deep learning and drug discovery technologies. Their proprietary DragonFold technology allows for rapid and accurate modeling of protein and small molecule interactions, which accelerates the identification of novel small molecule inhibitors targeting challenging cancer-causing genes and other disease targets.

The company focuses on drug discovery and development, particularly for cancer and other diseases with high unmet medical needs. CHARM Therapeutics has developed a pipeline of therapeutics aimed at addressing the significant portion of the human proteome that remains undruggable. They combine AI-driven methods with state-of-the-art laboratory facilities to translate computational predictions into viable drug candidates. With a commitment to an entrepreneurial and interdisciplinary culture, CHARM Therapeutics recruits talented scientists, engineers, and entrepreneurs dedicated to advancing drug discovery through innovative approaches.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6894137f_473e_4313_8555_5ec3290c78c1.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1349', 'Isometric', 'Isometric HQ Limited', 'https://isometric.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/isometric-hq/', 'Isometric operates as a carbon removal registry and science platform. The company focuses on providing high-quality carbon credits that are backed by scientific rigor and transparency. Their approach emphasizes the importance of credible and verifiable carbon offset solutions. 

Isometric is dedicated to advancing carbon removal efforts and supporting sustainability initiatives through its platform.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for some roles.', '1', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4cd88b35_3116_48a1_9065_a3a32d232a4d.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/isometric', null), ('1350', 'Panaseer', 'Panaseer Limited', 'https://panaseer.com/?nab=0', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/panaseer/', 'Panaseer is a cybersecurity company founded in 2014 by Nik Whitfield, who is the current CEO. The company specializes in a Continuous Controls Monitoring platform designed for enterprise security. This platform helps organizations enhance their security posture by automating security metrics, measurement, and reporting. It provides data-driven insights that assist security, risk, and IT leaders in making informed, risk-based decisions.

The platform aggregates and analyzes security data across an organization''s IT infrastructure, including assets and applications. By utilizing advanced analytics and machine learning, Panaseer identifies and prioritizes security risks, optimizes security investments, and automates risk assessments. This enables businesses to continuously monitor their security controls and improve their overall cybersecurity effectiveness.

Panaseer targets large enterprises, including major financial institutions and critical infrastructure organizations. The company has been recognized as a leading cybersecurity startup, earning accolades such as Europe''s Hottest CyberTech Startup at the 2019 Europas awards. It has secured approximately $15.5 million in funding from various investors, including Evolution Equity Partners and Cisco Investments.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8bfd70fa_8cbc_4a00_85a9_802b86d1dbda.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1351', 'IMMO ', 'IMMO Investment Technologies UK Limited', 'https://www.immo.capital/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/immoinvesttech/', 'IMMO is a European technology-driven residential real estate company founded in 2017. It specializes in building and managing portfolios of single-family rental homes for institutional investors. By leveraging advanced technology and expert investment management, IMMO makes the residential real estate market more accessible to these investors, who typically focus on larger multifamily projects.

The company operates an integrated platform that covers the entire real estate value chain, including capital sourcing, underwriting, acquisitions, retrofitting, renting, and property management. This comprehensive approach allows IMMO to innovate in areas such as retrofitting homes to meet energy performance standards and enhancing tenant services. With a team of over 150 professionals from leading global firms, IMMO is well-equipped to optimize returns and sustainability in residential asset management. Its primary customers are institutional investors looking to tap into the granular residential real estate market, which represents a significant portion of residential transactions in Europe.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e6c37c42_1eb3_4351_9ed4_c948e18c0098.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1352', 'Instanda', 'F2X Group Limited', 'https://instanda.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/instanda/', 'INSTANDA is a London-based technology company that specializes in a fully digital, no-code insurance management platform. Founded in 2015, it offers a solution designed for insurance carriers, Managing General Agents (MGAs), and brokers globally. The platform allows insurers to create and distribute a wide range of insurance products quickly and efficiently, with an average launch time of about 12 weeks.

The platform features no-code product design, automated workflows for quoting and underwriting, and multi-channel distribution capabilities. It also includes data management and analytics tools to enhance operational efficiency and risk evaluation. INSTANDA serves a diverse client base across over 170 countries, including major insurance carriers and brokers, and emphasizes collaboration with clients to ensure its platform meets industry needs. The company aims to make insurance more accessible and efficient, focusing on innovation and customer-centric solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/691bed7a_4e19_413f_bd8e_b526d0f860f8.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'instanda', null), ('1353', 'Synthace', 'Synthace Limited', 'https://www.synthace.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/synthace/', 'Synthace is a life sciences technology company founded in 2011 by Markus Gershater and Sean Ward. The company focuses on transforming laboratory research through automation and software innovation. Initially a synthetic biology firm, Synthace shifted in 2017 to provide a digital experiment platform that automates and optimizes life science research and development workflows.

The flagship product, Antha, is designed to simplify the programming, execution, and analysis of complex biological experiments without requiring coding skills. Antha allows scientists to design experiments, run them in automated labs, and generate structured data that integrates raw results with metadata. The platform supports various protocols, including ELISA, DNA assembly, and qPCR, and connects with laboratory devices through partnerships with companies like Hamilton and Tecan. Synthace''s platform is particularly focused on accelerating research in gene therapies and bioprocessing, while also being adaptable to other life science applications. 

The company serves a prestigious customer base, including many of the top pharmaceutical companies globally, and is led by a multidisciplinary team with expertise in life sciences and software development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6ad4e5b9_7bc5_4306_815f_5481e6a66087.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1354', 'HyperJar', 'HyperJar Limited', 'https://hyperjar.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hyperjar/', 'HyperJar is a London-based fintech company founded in 2016, focused on enhancing personal money management through its innovative digital spending and budgeting technology. Its main product, the HyperJar app, combines a digital wallet with a prepaid debit card, allowing users to organize their finances into virtual "jars" for budgeting, saving, and spending. This system helps users allocate funds for specific goals, making money management more visual and controlled.

The app includes features such as visual budgeting, group saving for shared expenses, and access to instant rewards and cashback on spending. HyperJar has gained a substantial user base, surpassing 600,000 users by 2024, and is recognized as one of the top-rated digital accounts in the UK. Additionally, HyperJar offers a B2B platform called HyperLayer, which licenses its technology to banks and merchants, enabling them to provide enhanced spending and budgeting services.

With significant funding, including a £24 million Series A round in 2023, HyperJar aims to expand its offerings beyond budgeting tools to meet the evolving needs of customers in the UK, Europe, and North America.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/13bd0748_ef44_42e9_8cad_7c6d2eaf96ea.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1355', 'PetsApp', 'PetsApp Limited', 'https://petsapp.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/petsapp/', 'PetsApp is a UK-based company located in London, founded in 2018. It offers a digital client engagement and communication platform tailored for veterinary clinics. The platform enhances interactions between veterinary teams and pet owners through various integrated tools designed to streamline practice management and improve client communication.

Key features of PetsApp''s platform include real-time communication via text, SMS, and WhatsApp, appointment scheduling with automated reminders, video consultations for remote care, and digital payment processing. It also provides wellness and loyalty plans, AI-assisted communication tools, care plan management, and marketing campaign management. The platform supports over 15,000 veterinary professionals globally and has registered more than 6.3 million pets, processing over $13 million in transactions.

Additionally, PetsApp fosters a community called PetsApp Together, which offers veterinary professionals access to a learning library, training academy, and continuing professional development events. This commitment to supporting veterinary teams helps improve operational efficiency and enhances pet owner satisfaction.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/55e76b54_e869_4b0b_9a5e_92aae989d795.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1357', 'Forecast', 'Forecast Technologies limited', 'https://www.forecast.app/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/forecasthq', 'Forecast is a software company founded in 2016, based in Copenhagen, Denmark, with an additional presence in London. The company specializes in AI-native Professional Services Automation (PSA) software, aimed at enhancing project delivery and resource management for professional services organizations. With a team of around 72 employees, Forecast has successfully raised $5.5 million in funding.

The platform integrates various functionalities, including project management, resource management, team collaboration, accounting, and business intelligence. It leverages AI to analyze historical project data, helping users predict resource needs, identify potential delays, and optimize team assignments. Key features include AI-powered timesheets, project planning tools, resource management capabilities, and financial management tools such as invoicing and real-time margin analysis. Forecast''s platform is designed to provide real-time insights, enabling teams to deliver projects on time and within budget while improving billable hours and utilization rates. 

Target customers include tech startups, marketing agencies, IT departments, and professional services firms looking to enhance their project planning and financial oversight through AI-driven automation. The company fosters a culture of innovation and collaboration, offering various employee benefits to support well-being and continuous learning.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/914375d6_d4da_4a21_af12_6e1e3245511f.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'forecasthq', null), ('1358', 'FaceIT', 'Face It Limited', 'https://www.faceit.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/face-it-ltd-/', 'FACEIT Ltd is an independent esports platform founded in London in 2011 by Niccolo Maisto, Michele Attisani, and Alessandro Avallone. The company specializes in competitive online multiplayer gaming, allowing players to participate in tournaments and leagues for both virtual and real-world prizes. With over 25 million users worldwide, FACEIT hosts millions of game sessions each month across popular esports titles like Counter-Strike 2, League of Legends, and Dota 2.

FACEIT organizes and administers competitive leagues and tournaments, providing structured play and social features that support the competitive gaming ecosystem. The platform connects players, organizers, game developers, and brands in a community-driven environment. A significant milestone for FACEIT was hosting the FACEIT Major: London 2018, the first Counter-Strike: Global Offensive Major in the UK, which featured a $1 million prize pool.

In January 2022, FACEIT was acquired by Savvy Gaming Group, leading to the formation of the ESL FACEIT Group. This acquisition combined FACEIT’s platform with ESL’s event management expertise, enhancing its role in the global esports industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/23080402_088b_4c12_b31e_5480367b3bb8.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1360', 'Doctify', 'Doctify Limited', 'https://www.doctify.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/doctify/', 'Doctify is a healthtech company based in London, founded in 2015. It operates a global healthcare platform that enhances transparency, trust, and accessibility in private healthcare. The platform connects patients with healthcare providers, including doctors, dentists, clinics, and hospitals, across multiple countries such as the UK, UAE, Germany, and Austria.

The core service of Doctify is its online booking and review platform, which allows patients to search, compare, and book appointments with healthcare specialists quickly. It features verified patient reviews to help users make informed decisions. For healthcare providers, Doctify offers tools to manage their online reputation, collect patient feedback, and improve visibility. The company aims to support 100 million patients by 2025, fostering a patient-centric approach in healthcare. With offices in London, Munich, and Vienna, Doctify emphasizes innovation, security, and collaboration in its mission to improve healthcare experiences.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bbdc78f1_6fe0_4591_9f48_19b898bd299e.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'doctify', null), ('1361', 'Slamcore', 'SLAMcore Limited', 'https://www.slamcore.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/slamcore-limited/', 'Slamcore is a UK-based technology company that specializes in Spatial AI software for real-time localization, mapping, and perception, primarily aimed at robotics and autonomous machines. Founded in 2016 as a spin-out from Imperial College London, Slamcore utilizes advanced vision-based SLAM, sensor fusion, and AI to help robots, drones, and autonomous vehicles navigate complex environments with precision.

The company offers a Software Development Kit (SDK) that integrates vision-based SLAM and sensor fusion algorithms, enabling real-time localization and mapping capabilities. This SDK supports various operating systems and works with both off-the-shelf and custom sensors. Additionally, Slamcore Aware, set to launch in 2024, is designed for industrial automation, enhancing safety and efficiency by tracking vehicles and assets in real time. Slamcore serves a wide range of industries, including robotics, autonomous vehicles, and industrial automation, and has onboarded over 100 companies to its SDK.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2f4e61d6_1df8_45d9_a500_d526e22de45b.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1362', 'Pactio', 'Pactio Technologies Limited', 'https://pactio.io', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pactio-tech/', 'Pactio is a London-based technology company founded in 2021, specializing in digital solutions for private capital markets, particularly private equity. The company offers a transaction management platform that streamlines deal execution, risk management, and workflow automation for private capital investors and their advisors. 

Pactio''s platform serves as a multi-sided tool for various stakeholders, including investors, lawyers, tax advisers, and fund administrators. Key features include centralized deal data for improved accuracy, tools for monitoring deal progress, and AI-native accounting workflows integrated with Microsoft Office. The platform aims to replace outdated manual processes, providing a more efficient and reliable approach to private equity deal-making.

Pactio targets private equity firms and their professional advisors, forming strategic partnerships with firms like Alvarez & Marsal. The company has successfully raised £11 million in a Series A funding round, highlighting its innovative position in the private capital technology sector.', 'The company can offer sponsorship for the majority of their roles in the UK.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dda87771_6c46_4222_9f23_10988f51fe62.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1363', 'Connected Kerb', 'Connected Kerb Limited', 'https://www.connectedkerb.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/connected-kerb/', 'Connected Kerb is a UK-based electric vehicle (EV) charging company founded in 2017 and headquartered in London. The company focuses on creating inclusive, convenient, and reliable EV charging solutions. It specializes in the manufacture and deployment of charge points that integrate power and data delivery at the kerbside, supporting the development of smart urban infrastructure.

With a nationwide network of approximately 10,000 charge points, Connected Kerb is one of the fastest-growing EV charge point networks in the UK. The company serves a diverse range of customers, including public sector bodies, property developers, fleet operators, workplaces, car parks, and local authorities. Its mission is to accelerate the transition to electric vehicles and promote sustainable mobility through scalable and dependable charging networks.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/89f21de4_5d9f_408e_be37_f34372e6697a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1364', 'Selina Finance', 'Selina Finance Limited', 'https://www.selinafinance.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/selina-finance-limited/', 'Selina Finance is a UK-based fintech company founded in 2018 and headquartered in London. It specializes in secured lending products that help homeowners leverage the equity in their properties. Notably, it is the first company in the UK to offer a Home Equity Line of Credit (HELOC), allowing customers to draw, repay, and redraw funds over a five-year period without early repayment charges. Selina Finance is regulated by the FCA and aims to empower homeowners by providing simple and flexible financial solutions.

The company offers a range of products, including HELOCs and traditional homeowner loans, which cater to various funding needs such as home improvements, debt consolidation, and education expenses. With loan-to-value ratios up to 85%, Selina Finance provides options for both fixed and variable rates, accommodating diverse income types. The application process is efficient, allowing customers to receive quotes quickly and access funds within 48 hours after approval. As a Certified B Corp™, Selina Finance is committed to social and environmental performance, reflecting its dedication to responsible lending and customer satisfaction.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c8ba9c41_25bb_468f_81cd_e7fc1264ccca.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'recruitee', 'selinafinance', null), ('1365', 'Monument Bank', 'Monument Bank Limited', 'https://www.monument.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/monumentbank/', 'No specific information found.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0f5820ff_23bf_4efe_92ba_46bf65b0420f.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1366', 'Brsk', 'Brsk Limited', 'https://www.brsk.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/brskfullfibre/', 'Brsk is a UK-based full-fibre broadband provider established in 2020 by Giorgio Iovino and Ian Kock. The company builds, owns, and operates its own fibre-optic network, delivering gigabit-capable internet to homes and businesses in underserved towns and suburban areas, including West Yorkshire, Lancashire, Greater Manchester, Cheshire, and the West Midlands.

Brsk offers ultrafast broadband with speeds up to 14 times faster than the UK average, typically around 900Mbps. Their fibre-only optic cables ensure low latency and high reliability, making them suitable for streaming, gaming, and multi-device usage. The company provides a variety of flexible broadband packages, including no-contract options and transparent pricing. Brsk manages the entire process from network construction to customer installation and support, emphasizing a customer-centric approach with a dedicated team based in the UK and South Africa.

In June 2024, Brsk merged with Netomnia, creating the second-largest alternative fibre network in the UK. This merger aims to expand coverage to three million premises, enhancing access to full-fibre connectivity for more communities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f1e8599b_4796_46fb_a2c8_502762c67a37.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'teamtailor', 'app', null), ('1368', 'Vorboss', 'Vorboss Limited', 'http://vorboss.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/vorboss/', 'Vorboss is a UK-based telecommunications company that specializes in high-capacity enterprise fibre networks, primarily serving business customers in Central London. Founded in 2006, Vorboss has built one of the highest capacity fibre networks in the area, offering dedicated fibre connectivity with minimum speeds of 10 Gbps, scalable up to 100 Gbps. The company owns and operates its entire infrastructure, featuring over 500 km of underground fibre-optic cables that connect various telecom chambers, datacenters, and customer sites.

In addition to dedicated fibre connectivity, Vorboss provides managed IT services, including onboarding, user management, and troubleshooting. They also offer proactive cybersecurity protection, ensuring clients have comprehensive support for their IT needs. Vorboss is committed to sustainability, exemplified by their innovative electric cargo bicycle for network servicing, designed to operate efficiently within London''s Clean Air Zone. With a strong focus on customer service and engineering excellence, Vorboss is a preferred provider for businesses requiring reliable and scalable internet and IT solutions.', 'The company is not currently offering visa sponsorship.', '2', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/78da8f69_6d9a_4115_9d47_34d8c336b259.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1369', 'Revalue', 'Revalue Nature Ltd', 'https://revalue.earth', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/revalue-nature/', 'Revalue is a company focused on creating high-quality carbon credits to promote environmental sustainability and address climate change. Their mission is to develop reliable carbon credits that support businesses and investors in their carbon reduction efforts while allowing them to concentrate on their core activities.

The company collaborates with project operators, who are leading entities implementing carbon reduction initiatives, and strategic capital investors, who provide funding for large-scale environmental projects. Revalue emphasizes the integrity and effectiveness of carbon credits, which represent the reduction or removal of one metric ton of carbon dioxide or equivalent greenhouse gases. By prioritizing transparency and quality, Revalue aims to foster trust in carbon markets and drive meaningful climate action.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/74dbcbe6_62d1_477d_a0d4_2714ec4f8611.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'revalue', null), ('1371', 'Mirriad', 'Mirriad Advertising Plc', 'https://www.mirriad.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mirriad/', 'Mirriad is a global leader in virtual product placement (VPP) and in-content advertising. The company offers an AI-powered platform that seamlessly integrates brands and products into premium video content across various media, including television, streaming services, and influencer channels. This innovative approach enhances advertising effectiveness and viewer engagement while creating new revenue opportunities for content owners.

Founded on award-winning technology initially used in feature films, Mirriad operates in over 11 countries and collaborates with more than 100 global brands and 60 premium content partners. Its services include a virtual product placement platform that uses patented AI and computer vision technology, a diverse supplier marketplace, and programmatic virtual integrations. These offerings allow advertisers to connect authentically with audiences and help content owners monetize their inventory effectively.

