The company provides services such as automated transaction servicing, securitization as a service, AI-driven credit scoring, and advanced analytics. These tools enhance risk transparency and streamline the securitization process. Tradeteq has processed over $4.5 billion in notes and collaborates with more than 100 institutional investors and 85 asset originators. The company aims to support small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) by improving liquidity and working capital management. Headquartered in London, Tradeteq is recognized for its commitment to security and operational excellence with a SOC2 Type 2 attestation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/87bd144f_0f0a_4f89_9222_104b6430c90f.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1415', 'AviadoBio', 'Aviadobio Limited', 'https://aviadobio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/aviadobio/', 'AviadoBio is a British biotechnology company based in London, established in 2019. The company specializes in developing gene therapies for neurodegenerative disorders, particularly frontotemporal dementia (FTD) and amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS). AviadoBio builds on research from King’s College London and the UK Dementia Research Institute, aiming to improve patient lives by addressing the genetic causes of these diseases.

The company''s lead product candidate, AVB-101, is an investigational gene therapy designed to treat FTD caused by GRN gene mutations. This therapy delivers a functional copy of the GRN gene directly to affected brain regions through a minimally invasive procedure. AviadoBio focuses on the research, development, and clinical translation of gene therapies, utilizing expertise in vector design and precision delivery to create effective gene therapy vectors.

AviadoBio attracts investment from notable venture capital and life sciences firms, reflecting its commitment to advancing gene therapies on a global scale. The company engages with patients, clinical researchers, healthcare providers, and the medical community to promote innovative treatments for neurodegenerative diseases.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d80345eb_b296_41ab_a9da_457fddb71997.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'aviadobio', null), ('1416', 'Qflow', 'Qualis Flow Limited', 'https://www.qualisflow.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/qualis-flow/', 'Qualis Flow, known as Qflow, is a technology company founded in May 2018 and based in London, England. The company focuses on transforming the construction industry by promoting sustainable practices and reducing environmental impact. Qflow leverages data-driven insights and technology to create a more efficient and responsible construction sector.

Qflow offers a digital platform that collects real-time materials and waste data from construction sites. This platform enables teams to make informed decisions regarding costs, carbon footprints, and quality. It features automated auditing processes to enhance data quality and integrates with existing tools like Power BI and SAP for streamlined data management. Additionally, Qflow supports sustainability and ESG reporting, helping construction teams identify opportunities to reduce carbon emissions and improve compliance with environmental standards.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a2dd1500_94c9_4876_a6c1_41ce47f36df7.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'qflow', null), ('1417', 'General Index', 'General Index Ltd', 'https://www.general-index.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/generalindex/', 'General Index is a UK-based company that specializes in providing energy commodity price benchmarks. Founded in 2019 and headquartered in London, it offers over 4,000 daily prices across a wide range of commodities, including crude oil, refined products, sustainable aviation fuels, hydrogen, and biofuels. The company focuses on data-driven transparency and consistency, relying on extensive data for its pricing indices.

General Index provides flexible data access options, including APIs and terminal integration, making it easy for clients to incorporate their data into existing systems. The company partners with clients to tailor data solutions for their specific needs, supporting energy consulting firms and financial services with reliable pricing data. Its pricing data is trusted by major industry players such as Bloomberg, BP, ExxonMobil, and TotalEnergies, underscoring its credibility in the energy and financial sectors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/79e35cfe_ad88_47f4_bcf7_193b466e3fe1.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'hibob', 'generalindex', null), ('1418', 'Bike Club', 'The Bike Club Limited', 'https://bikeclub.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bike-club/', 'Bike Club is a UK-based company founded in 2016 that provides a subscription service for children''s bikes. Families can rent and exchange bikes as their children grow, ensuring they always have the right size. With over 50,000 members, Bike Club is one of the largest kids’ bike rental networks globally and the second largest overall. The company is committed to sustainability and social responsibility, having been certified as a B-Corp in 2023.

The service includes monthly subscription plans with no large upfront costs and flexible exchanges for larger bike sizes. Customers can cancel or exchange their subscriptions at any time. Bike Club refurbishes returned bikes to high standards, supporting a circular economy and reducing waste. The subscription options cover various categories of kids’ bikes, including balance bikes, first pedals, hybrid bikes, and mountain bikes, catering to families looking for cost-effective and convenient cycling solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6b84c7b1_4af3_4d47_844c_742098f496af.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1419', 'AgDevCo', 'AgDevCo Limited', 'https://www.agdevco.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/agdevco/', 'AgDevCo is a UK-based private limited company that focuses on long-term debt and equity investments in African agriculture. Founded in 2008, the company aims to reduce poverty and improve food security by developing a robust commercial agricultural sector across eight African countries, including Ghana, Malawi, and Uganda. AgDevCo acts as a specialist investor, supporting early-stage and growth-stage agribusinesses with proven business models.

The company provides financing across the agricultural value chain, including investments in inputs, primary production, processing, and storage, marketing, and distribution. AgDevCo typically invests amounts starting from $250,000 and partners with established regional businesses for broader investments. Its financial instruments are designed to support agribusiness growth and sustainability, complemented by technical assistance to enhance operational and governance standards. AgDevCo''s efforts have positively impacted over 764,000 small-scale farmers and created or sustained approximately 15,600 jobs, highlighting its commitment to social and economic development in the region.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a622d757_68ee_43eb_a296_1e35a018a86a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1422', 'Complement Therapeutics', 'Complement Therapeutics Limited', 'https://complementtx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/complement-therapeutics/', 'Complement Therapeutics is an early-stage biotechnology company focused on developing novel therapeutics for complement-mediated diseases. Originating from the University of Manchester, the company is dedicated to addressing conditions caused by dysregulation of the complement system. Its lead product, CTx001, is a gene therapy candidate aimed at treating dry age-related macular degeneration, a significant cause of blindness.

The company has created the Complement Precision Medicine (CPM) platform, which utilizes a mass spectrometry-based methodology to analyze over 30 proteins in the complement cascade from blood samples. This technology enhances diagnosis, patient stratification, and monitoring of complement-related diseases, supporting a precision medicine approach. Complement Therapeutics is also exploring various therapeutic modalities, including adeno-associated virus (AAV) gene therapies and protein-based treatments, to meet unmet medical needs in this area. Headquartered in Germany, the company has successfully raised substantial funding to advance its research and development efforts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/fc5fc050_0aea_4f94_a5e0_9710c0833c9b.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1423', 'Molo Finance', 'Colcap Financial UK Limited', 'https://molofinance.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/molofinance/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Molo is a fintech company based in London, founded in 2017. It specializes in digital mortgage solutions and is recognized as the UK''s first fully-digital mortgage lender. Molo offers a seamless online experience with real-time lending decisions, aiming to innovate the mortgage industry.

The company provides a variety of mortgage products, including buy-to-let mortgages, residential mortgages, portfolio BTL mortgages, HMO mortgages, and remortgage options. Molo also caters to first-time landlords entering the buy-to-let market. Its services are designed for individual landlords, portfolio landlords, and overseas customers through intermediary partners.

Molo is led by CEO Matt Kimber and supported by a team of executives. The company has received venture capital backing and secured Series A funding in 2020 to aid its growth and product diversification. Molo operates from its London office and continues to focus on delivering digital mortgage services.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c28b3e4d_128a_4c24_8731_be5a1c9819e7.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1424', 'Piclo', 'Open Utility Limited', 'https://www.piclo.energy/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/piclo/', 'Piclo is a global software company that operates the leading independent marketplace for energy flexibility. Its mission is to accelerate the decarbonization of electricity grids by connecting flexibility providers with buyers across various markets. Piclo''s platforms facilitate the efficient procurement, operation, and settlement of flexibility services, helping to balance supply and demand in renewable energy systems.

The company offers several innovative solutions, including Piclo Marketplace, which connects buyers and sellers of energy flexibility, and Piclo Flex, a cloud-based platform for managing local flexibility markets. Piclo Max allows flexibility sellers to access multiple electricity markets from a single interface, while Piclo Engage provides transparency and control over energy usage for generators and consumers. With a strong presence in the USA, Europe, and Australia, Piclo serves a diverse range of stakeholders, including utilities and energy retailers, and has facilitated over $100 million in flexibility contracts globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ed07acea_30bd_4375_8deb_5e6331a5c5da.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1425', 'Snoop', 'Usnoop Limited', 'https://snoop.app/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/snoop', 'Snoop is a consumer-focused technology company based in Bradford, UK, founded in April 2020 by Dame Jayne-Anne Gadhia. The company aims to help individuals spend, save, and live smarter by providing data-driven financial insights through its core product, the Snoop app. This mobile application connects to users'' financial accounts using open banking to analyze spending patterns and deliver personalized recommendations for saving money.

