The company offers an immersive F1 racing simulation experience with 60 motion-enabled simulators suitable for all skill levels. Guests can enjoy a premium hospitality experience featuring a diverse food menu and stylish beverage options, including F1-themed cocktails. F1® Arcade venues are designed with sophisticated interiors that reflect the excitement of Formula 1, creating a competitive and social atmosphere. They also host watch parties for live Grand Prix events, enhancing the fan experience.

Currently, F1® Arcade has locations in London, Birmingham, and Boston Seaport, with plans to open in Washington D.C. in Fall 2024 and a flagship site in Las Vegas in 2025. The company aims to establish 30 locations worldwide over the next five years, combining technology, hospitality, and the allure of Formula 1 racing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/48058ccc_fb63_44de_b03f_9b7381cd4ae9.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1430', 'Altruistiq', 'Expanding Circle Limited', 'https://altruistiq.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/altruistiq/', 'Altruistiq is a London-based technology company founded in January 2021 by Saif Hameed. The company focuses on helping enterprise brands build, buy, and sell products that are better for the planet through advanced sustainability data solutions. Altruistiq''s mission is to equip sustainability teams with accurate environmental data, enabling informed decisions to manage and reduce carbon footprints effectively.

The company offers a Sustainability Data Management Platform tailored for large enterprises with complex global supply chains. This platform automates the measurement, management, and exchange of sustainability data, allowing companies to track their environmental impact in real time. Key features include granular insights for detailed sustainability analysis, automated data integration, and an audit-ready design compliant with international greenhouse gas accounting standards. Altruistiq emphasizes measurable impact and transparency, reflected in its B-Corp certification and commitment to a carbon-neutral strategy. The company fosters a culture of empathy, continuous learning, and collaboration, dedicated to advancing sustainability through technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d3936c7e_9bed_4b00_9427_c6b6c4238c0a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1431', 'SDCl Group', 'Sustainable Development Capital LLP', 'https://www.sdclgroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sustainable-development-capital-llp/', 'Sustainable Development Capital LLP (SDCL) is a London-based investment firm specializing in energy transition solutions. Established in 2007, SDCL manages over $2.5 billion in assets and operates globally with offices in major cities including New York, Dublin, and Singapore. The firm is regulated by the UK Financial Conduct Authority and is committed to sustainability, being a signatory to the UN Principles for Responsible Investment.

SDCL focuses on developing and investing in sustainable energy infrastructure projects. Their services include energy efficiency solutions such as LED lighting and HVAC systems, on-site generation like solar energy with storage, and decentralized energy solutions for commercial and public sector clients. Additionally, SDCL''s investment banking division offers strategic financial advisory services in the energy, water, and waste sectors. The firm serves a diverse range of clients, including Citigroup, the UK National Health Service, and Tesco, and is actively involved in projects that support net-zero targets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ad5bce87_9655_42ba_b60d_632444e1a990.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'sdclgroup', null), ('1432', 'Freddie''s Flowers', 'Freddie''s Flowers Ltd', 'https://www.freddiesflowers.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/freddie%27s-flowers/', 'Freddie''s Flowers is a UK-based company founded in October 2014 by Freddie Garland. It operates as a direct-to-consumer flower subscription service, delivering unique, seasonal flower arrangements to customers'' homes. The company aims to make flowers more accessible and promotes them as an everyday joy rather than just for special occasions.

Freddie''s Flowers offers a variety of carefully curated seasonal stems in different sizes. Customers can subscribe for regular deliveries or purchase arrangements as one-off gifts. The company has experienced significant growth, nearly doubling its customer base and expanding its operations into Germany. 

Headquartered in the London Borough of Wandsworth, Freddie''s Flowers is a Certified B Corporation, reflecting its commitment to ethical and sustainable practices. It focuses on product quality, ethical marketing, and customer feedback, appealing to consumers who value fresh, responsibly sourced flowers delivered conveniently.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f1cf1a87_3aea_40ce_8546_2723c34041cb.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1433', 'Pirum', 'Pirum Systems Limited', 'https://www.pirum.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pirum-systems-ltd/', 'Pirum is a UK-based financial services technology company founded in 2000 and headquartered in London. It specializes in providing automated and secure solutions for the securities finance and collateral management industries. Pirum''s platform covers the entire trade lifecycle, from pre-trade to post-trade and collateral services, and is recognized as a global industry standard.

The company offers a centralized platform that facilitates near real-time communication and processing of securities finance transactions. Its services include trade reconciliation, lifecycle event management, billing, and regulatory compliance support. Pirum''s solutions are designed to integrate seamlessly with clients'' existing systems, enhancing operational efficiency and risk management. With a client base of over 150 financial institutions, including many of the world''s leading banks and asset managers, Pirum plays a critical role in the global securities finance market, processing over USD 3 trillion in transactions daily.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1e2994c6_bfa3_4da8_be01_09c7fefbfa78.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1434', 'Leah', 'ContractPod Technologies Limited', 'https://leahai.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/leahai-ai', 'Leah (formerly ContractPodAi) is an enterprise software company focused on agentic AI for legal, contracting, procurement, finance, and adjacent functions. Its portfolio centers on Leah Agentic OS—an operating system for building and orchestrating intelligent domain agents—and Leah Agentic CLM, a contract lifecycle management product. Positioned to augment human judgment, Leah’s platform automates complex workflows, integrates data across systems, and emphasizes governance, compliance, and measurable ROI. The company cites partnerships with leading AI providers and a security posture that includes SOC 1/SOC 2 compliance, GDPR/CCPA alignment, and zero‑retention policies with certain model providers. Leah operates globally with offices including London and New York and traces its roots to contract management, with subsequent expansion into broader agentic AI orchestration.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e9db4a7f_28b1_493f_a9e9_1ac66c58adc2.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'leah', null), ('1435', 'Resolution Therapeutics', 'Resolution Therapeutics Ltd', 'https://resolution-tx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/resolution-therapeutics/', 'Resolution Therapeutics is a biotechnology company dedicated to developing macrophage cell therapies for severe inflammatory and fibrotic organ diseases, with a primary focus on chronic liver disease and cirrhosis. Founded in 2019 through a collaboration involving the University of Edinburgh, the Scottish National Blood Transfusion Service, and Syncona Investment Management, the company aims to enhance treatment options for patients facing hepatic decompensation.

