The company offers a unique solution that captures real-time feedback from restaurant guests through its One-Minute Review platform. This tool engages a significant percentage of customers and delivers insights at various levels, including location, shift, server, and dish. Yumpingo also features Yumpingo Pay, a pay-at-table solution that enhances the dining experience. 

Yumpingo collaborates with major restaurant brands like Texas Roadhouse, California Pizza Kitchen, and Nando’s, showcasing its capability to support large-scale operations. The company aims to expand internationally, focusing on improving customer satisfaction and operational efficiency in the hospitality sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3a2cb037_3ee8_428f_8039_5fa03246febd.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1458', 'UpdraftPlus', 'Updraft WP Software Ltd', 'https://updraftplus.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/updraftplus/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7e8d3b4e_262e_44f1_8ade_4a063b52b762.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'workable', 'teamupdraft', null), ('1459', 'TreesPlease Games', 'TreesPlease Games Limited', 'https://www.treespleasegames.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/treesplease-games/', 'TreesPlease Games is a UK-based mobile video game developer founded in 2019, with a mission to address climate change through engaging gameplay. Headquartered in Brighton, the company creates casual free-to-play games that integrate environmental themes. Their flagship game, *Longleaf Valley*, allows players to restore landscapes by merging items and planting virtual trees, with profits supporting real-world tree planting initiatives.

The company operates with a skilled team of about 15 professionals, many of whom have experience at major studios like King and Ubisoft. TreesPlease Games emphasizes a positive work culture and aims to provide players with enjoyable experiences that also contribute to environmental causes. Their target audience includes casual mobile gamers who appreciate merge games and are motivated by sustainability. Through their innovative approach, TreesPlease Games combines entertainment with a commitment to making a positive impact on the planet.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bd692457_c320_4f95_bb25_303c82cfdf8e.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1460', 'Etopia', 'Project Etopia', 'https://www.etopia.eco/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/project-etopia/', 'Etopia is a national manufacturer and supplier specializing in high-performance Structural Insulated Panel (SIP) solutions, primarily serving the South West of the UK. The company offers a full turnkey service that encompasses design, manufacture, delivery, installation, and aftercare support for their panellised building systems.

Their core product is a load-bearing SIP system that enables developers, housing associations, and construction clients to create energy-efficient and sustainable structures. Etopia manufactures SIPs offsite in high volumes, ensuring timely delivery and installation. Their services include design collaboration with clients, offsite manufacturing of various components, project management for delivery and installation, and ongoing sales and aftercare support.

Etopia emphasizes sustainability and efficiency throughout the building lifecycle, encouraging early project engagement to maximize savings in carbon emissions, time, and resources. They cater to stakeholders involved in sustainable building projects, providing innovative construction solutions that focus on high performance and environmental impact.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f6e60559_3ddf_4cc3_b0a8_42fe3b216387.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1461', 'Quintain', 'Quintain Services Limited', 'https://www.quintain.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quintain-estates-and-development/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Quintain Limited is a British property investment and development company founded in 1992 and based in London. The company specializes in urban regeneration and mixed-use developments, focusing on transforming large sites into vibrant communities. Its flagship project, Wembley Park, is the largest build-to-rent development in the UK, featuring over 5,000 homes, retail spaces, leisure facilities, and hospitality venues.

Quintain operates as a vertically integrated business, managing all aspects of property development from land acquisition to asset management. This approach ensures quality and innovation throughout the development process. In addition to its London projects, Quintain has expanded into Ireland, where it manages over 460 acres of development land and plans to deliver thousands of homes and commercial spaces. The company''s diverse portfolio includes residential, retail, office, leisure, and healthcare properties, as well as student accommodation and science parks. Quintain often collaborates with institutional investors and other developers to execute large-scale regeneration projects.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/76899aae_0228_4241_891d_744b048d47a7.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1462', 'Tymit', 'Tymit Ltd', 'https://tymit.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tymit/', 'Tymit is a fintech company based in England, founded in 2019. It specializes in flexible and transparent credit and installment payment solutions, primarily for businesses in the retail and travel sectors. Tymit operates as a one-stop platform that allows these businesses to offer branded installment programs to their customers, utilizing open-loop credit card rails and Visa’s infrastructure.

The company provides a white-labelled installment platform with modular APIs, enabling partners to integrate installment payment capabilities into their customer journeys. Tymit’s offerings include installment programs that allow post-purchase payments in flexible installments, as well as Buy Now Pay Later (BNPL) solutions that prioritize transparency and simplicity. The platform also features loyalty schemes and credit-building tools to enhance customer engagement. Tymit aims to improve financial health and customer experience by giving users control over their repayment schedules and eliminating hidden fees.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/398eb551_4831_45ae_b9b4_b4cd9a537bc5.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1463', 'Kennek', 'Kennek Solutions Limited', 'https://kennek.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kennek/', 'kennek is a London-based fintech company that specializes in loan management software for lenders. Founded in 2021, it operates as KENNEK SOLUTIONS LTD and offers a comprehensive SaaS platform that manages all aspects of lending operations, from loan origination to maturity. The platform is designed by former lenders who understand the challenges in the industry, ensuring it effectively addresses operational inefficiencies.

The software includes features such as automated loan origination and lifecycle management, configurable workflows, and risk management tools. It also provides investor management capabilities, automating reporting and performance tracking. Kennek primarily serves lenders and loan investors, helping them operate more efficiently and cost-effectively. The company has raised significant funding, reflecting strong investor confidence in its innovative approach to loan management.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ffde3f3d_6dfe_4214_977b_76c3af75e6d6.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1464', 'Medefer', 'Medefer Ltd', 'https://medefer.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/medefer/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Medefer is a UK-based digital healthcare company that specializes in virtual outpatient services. Founded in 2013, the company connects patients directly with consultant specialists through a digital-first model, improving access to specialist care while reducing waiting times and travel needs. Medefer operates as a CQC-registered healthcare provider and partners with the NHS to enhance outpatient care using technology.

The company offers three core services: consultant-led care, a virtual outpatient pathway that manages the patient journey from GP referral to discharge, and a technology platform for efficient virtual consultations. Medefer''s system allows NHS consultants to review cases significantly faster than traditional methods, helping to reduce outpatient costs and improve patient outcomes. Their range of specialist treatments includes weight loss management, skin problem treatments, menopause support, prostate cancer testing, and sleep problem management.

Medefer prioritizes patient safety and data security, employing bank-level encryption and adhering to NHS safety frameworks. The company values collaboration, innovation, and a patient-first approach, aiming to build a diverse team that reflects the communities it serves.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4851ea69_98ea_42ce_9651_7ae1e6543971.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'medefer', null), ('1465', 'Penfold', 'Penfold Technology Limited', 'https://getpenfold.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/penfold/', 'Penfold is a UK-based fintech company that specializes in pension savings solutions. Founded in 2019, its mission is to simplify and modernize workplace auto-enrolment for both employers and employees. The company aims to help individuals save more consistently for retirement through a flexible and transparent pension platform. Penfold focuses on building healthy saving habits by providing real-time visibility into pension growth and offering friendly customer support.

The digital pension platform allows users to manage their retirement savings with ease, offering flexibility over contributions and investment choices. It also streamlines the auto-enrolment process for employers, making compliance straightforward. Penfold serves a diverse clientele, including self-employed individuals, limited company directors, full-time employees, and businesses seeking improved pension solutions. With over 100,000 users and recognition from industry awards, Penfold is committed to making pensions accessible and user-friendly.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/87a11e1f_7510_420f_9ffb_e3e2631b9a9e.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1466', 'HICX', 'HICX Solutions Ltd', 'https://www.hicx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hicx/', 'HICX is a technology company focused on Supplier Experience Management (SXM). They provide a cloud-native, low-code platform that helps large enterprises optimize their supplier relationships and manage data effectively. The platform consolidates supplier information from various systems, streamlining processes such as onboarding, master data management, and compliance. This creates a single source of truth for supplier data, enhancing efficiency for both enterprises and their suppliers.

The HICX platform integrates seamlessly with existing enterprise technology, supporting rapid deployment and scalability. With a supplier-first approach, it aims to simplify business interactions between suppliers and their customers, fostering mutual value. HICX serves a diverse range of large, global enterprises, including notable clients like Mondelez International, BAE Systems, and EDF Energy. Headquartered in London, UK, HICX operates in a collaborative environment that supports innovation and access to talent and strategic partners.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/cfd7abb8_2a96_40db_acb8_6bdb57423156.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workable', 'hicx-solutions', null), ('1467', 'Gresham House', 'Gresham House Limited', 'https://greshamhouse.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gresham-house/', 'Gresham House is a specialist asset management company based in London, with a history dating back to 1857. It is publicly listed on the London Stock Exchange under the ticker GHE. The company manages over £8.5 billion in assets and focuses on delivering sustainable investment performance while maintaining high service standards for a diverse range of clients.

The firm specializes in illiquid and differentiated assets, with a strong emphasis on sustainable and impact-driven investments. Its expertise is divided into two main areas: Real Assets, which includes forestry, energy transition, sustainable infrastructure, and real estate, and Strategic Equity, which encompasses investments in both public and private equity markets. Gresham House offers a variety of investment funds and tailored opportunities designed to meet the needs of individual investors, financial advisers, institutional investors, family offices, charities, and endowments. The company is committed to creating long-term value through investments that also deliver positive environmental and social outcomes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8c8e6893_08d5_41d5_93ca_0236b9b0d6ed.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'gresham', null), ('1468', 'Quinbrook Infrastructure Partners', 'Quinbrook Infrastructure Partners Limited', 'https://www.quinbrook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quinbrook-infrastructure-partners/?originalSubdomain=au', 'Quinbrook Infrastructure Partners is a specialist investment manager dedicated to renewable energy infrastructure. Founded in July 2015 by David Scaysbrook and Rory Quinlan, the company focuses on low-carbon and renewable energy projects in the US, UK, and Australia. With a leadership team that has invested over USD 5.6 billion in equity capital since the early 1990s, Quinbrook is well-equipped to support the energy transition.

The company invests in a variety of technologies, including solar photovoltaic projects, onshore wind farms, battery storage solutions, biomass energy, and electric vehicle charging infrastructure. Quinbrook also engages in fugitive methane recovery, demand response, grid support, and the development of community energy networks. With offices in New York, Houston, London, and Brisbane, Quinbrook leverages local expertise to manage its diverse portfolio effectively. Their commitment to ESG practices has earned them several awards, highlighting their role in advancing sustainable energy solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3d588a46_6df2_441a_a6fe_8f445afb50c9.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1469', 'Moonpig', 'Moonpic.com Limited', 'https://www.moonpig.group/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/moonpig-com/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '16', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9722fbd1_1b27_4095_9d1f_172bd6b295d1.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'lever', 'moonpig', null), ('1470', 'hackajob', 'Hackajob Ltd', 'https://hackajob.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hackajob/', 'hackajob is a technology-driven recruitment platform founded in 2014/2015, with offices in the UK and Romania. It connects technical talent with companies looking to efficiently scale their tech teams. The platform empowers candidates by allowing them to control their job search experience through a brief survey that outlines their preferences, such as salary and location. This personalized approach leads to high engagement rates, with candidates responding to 80% of employer requests.

The company offers a talent marketplace where employers can find pre-vetted technical candidates globally. Its AI matching algorithm streamlines the recruitment process by pairing candidates with suitable job opportunities. Additionally, hackajob provides technical hiring solutions, including coding tests and employer branding services. Initially focused on the UK market, hackajob has expanded its reach to include the US, catering to a diverse talent pool and meeting the needs of various companies, from startups to large enterprises.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/906bc0a7_446d_4134_934c_297ef7da6888.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'hackajob', null), ('1471', 'Papier', 'Papier Ltd', 'https://www.papier.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/papier/', 'Papier is a London-based retail company founded in 2015, specializing in premium, personalized stationery products. The company offers a diverse range of items, including customized notebooks, notecards, diaries, planners, and framed photo prints. Each product is designed to inspire creativity and meaningful expression, allowing customers to reflect their individual thoughts and feelings.

With a strong commitment to sustainability, Papier sources paper from sustainably managed forests and uses plastic-free, recyclable packaging for nearly all its products. The company collaborates with emerging artists and iconic brands to create artistically curated designs. Papier operates offices in London and New York and employs between 51-200 people, fostering a creative work environment that encourages inspiration and connection.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2ce9505f_b9ea_416d_a328_0fb6836d5377.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1472', 'Plastic Energy', 'Plastic Energy Ltd', 'https://plasticenergy.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/plastic-energy/', 'Plastic Energy is a global industrial technology company based in London, specializing in chemical recycling to promote a circular economy for plastics. Founded in 2012, the company employs around 200 people across various locations, including the UK, Singapore, Malaysia, Spain, and France. Its mission is to transform plastic waste, particularly hard-to-recycle materials, into TACOIL™, a recycled feedstock that replaces fossil oils in the production of new plastics.

The company operates two continuous chemical recycling plants in Spain, utilizing a patented thermal anaerobic conversion (TAC™) process. This innovative method heats plastics in the absence of oxygen to produce hydrocarbon vapors, which are condensed into TACOIL™. Plastic Energy''s technology significantly reduces carbon emissions compared to traditional waste management methods, contributing to global efforts in sustainable plastic waste management. The company also offers commercial packages and digital services to support partners in implementing its recycling technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0b2cefe1_7de6_47ea_8eee_494caed7000b.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1473', 'Core Power', 'Core Power (UK) Ltd', 'https://corepower.energy/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/core-poweruk/', 'CORE POWER is a technology and market development company focused on advanced nuclear energy solutions for ocean transport and heavy industry. Founded in 2018, it operates internationally with offices in London, Washington, D.C., and Tokyo. The company aims to design and build scalable nuclear technology that provides clean and efficient energy for maritime and industrial applications.

The flagship initiative, the Liberty program, is dedicated to developing floating nuclear power plants (FNPPs) that can generate up to 175 gigawatt-hours of clean electricity annually. These modular reactors are intended to power ships, port equipment, and coastal infrastructure. CORE POWER also offers advanced nuclear reactor technology, engineering and design services, regulatory standards development, and project financing to support the deployment of these innovative solutions.

By targeting the heavy industry and ocean transportation sectors, CORE POWER seeks to provide sustainable, low-carbon energy alternatives that help reduce greenhouse gas emissions and support climate change mitigation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/431c68c3_9868_4f46_9037_6bd33cc30e1b.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'corepowerenergy', null), ('1474', 'Ozone API', 'Ozone Financial Technology Limited', 'https://ozoneapi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ozoneapi/', 'Ozone API is a fintech company based in London, UK, specializing in open banking and open finance technology. Founded by the creators of the UK open banking standard, the company provides a standards-based open API platform that helps financial institutions comply with global regulations like PSD2, UK Open Banking, and others. This platform allows banks to securely expose APIs, manage third-party providers, and efficiently handle customer authentication and consent management.

In addition to regulatory compliance, Ozone API enables financial institutions to monetize open banking through premium APIs and Banking-as-a-Service models. The platform includes a rich catalog of APIs and tools for creating new revenue streams and enhancing customer experiences. Ozone API serves a diverse global customer base, including banks, regulators, and technology partners across Europe, the Middle East, Asia-Pacific, and Latin America. The company fosters a culture of innovation and collaboration, focusing on customer success and leadership in the open banking ecosystem.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/321da342_1910_41c2_8b9f_01966897b4bf.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1475', 'GB News', 'GB News Limited', 'https://www.gbnews.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gb-news/', 'GB News is a British multi-media news organization and television channel that launched on June 13, 2021. Headquartered in London, it broadcasts 24-hour news coverage, political commentary, and current affairs programming across various platforms, including Freeview, Sky, YouView, Freesat, and Virgin Media. The channel aims to provide a range of perspectives on UK issues, targeting audiences who feel underserved by traditional media.

The programming includes shows like *The Political Correction* and *Farage*, featuring prominent figures such as Nigel Farage. GB News has gained recognition in the industry, with its *Breakfast* show winning an award at the 2023 TRIC Awards. The channel has experienced growth in viewership and employment, expanding its team significantly since its inception. With a focus on robust debate and diverse viewpoints, GB News positions itself as a right-leaning alternative in the UK media landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1a212a55_d3c6_4922_87a0_85875c2ed2ac.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1476', 'Basecamp Research', 'Basecamp Research ', 'https://www.basecamp-research.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/basecamp-research/', 'Basecamp Research is a London-based artificial intelligence company founded in 2019. It focuses on addressing critical challenges in the life sciences by exploring "Beyond Known Biology™" through advanced AI-driven biological design. The company utilizes a vast proprietary biological knowledge graph, built from ethically sourced data, to train AI models that understand the complexity of biology. This allows Basecamp Research to design novel proteins and biological systems with enhanced performance for applications in pharmaceuticals, food, and industrial sectors.

The company continuously expands its biological database, which includes over 9.8 billion protein sequences and more than one million newly discovered microbial species. Basecamp Research also offers collaborative research programs, providing early access to its data for select researchers. It partners with leading biopharma companies and academic institutions, including a multi-year collaboration with the Broad Institute of MIT and Harvard to develop novel genetic medicines. With a diverse team and a commitment to innovation, Basecamp Research aims to revolutionize life sciences and unlock the secrets of biodiversity.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7462f697_0a3c_4323_8211_bc9014ff2a2d.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1477', 'Orca Computing', 'Orca Computing Limited', 'https://orcacomputing.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/orcacomputing', 'ORCA Computing is a UK-based quantum computing company founded in 2019 as a spin-out from the University of Oxford. With headquarters in London and additional offices in Toronto and Austin, ORCA specializes in developing full-stack photonic quantum computing systems. These systems utilize single photons traveling through optical fiber and incorporate telecom-grade components to create scalable, modular quantum processors.

The company''s mission is to make quantum computing practical by delivering near-term quantum accelerators for applications in generative AI, machine learning, and optimization. ORCA''s technology features a novel architecture that offers low noise and natural networking capabilities, allowing seamless integration into existing high-performance computing environments. They have successfully deployed on-premises quantum photonic systems to customers worldwide, including the UK Ministry of Defence and the National Quantum Computing Centre. With a dedicated team and significant funding, ORCA Computing is committed to advancing quantum technology for real-world applications.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/2d3445d8_bb84_4c1f_b58d_04a4f8bf9c99.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'orca', null), ('1478', 'Gemba', 'TLN Training Limited', 'https://thegemba.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/thegemba/', 'Gemba is a neobank founded in 2017 and based in London, England. The company specializes in financial infrastructure and business management solutions for the financial services industry. Gemba offers a range of services, including business account management with dedicated IBANs, international payment processing, escrow services, and API banking integration. These services are designed to facilitate seamless financial operations for clients.

