The proprietary Supply@ME IM platform allows businesses to unlock liquidity from their inventory without incurring debt. This service is designed for manufacturing and trading companies, enabling them to monetize existing stock to meet working capital needs and accelerate growth. The company is led by CEO Alessandro Zamboni and has a dedicated team of 21 employees. 

Supply@ME Capital has undergone several name changes, previously known as ABAL Group PLC and Imaginatik PLC, before rebranding in 2020. The company continues to focus on providing innovative inventory financing solutions, positioning itself as a key player in the fintech sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5fe5207c_ef69_4d62_9f23_728bb8731176.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1499', 'Gore Street Capital', 'Gore Street Capital Limited', 'https://www.gorestreetcap.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gore-street-capital/', 'Gore Street Capital is a renewable energy and private equity investment manager established in 2015. The company specializes in energy storage solutions that facilitate the global transition to sustainable energy. It is recognized as a leader in managing utility-scale energy storage systems, which are essential for balancing supply and demand on electricity grids powered by renewable sources like solar and wind.

The firm operates internationally, managing a diverse portfolio of renewable energy assets with a strong focus on energy storage technologies. Gore Street Capital launched the Gore Street Energy Storage Fund (GSF) in 2018, the UK’s first listed energy storage fund, which holds a capacity of approximately 1.7 gigawatts across multiple grid systems. The company collaborates with institutional investors, commercial partners, and regulatory bodies to develop and manage energy storage projects, aiming to enhance grid stability and reduce reliance on fossil fuels. Sustainability is central to its mission, as it seeks to create both financial returns and positive environmental impact through its investments.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e8c95185_8f27_41c1_ae06_41227656c4a8.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1500', 'Buster + Punch', 'Buster and Punch Limited', 'https://www.busterandpunch.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/buster-punch/', 'Buster + Punch is a London-based design company founded in 2013 by architect and industrial designer Massimo Buster Minale. The brand specializes in transforming everyday home fittings into high-end design pieces made from rare, solid metals. Their mission is to reinvent forgotten home items into memorable, premium products that combine functionality with bold aesthetics inspired by London’s fashion and music scenes.

The product range includes architectural hardware like door handles and cabinet pulls, innovative lighting solutions such as pendant lamps and the first designer LED light bulb, bespoke furniture, kitchen faucets, and various accessories. Buster + Punch caters to a clientele that values craftsmanship and design innovation, including private homeowners and notable collaborators like Travis Barker and The Oppenheim Group. The company also supports the North American market with dedicated sales and customer support, fulfilling inventory from within the United States. Their ethos emphasizes craftsmanship, creativity, and a unique approach to home fashion, while advocating for authentic design through their membership in Be Original Americas.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4e086ee2_d844_4fb7_ae0c_847c1322929a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1501', 'Hidden Road', 'Hidden Road Partners UK LLP', 'https://hiddenroad.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hiddenroad/', 'Hidden Road is a London-based financial services firm that specializes in providing technology-driven prime brokerage, clearing, and financing services to institutional clients. The company focuses on maintaining a conflict-free model, ensuring that it does not compete with its clients or have conflicts of interest with counterparties, custodians, or trading venues. 

Hidden Road offers a unified platform for real-time risk management across various asset classes, including traditional financial instruments and digital assets. Its core services include prime brokerage, clearing services, and tailored financing solutions. Recently, the company launched cash-settled over-the-counter digital asset swaps for U.S. institutional clients, enhancing its offerings in the digital asset market. With a strong capital base and proprietary technology, Hidden Road aims to scale its operations and become a leading global credit network for institutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/581e601e_5870_4665_8e9b_3f9323293a75.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'hiddenroad', null), ('1502', 'Circulor', 'Circulor Ltd', 'https://www.circulor.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/circulor/', 'Circulor is a technology company founded in 2017, dedicated to enhancing the responsibility, transparency, and sustainability of global supply chains. The company specializes in blockchain-based traceability solutions that track critical materials like cobalt, lithium, nickel, and tantalum from extraction to manufacturing, ultimately supporting products such as electric vehicle batteries and mobile phones.

Circulor offers a proven software platform that combines blockchain technology with machine learning to create a secure record of materials throughout complex supply chains. This platform captures essential data, including custody, location, and environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. The company provides services such as supply chain traceability software, environmental impact measurement, ethical sourcing verification, and data integration to help businesses achieve their sustainability goals.

With a strong focus on industries like automotive, mining, electronics, and agri-food, Circulor serves a diverse range of clients, including global manufacturers and mining companies. Recognized as a leader in supply chain sustainability technology, Circulor has received accolades such as the Technology Pioneer designation from the World Economic Forum and the DIGITALEUROPE Future Unicorn Award.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3e4e4684_1920_4f04_a586_1d0e34df9f7c.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1503', 'The Thinking Traveller', 'The Thinking Traveller Ltd', 'https://www.thethinkingtraveller.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the-thinking-traveller-ltd./?originalSubdomain=uk', 'The Thinking Traveller is a luxury travel company that specializes in high-end villa rentals and curated experiences across the Mediterranean. Founded in 2002 by Rossella and Huw Beaugié in Sicily, the company offers a portfolio of over 325 exclusive properties, including historic villas in destinations like Puglia, Tuscany, Greece, and Corsica. Prices for these unique rentals range from £3,000 to £80,000 per week, and they are available only through The Thinking Traveller.

The company emphasizes personalized service and local expertise, ensuring exceptional client experiences. Their commitment to sustainability is reflected in their status as a certified B Corporation, and they actively support environmental initiatives. The Thinking Traveller also merged with White Key Villas in 2021, enhancing their presence in the luxury villa market. They focus on responsible tourism and community engagement, believing that thoughtful tourism can positively impact local communities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ac414ffa_c2ff_4c57_8a05_cbf1174265da.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'teamtailor', 'thethinkingtraveller', null), ('1504', 'what3words', 'what3words Limited', 'https://what3words.com/pretty.needed.chill', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/what3words/', 'what3words is a technology company founded in 2013, focused on improving location communication worldwide. The company has developed a unique geocoding system that divides the globe into 57 trillion 3-meter by 3-meter squares, each identified by a combination of three simple words. This innovative approach makes sharing and navigating to precise locations easy and memorable.

Headquartered in the UK, what3words serves various industries with its core product, the what3words addressing system, which is accessible through a free app and API. The company also offers integration services for businesses, allowing them to incorporate the three-word addressing system into their platforms. Key customers include logistics and delivery companies, emergency services, and automotive manufacturers like Mercedes-Benz, which has integrated the system into its navigation systems. The company generates revenue by licensing its technology to businesses, enhancing operational efficiency and accuracy in location sharing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9a167fdb_5ae8_44ee_8859_2b121d958238.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1505', 'Valarian', 'Valarian Technologies Limited', 'https://valarian.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/valarian/', 'Valarian is a UK-based private limited company that specializes in secure communication and data security solutions for sensitive environments, including enterprise and government defense sectors. Incorporated in November 2019, Valarian, formerly known as Worldr Technologies Limited, operates from London.

The company has developed the ACRA platform, which provides "isolation-first" infrastructure technology. This platform helps governments and enterprises control and protect sensitive data by creating secure, compartmentalized environments. Valarian''s offerings include secure data infrastructure and communication security solutions designed for high-security applications, ensuring data integrity and confidentiality.

Valarian serves government defense organizations and enterprise clients that require advanced data security measures, reflecting its focus on sectors with critical security needs.', 'Sponsorship is only offered to "really highly skilled" applicants, and there have been no exceptions made to this approach historically. Lower-cost options (i.e., candidates without visa requirements) generally take priority.', '1', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b9296037_eecc_4b3b_ab0a_e28a47174fcc.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'lever', 'valarian', null), ('1506', 'Shaftesbury Capital', 'Shaftesbury Capital plc', 'https://www.shaftesburycapital.com/en/index.html', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/shaftesbury-capital/', 'Shaftesbury Capital PLC is a prominent real estate investment trust (REIT) that specializes in owning, managing, and developing mixed-use properties in London''s West End. The company’s portfolio spans approximately 2.7 million square feet of lettable space, featuring retail, leisure, commercial, and residential properties in vibrant areas such as Covent Garden, Carnaby Street, Soho, and Chinatown.

With a history dating back to 1933, Shaftesbury Capital has evolved significantly, including a merger with Shaftesbury PLC in 2023. The company focuses on strategic acquisitions and urban regeneration projects to enhance asset value and create thriving urban destinations. It offers a range of properties, including retail spaces in high-profile districts, commercial offices, and residential units within mixed-use developments. Shaftesbury Capital is publicly listed on the London and Johannesburg stock exchanges and is part of the FTSE 250 Index, highlighting its financial stability and commitment to sustainable urban development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1d1033e1_71c5_4dfb_8106_dadfe963e855.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1508', 'Kilter Finance', 'Kilter Finance Services Limited', 'https://kilterfinance.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kilterfinance/', 'Kilter Finance is a KKR-backed insurance-focussed specialty finance platform.

We are led by a team with a proven investment track record.

We have committed capital from KKR and a Japanese bank, as well as from a growing network of co-investors.

We are insurance-focussed and invest in and lend to life, health, annuity and casualty insurers. 

We have now made seven investments and are actively seeking further opportunities.

Our goal is to be expert partners and provide agile solutions to the counterparties we work with.

For more information contact Charles Lens at charles.lens@kilterfinance.com', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/479feddf_c672_4184_98dc_929993f4ee05.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1509', 'Social Value Portal', 'Social Value Portal', 'https://www.socialvalueportal.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/social-value-portal/', 'Social Value Portal is a London-based social enterprise focused on helping organizations measure, manage, and report their social, economic, and environmental impact. Founded by Guy Battle, the company aligns with the UK Public Services (Social Value) Act 2012 and aims to integrate social value into everyday business practices. Their mission is to support businesses and public sector organizations in delivering better social value, enhancing community wellbeing alongside profit.

The company offers the Social Value Workspace, a comprehensive online platform used by over 24,000 organizations. This platform utilizes the Social Value TOM System™, a leading standard for quantifying social benefits in line with international frameworks like the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals. In addition to the platform, Social Value Portal provides expert consultancy services, helping clients across various sectors embed social value into their strategies and projects. They also host the annual Social Value Conference and are active in setting industry standards through the National Social Value Taskforce. As a certified B Corporation, Social Value Portal is committed to ethical business practices and social impact.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/67608d34_d2ac_4c48_b729_24873a369ad4.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1510', 'Humaans', 'Humaans Software UK Limited', 'https://humaans.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/humaans/', 'Humaans is a London-based HR technology company founded in 2020. It offers an AI-powered human resources information system (HRIS) designed to simplify and automate employee management for mid-market and enterprise companies worldwide. The platform serves as a centralized hub for employee data, enabling collaboration among People Ops, Finance, and IT teams while integrating various workforce management solutions.

The Humaans platform automates the entire employment lifecycle, including onboarding, offboarding, performance management, and compensation reviews. It features a centralized employee database, workflow automation tools, an AI companion for HR-related inquiries, and real-time analytics for data-driven decision-making. Humaans focuses on delivering a user-friendly experience and deep workforce insights, making it an ideal choice for organizations looking to modernize their HR processes. The company is backed by significant funding and is expanding its capabilities to meet the needs of larger markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '9', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c903b28c_805f_4de2_b190_bdc3f2113b5f.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/humaans', null), ('1511', 'Paragraf', 'Paragraf Ltd', 'https://www.paragraf.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/paragrafltd/', 'Paragraf is a graphene electronics company founded in 2017 as a spin-out from the University of Cambridge. It is the first company in the world to mass-produce graphene-based electronic devices using standard semiconductor manufacturing processes. Paragraf focuses on developing advanced graphene electronic components, including Graphene Hall Sensors (GHS) and Graphene Field-Effect Transistors (GFETs), utilizing a proprietary graphene growth process.

The company’s products are designed for exceptional sensitivity, robustness, and energy efficiency, addressing challenges in sectors such as automotive, industrial automation, cryogenics, healthcare, and agri-tech. Paragraf also offers Multi-Sensor Test (MiST) kits for testing graphene sensors and is involved in biosensor development for healthcare diagnostics. Its customer base includes notable organizations like CERN, Rolls Royce, and various healthcare institutions, supporting its growth and innovation in both industrial and biomedical fields. Paragraf has raised approximately $85 million in funding to enhance production and advance its technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1254bbc7_d4e1_4858_9abc_2b477102c0f6.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'teamtailor', 'paragraf', null), ('1512', 'Molten Ventures', 'Molten Ventures Plc', 'https://www.moltenventures.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/molten-ventures/', 'Molten Ventures is a prominent British venture capital firm that invests in high-growth private technology companies throughout Europe. Established in 2006 and rebranded in 2021, the firm is publicly listed on the London Stock Exchange and is part of the FTSE 250 Index. With offices in London, Dublin, and Cambridge, Molten Ventures focuses on various stages of investment, from seed to late-stage funding.

The firm specializes in sectors such as fintech, AI, spacetech, consumer technology, and life sciences, typically investing between £2 million and £50 million per company. Molten Ventures emphasizes backing technology businesses with proven demand and scalable models. Since its IPO in 2016, it has deployed over £1 billion in capital and has a gross portfolio value of approximately £1.37 billion. Its portfolio includes notable companies like Graphcore, Ledger, and Revolut, primarily targeting firms based in Europe and the United States.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7e5844f5_dd94_4fdc_a620_8f606d749cee.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1513', 'Riverlane', 'Riverlane Ltd', 'https://www.riverlane.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/river-lane-research-ltd/', 'Riverlane is a quantum computing company founded in 2016, dedicated to making quantum technology practical through advanced software solutions. Its flagship product, Deltaflow, is a Quantum Error Correction Stack designed to address data errors that hinder the scalability of quantum computers. This technology aims to enhance the reliability and effectiveness of quantum machines, enabling them to deliver useful computational results.

The company collaborates with governments, quantum hardware manufacturers, and leading research institutions to advance the capabilities of quantum computing. Riverlane operates globally, with offices in Cambridge, UK, Boston, and San Francisco, and has grown to nearly 100 employees. With over $90 million in funding, Riverlane is focused on accelerating the commercial viability of quantum technology, contributing to advancements comparable to the industrial and digital revolutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '20', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1808e0e9_e524_4e22_a291_8601fe789e99.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'riverlane', null), ('1514', 'Evonetix', 'Evonetix Ltd', 'https://www.evonetix.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/evonetix-ltd/', 'Evonetix Ltd is a UK-based biotechnology company founded in 2015. The company specializes in developing a desktop platform for gene synthesis that produces high-quality, gene-length DNA with exceptional accuracy and scale. Utilizing proprietary technology that combines physics and biology on a silicon chip, Evonetix''s platform features thousands of independently controlled reaction sites, enabling parallel DNA synthesis. This innovative approach supports both chemical and enzymatic synthesis, with built-in error identification and removal for enhanced accuracy.

The platform aims to democratize access to DNA synthesis, making it easier for researchers to synthesize DNA quickly and accurately. This capability is essential for advancing various fields, including healthcare, sustainable agriculture, and personalized medicine. Evonetix serves customers in synthetic biology, biotechnology, and pharmaceutical development, providing tools for applications such as vaccine development and antibody therapeutics. Headquartered in Cambridge, UK, the company employs around 99 people and has raised over $66 million in funding, reflecting strong confidence in its technology and market potential.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d8e3387d_a25e_40a7_a789_c1c511bd6a95.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1515', 'Ledger', 'Ledge Technologies UK Ltd', 'https://www.ledger.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ledgerhq/', 'Ledger is a prominent company that specializes in security and infrastructure solutions for cryptocurrencies and blockchain applications. Founded in 2014 and headquartered in France, Ledger employs around 600 people across nine global offices. The company is dedicated to providing top-notch security for cryptocurrency holders and enterprises, focusing on the secure ownership and management of crypto assets.

Ledger is well-known for its hardware wallets, including the Ledger Nano S, Ledger Nano X, and the recently launched Ledger Stax. These wallets securely store private keys offline, protecting digital assets from theft. Additionally, Ledger offers Ledger Live, a software interface that allows users to manage their crypto assets securely, supporting a wide range of cryptocurrencies and tokens. For businesses, Ledger provides Ledger Vault, an enterprise-grade security solution designed to secure large-scale crypto asset holdings and ensure compliance with financial regulations.

Overall, Ledger delivers a comprehensive suite of products and services that empower both individual users and businesses to safely control and grow their cryptocurrency assets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ccf76c26_c003_4c61_aad5_4177a0b4488d.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/ledger', null), ('1516', 'Sixfold ', 'Sixfold Biosciences Limited', 'https://www.sixfold.bio/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sixfoldbioscience/', 'Sixfold Bioscience is a biotechnology company based in London, founded in 2018. It specializes in RNA therapeutics delivery systems, utilizing AI-driven methods to enhance precision medicine. The company operates from the Translation and Innovation Hub at Imperial College London and has a team of approximately 20 to 27 staff members. Sixfold has received funding from Y Combinator, venture capital, and various grants, including Innovate UK and Horizon2020.

The core technology of Sixfold is the Mergo® platform, a patented system designed for systemic RNA delivery. This modular platform employs AI to create nanoparticles that improve tissue targeting, safety, and efficacy. It supports both siRNA and mRNA payloads and has shown promising results in preclinical studies for RNA delivery. Sixfold is focused on therapeutic development, particularly in oncology, and collaborates with several academic institutions and industry partners to advance its projects. The company aims to license its delivery systems for clinical applications, expanding its impact in the field of biotechnology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/16bb0c0d_fdc2_4624_9b16_eca4c84f0aa5.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'sixfold', null), ('1517', 'FocalPoint', 'Focal Point Positioning Ltd', 'https://focalpointpositioning.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fppnt/', 'FocalPoint is a UK-based technology company founded in 2015, specializing in navigation and positioning software that enhances the accuracy and reliability of Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) devices. Headquartered in Cambridge, England, with a subsidiary in the USA and recent expansion into Asia, FocalPoint aims to improve positioning solutions globally through advanced technologies.

The company offers software solutions that address challenges in autonomous systems, robotics, transportation, and sensor technologies. Their products utilize artificial intelligence, machine learning, and computer vision to enhance navigation and mapping for various applications, including autonomous vehicles. In 2023, FocalPoint launched SGNSS-Auto, targeting specific challenges in the automotive industry. Their services are primarily B2B, delivered through SaaS subscription models, and focus on sectors such as IoT and transportation.

FocalPoint has received multiple rounds of funding to support its innovation and global expansion. Their partnerships with automotive manufacturers and technology companies highlight their commitment to providing precise and secure positioning solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f4158c0d_e9b0_41c1_a80e_36bf86a77f9a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'focalpoint', null), ('1518', 'ICEYE', 'Iceye Information Solutions UK Ltd', 'https://www.iceye.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/iceye/', 'ICEYE is a Finnish technology company founded in 2014, specializing in synthetic-aperture radar (SAR) satellites. It operates the largest constellation of small SAR satellites, providing high-frequency radar imaging of any location on Earth, regardless of weather or lighting conditions. The company offers timely and reliable SAR satellite imagery with revisit rates exceeding 15 times per day, supporting various applications such as disaster management, maritime monitoring, and environmental assessments.

ICEYE''s SAR data products include high-resolution X-band radar images in multiple formats and ground resolutions. The company is continuously expanding its satellite constellation, with over 20 satellites launched by early 2022, and plans for further growth based on market demand. Key applications of ICEYE''s data include monitoring floods, wildfires, and illegal deforestation, as well as supporting energy network surveillance and agricultural compliance.

In addition to data services, ICEYE provides options for customers to purchase and operate their own radar imaging satellites or have ICEYE manage them. Headquartered in Espoo, Finland, ICEYE aims to democratize access to spaceborne radar imaging, enabling data-driven decision-making across various industries.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/61c99e7f_f5a0_4447_a247_97408e816cdf.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workable', 'iceye', null), ('1519', 'Trip', 'Trip Drink Ltd', 'https://drink-trip.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tripdrinks/', 'TRIP is a UK-based company founded in 2019 by Olivia Ferdi and Daniel Khoury. It specializes in manufacturing soft drinks infused with CBD (cannabidiol) and natural adaptogens. Recognized as the UK''s leading CBD brand, TRIP holds 88% of the CBD drinks market share and is the fastest growing soft drinks brand in the country. The company operates as TRIP DRINK LTD, focusing on producing refreshing beverages and bottled waters.

TRIP offers a variety of lightly sparkling drinks infused with CBD, magnesium, and botanicals like Ashwagandha and Lion’s Mane. These beverages are designed to promote calm, reduce stress, and support mental wellbeing without the negative effects of alcohol. The company emphasizes destigmatizing mental health conversations and aims to create accessible CBD products that fit into everyday life. TRIP also partners with the Calm app, providing customers with a three-month free subscription with every purchase, reinforcing its commitment to mindfulness and relaxation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dc267a43_6b97_4849_a4ce_237c0e208dcb.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1520', 'GiantX', 'Excel LEC Limited', 'https://giantx.gg/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/giantx/', 'GIANTX is a European esports organization formed in December 2023 from the merger of EXCEL ESPORTS and Giants Gaming. With headquarters in London and Malaga, and a performance center in Berlin, GIANTX combines the strengths of both predecessor companies to create a unified global esports brand. The organization employs around 60 staff members and focuses on expanding its competitive presence in the UK, Spain, and Latin America.

GIANTX competes in major esports titles, primarily League of Legends and VALORANT. The company is dedicated to team management, content creation, and marketing to engage its global fanbase. It also emphasizes partnership development and sponsorships, while supporting player development through its Berlin performance center. Registered as GIANTX LTD in the UK, the organization reflects a multifaceted role in esports and digital services, aiming for competitive success and brand growth across multiple markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/16f06c9c_66d1_41f9_b633_50157027de94.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1521', 'ChargedUp', 'Innovative Energy Solutions Ltd', 'https://www.chargedup.green/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/joinchargedup/', 'ChargedUp is a UK-based company that specializes in power bank rental technology. It operates a network of self-service charging stations, allowing users to borrow portable battery packs to charge their mobile devices on the go. Founded by Hugo Tilmouth and others, ChargedUp addresses the common issue of mobile phones running out of battery while away from home.

As the market leader in the UK for power bank rental services, ChargedUp has thousands of stations located in venues such as restaurants, cafes, transport hubs, sports stadiums, and shopping centers. The company emphasizes sustainability by partnering with Ecotricity to ensure that all power banks are charged using renewable energy sources. Users can easily locate stations and manage rentals through the ChargedUp mobile app, enhancing convenience and promoting eco-friendly consumption.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1f108c73_a87b_45a4_be9d_34195abb2252.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1522', '7bridges', 'Seven Bridges Limited', 'https://www.the7bridges.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/the7bridges/', '7bridges is a London-based company that specializes in AI-powered logistics and supply chain management solutions. The company offers a web-based platform that utilizes advanced machine learning and AI simulation to automate and optimize logistics networks. This technology aims to create more integrated, adaptable, and resilient supply chains, supporting businesses in achieving scalable and sustainable outcomes.

Founded in London, 7bridges operates in the B2B SaaS sector, focusing on transportation, logistics, and enterprise software. The platform is designed for complex supply chain data integration and provides tools for logistics network optimization. It serves various industries, including med-tech, healthcare, retail, manufacturing, aerospace, and defense, targeting enterprises looking to enhance logistics efficiency and profitability through AI-driven solutions. Recently, 7bridges was acquired by IFS to expand its capabilities in AI-driven supply chain management across multiple sectors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1facf2bf_2f31_4fee_b065_9b2e74312223.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'the7bridges', null), ('1524', 'Contilio', 'Contilio Limited', 'https://www.contilio.com/index.html', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/contilio/', 'Contilio 3D AI is a technology company based in London, UK, founded in 2019. It specializes in advanced 3D AI analytics tailored for the construction industry. The company offers a powerful platform that automates the analysis of 3D site data, such as laser scans and 360-degree photos, delivering insights in hours instead of weeks.

The platform enhances construction project management by automating processes like quantity tracking, installation quality verification, and progress tracking. It also creates cognitive digital twins, which are intelligent digital representations of construction sites. Contilio''s solution supports general contractors, asset owners, and real estate developers in managing their construction portfolios effectively, providing real-time insights that improve productivity and sustainability.

Contilio''s technology is particularly beneficial for large-scale projects, such as data centers, where it can analyze extensive site areas quickly. The platform integrates seamlessly with existing project schedules and Building Information Modeling (BIM) systems, helping clients achieve timely and cost-effective project delivery. With a dedicated team, Contilio aims to save clients money by minimizing delays and waste while enhancing risk management.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d9db4d65_a242_4400_bcd8_707caac0f395.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'contilio', null), ('1525', 'AccelerComm', 'AccelerComm Limited', 'https://www.accelercomm.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/accelercomm-ltd/', 'AccelerComm Ltd is a UK-based semiconductor intellectual property (IP) company that specializes in high-performance physical layer solutions for wireless communications, focusing on 4G LTE and 5G New Radio (NR) technologies. Founded in 2016 and headquartered in Southampton, the company develops advanced channel coding and signal processing IP cores that enhance digital communications with low power consumption, targeting both terrestrial and satellite radio access networks.

The company offers a range of customizable, licensable IP cores and software libraries designed to optimize physical layer processing. Key products include a patented polar encoding and decoding IP for 5G NR, an ultra-parallel turbo decoder for LTE, and a developing low-density parity-check (LDPC) chain for 5G networks. AccelerComm also provides complete physical layer solutions that meet the specific requirements of both terrestrial and satellite applications.

AccelerComm serves various markets, including telecommunications, satellite communications, private networks, and defense. Their customers include network equipment manufacturers and technology companies looking to enhance wireless network performance. The company is supported by prominent investors and partners with semiconductor firms to optimize their IP for FPGA platforms.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7cd3d62f_88a3_4b6b_8b22_9bb32cab6007.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'pinpoint', 'accelercomm', null), ('1526', 'Alloyed', 'Alloyed Limited', 'https://alloyed.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/alloyed', 'Alloyed is a technology-driven company focused on developing advanced digital platforms for designing superior metal alloys and components. They specialize in additive manufacturing and aim to expand into various digital production processes. Alloyed utilizes proprietary techniques to create customized metal alloys that enhance performance characteristics such as strength, weight, and temperature resistance.

The company offers a range of services, including customized alloy development, additive manufacturing process optimization through software platforms like Engine® and Architect®, and advanced component design for complex geometries. Alloyed also provides end-to-end production support and manufactures high-precision metal components for industries such as aerospace, electronics, wearables, and luxury goods. Their notable clients include Boeing and Microsoft, showcasing their expertise in delivering innovative materials and manufacturing solutions. With significant funding and a strong academic foundation, Alloyed is positioned as a leader in the additive manufacturing sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/26130b01_0cbd_49ba_8152_feac188b8777.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1527', 'Archangel Lightworks', 'Archangel Lightworks Ltd', 'https://www.archangel.works/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/archangellightworks/', 'Archangel Lightworks is a UK-based aerospace and defense company founded in 2017 and headquartered in London. The company specializes in deployable laser communication systems that connect space networks with terrestrial networks. Their core product, the TERRA-M, is a compact optical ground station designed to provide secure, high-bandwidth laser communication links. This innovative solution significantly reduces the size, weight, power, and cost compared to traditional optical ground equipment.

The company focuses on addressing global challenges such as economic inclusion and climate change by offering resilient connectivity solutions that can be deployed in areas lacking traditional infrastructure. Archangel Lightworks has received over $5 million in seed funding and support from the UK Space Agency, particularly through programs like HALO, which have contributed to the development of their laser communication technologies. Their mission is to enhance connectivity and bridge the gap between space and terrestrial networks, making secure communication more accessible.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/65537f36_59f9_46b3_9040_8a9d2d5612e6.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'breezy', 'archangellightworks', null), ('1528', 'Advanced Electric Machines (AEM)', 'Advanced Electric Machines Limited', 'https://advancedelectricmachines.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/advanced-electric-machines', 'Advanced Electric Machines (AEM) is a company focused on electric motor technology, specializing in the design and manufacture of magnet-free electric powertrain systems. Founded in 2017 and based in the North East of England, AEM emerged from Newcastle University''s electric motor research team. The company aims to provide sustainable and high-performing powertrain solutions for electric vehicles, reducing reliance on rare earth materials and copper.

AEM develops innovative electric motor technologies suitable for various applications, including passenger cars, commercial vehicles, off-highway machinery, industrial systems, and rail infrastructure. Their products are designed to enhance performance, range, and efficiency while being highly recyclable. AEM collaborates with leading vehicle manufacturers and industrial partners globally, contributing to green mobility initiatives. In 2023, the company completed a Series A investment round and launched new branding, marking significant growth in their mission to disrupt the electric vehicle industry with sustainable solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8c52bb29_d7c9_4592_a6fa_4d6e881d1658.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'advancedelectricmachines', null), ('1529', 'Axol', 'Censo Biotechnologies Ltd', 'https://axolbio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/axol-bioscience-ltd-/', 'Axol Bioscience Ltd. is a biotechnology company based in Cambridge, England, specializing in high-quality human cell products. Founded in 2012, the company focuses on developing induced pluripotent stem cells (iPSCs), along with media and growth supplements essential for cell culture research and drug discovery.

The company offers a variety of custom services, including bespoke iPSC reprogramming and differentiation, cell culture media services, and disease modeling. These services support research and drug development by providing disease-relevant human cells and optimizing conditions for cell growth. Axol also produces ready-to-use human iPSCs and custom cell-derived products tailored to specific research needs.

With a reported revenue of approximately $10.4 million and a team of around 51 employees, Axol Bioscience operates in the biotechnology research sector, focusing on advanced therapeutics and regenerative medicine. Its technologies play a vital role in pharmaceutical research and development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4c3486ba_8144_4cf9_8fa0_d2d47b3c6954.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1530', 'Barinthus Biotherapeutics', 'Barinthus Biotheraputics (UK) Limited', 'https://www.barinthusbio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/barinthusbiotherapeutics/', 'Barinthus Biotherapeutics plc is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company based in the United Kingdom. Founded in 2016 as a spinout from the University of Oxford, it focuses on developing novel immunotherapies that help T cells combat autoimmunity and inflammatory diseases. The company emerged from a merger in 2021, combining expertise from Vaccitech and Avidea Technologies, and is publicly traded on Nasdaq under the ticker BRNS.

Barinthus specializes in antigen-specific immunotherapies, utilizing proprietary platforms such as Chimpanzee Adenovirus Oxford (ChAdOx) and Modified Vaccinia Ankara (MVA) viral vectors. Their key product candidates include VTP-200, aimed at treating low-grade HPV-related cervical lesions, and VTP-300, designed for chronic Hepatitis B virus infection. The company is dedicated to improving patient outcomes through innovative science and clinical development, targeting patients with chronic infectious diseases, autoimmune disorders, and inflammatory conditions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/aca833f6_5da6_4f2e_8364_717c84a90622.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'barinthusbio', null), ('1531', 'Bicycle ', 'BicycleTx Limited', 'https://www.bicycletherapeutics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bicycle-therapeutics/', 'Bicycle Therapeutics is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company founded in 2009, based in Cambridge, UK, with significant operations in Cambridge, MA. The company specializes in developing precision-guided therapeutics using its proprietary Bicycle® technology platform, focusing on unmet medical needs in oncology and other therapeutic areas.

Bicycle Therapeutics aims to lead in solid tumor therapeutics by creating synthetic, constrained peptides known as Bicycles. These fully synthetic short peptides are designed to effectively penetrate tissues and target difficult cancer pathways. The company''s clinical pipeline includes several candidates, such as BT5528, BT8009, BT7480, and BT1718, which target various tumor antigens and are in different stages of clinical trials. Additionally, Bicycle is developing Bicycle Radio Conjugates (BRC™) for radiopharmaceutical applications.

The company collaborates with pharmaceutical companies and academic institutions to expand its technology into non-oncology areas, including anti-infectives, cardiovascular diseases, and central nervous system disorders. Bicycle Therapeutics is committed to developing transformative medicines for cancer patients and aims to address broader patient populations in underserved therapeutic areas.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/9768a0b4_99b1_4398_b7a8_f3da53d3391a.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'BicycleTherapeutics', null), ('1532', 'Biofidelity', 'Biofidelity Limited', 'https://biofidelity.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/biofidelity/', 'Biofidelity is a private genomic technology company based in Cambridge, UK, founded in 2019. The company focuses on enhancing cancer diagnostics to improve patient outcomes globally. Biofidelity''s mission is to simplify genomic analysis through innovative molecular technologies, making precision-driven insights more accessible throughout the cancer patient journey.

The company offers two main technologies: Aspyre® and Enspyre®. Aspyre® is a PCR-based technology that enables fast and decentralized testing for cancer biomarkers, particularly for non-small cell lung cancer. Enspyre® is an enrichment technology designed to detect specific DNA variants with high sensitivity, supporting applications like minimal residual disease detection. Together, these technologies provide an end-to-end solution for early detection, treatment selection, and ongoing monitoring in cancer care.

Biofidelity''s genomic testing solutions empower oncologists and healthcare providers with clinically actionable data, facilitating better screening and treatment decisions. The company aims to expand access to precision oncology and is actively pursuing partnerships and licensing opportunities to further its impact in the field.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7ae99cfe_8570_4bc0_9989_6a1948b7e18e.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1533', 'bit.bio', 'Bit Bio Limited', 'https://www.bit.bio/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bitbioltd/', 'bit.bio is a synthetic biology company founded in 2016 as a spinout from the University of Cambridge. The company specializes in designing and manufacturing consistent, defined, and scalable human cells for research, drug discovery, and cell therapy. Its core technology, the opti-ox™ platform, allows for the precise reprogramming of human induced pluripotent stem cells (iPSCs) into various mature human cell types.

The company offers a broad portfolio of human cell types and disease models under the brand ioCells, including nerve, immune, and muscle cells. These products aim to improve research quality and lower costs, making functional human cells more accessible. bit.bio serves biomedical researchers, pharmaceutical companies, and organizations focused on drug discovery and cell therapy development. The company has established collaborations with partners like The Michael J. Fox Foundation for Parkinson’s Research, emphasizing its commitment to disease modeling and therapeutic innovation. With over $200 million in funding from prominent investors, bit.bio is positioned to advance the field of precision medicine.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3b27c5a9_ceb6_4730_8e3e_5948b03f0500.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'bitbio', null), ('1534', 'Bumblebee Power', 'Bumblebee Power Ltd', 'https://bumblebeepower.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bumblebee-power/', 'Bumblebee Power is an early-stage, VC-backed company which is commercialising innovative inductive wireless charging technology. This patent protected technology has significantly superior performance characteristics compared with conventional technology. The company has achieved strong commercial interest as shown by the strong pipeline of customer development projects it is in the process of delivering.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a9c3ade6_5ac6_4901_a0f3_29cd71aba92a.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1535', 'Cambridge GaN Devices (CGD)', 'Cambridge GaN Devices Limited', 'https://camgandevices.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cambridge-gan-devices-limited/', 'Cambridge GaN Devices Ltd (CGD) is a fabless semiconductor company founded in 2016 by experts from Cambridge University. Based in Cambridge, UK, CGD specializes in gallium nitride (GaN) power transistors and integrated circuits (ICs) that enhance energy efficiency and compactness in power electronics.

The company''s flagship ICeGaN™ technology features 650V GaN power transistors and ICs designed for high efficiency and easy integration. CGD''s innovations include enhanced thermal performance packages for data centers and motor drives, as well as reference designs and evaluation kits developed in collaboration with partners like Qorvo® and ITRI. Their products serve various markets, including data centers, industrial and automotive applications, and consumer electronics, focusing on high-performance power supplies and compact adapters.

CGD is committed to advancing power electronics with reliable, energy-efficient solutions. The company has secured significant funding to support its growth and continues to showcase its technology at industry events.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/48b26464_7ace_4b47_ae51_b51aa11189d9.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'breezy', 'cambridge', null), ('1536', 'Carbon Re', 'Carbon Re Ltd', 'https://carbonre.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carbonre/', 'Carbon Re is an industrial climate-tech company that focuses on using artificial intelligence (AI) to significantly reduce carbon emissions in energy-intensive manufacturing sectors, particularly in foundational materials like cement, steel, and glass. Founded in 2021 by experts from the University of Cambridge and University College London, the company aims to remove gigatonnes of CO2 emissions annually by optimizing industrial processes and developing climate-friendly materials.

The company''s flagship product, Delta Zero Cement, is an AI-powered software platform that optimizes cement production through deep reinforcement learning. This technology autonomously controls plant operations, allowing cement producers to reduce fuel consumption and carbon emissions by up to 20%, while also lowering operational costs. Carbon Re''s technology is already in use in cement plants across three continents, demonstrating its effectiveness in achieving significant emissions reductions.

In addition to its innovative technology, Carbon Re fosters a strong company culture centered on transparency, continuous improvement, urgency, and reliability. The company is committed to building a diverse and inspiring workplace that encourages learning and ambition.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ca4ab05f_349b_499f_b2a6_8c5d91916422.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'carbon', null), ('1537', 'CMR Surgical', 'CMR Surgical Ltd', 'https://cmrsurgical.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cmrsurgical/', 'CMR Surgical is a British medical device company based in Cambridge, UK, focused on developing advanced robotic systems for minimal access surgery. Founded in 2014, the company aims to enhance surgical care worldwide by making minimally invasive procedures more accessible and effective for surgeons. CMR Surgical achieved Unicorn status in 2019 and has a valuation of $3 billion as of 2021, with a global presence that includes a manufacturing hub in Ely and partnerships across Europe, Latin America, Asia, the Middle East, Africa, Australia, and the United States.

The flagship product, the Versius Surgical Robotic System, is a modular, robot-assisted platform designed for laparoscopic surgery. It features independent modular arms for flexibility, an ergonomic console for comfort, and instruments that mimic human hand movements for enhanced precision. CMR Surgical supports the clinical adoption of Versius through partnerships with NHS hospitals and ongoing clinical trials, including pioneering studies in pediatric surgery and transoral robotic surgery. The company emphasizes a patient-centered approach and values innovation, diversity, and ethical practices in its operations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/961f12d9_7521_4e8f_8ba0_c72364879d9b.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1538', 'CN Bio', 'CN Bio Innovations', 'https://cn-bio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cnbio/', 'CN Bio is a UK-based biotechnology company founded in 2008 and headquartered in Cambridge. The company specializes in organ-on-a-chip (OOC) technology and microphysiological systems (MPS) that enhance drug discovery and preclinical research. With a strong foundation in scientific expertise, CN Bio collaborates with prestigious institutions, including the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and the US Food and Drug Administration.

The flagship product line, PhysioMimix® Organ-on-a-Chip, includes devices for modeling human organ functions and 3D validated human cells. These systems allow researchers to recreate human biology in vitro, providing reliable preclinical data that supports the development of safer therapeutics. CN Bio also offers contract research services that utilize their OOC technology to deliver insights into drug and disease mechanisms, catering to pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies. The company has received significant investment to expand its operations and meet the growing demand for innovative drug testing solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/75d91456_0871_4c50_93c7_13c4cc073723.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1540', 'CS Genetics', 'CS Genetics Limited', 'https://www.csgenetics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cs-genetics-limited/', 'CS Genetics is a biotechnology company based in Cambridge, England, that specializes in advancing single cell genomics technologies. Founded in 2014, the company focuses on simplifying complex workflows in genomics research to accelerate biological discovery.

Their flagship product, SimpleCell 3’ Gene Expression, allows researchers to conduct complete single-cell RNA sequencing experiments in just one day. This platform reduces costs per sample and eliminates batching complexity, supporting modular and automation-ready workflows. It is designed to scale from pilot studies to large population genomics projects, ensuring reliable data across various labs and study formats.

CS Genetics aims to remove barriers in genomics research, enabling scientists to focus on significant biological questions. The leadership team, composed of experienced professionals in the field, drives innovation and collaboration in cancer genome research and beyond. The company provides tools that empower researchers to conduct scalable and reliable single cell genomics experiments with ease.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e582e671_44e7_4788_b58b_5651f4dd7fc9.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'csgeneticsltd', null), ('1541', 'Diffblue', 'Diffblue Ltd', 'https://www.diffblue.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/diffblue/', 'Diffblue is a private limited company founded in 2016 as a spin-out from the University of Oxford. Based in London, it specializes in AI-driven software development tools, particularly for automated software testing. The company’s mission is to enhance software development by automating tedious tasks, allowing developers to focus on creating impactful products. 

Diffblue''s flagship product, Diffblue Cover, automatically generates Java unit tests and integrates with popular development environments like IntelliJ. It supports continuous integration and enterprise DevOps workflows, capable of writing a unit test every two seconds. The Cover Community Edition, released in 2020, offers a freeware version for broader access. The technology employs patented reinforcement learning to ensure accurate and error-free test generation, operating securely within customer environments.

Diffblue serves a range of notable clients, including major financial institutions and technology companies. The company has successfully raised significant funding to support its growth and innovation in the software development sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/540362f6_9733_4d70_b2ad_c8e9dede4834.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'diffblue', null), ('1542', 'Dukosi', 'Dukosi Limited', 'https://www.dukosi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/dukosi/', 'Dukosi is a fabless semiconductor company based in Edinburgh, Scotland, focused on advanced battery management technologies for electric vehicles, stationary energy storage systems, and industrial transportation. Founded in 2003, Dukosi shifted its focus in 2014 to develop innovative battery management systems featuring a patented chip-on-cell architecture. This technology allows for contactless communication and sensing at the individual battery cell level, significantly reducing the wiring and hardware typically needed in battery packs.

The company''s chip-on-cell technology enhances battery performance by enabling real-time monitoring of each cell''s status and health, making batteries lighter, smaller, and safer. Dukosi''s semiconductor chips and integrated circuits are designed specifically for battery management systems, facilitating wireless data communication and supporting a sustainable battery value chain. The company collaborates with major automotive manufacturers and battery producers globally, with offices in Edinburgh, Michigan, and Seoul. Dukosi has received recognition for its innovative approach and leadership in the industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d1f04759_06b6_4fb0_b09d_c04f4d15bce2.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'dukosi', null), ('1543', 'Evolito', 'Evolito Ltd', 'https://evolito.aero/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/evolito-ltd/', 'Evolito Ltd is a British aerospace company focused on developing and manufacturing advanced electric propulsion systems for aviation. Established in 2021 as a spin-off from YASA Limited, the company specializes in next-generation axial-flux electric motors, motor controller units, and battery management systems designed for aerospace applications. Evolito operates a 40,000-square-foot manufacturing and testing facility in Bicester, Oxfordshire, with the capacity to produce approximately 20,000 units annually.

The company targets the growing electric aviation market, including urban air mobility and hybrid-electric aircraft sectors. Notable clients include the French airship startup Flying Whales, which utilizes Evolito''s technology to power its airships. Evolito is led by Co-founder and CEO Dr. Chris Harris and has been recognized for its innovative culture and commitment to employee growth. The company is privately funded and aims to accelerate the adoption of sustainable aviation technologies.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '32', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dff1a623_f875_4585_819f_ad3824274795.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'evolito/Evolito_Career_Site', null), ('1544', 'First Light Fusion', 'First Light Fusion Limited', 'https://firstlightfusion.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/first-light-fusion/', 'First Light Fusion is a UK-based company founded in 2011 as a spin-out from Oxford University. It specializes in inertial confinement fusion technology aimed at developing clean and limitless fusion energy. Headquartered in Kidlington, England, the company employs a unique approach that combines high-velocity projectile impacts with proprietary amplifier technology to achieve the extreme conditions necessary for fusion.

The company designs and manufactures consumable fusion targets embedded with its amplifier technology, which are essential components in inertial fusion schemes. First Light Fusion collaborates with fusion operators globally and partners with universities and institutions in various sectors, including space exploration and defense. They utilize advanced artificial intelligence and simulation tools to optimize fusion target design and accelerate technology development. With a team of around 100 experts, First Light Fusion is focused on commercializing its technology and making a significant impact in the fusion energy landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1cc095fc_321f_4aca_87cc_f15f22462750.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'breezy', 'first', null), ('1545', 'Forefront RF', 'Forefront RF Limited', 'https://www.forefrontrf.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/forefront-rf/', 'Forefront RF is a fabless semiconductor company based in Cambridge, UK, founded in 2020. The company specializes in radio frequency front end (RFFE) solutions for smartphones, wearables, and IoT devices. Its key innovation is the patented Foretune™ technology, a tunable duplexer that dynamically adjusts to available frequency bands. This technology reduces the need for multiple fixed-frequency duplex filters, allowing for more compact device designs and efficient use of printed circuit board (PCB) space.

Forefront RF''s solutions simplify manufacturing and supply chains by providing a frequency-agnostic approach, which helps original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) and original design manufacturers (ODMs) streamline their design and production processes. The company focuses on developing and licensing its adaptive passive cancellation and tunable duplexer technologies, enhancing RF performance in multi-band devices. With a strong leadership team and significant funding rounds, Forefront RF is positioned as an innovative player in the semiconductor industry, targeting the growing demand for miniaturized and efficient electronic devices.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '5', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/69f3691a_7466_431f_95db_725aacf61f91.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'forefront', null), ('1546', 'Genomics', 'Genomics plc', 'https://www.genomicsplc.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/genomics-ltd/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/46b9768b_922e_4538_bfc6_0c3d3788f6d5.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/genomics', null), ('1547', 'iGii', 'Integrated Graphene Ltd', 'https://www.igii.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/igii/', 'iGii is a Scotland-based advanced materials company that specializes in the invention and commercialization of high-performing pure 3D Graphene Foam, known as Gii. Founded in 2016 and headquartered in Stirling, iGii has transitioned from a research-focused entity to a manufacturer with a strong emphasis on scalability and sustainability.

The company''s core product, Gii, is a porous 3D carbon nanostructure with exceptional properties. iGii primarily applies this material in two areas: point-of-care diagnostics and energy storage. For diagnostics, iGii has developed Gii-Sens, an electrochemical electrode set that enhances the sensitivity and affordability of diagnostic tests. In energy storage, iGii has produced the Gii-Cap, a graphene supercapacitor designed for fast charging and smart power solutions.

iGii''s technology offers advantages such as stable material costs, scalability for high-volume manufacturing, and environmentally sustainable production. The company collaborates closely with life science organizations and product innovators to support the entire product development lifecycle, from concept to commercialization. With reported revenue of approximately $55.1 million, iGii is positioned as a leader in advanced materials, driving innovation and reducing supply chain risks for manufacturers globally.', 'The company can offer sponsorship for its "more specialised" roles with a focus on Development Scientists and similar.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b367a1e0_a5a7_475c_888d_4b9dd698b6f1.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'integratedgraphene', null), ('1548', 'Gilead', 'Gilead Sciences Europe Limited', 'https://www.gilead.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gilead-sciences/', 'Gilead Sciences, Inc. is a biopharmaceutical company based in Foster City, California, founded in 1987. The company focuses on discovering, developing, and commercializing innovative medicines to meet unmet medical needs. Its primary therapeutic areas include HIV/AIDS, liver diseases, cancer, inflammation, and serious respiratory and cardiovascular conditions.

Gilead is well-known for its comprehensive treatment options for HIV, including single-tablet regimens and pre-exposure prophylaxis medications like Truvada. The company has also made significant advancements in treating chronic hepatitis C with products such as Harvoni. In addition, Gilead has expanded into cancer therapies through its acquisition of Kite Pharma, emphasizing cell therapy. The company is dedicated to improving patient care globally and actively works to address health disparities through initiatives aimed at underserved communities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4f9c964c_532b_49c0_b44a_628309df78aa.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'gileadcareers', null), ('1549', 'iota Sciences', 'iota Sciences Limited', 'https://iotasciences.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/iotasciences/', 'iotaSciences is a biotechnology company based in Oxfordshire, UK, that specializes in automated solutions for single-cell biology handling. Founded in 2016 as a spin-out from the University of Oxford, the company develops tools aimed at advancing cell and gene therapy research. Their offerings cater to a multimillion-dollar market in life sciences and biopharmaceutical development.

The company provides a fully automated single-cell cloning platform that simplifies the isolation and culturing of single cells, enhancing monoclonality confirmation and accelerating cell-line engineering. Additionally, iotaSciences offers custom solutions tailored to support research and development workflows in cell biology and gene therapy, utilizing proprietary automation and imaging technologies to ensure precision and regulatory compliance.

With a team of around 20 employees and an annual revenue of $5 million, iotaSciences is focused on expanding its commercial operations in Europe, the U.S., and Asia, following a recent equity financing round. The company targets academic institutions, biopharmaceutical companies, and developers in the cell and gene therapy space, providing essential tools for therapeutic research.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/479a7a3d_3e51_4088_94a8_941dbc69d81c.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1550', 'Micrographia Bio', 'Micrographia Bio Limited', 'https://www.micrographiabio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/micrographia-bio/', 'Micrographia Bio is an applied AI-first life sciences company founded in 2019 and based in London, UK. The company focuses on enhancing drug discovery through its innovative spatial proteomics platform, which combines multiplexed microscopy with advanced machine-intelligent computer vision. This technology allows for rapid and accurate analysis of protein interactions within cells, helping to determine the mechanisms of action of potential therapeutics.

The platform supports drug developers and researchers by providing high-throughput analysis of microscopy images, enabling a deeper understanding of disease mechanisms at the subcellular level. Micrographia Bio is also developing its own pipeline of therapeutic candidates targeting key cellular pathways, with applications in cancer, neurodegeneration, and neuropsychiatric disorders. The company aims to improve the success rate of drug discovery by mapping chemical compounds to their actual activities inside human cells.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/a22b999e_dc2a_436a_bee1_fa68eda3a6b9.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1551', 'Carnall Farrar (CF)', 'Carnall Farrar Limited', 'https://www.carnallfarrar.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cf-healthcare-consulting/', 'Carnall Farrar (CF) is a healthcare consulting firm established in 2013, focused on improving health and healthcare outcomes. The firm collaborates with leaders and frontline teams in the healthcare sector, emphasizing values-driven consultancy, innovation, and collaboration.

