With over 2,000 engagements, CF serves various clients, including health systems and life sciences organizations. The firm has received multiple awards for its excellence in healthcare consulting and is recognized as a top UK consultancy in the healthcare and life sciences sectors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d3c153c5_a9bb_452e_80d8_4efda6d6c1eb.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workable', 'carnallfarrar', null), ('1552', 'Mind Foundry', 'Mind Foundry Limited', 'https://www.mindfoundry.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mind-foundry/', 'Mind Foundry is an artificial intelligence company based in Oxford, UK, founded by machine learning professors Stephen Roberts and Michael Osborne. The company focuses on developing responsible AI solutions that adhere to trusted scientific principles. Their algorithms are designed to be humble, honest, and aware of their limitations, making them suitable for high-stakes applications where decisions can significantly impact individuals or populations, such as in the insurance sector.

The company offers an AI platform that integrates machine learning models with domain expertise to address complex challenges like risk management. Mind Foundry emphasizes continuous model improvement and bias mitigation to ensure accuracy and fairness over time. They also provide tools that enhance organizational efficiency and employee experience, particularly in high-stakes contexts. Mind Foundry is dedicated to aligning AI with human values and fostering a diverse and inclusive environment while empowering teams through innovative technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '4', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3e44ecc5_4e17_4464_b844_018762aeaca5.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1553', 'Nucleome', 'Nucleome Therapeutics Limited', 'https://nucleome.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/nucleome-therapeutics/', 'Nucleome Therapeutics is a biotechnology company founded in 2019 by experts in gene regulation from the University of Oxford. Based in Oxford Science Park, England, the company focuses on decoding the regulatory genome to enhance personalized medicine. Nucleome aims to understand how genetic variations influence gene function and disease biology, which is essential for drug discovery and development.

The company offers drug discovery research services by utilizing the three-dimensional structure of the genome. By combining computational and biological expertise, Nucleome identifies genetically validated drug targets and determines patient responses to treatments. Their platform integrates genetic information across disease populations, providing insights into molecular networks that underlie diseases.

Nucleome is developing a pipeline of drug assets targeting autoimmune diseases, including rheumatoid arthritis, lupus, inflammatory bowel disease, and multiple sclerosis. The company has secured significant funding from notable investors, which supports its programs and the expansion of its dark genome atlas. Nucleome collaborates with major pharmaceutical companies to apply its insights in drug development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f72ef3da_66fb_4df1_8bde_a45e07d4678c.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'nucleome', null), ('1555', 'Osler Diagnostics', 'Osler Diagnostics Ltd', 'https://www.oslerdiagnostics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oslerdiagnostics/', 'Osler Diagnostics is a UK-based company founded in 2017 as a spin-out from the University of Oxford. Headquartered in Oxford, the company employs around 100 staff and has raised over $85 million in funding from leading investors. Osler''s mission is to enable individuals to access, understand, and act on their health for improved well-being.

The company has developed the Osler Origin, a portable lab device that provides lab-quality diagnostics at the point of care. This device supports a wide range of diagnostic tests suitable for various healthcare settings, including emergency departments, doctor’s offices, and retail pharmacies. The Osler Origin utilizes proprietary technologies such as the Osler HemaTap® for sample addition and electrochemical biosensing, all based on extensive research from Oxford University.

Osler Diagnostics aims to enhance global healthcare by making high-performance diagnostic testing accessible to diverse users. Their team consists of experts from the diagnostics industry, engineering, and science, led by CEO Connor Campbell.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/98a361fb_a3b6_4af4_80a9_9c708c858890.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'oslerdiagnostics', null), ('1556', 'ONI', 'Oxford Nanoimaging Ltd', 'https://oni.bio/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/onibio/', 'ONI is a UK-based start-up founded in 2016, specializing in the development and manufacturing of super-resolution microscopes. Based in Oxford, the company aims to enhance scientific research by providing tools that allow researchers to visualize microscopic details with exceptional clarity. With approximately 107 employees, ONI has raised over $75 million in funding to support its mission of democratizing access to advanced microscopy.

The company offers a range of products designed for life sciences research, including the Nanoimager, a compact benchtop microscope; the Aplo Scope, which combines high-power imaging with live cell capabilities; and the Aplo Flow, an automated liquid handling system for sample preparation. Additionally, ONI provides sample preparation kits and CODI software, a cloud-based platform for data analysis and collaboration. ONI serves academic and industrial researchers in fields such as cell biology, immunology, and molecular biology, helping them make significant discoveries in disease mechanisms and drug development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8d02be0f_c9b2_4170_a28d_89408f7d1aa5.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1557', 'Oxford PV', 'Oxford Photovoltaics Limited', 'https://www.oxfordpv.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oxfordpv/', 'Oxford PV is a British solar technology company founded in 2010 as a spin-off from the University of Oxford. The company specializes in developing and commercializing perovskite-based photovoltaic technology, particularly perovskite-on-silicon tandem solar cells. This innovative approach significantly enhances solar panel efficiency beyond traditional silicon cells.

Headquartered in Yarnton, Oxfordshire, with a pilot production line in Brandenburg an der Havel, Germany, Oxford PV focuses on scaling its technology for industrial production and commercial deployment. Their perovskite-on-silicon tandem solar cells have achieved world record efficiencies, with industrial-sized modules reaching 25% efficiency and residential panels achieving 26.9% efficiency. The company collaborates with industry partners to integrate its technology into existing solar markets, enabling users to generate more power from the same area, making solar energy more cost-effective and efficient.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d970592a_a5a9_45b3_8998_e752e22b1773.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1558', 'Perspectum', 'Perspectum Ltd', 'https://www.perspectum.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/perspectum-ltd/', 'Perspectum Ltd is a global medical technology company founded in 2012 as a spinout from the University of Oxford. Headquartered in Oxford, UK, with offices in the U.S. and Singapore, the company specializes in advanced digital imaging solutions for chronic systemic diseases, including liver and bile diseases, long COVID, diabetes, and cancer. Perspectum develops multiparametric MRI-based technologies that enhance the detection, diagnosis, and monitoring of these complex conditions, supporting early intervention and personalized treatment.

The company’s proprietary imaging software and digital tools provide precise, quantitative data that track disease progression and treatment response, particularly in liver disease. These technologies are widely used in clinical practice and research, playing a significant role in commercial liver clinical trials worldwide. Perspectum''s offerings include multiparametric MRI imaging software, digital diagnostic tools, and clinical trial support technologies, all aimed at improving diagnostic and monitoring capabilities for healthcare providers, clinicians, and researchers. With a team of over 200 employees and substantial funding, Perspectum is committed to advancing patient care through scientific innovation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/673a89da_5e09_49f0_b44c_ce4ab0a0dc6e.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1559', 'Pragmatic', 'Pragmatic Semiconductor Ltd', 'https://www.pragmaticsemi.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pragmatic-semiconductor/', 'Pragmatic Semiconductor is a leading company in semiconductor technology, based in Cambridge, United Kingdom, with a significant manufacturing site in Durham. The company specializes in developing and manufacturing flexible integrated circuits (FlexICs) that are cost-effective and sustainable. Their innovative platform allows for faster production cycles compared to traditional silicon chips, making it ideal for applications in Internet of Things (IoT) devices, smart packaging, and sensors.

The company operates the UK''s first 300mm wafer fab in Durham, capable of producing billions of FlexICs annually. This facility emphasizes sustainability, utilizing thin-film semiconductors that reduce water and energy consumption. Pragmatic Semiconductor has raised over $400 million in funding and collaborates with various partners to advance its technology and expand its market reach. Their focus on enabling item-level intelligence positions them as a key player in industries that require real-time supply chain visibility and edge intelligence.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/07916f2d_7dae_4ad3_b625_d91641bad7b7.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1560', 'QuellTX', 'Quell Therapeutics Ltd', 'https://quell-tx.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quell-therapeutics/', 'Quell Therapeutics is a clinical-stage biotechnology company based in London, UK, founded in 2019. The company is dedicated to transforming the treatment of severe immune-mediated and inflammatory diseases. With a team of over 150 employees, Quell Therapeutics was established by leading immunological experts from prestigious institutions.

The company specializes in developing engineered T regulatory (Treg) cell therapies. These therapies aim to enhance Tregs, which are essential for regulating the immune system and preventing autoimmunity. Quell''s innovative approach targets specific sites in the body, such as the liver, to manage unwanted immune responses. This technology has the potential to treat autoimmune diseases and prevent organ rejection without relying on immunosuppressive medications.

Quell Therapeutics has formed a significant partnership with AstraZeneca, receiving an upfront payment of $85 million to advance its cell therapy technologies. The company aspires to be a leader in cell therapy, focusing on improving the lives of patients in solid organ transplantation and autoimmune conditions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5db1b698_c8ca_4d69_9a9f_25bb438d0692.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1561', 'Quotient Sciences', 'Quotient Sciences Ltd', 'https://www.quotientsciences.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/quotient-sciences/', 'Quotient Sciences is a global leader in drug development and manufacturing, specializing in integrated programs for small molecule and synthetic peptide drug programs. With over 30 years of experience, the company operates as a contract research organization (CRO), contract development and manufacturing organization (CDMO), and contract research and development manufacturing organization (CRDMO). Their mission is to transform ideas into solutions and molecules into cures, emphasizing speed and efficiency to address urgent healthcare needs.

The company offers a wide range of services, including candidate selection, early and late phase development, drug substance synthesis, clinical trial manufacturing, and commercial manufacturing. Quotient Sciences also features the Translational Pharmaceutics® platform, which combines formulation development with real-time adaptive GMP manufacturing to optimize drug formulations and reduce timelines. They serve leading pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies worldwide, supporting drug programs from Phase I clinical trials to commercial launch, and have received multiple awards for excellence in their field.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/df39fe61_49e8_4cd0_8e19_514f3b35eb8f.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'quotient', null), ('1562', 'Secondmind', 'Secondmind Ltd', 'https://www.secondmind.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/secondmind-ai/', 'Secondmind is a technology company that specializes in AI-powered decision-making platforms for the automotive engineering sector. Founded in 2016, it operates from Cambridge, UK, and Yokohama, Japan. The company focuses on helping automotive engineers design cleaner and more efficient vehicles by utilizing advanced machine learning techniques.

Their flagship product, the Secondmind Active Learning platform, significantly reduces the time and effort required for vehicle design and development. This cloud-native software optimizes complex system designs and calibrations, allowing engineers to achieve their goals with fewer simulations and prototypes. Secondmind''s technology enables faster design cycles and supports the transition to carbon-neutral mobility.

Secondmind primarily serves automotive engineers and manufacturers, including major companies like General Motors and Mazda. Their platform enhances e-powertrain performance, reduces test bench time, and minimizes data correction errors. The company has received industry recognition, including awards for innovation in alternative powertrains and has been named among the UK''s top startups to watch.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/df0069ea_5733_4892_92c8_f5b43be6e24e.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'secondmind', null), ('1563', 'T-Cypher Bio', 'T-Cypher Bio Limited', 'https://tcypherbio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/t-cypher-bio/', 'T-Cypher Bio is a UK-based biotechnology company founded in 2015 and headquartered in Oxford. The company specializes in discovering and developing T cell receptor (TCR)-based therapeutics aimed at treating immune-mediated diseases, including cancer and autoimmune disorders. T-Cypher Bio utilizes proprietary platforms to identify and validate disease-specific targets, particularly focusing on solid tumors.

The core technology platform, T-Cα, enables high-throughput profiling of the immune synapse, allowing the mapping of intracellular target spaces and T cell specificity. This innovative approach helps discover druggable targets, including those from the ''dark genome.'' T-Cypher Bio''s pipeline includes T cell engagers targeting novel tumor-specific antigens, with clinical studies planned to begin by the end of 2026. The company collaborates with leading immunologists to integrate advanced research into their therapeutic development.

T-Cypher Bio aims to expand treatment options for patients with limited alternatives, impacting tens of thousands of individuals annually. They actively seek professionals with expertise in various fields to join their team and contribute to their mission of advancing immune-based therapies.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4315d12f_a1c3_405b_a400_3214eeee18a2.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'tcypher', null), ('1564', 'Theolytics', 'Theolytics Ltd', 'https://www.theolytics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/theolytics/', 'Theolytics is a clinical-stage biotechnology company focused on developing next-generation oncolytic viral therapies for cancer treatment. Founded in 2017 and based in Oxford, the company utilizes a proprietary adenovirus platform to create targeted, self-amplifying therapeutic agents. These agents are designed to selectively infect and destroy cancer cells while preserving healthy tissue.

Theolytics is particularly dedicated to addressing hard-to-treat cancers, including platinum-resistant ovarian cancer and colorectal cancer. Their lead product candidate, THEO-260, is an innovative oncolytic immunotherapy that not only targets cancer cells but also cancer-associated fibroblasts, enhancing the immune response and potentially improving treatment outcomes. The company employs a unique discovery approach, leveraging a viral library of over 100 million variants tested against real patient tumor samples, which allows for precise therapy optimization. 

With a multidisciplinary team experienced in virology, cancer biology, and immunology, Theolytics collaborates with leading investors and biopharmaceutical partners to advance its mission of delivering innovative cancer therapies that improve patient outcomes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4045804c_72e3_4eae_8f24_66be5ce969f6.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1565', 'Wayland Additive', 'Wayland Additive', 'https://www.waylandadditive.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wayland-additive/', 'Wayland Additive Limited is a UK-based company that develops, manufactures, and sells metal additive manufacturing machines using electron beam (eBeam) 3D printing technology. Founded in 2019 and headquartered in Huddersfield, England, the company combines over 150 years of expertise in electron beam manufacturing, originally from semiconductor engineering, to enhance precision and efficiency in metal additive manufacturing.

The flagship product, the Calibur3 metal 3D printing machine, is aimed at industrial users in sectors such as aerospace, medical, and mining. Wayland Additive addresses technical challenges in eBeam additive manufacturing and collaborates closely with customers on material and application development to meet specific industrial needs. The company has established a strong presence in precision-driven markets, serving notable clients like the UK Royal Air Force and Exergy Solutions in Canada.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bbb89cac_64bb_40a3_8187_86288d071b81.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1566', 'YASA', 'YASA Limited', 'https://yasa.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/yasa-motors/', 'YASA Limited is a British company that designs and manufactures high-performance electric motors and motor controllers, primarily for automotive and industrial applications. Founded in 2009 as a spin-out from the University of Oxford by Dr. Tim Woolmer, YASA specializes in axial-flux electric motors, which are compact, lightweight, and highly efficient. The company’s headquarters and manufacturing facilities are located in Oxfordshire, UK, with plans to expand to a new site in Bicester in 2024.

YASA produces a range of electric motors and generators, including the YASA-750, YASA-400, and YASA-250, known for their unique "pancake" shape that allows for high torque output without overheating. The company also offers bespoke motor design services for medium- and high-volume applications, supporting various sectors such as automotive, marine, aerospace, and industrial machinery. Acquired by Mercedes-Benz in 2021, YASA is committed to advancing electrification and sustainable transportation through its innovative motor technology.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7c86c893_7fd9_4312_8fd3_22ee11963839.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'yasa', null), ('1567', 'ZiO Health', 'ZiO Health Limited', 'https://www.zio-health.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ziohealth/', 'ZiO Health is a medical technology and biotechnology company founded in 2015-2016 by Dr. Neel Patel and Dr. Shaolin Liang. The company focuses on developing pocket-sized biosensor technology that brings laboratory-grade molecular testing directly to the point of care, including home settings. Their mission is to make molecular-level testing accessible to everyone, optimizing long-term health and preventing sickness.

The company offers a range of products, including the Home Health Hub, which provides instant test results and personalized wellness advice. They also specialize in Therapeutic Drug Monitoring (TDM) with AI-guided devices that monitor drug concentrations in blood, particularly for vancomycin. Their technology is adaptable for various medications and applications, including heart failure screening and custom solutions for healthcare partners. ZiO Health integrates proprietary biosensors with machine learning and AI algorithms to deliver immediate, personalized diagnostic results, enhancing patient outcomes and reducing healthcare costs.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1b759ea5_13ea_47da_87c3_654052731c57.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1568', 'NetPurpose', 'Net Purpose Ltd', 'https://www.netpurpose.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/net-purpose/', 'Net Purpose is a London-based company founded in 2019 that specializes in impact data aggregation services for investors. The company provides raw, quantitative data on the social and environmental outcomes of publicly listed companies and investment portfolios. This data helps investors monitor their portfolios, comply with ESG regulations, and enhance their sustainable investing strategies.

The platform offers comprehensive features, including data collection and analysis from thousands of global sources, ESG metrics across 200 indicators, and tools for portfolio reporting and impact evaluation. Net Purpose also assists investors in aligning their investments with the United Nations'' Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). With a growing customer base and significant funding, Net Purpose supports clients managing over $5 trillion in assets, powering more than $100 billion in sustainable funds.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4182ce89_0d29_4897_9bef_b604396add3c.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1569', 'Black Swan Data', 'Black Swan Data Limited', 'https://www.blackswan.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/black-swan-data/', 'Black Swan Data is a London-based technology and market research company founded in 2011 by Steve King and Hugo Amos. The company specializes in predictive analytics using artificial intelligence to analyze real-time social data and forecast consumer trends. Its core product, Trendscope, is a proprietary data analytics platform that processes millions of publicly available conversations from social media, blogs, and news to predict emerging trends and consumer behaviors.

Black Swan Data serves various industries, including consumer packaged goods, food and beverages, beauty and skincare, and alcohol. The platform provides insights that help teams in marketing, innovation, and insights to anticipate market demand and optimize product development. Notable clients include Disney and PepsiCo, where the company has supported significant projects and product innovations. 

In 2020, Black Swan Data was acquired by Mintel, enhancing its predictive capabilities and innovation timelines for clients. The company operates globally with offices in London, New York, Cape Town, and Szeged, employing over 160 people from diverse backgrounds. Its values focus on transparency, innovation, sustainability, and creating a positive impact.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1f51f8f7_f3c9_4d07_a4b3_49fee3ee3aaa.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'greenhouse', 'blackswan', null), ('1570', 'FundamentalVR', 'FVRVS Ltd', 'https://fundamentalsurgery.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fundamentalvr/', 'FundamentalVR is a healthcare technology company based in London, with additional offices in the US. Founded in 2012, the company focuses on creating immersive virtual reality environments for surgical training. Its mission is to enhance human capability through precision simulation, advancing pre-human training in the healthcare sector.

The flagship product, the Fundamental Surgery Platform, offers a virtual reality environment where surgeons can practice on virtual patients with realistic haptic feedback. This enhances the training experience by providing tactile sensations during simulations. Other offerings include StandaloneVR for individual training sessions and CollaborationVR, which enables multiple users to engage in virtual operating rooms for collaborative training and meetings. FundamentalVR is affiliated with notable medical institutions, reinforcing its commitment to high standards in medical education. The company has received recognition for its innovative contributions, winning three awards at the BOLD Awards in 2023.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/14ca110e_ae35_46ca_a9ba_3e43ad737628.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1571', 'Collectiv Food', 'Caprera Ltd', 'https://collectivfood.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/collectivfood/', 'Collectiv Food is a Certified B Corporation based in West London, operating in the UK and France since 2018. The company focuses on creating a sustainable and efficient food supply chain for professional kitchens in urban areas. By connecting food producers directly with buyers, Collectiv Food eliminates traditional wholesalers, improving pricing, traceability, and reducing environmental impact.

The company sources a variety of quality products, including meat, seafood, and plant-based items, leveraging collective buying power to offer competitive prices. Collectiv Food ensures full traceability of its products and provides a streamlined delivery service to professional kitchens, making it easier for them to receive the food they need without logistical challenges. 

Collectiv Food serves a diverse range of customers in the foodservice industry, including restaurants, hotel kitchens, catering firms, and independent food businesses. The company is recognized for its ethical practices and has raised significant venture capital funding to support its mission of transforming the food supply ecosystem.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/34326f6a_4d45_45a8_834b_2a182dfdf4df.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'breezy', 'collectiv', null), ('1572', 'Anton', 'Anton Corp Limited', 'https://antoncorp.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/anton-capital-ltd', 'No specific information found.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b5dd48e6_3964_4713_bc91_ac66c3506c5f.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'anton', null), ('1573', 'Tabeo', 'Tabeo Limited', 'https://tabeo.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tabeo/', 'Tabeo Tech Limited is a UK-based software development company founded in 2016. It specializes in creating an integrated platform for the finance sector, specifically designed for regulated primary care providers such as dentists, opticians, and vets. The platform streamlines payment processing, finance options, and plan management, helping providers manage costs not covered by state or private insurance.

The platform automates essential tasks like payment reconciliation and finance approval, allowing healthcare providers to concentrate on patient care. It is user-friendly on both desktop and mobile devices, with plans to expand features to include payroll and time tracking by mid-2025. Tabeo partners with global leaders to provide the necessary capital and infrastructure, focusing on delivering valuable features to its users.

Targeting primary care providers in the UK and Europe, Tabeo aims to simplify payments and automate workflows in the healthcare sector. The company operates remotely with a distributed team across 11 countries and is committed to sustainable growth while adhering to local regulations. Its headquarters are in London, Greater London.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e7e3c870_337f_48d0_877f_204c7e11367e.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'breezy', 'tabeo', null), ('1574', 'Get Living', 'Get Living London Ltd', 'https://www.getliving.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/getliving/', 'Get Living is a UK-based company founded in 2013 that focuses on the build-to-rent (BtR) sector. It creates large-scale, sustainable neighbourhoods that provide high-quality rental homes alongside vibrant community living. The company manages over 5,700 homes across seven neighbourhoods in cities like London, Manchester, and Birmingham, with more developments in progress.

The mission of Get Living is to enhance the rental experience by fostering communities that promote belonging and opportunity. Their neighbourhoods include not just residential spaces but also retail outlets, cafés, and public areas designed to encourage social connections. Get Living emphasizes long-term tenancies, eliminating middlemen and unnecessary fees, while ensuring secure, quality homes. Their portfolio features notable neighbourhoods such as East Village, Elephant Central, and The Oakgate, catering to renters who seek both quality living and a sense of community. The company is committed to sustainability and positive social impact, integrating these principles into its operations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e216563d_de79_4efa_9901_145c4a867bd5.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'breezy', 'get', null), ('1575', 'LivaNova', 'LivaNova Plc', 'https://www.livanova.com/en-us', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/livanova/', 'LivaNova PLC is a global medical technology company based in London, UK. Established in 2015 through a merger between Cyberonics, Inc. and Sorin S.p.A., LivaNova specializes in innovative medical devices and therapies for neurological and cardiac conditions.

The company operates in two main segments: Cardiopulmonary and Neuromodulation. The Cardiopulmonary segment provides a variety of products, including heart-lung machines and oxygenators, used in cardiac surgery. The Neuromodulation segment focuses on the Vagus Nerve Stimulation (VNS) Therapy System, which treats difficult-to-treat depression and drug-resistant epilepsy. LivaNova serves a diverse customer base, including healthcare providers and medical institutions, distributing its products in over 100 countries.

With around 2,900 employees, LivaNova reported revenues of approximately $1.25 billion in 2024. The company is committed to high quality and ethical practices, aiming to improve patient outcomes through its advanced therapies for heart and brain conditions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '3', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c76b647f_35ff_48dc_9bfd_e449e7f9ca62.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'livanova', null), ('1576', 'Sabio', 'Sabio Limited', 'https://sabiogroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sabio/', 'Sabio is a UK-based technology and customer experience company founded in 1998. It specializes in unified communications, contact center solutions, and digital transformation services. The company aims to enhance customer interactions and operational efficiency for organizations across various industries, including banking, housing, insurance, travel, leisure, utilities, and retail.

Sabio offers a wide range of services, including AI-driven tools for automation, workforce optimization, and contact center performance enhancements. They provide integration and support for CRM platforms like Salesforce, ensuring personalized customer experiences. Additionally, Sabio delivers cloud transformation services, data analytics for actionable insights, and expert consultancy to optimize contact center operations. Their solutions are designed to help organizations reduce costs, improve agent satisfaction, and elevate customer service across multiple channels.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/552b6898_0e1a_44d7_87b6_524874d1d6e6.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1577', 'Hived', 'Hived Limited', 'https://www.hived.space/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hived-space/about/', 'HIVED is the UK''s first customer-centric, tech-enabled, all-electric parcel delivery company, founded in 2021 by Murvah Iqbal and Mathias Krieger. Initially starting with bike deliveries, HIVED has evolved to operate a fully electric fleet, including electric heavy goods vehicles and vans, all powered by renewable electricity. The company focuses on providing sustainable delivery solutions tailored for the ecommerce sector, offering same-day, next-day, and two-day delivery services primarily within Greater London.

HIVED utilizes advanced AI technology to optimize delivery journeys, ensuring precision and efficiency. This approach enhances customer experience through real-time tracking and transparency. With a commitment to 100% emission-free delivery, HIVED aims to reduce the environmental impact of logistics while maintaining high service standards. The company has gained recognition as UK Startup of the Year 2024 and is rapidly growing as one of Europe''s fastest-growing startups, serving major ecommerce brands and their customers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/bf738743_6304_41ee_b77e_6d5625a53f4a.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'teamtailor', 'hivedhq', null), ('1578', 'Zellis', 'Zellis UK Limited', 'https://www.zellis.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zellisukltd/about/', 'Zellis is a prominent company based in the UK and Ireland, specializing in AI-enabled HR, workforce management, and payroll solutions. Founded in 1963, Zellis has evolved through various transformations and is now recognized as the largest payroll, HR, and managed service provider in the region. The company is headquartered in Hemel Hempstead, UK.

Zellis offers a wide array of services aimed at enhancing HR processes and payroll accuracy. Its core offerings include managed services for payroll administration, HR outsourcing, and recruitment support. The flagship Zellis HCM Cloud platform integrates payroll, HR, and workforce management functionalities. Additionally, Zellis provides workforce management solutions, compliance tools, and data management services. The company serves nearly 1,000 customers, processing payments for approximately three million people monthly and handling around £26 billion annually through its payroll services. Zellis has received multiple industry awards, highlighting its commitment to excellence in payroll and HR software.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e86843b1_0a7f_4d4f_a812_1c93c5d79440.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1579', 'Mintel ', 'Mintel Group Limited', 'https://www.mintel.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mintel/', 'Mintel is a global market intelligence and research firm based in London, UK, with over 50 years of experience. Founded in 1972, it specializes in providing in-depth consumer, product, and market insights to help businesses understand trends and consumer behavior. With offices in major cities worldwide, Mintel employs more than 1,200 people and serves a diverse range of clients, including global brands and retailers.

The company offers a variety of services, including market research reports, a Global New Products Database, and specialized tools like Mintel Comperemedia and Mintel Inspire. Its research methodologies involve tracking around 40,000 product launches monthly and conducting consumer surveys with over 1 million participants across four continents. Mintel''s mission is to empower clients with actionable intelligence, enabling them to innovate and make informed strategic decisions in their markets.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b51874fe_7baf_460e_bac9_096829164b80.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'mintel', null), ('1580', 'Springer Nature', 'Spring Nature Limited', 'https://www.springernature.com/in', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/springernature/', 'Springer Nature is a prominent global academic publishing company formed in May 2015 from the merger of Springer Science+Business Media and Holtzbrinck Publishing Group''s Nature Publishing Group, Palgrave Macmillan, and Macmillan Education. With roots dating back to the 19th century, it combines a rich heritage with a focus on advancing research and education.

The company publishes over 3,000 journals, including around 700 fully open access journals, and has significantly expanded its open access book publishing. Springer Nature also produces scientific, technical, and medical conference proceedings and offers educational content through its various imprints. It serves a diverse customer base, including researchers, academics, educators, and professionals across multiple fields. The company emphasizes innovation and technology to enhance the dissemination of knowledge and support authors in sharing their work globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/709f7208_7ca4_43f0_8356_10d417b2f1db.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'springernature', null), ('1581', 'Smart Pension', 'Smart Pension Limited', 'https://www.smart.co/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/smart-pension/?originalSubdomain=uk', 'Smart Pension is a UK-based workplace pension provider that operates as a defined contribution master trust. Established in 2015, it has quickly become one of the largest providers in the UK, managing over £6 billion in assets and serving 1.5 million members across more than 90,000 employers. The company focuses on a digital-first approach, offering automated pension management while emphasizing environmental, social, and governance (ESG) principles.

Smart Pension provides auto-enrolment-compliant pension schemes for employers, featuring automated setup and payroll integration. Its master trust structure ensures independent governance through a board of trustees dedicated to acting in the best interests of members. The digital platform allows employees to track contributions, adjust investment strategies, and access retirement planning tools. With a commitment to sustainability, Smart Pension prioritizes investments in companies with strong ESG credentials. The company continues to grow, adding approximately £100 million in assets every four weeks and positioning itself as a leader in the consolidation of master trusts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '3', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b5e18d88_96bd_45c5_b182_7ab05e016a3e.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'smart', null), ('1582', 'HSBC Innovation Bank', 'HSBC Innovation Bank Limited', 'https://www.hsbcinnovationbanking.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hsbc/', 'HSBC Innovation Banking is a division of HSBC that focuses on providing financial services to innovation-driven businesses and investors in the technology, life sciences, and healthcare sectors. With interconnected hubs in the US, UK, Israel, and Hong Kong, it offers tailored banking solutions for startups, growth-stage companies, and institutional investors.

The division supports clients at various growth stages, from pre-Series A to post-IPO, by combining HSBC’s global network with sector-specific expertise. Its services include early-stage banking with competitive pricing and digital tools, venture and growth financing, global fund banking, and cross-border solutions. HSBC Innovation Banking also has dedicated teams that provide industry-aligned financial strategies, helping clients navigate international expansion and connect with investors and corporate partners.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d4df6bb9_80ca_48a1_b23e_d8588c77e247.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'hsbc/External', null), ('1583', 'Isio', 'Isio Group Limited', 'https://www.isio.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/isiogroup/', 'Isio is an independent consultancy based in the UK, specializing in pensions, investment advice, employee benefits, and wealth management. Founded in 2020, Isio has quickly grown to become one of the largest pensions advisory firms in the country, employing between 1,001 and 5,000 people. The company is led by CEO Andrew Coles and aims to create better financial outcomes for clients, employees, and society through informed decision-making.

Isio offers a wide range of services, including strategic pensions advisory, investment guidance, employee benefits consulting, and personalized wealth management. The firm also develops digital and data solutions, with proprietary products like Nova, Fusion, and Engage, which enhance client outcomes across various sectors. Isio is committed to diversity, inclusion, and sustainability, and has received recognition for its excellence in the financial services industry. Through strategic acquisitions, Isio continues to strengthen its market position and service capabilities.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e76fd131_5ca7_418c_ab9f_dca457097805.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1584', 'Hikma', 'Hikma Pharmaceuticals Plc', 'https://www.hikma.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hikma-pharmaceuticals/?hl=en', 'Hikma Pharmaceuticals is a multinational pharmaceutical company founded in 1978 in Amman, Jordan, by Samih Darwazah. The company is dedicated to making high-quality medicines accessible and focuses on providing affordable and innovative treatments worldwide. Hikma is listed on the London Stock Exchange and is part of the FTSE 100 Index.

