BII manages assets valued between £7.7 to £9.9 billion and invests annually between £1.5 to £2 billion in sectors like green infrastructure and technology. The institution emphasizes impact investing, measuring success through positive economic, environmental, and social outcomes. BII provides development finance and impact investment capital to private sector companies, supports climate finance initiatives, and promotes investments in women-owned businesses. It collaborates with over 1,600 businesses and partners with governments and international organizations to maximize its impact and sustainability efforts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3e2a026e_9431_40de_9952_837d835fd056.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1670', 'Jupiter Asset Management', 'Jupiter Asset Management Limited', 'https://www.jupiteram.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jupiter-asset-management/', 'Jupiter Asset Management is a UK-based active asset management company founded in 1985. It specializes in managing equity and bond investments for private and institutional investors. As of June 30, 2025, Jupiter manages approximately £47.1 billion ($64.5 billion) in assets. The company is known for its entrepreneurial culture and commitment to high conviction, active management, helping clients achieve their long-term investment goals.

Jupiter emphasizes diverse thinking and creativity in its investment approach, allowing fund managers the freedom to follow their own investment philosophies. The company nurtures home-grown talent and prioritizes diversity and inclusion, believing that a varied workforce enhances its business. Jupiter offers a wide range of actively managed investment strategies, including equity and fixed income funds, tailored to meet the needs of its diverse client base.

With a strong commitment to corporate governance and transparency, Jupiter provides shareholders with access to financial information and encourages employee ownership through share awards. This alignment of interests ultimately benefits clients, reinforcing Jupiter''s client-first culture and dedication to superior performance.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7b3e5459_e707_4afa_a678_91d7b7b6b598.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'jupiter_careers', null), ('1671', 'Salesforce', 'Salesforce UK Limited', 'https://www.salesforce.com/uk/?ir=1', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/salesforce/', 'Salesforce is a global leader in cloud computing, founded in 1999 in San Francisco by Marc Benioff and his team. The company pioneered the Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) model, providing customer relationship management (CRM) solutions that are delivered entirely over the internet. This innovation has transformed how businesses engage with their customers by simplifying software installation and maintenance.

The core offering of Salesforce is its cloud-based CRM platform, which helps businesses manage sales, customer service, marketing, and analytics. The company also provides a platform for building custom applications and hosts AppExchange, a marketplace for third-party business apps. Salesforce offers various cloud solutions, including Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, and Marketing Cloud, all designed to enhance customer engagement and streamline business operations. With mobile access and integrated automation tools, Salesforce supports a flexible and efficient work environment for its users. 

Salesforce serves a diverse range of customers, from small businesses to large enterprises, across multiple industries, including technology, finance, and healthcare. Its commitment to customer success and innovation has established it as a dominant player in the cloud computing industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/01afb8fb_3834_492e_b12f_61ca4ff8dfd7.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1672', 'Sony PlayStation', 'Sony Interactive Entertainment Europe Limited', 'https://sonyinteractive.com/en/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sony-interactive-entertainment-llc/', 'Sony Interactive Entertainment (SIE) is a leading company in interactive entertainment and a subsidiary of Sony Group Corporation. Based in San Mateo, California, with additional hubs in London and Tokyo, SIE is renowned for its PlayStation brand, which includes gaming consoles, services, and content. The company was established in 1993 and launched the original PlayStation console in 1994. In 2016, it restructured to form Sony Interactive Entertainment LLC, integrating hardware, software, and online services.

SIE offers a range of gaming consoles, including the PlayStation series from the original PlayStation to the PlayStation 5, as well as portable systems like the PlayStation Portable and PlayStation Vita. The company also develops games through PlayStation Studios, featuring exclusive titles from renowned developers. Its services include the PlayStation Network, which provides online multiplayer, a digital storefront, and subscription options like PlayStation Plus and PlayStation Now. SIE aims to reach diverse gaming audiences, from core gamers to casual players and VR enthusiasts, while continuously expanding its global presence.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c61c7684_8a60_42b6_bb9b_3654c297cb80.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'naughtydog', null), ('1673', 'Sony Global', 'Sony Europe B.V', 'https://www.sony.com/en/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sony/', 'Sony Corporation, founded in 1946, is a Japanese multinational conglomerate known for its innovation in electronics, entertainment, and technology. The company was established by Masaru Ibuka and Akio Morita, with a philosophy that emphasizes creativity and societal contribution. Sony''s name reflects its early focus on audio technology and a youthful spirit.

Sony operates in various sectors, including consumer electronics, gaming, entertainment, semiconductors, and financial services. It is recognized for pioneering products like Japan’s first magnetic tape recorder and the Walkman. The PlayStation consoles have made a significant impact in the global gaming industry, while Sony Pictures and Sony Music contribute to its entertainment portfolio. The company also produces imaging sensors used in smartphones and industrial applications.

With a global presence, Sony has R&D centers and manufacturing facilities across North America, Europe, and Asia. The company continues to focus on advanced technologies, including AI and robotics, while expanding its entertainment ecosystem through streaming services and immersive gaming experiences.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/160893c0_246c_4b26_8b76_9edbedebda27.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1674', 'Omnicom Media Group UK', 'Omnicom Europe Limited', 'https://omnicommediagroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/omnicom-media-group_2/', 'Omnicom Media Group (OMG) is the media services division of Omnicom Group Inc., a leading global company in advertising and marketing. Based in New York City, OMG focuses on strategic media planning and buying, helping clients optimize their media investments across various platforms.

The services offered by Omnicom Media Group include developing tailored media strategies, negotiating media purchases in digital, television, print, and outdoor advertising, and providing data-driven insights to enhance campaign effectiveness. They also specialize in digital media solutions, including social media and online video advertising. As part of Omnicom Group Inc., OMG benefits from a wide range of additional marketing services, enhancing its capabilities in the industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '62', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0fa8ac2a_5667_424c_abb2_7ff1677ee5b5.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'greenhouse', 'omguk', null), ('1675', 'Poli', 'Jobs That Sponsor Limited', 'https://withpoli.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/96204026/', 'Poly is a global communications technology company that specializes in video, voice, and content collaboration solutions. As a subsidiary of HP Inc., Poly integrates its offerings into HP’s portfolio to enhance hybrid and remote work environments. The company was originally founded as Polycom in 1990, merged with Plantronics in 2018, and rebranded as Poly in 2019.

Poly provides a wide range of products designed for various workspaces, including professional headsets, desk phones, and video conferencing equipment. Their solutions focus on delivering high-quality audio and video experiences, making communication more effective in modern workplaces. Additionally, Poly offers software and services that enhance collaboration and productivity, including analytics tools and AI-powered features. Their target customers include enterprises, remote workers, IT departments, and professionals across various industries who seek reliable communication solutions.', 'Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1ce7116e_3939_417b_a43b_64a72f67eb8e.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1676', 'Oxford University Press', 'Oxford Press Limited', 'https://corp.oup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oup/', 'Oxford University Press (OUP) is the largest university press in the world, established in 1586 as part of the University of Oxford. It publishes around 6,000 new titles each year, covering a wide range of academic and educational fields. Its offerings include academic journals, English language teaching materials, children''s books, music publications, religious texts, reference works, and classic literature.

With a global presence, OUP has offices in multiple countries, including a significant international office in New York. The organization adapts to technological advancements by providing many publications in electronic formats. As a charitable entity, OUP''s profits support the University of Oxford''s mission in scholarship, research, and education. It serves a diverse customer base, including academic institutions, educators, students, researchers, libraries, and general readers. OUP is headquartered in Oxford, England, and employs nearly 6,000 people worldwide, reflecting a rich heritage in publishing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5171d4c2_80c8_4c39_97b8_02e74f77ae4e.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'corp', null), ('1677', 'Daily Mail and General Trust (DMGT)', 'Daily Mail and General Trust plc', 'https://www.dmgt.com/', 'https://linkedin.com/company/dmgtplc/', 'DMGT plc, or Daily Mail and General Trust, is a diversified multinational company based in London with a rich history spanning over 130 years. Originally established in 1922 to manage the Harmsworth family''s newspaper interests, DMGT has grown into a conglomerate that operates in consumer media, business-to-business services, and venture capital. The company generates around £1 billion in annual revenue through its various subsidiaries in the UK, Ireland, and globally.

In consumer media, DMGT publishes well-known titles such as the Daily Mail, The Mail on Sunday, and Metro, along with the digital platform MailOnline. Its B2B services include Risk Management Solutions, which specializes in catastrophe risk modeling, and Euromoney Institutional Investor, which serves finance professionals. DMG Events organizes exhibitions and conferences, while Landmark provides property information services. Additionally, dmg ventures invests in early-stage technology startups, focusing on innovations in both consumer and B2B sectors. DMGT is committed to sustainability and has initiatives aimed at carbon reduction and environmental compliance.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4dccf11d_0246_4d8a_9a90_3fb4eb723aac.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'dmgt', null), ('1678', 'RingCentral', 'RingCentral UK Ltd', 'https://www.ringcentral.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ringcentral/', 'RingCentral, Inc. is a prominent American provider of cloud-based communication and collaboration solutions, established in 1999 and headquartered in Belmont, California. The company specializes in unified communications as a service (UCaaS), contact center as a service (CCaaS), and AI-powered communication tools, catering to businesses globally. With a revenue of over $2.2 billion in 2023, RingCentral has expanded its focus from small businesses to a wide range of enterprise clients.

The company offers a diverse suite of products, including RingCentral MVP, which integrates messaging, video conferencing, and cloud phone systems. Their cloud-based contact center solution enhances customer engagement with AI tools, while platforms like RingEX and RingCX support business growth and customer experience management. RingCentral also provides over 500 pre-built integrations and custom API development to streamline workflows.

RingCentral serves various industries, including healthcare, finance, education, and technology, with a customer base that includes both small businesses and large enterprises. The company has a global presence, operating in North America, Europe, Asia, and Australia, and maintains a strong reseller network and partnerships with major telecom providers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '12', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0469303b_d027_49eb_bfd1_9de216df0c04.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workday', 'ringcentral/RingCentral_Careers', null), ('1679', 'Rocket Software', 'Rocket Software UK Limited', 'https://www.rocketsoftware.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rocket-software/', 'Rocket Software is a global technology company founded in 1990 and headquartered near Boston, Massachusetts. The company specializes in software development aimed at modernizing and enhancing legacy IT systems, particularly those operating on IBM platforms like IBM Z and IBM Power. With a mission to help organizations modernize their critical systems without disruption, Rocket Software serves over 12,500 customers worldwide, including 43 of the Fortune 50 companies across various industries such as banking, healthcare, manufacturing, and government.

The company offers a range of services, including application modernization tools, data management solutions, and platforms for DevOps and automation. It also provides specialized tools for security and vulnerability management, as well as enterprise information management. Rocket Software has expanded its capabilities through strategic acquisitions, enhancing its product portfolio and customer base. The company fosters a culture of empathy and community commitment, supporting employee volunteerism and investing in the development of future software developers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/29e77516_061f_4d7a_902a_ea4bce6eea20.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'rocketsoftware', null), ('1680', 'esure Group', 'esure Services Limited', 'https://www.esuregroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/esure/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '21', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/1950e7b3_6cf3_4366_b731_4728c2d1c345.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'esureGroup', null), ('1681', 'PostHog', 'Hiberly Ltd', 'https://posthog.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/posthog/', 'PostHog is a technology company founded in January 2020 by James Hawkins and Tim Glaser, emerging from Y Combinator''s Winter 2020 batch. It offers a comprehensive product and data analytics platform tailored for product engineers, product managers, and designers at high-growth startups, particularly those transitioning from Series B to IPO. The platform enables teams to analyze, test, observe, and deploy new features efficiently within a single integrated system.

Initially starting as an open-source product analytics tool, PostHog has grown to serve over 100,000 users and 70,000 teams worldwide. Its offerings include product analytics for tracking user behavior, feature testing and deployment tools for safe experimentation, real-time observability for monitoring product performance, and data warehouse integration for enhanced data accessibility. The platform is designed to be developer-friendly, streamlining analytics and deployment processes to allow engineering teams to focus on building user-centric products.', 'Sponsorship can be offered to successful applicants if they are already based in the UK or US. The company does not accommodate for, or offer sponsorship on the basis of, relocation.', '1', '1', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3a3b534d_c535_4c34_96cd_e658ace4d80f.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/posthog', null), ('1682', 'Fitch Group', 'Fitch Ratings Limited', 'https://www.fitch.group/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fitchgroup/', 'Fitch Group, Inc. is a global financial services organization known for its leadership in credit ratings, research, and risk analysis. Founded in 1913 in New York City, it has grown to become one of the "Big Three" credit rating agencies, alongside Moody’s and Standard & Poor’s. The company operates from dual headquarters in New York and London, with a presence in over 38 offices worldwide.

Fitch provides a range of services, including forward-looking credit ratings for corporations, governments, and financial instruments, as well as in-depth research and commentary on market trends and economic forecasts. The company also offers risk solutions, including analytics and advisory services, and is recognized for its transparency in environmental, social, and governance (ESG) ratings. Fitch serves a diverse clientele, including investors, investment banks, debt issuers, and corporations across various industries, helping them assess credit risk and comply with regulatory requirements. With a workforce of over 2,000 employees, Fitch combines local expertise with a global network to deliver valuable insights.', 'Sponsorship can be offered on a case-by-case basis.', '4', '74', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/31744ba8_5a00_4ab9_93e5_769c4b909060.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1683', 'Canada Goose', 'Canada Goose Services Limited', 'https://www.canadagoose.com/uk/en/home-page', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/canada-goose-inc/', 'Canada Goose is a Canadian luxury apparel company founded in 1957 in Toronto. Originally named Metro Sportswear Ltd, it specialized in wool vests, raincoats, and snowmobile suits. The company evolved significantly after David Reiss joined in 1972, introducing a down-filling machine that enhanced the production of winter jackets. The brand name changed to Canada Goose in 2000, and under the leadership of Dani Reiss, who became CEO in 2001, the company focused on consumer products and experienced rapid growth.

Canada Goose is known for its high-quality winter apparel, particularly down-filled parkas and jackets designed for extreme cold weather. The flagship product, the Expedition Parka, was initially developed for scientists in Antarctica and is recognized for its warmth and functionality. The product range has expanded to include year-round apparel, accessories, and footwear, all emphasizing craftsmanship and Canadian manufacturing. The brand appeals to a diverse customer base, including outdoor enthusiasts and luxury consumers seeking reliable and stylish cold-weather gear.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e5257df6_583a_44d1_9bdc_703c2b3b46c0.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'CanadaGooseCareers', null), ('1684', 'Autolus', 'Autolus Ltd', 'https://www.autolus.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/autolus-ltd-/', 'Autolus Therapeutics plc is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company based in London, UK, with operations in Philadelphia, USA. Founded in 2014 by Dr. Martin Pule, the company specializes in next-generation programmed T-cell therapies for cancer treatment. Under the leadership of CEO Christian Itin, Autolus focuses on developing chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) T-cell therapies that target hematological malignancies and solid tumors.

The company has a diverse product pipeline, including AUTO1, which is in Phase 2 for B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia, and AUTO3, currently in Phase 1/2 for solid tumors. Autolus has in-house capabilities for T-cell engineering and production, and it actively collaborates with healthcare providers to develop patient-specific therapies. The company is listed on NASDAQ under the ticker AUTL and aims to address high unmet needs in oncology, particularly for relapsed or refractory blood cancers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e3f5867c_38f9_4e34_8d84_b1391e2c657d.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1686', 'JPMorganChase', 'JPMorgan Chase Bank, National Association', 'https://www.jpmorgan.com/global', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jpmorgan/', 'J.P. Morgan is a prominent financial services firm that operates as part of JPMorgan Chase & Co., one of the largest financial institutions in the world. The company has a rich history dating back to the late 19th century, founded by J.P. Morgan and Anthony Drexel. It played a significant role in shaping the U.S. financial landscape, including the merger that created General Electric.

J.P. Morgan provides a variety of financial services, including investment banking, commercial banking, financial transaction processing, and asset management. The firm serves a diverse clientele, including corporations, governments, financial institutions, and individual investors, across various sectors and regions. Its extensive offerings and historical significance make J.P. Morgan a key player in the global financial sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '734', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/0b9e59b3_a214_4588_9bbe_e6489213fc51.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'jpmc', 'jpmc', null), ('1687', 'Cleantech Group', 'Cleantech Group Europe Limited', 'https://www.cleantech.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cleantech-group/', 'Cleantech Group is a research-driven company founded in 2000 and based in San Francisco, with a global presence across North America, Europe, and Asia. The company focuses on catalyzing sustainable growth through innovation in the cleantech sector, addressing environmental and climate challenges.

Cleantech Group offers a range of services structured around four main pillars: research, consulting, events, and advocacy. Their research provides in-depth analysis and insights on cleantech trends, while consulting services help clients set strategic priorities and engage with innovation partners. The company organizes events that facilitate networking and knowledge exchange among stakeholders in the cleantech ecosystem. Additionally, they promote collaboration among businesses, finance, government, and civil society to drive impactful climate innovation.

Recognized as a leading authority in cleantech innovation, Cleantech Group publishes the Global Cleantech 100 report, highlighting innovative companies in the sector. Their diverse clientele includes corporates, investors, governments, entrepreneurs, and other stakeholders seeking to advance sustainability and innovation.', 'Sponsorship can be offered across most roles and many London-based employees are being sponsored.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d0c72eda_534e_45ae_b7a7_c5526f6fff00.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'cleantechgroup', null), ('1688', 'Entrust', 'Entrust (Europe) Limited', 'https://www.entrust.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/entrust/', 'Entrust is a global technology company based in Shakopee, Minnesota, specializing in digital security solutions. With a workforce of over 2,500 employees, Entrust serves customers in more than 150 countries. The company offers a range of products and services focused on secure financial card issuance, e-passport production, user authentication, and digital certificates for websites and mobile devices.

Entrust''s portfolio includes solutions for identity verification, cloud security, data encryption, and hardware security modules. The company has enhanced its capabilities through strategic acquisitions, including Onfido for identity verification, HyTrust for cloud security, and WorldReach Software for border management. Entrust''s customers span government agencies, financial institutions, and enterprises that require secure identity and data protection for various activities. The company rebranded from Entrust Datacard to Entrust in 2020 to highlight its commitment to secure identity and data protection.', 'The company is able to offer sponsorship for some roles. ', '1', '18', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/06118f3a_45f1_40b7_8622_8806934b2ebb.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1689', 'Jaguar Land Rover (JLR)', 'Jaguar Land Rover Limited', 'https://www.jaguarlandrover.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jaguar-land-rover_1/', null, 'The company offers sponsorship on a case-by-case basis.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b70f7e85_6aaf_4b0d_a4b6_1498534b3cfc.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'jaguarlandrover', null), ('1690', 'NHS', 'NHS', 'https://nhs.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/nhs/', 'The National Health Service (NHS) is the collective term for the publicly funded healthcare systems of the United Kingdom: the National Health Service (England), NHS Scotland, NHS Wales, and Health and Social Care (Northern Ireland) which was created separately and is often referred to locally as "the NHS". The original three systems were established in 1948 (NHS Wales/GIG Cymru was founded in 1969) as part of major social reforms following the Second World War, and officially launched at Park Hospital in Davyhulme, near Manchester, England (now known as Trafford General Hospital). The founding principles were that services should be comprehensive, universal and free at the point of delivery. Each service provides a comprehensive range of health services, provided without charge for residents of the United Kingdom apart from dental treatment and optical care. In England, NHS patients have to pay prescription charges; some, such as those aged over 60, or those on certain state benefits, are exempt. Taken together, the four services in 2015–16 employed around 1.6 million people with a combined budget of £136.7 billion. In 2024, the total health sector workforce across the United Kingdom was 1,499,368.', 'Many roles can be sponsored.', '1', '4209', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/33c3e8fe-0259-49ae-a796-269d7c2b56e2.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'teamtailor', 'nhs', null), ('1691', 'DNEG', 'Double Negative Limited', 'https://www.dneg.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/dnegvfx/', 'DNEG, formerly known as Double Negative, is a prominent British-Indian visual effects (VFX), computer animation, and stereo conversion studio founded in 1998 in London. The company was established by a group of seven founders who aimed to merge artistic excellence with technological innovation in the visual effects industry. DNEG rebranded in 2014 after merging with the Indian company Prime Focus, which expanded its global presence.

Headquartered in Fitzrovia, London, DNEG operates studios in various locations, including Vancouver, Mumbai, Los Angeles, and Toronto, employing around 7,000 people worldwide. The company specializes in high-end visual effects and animation services for feature films, television, and streaming content. Their offerings include invisible effects, digital environments, character animation, and stereo conversion for 3D films. DNEG has received numerous accolades, including 8 Academy Awards and 8 BAFTA Awards, for its work on major film franchises and productions, solidifying its reputation in the global VFX industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8a37682a-808f-47e4-8842-b4ed7f034b37.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'jobvite', 'double-negative-visual-effects', null), ('1692', 'Lucanet', 'LucaNet (UK) Limited', 'https://www.lucanet.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lucanet-ag/', 'Lucanet is a German financial software company founded in 1999, specializing in Financial Performance Management (FPM) solutions for CFO offices and finance teams. Its flagship product, the CFO Solution Platform, is a cloud-based SaaS platform that integrates key financial management functions such as consolidation, planning, reporting, ESG reporting, lease accounting, and tax compliance. This platform is compatible with various ERP systems and databases, allowing for seamless integration and quick adoption.

With over 500 employees, Lucanet serves more than 5,000 organizations globally, including notable clients like Toshiba, Leica, and Rocket Internet. The company focuses on simplifying and digitalizing financial management processes, enabling finance teams to automate complex tasks and reduce risks associated with manual data entry. Lucanet has expanded its capabilities through strategic partnerships and acquisitions, reinforcing its position as a leader in corporate performance management software.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/10307eb8-aa9b-4310-bca4-cb9c3b89a5ed.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1693', 'AB Tasty', 'AB TASTY LIMITED LTD', 'https://www.abtasty.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ab-tasty/', 'AB Tasty is a Software as a Service (SaaS) company that specializes in website optimization and conversion rate improvement. Founded in 2014 by Alix de Sagazan and Rémi Aubert, the company promotes a test-and-learn approach to help businesses achieve better results through continuous optimization.

The AB Tasty platform enables marketers to make data-driven decisions by running A/B tests, multivariate tests, and creating personalized user experiences. Its tools are designed to be fast and accessible, allowing clients to effectively enhance their digital presence. The company has expanded its capabilities through acquisitions, including epoq and Dotaki, which enhance its personalization features.

With over 1,000 customers worldwide, AB Tasty serves various industries that rely on digital marketing and e-commerce. The company has a global presence with offices in multiple countries, including France, the UK, Germany, Spain, the US, Singapore, and Australia. AB Tasty fosters a culture of creativity and collaboration among its team of around 300 employees, focusing on innovation and agility in its operations.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/4646a697-715a-40ff-86c1-4074a1a5bb56.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('1694', 'Land Securities (Landsec)', 'Land Securities Properties Limited', 'https://landsec.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/landsec/', 'Landsec, officially known as Land Securities Group PLC, is the largest commercial property development and investment company in the UK. Founded in 1944 by Harold Samuel, the company has been publicly traded as a Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT) since 2007. Headquartered in London, Landsec manages approximately 97 properties across 24 million square feet, with a market capitalization of $4.1 billion as of 2022.

The company specializes in property development, focusing on commercial and mixed-use projects, including notable assets like Piccadilly Lights, Westgate Oxford shopping center, and Trinity Leeds retail complex. Landsec also offers investment management services, providing shareholders with exposure to prime UK real estate. The company is committed to sustainability, with a significant portion of its office buildings holding high Energy Performance Certificate ratings and recognition for its climate leadership.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/fec85bc3-4b38-4eb2-8a37-5b66988c4b12.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'Landseccareers', null), ('1695', 'Rolls-Royce', 'Rolls-Royce plc', 'https://rolls-royce.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rolls-royce/', 'Rolls-Royce is a British multinational engineering company founded in 1904 by Charles Rolls and Henry Royce. Initially known for its luxury automobiles, the brand became synonymous with high-performance and exquisite craftsmanship, producing iconic models like the Silver Ghost and Phantom. Over the years, Rolls-Royce transitioned into the aerospace sector, establishing itself as a leader in the design and manufacture of aircraft engines for military and commercial aviation.

Today, Rolls-Royce plc focuses on aerospace propulsion systems and power solutions. The company produces a range of engines, including turbofan, turboprop, and jet engines, with notable models such as the RB211 and Trent series. Additionally, Rolls-Royce provides power generation and propulsion systems for marine, energy, and industrial applications. The company also offers comprehensive maintenance, repair, and overhaul services to support its customers worldwide, ensuring operational efficiency and reliability. Rolls-Royce serves a diverse clientele, including commercial airlines, military forces, and energy companies, while its automotive segment is now managed by BMW.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/945f50a6-cff1-4a70-a3f9-7027ed97c4d6.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workday', 'rollsroyce/Careers', null), ('1696', 'Grant Thornton', 'Grant Thornton Services LLP', 'https://www.grantthornton.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/grant-thornton-uk-llp/', 'Grant Thornton UK is a prominent professional services firm based in London, with a history dating back to 1904. As part of the global Grant Thornton network, the firm has grown to become one of the largest accounting and advisory services providers in the UK, employing over 5,500 people across more than 20 offices.

The firm offers a wide range of services, including audit and assurance, tax advisory, and various advisory services such as business consulting and risk management. Grant Thornton UK focuses on serving medium and large corporates, government organizations, and individual clients, helping them navigate regulatory challenges and achieve sustainable growth. With a commitment to mid-sized companies, the firm leverages its extensive expertise to support clients in improving operational effectiveness and managing risks.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '30', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c40225db-245d-4e1d-92fe-7745de546e52.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'CareersGrantThornton', null), ('1697', 'Oracle', 'Oracle Corporation UK Limited', 'https://www.oracle.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oracle/', 'Wharton Online is the digital education division of the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania, established in 2015. It offers high-quality business education through online platforms, reaching millions of learners worldwide. With a dedicated team of about 10 people, Wharton Online maintains an entrepreneurial spirit in the education technology space.

The division provides over 80 courses taught by tenured faculty, including specializations in fintech, healthcare management, business foundations, and entrepreneurship. Wharton Online also offers accredited certificates, such as the Leadership and Management Certificate and the Business Analytics Certificate, recognized by the International Association for Continuing Education and Training (IACET). Courses are available on major online learning platforms like Coursera and edX, and through partnerships with organizations like Emeritus and ExecOnline. Wharton Online collaborates with other University of Pennsylvania schools to create interdisciplinary content and serves both individual learners and global corporations seeking customized training.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/10f95ce9-09d6-4ba2-b701-803d27f73a23.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'bamboohr', 'oracle', null), ('1698', 'T.D. Williamson', 'TD Williamson (UK) Limited', 'https://www.tdwilliamson.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tdw/', 'T.D. Williamson (TDW) is a global leader in pipeline equipment, products, and services, ensuring the safe and efficient operation of pressurized pipeline systems. Founded in 1920 in Tulsa, Oklahoma, TDW has evolved into a pioneering solutions provider with a focus on maximizing pipeline uptime and minimizing operational risks. The company emphasizes sustainability and innovation, aligning its efforts with industry goals for a more sustainable energy future.

TDW offers a comprehensive range of products and services tailored to the pipeline industry. This includes pipeline pigging systems for cleaning and maintaining pipelines, advanced isolation solutions like the STOPPLE® Train system, and pipeline inspection and integrity services. Additionally, TDW provides specialized equipment for pipeline modifications, corrosion protection, and comprehensive training programs. Serving a diverse customer base in the oil and gas sector, TDW supports pipeline operators worldwide in maintaining safe and reliable energy infrastructure.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b6fd0be4-6993-4005-9dd1-6790a727e3f9.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workday', 'tdwilliamson/TDWCareers', null), ('1699', 'Shell', 'Shell International Ltd', 'https://www.shell.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/shell/', 'Shell plc is a prominent global energy company based in The Hague, Netherlands, with a rich history that began in the late 19th century. Formed in 1907 from the merger of the Royal Dutch Petroleum Company and the Shell Transport and Trading Company, Shell operates in over 90 countries and is a key player in the oil and gas industry.

The company focuses on the exploration, production, refining, and marketing of crude oil and natural gas. Shell explores and extracts these resources worldwide, with operations in regions such as Russia, Venezuela, and the US. It refines crude oil into various fuels, including gasoline and diesel, and markets these products through a vast network of service stations. Additionally, Shell produces chemical feedstocks and specialty chemicals for industrial applications, a segment it has developed since 1929. The company is also expanding into renewable energy and low-carbon technologies. 

Shell serves a diverse customer base, including individual consumers, industrial clients, and the aviation and shipping industries, all recognized by its iconic yellow and red shell logo.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ac01c8e0-92d0-493b-810a-6112d470598c.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workday', 'shell/ShellCareers', null), ('1700', 'Barclays', 'Barclays Bank UK PLC', 'https://www.barclays.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/barclays-bank/', 'Barclays UK is a prominent British financial institution with a history that dates back to 1690. Originally founded by goldsmith bankers John Freame and Thomas Gould in London, it became known as Barclays in 1736. As one of the UK''s oldest and largest banks, it is recognized as part of the "big four" banks by market share.

Operating as a key division of Barclays PLC, Barclays UK provides a wide array of financial services. Its offerings include retail banking products such as current accounts, savings accounts, mortgages, and credit cards. The bank also serves corporate clients with business accounts, lending, and cash management solutions. Additionally, it supports investment banking activities, providing advisory and risk management services, and offers wealth management for high-net-worth individuals. With a commitment to innovation, Barclays has been a leader in digital banking, continuously enhancing customer convenience through technology. The bank is headquartered in London and serves approximately 48 million customers globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '390', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8e7eb686-dbbd-4efc-8f8c-b0c87c9e40e3.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'External_Career_Site_Barclays', null), ('1701', 'SAP', 'SAP UK Limited', 'https://www.sap.com/uk/index.html', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sap/', 'SAP is a global leader in enterprise software, founded in 1972 in Germany by five former IBM employees. The company focuses on developing applications that enable real-time business data processing, addressing inefficiencies in traditional systems. 

SAP''s core offering is its enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, which integrates various business functions into a unified system. This helps streamline processes and improve information flow across organizations. Key products include SAP R/1, R/2, R/3, and the next-generation SAP S/4HANA, along with platforms like SAP NetWeaver and SAP HANA. SAP also offers solutions in finance, supply chain, human resources, customer relationship management, and analytics, and has expanded into cloud services, machine learning, and IoT solutions.

SAP serves a diverse global customer base across multiple industries, including manufacturing, retail, finance, healthcare, and the public sector. Its software solutions support businesses of all sizes, enabling them to optimize operations and drive growth in a digital economy.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3ebe4c50-0343-4c99-8e6a-684de45fd1fa.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'sap', null), ('1702', 'Guardian News & Media', 'Guardian News and Media Ltd.', 'https://theguardian.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/theguardian/', 'The Guardian is a prominent British daily newspaper recognized for its investigative journalism and independent editorial stance. Founded in 1821 as the Manchester Guardian, it transitioned to a national publication in 1959 and moved its editorial staff to London in 1964, enhancing its influence across the UK.

The Guardian provides extensive news coverage across various topics, including politics, culture, sports, and international affairs. It is well-regarded for its in-depth reporting and balanced editorial approach. In addition to its print publication, The Guardian has a strong digital presence, offering real-time news updates and multimedia content to a global audience. The Guardian Media Group also publishes The Observer, a Sunday newspaper known for its analysis and commentary.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b3829c94-494d-4053-b013-6cd39a3e7b58.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'guardian', null), ('1703', 'Vodafone', 'Vodafone Limited', 'https://www.vodafone.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/vodafone/', 'Vodafone Group Plc is a leading British multinational telecommunications company based in Newbury and London. Established in 1984, it has grown to be one of the largest mobile network operators worldwide, with a strong presence in Asia, Africa, Europe, and Oceania. Vodafone made history by initiating the UK''s first mobile phone call in 1985 and has continued to innovate, including the first 3G call in 2001 and a live holographic call using 5G technology.

The company provides a wide range of telecommunications services, such as mobile voice communications, messaging, data services, and fixed broadband. Vodafone also offers integrated communications, mobile advertising, and machine-to-machine solutions for IoT applications. Its product lineup includes various branded phones and devices, catering to different customer needs from basic mobile phones to advanced smart devices. With a diverse customer base that includes individual consumers and businesses, Vodafone is committed to meeting the evolving demands of the telecommunications market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '121', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/54e77e1b-4b6c-45a3-bf53-9e6e85ce05f4.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'workday', 'vodafone/Careers_Vodafone', null), ('1705', 'Hippo Labs', 'HIPPO LABS LTD', 'https://www.hippolabs.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hippo-labs-ltd/', 'Hippo Labs Ltd is a UK-based software development company founded in March 2021 and headquartered in London. The company specializes in healthcare technology aimed at NHS GP Practices. Founded by Sachin Gupta and Alistair McMaster, Hippo Labs focuses on improving health outcomes through innovative digital tools.

Their flagship product, the Hippo Recaller, automates patient recalls and appointment scheduling, allowing healthcare professionals to concentrate on patient care. The software operates in three stages: it intelligently analyzes patient needs, automates communication for self-booking, and provides lists for personal follow-up. Additionally, it offers deep-dive analytics for tracking quality and outcomes, ensuring transparency for practices.

Hippo Labs prioritizes security and compliance with NHS digital standards, ensuring patient data is protected. Their solutions are designed for quick setup and are supported by dedicated customer service. Currently, their platform supports proactive care for over 100,000 patients, demonstrating effectiveness in improving patient outcomes while reducing administrative workloads. The company is also part of the DigitalHealth.London Accelerator program, highlighting its commitment to healthcare innovation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/75e272bf-8556-4a92-bc62-33db672b5777.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'bamboohr', 'hippolabs', null), ('1706', 'Moneycorp', 'TTT MONEYCORP LIMITED', 'https://www.moneycorp.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/moneycorp/', 'Moneycorp is a British financial services company based in London, specializing in foreign exchange and international payments. Founded in 1962, it has evolved from a bureau de change into a global provider of cross-border payment solutions, operating in the UK, North America, Europe, and Asia.

The company offers a wide range of services, including spot foreign exchange transactions, forward contracts, option contracts, and mass payment services through API integrations and a self-service platform. Moneycorp supports payments in over 120 currencies and serves a diverse client base, including individuals, small and medium-sized enterprises, large corporations, and financial institutions. With a strong focus on B2B services, approximately 90-91% of its revenue comes from corporate and institutional clients.

Moneycorp combines advanced technology with personalized service to deliver secure and efficient payment solutions. The company emphasizes values such as belonging, excellence, accountability, client orientation, and entrepreneurship, making it a trusted partner in the global payments landscape.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7188949d-d6c0-47ba-9585-32afb2cc580b.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'jobvite', 'moneycorp', null), ('1707', 'JD Group', 'J D Sports Fashion PLC', 'https://www.jdplc.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jd-sports-fashion-plc', 'JD Sports Fashion plc is a British multinational sports-fashion retailer based in Bury, Greater Manchester. Founded in 1981, the company has expanded to operate over 4,500 stores in 36 countries, with a strong presence in the UK, Europe, North America, and Asia Pacific. JD Sports is publicly traded on the London Stock Exchange and has a market capitalization of approximately £8 billion.

The company specializes in branded sportswear, footwear, outdoor gear, and streetwear, catering primarily to youth and young adults aged 16-35. JD Sports combines physical retail locations, such as flagship stores in Times Square and Oxford Street, with integrated e-commerce platforms to enhance its omnichannel strategy. The company is also known for its acquisition-driven growth, having acquired notable brands like Shoe Palace and Finish Line. JD Sports is committed to social responsibility through initiatives like The JD Foundation, which supports disadvantaged youth, and focuses on sustainable operations and ethical labor practices.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/189692bc-7791-457f-9c9c-1e1fb2057bdc.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1708', 'Haleon', 'HALEON UK SERVICES LIMITED', 'https://www.haleon.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/haleon/', 'Haleon is a global consumer healthcare company that became independent on July 18, 2022, following a demerger from GlaxoSmithKline. It is publicly traded on the London and New York stock exchanges and is part of the FTSE 100 index. The company has roots dating back to 1715, evolving from a single apothecary shop into a leader in consumer health products through the integration of brands from GSK, Novartis, and Pfizer.

Haleon offers a wide range of consumer healthcare products across various categories, including therapeutic oral health with brands like Sensodyne, vitamins and supplements such as Centrum, pain relief products like Panadol and Advil, and respiratory health solutions like Theraflu. The company operates in over 100 markets, focusing on everyday health needs with science-backed products. With a reported revenue of approximately £10.4 billion in 2022 and a workforce of about 22,000 employees, Haleon is dedicated to enhancing health through trusted brands and innovation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '12', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ab4f6a31-7b07-4073-95c1-4827d687bc11.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'gsknch/GSKCareers', null), ('1709', 'Tessl', 'Tessl AI Limite', 'https://www.tessl.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tesslio/', 'Tessl is a London-based startup focused on AI Native Software Development, integrating artificial intelligence into the software creation and maintenance process. Founded by an experienced entrepreneur, Tessl aims to change how developers and their teams design, write, test, and maintain software by automating these tasks with AI.

The company offers an AI-powered platform that allows users to specify software requirements in natural language or code. This platform generates code, supports testing in a sandbox environment, and automates ongoing maintenance to ensure software reliability. Tessl''s services include automated code remediation and a specification-centric development approach, enabling teams to adapt software dynamically based on usage patterns. The company operates on a subscription-based model and is currently in a testing phase, with plans for a commercial launch in 2025. Tessl envisions a future where software development is faster and more adaptable, addressing the complexities of modern software.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/191e76cd-876b-4675-a068-839fec19bdbd.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1710', 'McLaren Racing', 'McLaren Racing Limited', 'https://www.mclaren.com/racing/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mclaren-racing-ltd/', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '16', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7a55f701-7ddb-43c4-9db5-20667963ede3.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'recruitee', 'racingcareers.mclaren.com', null), ('1711', 'Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS Formula One Team', 'Mercedes-Benz Grand Prix Ltd', 'https://www.mercedesamgf1.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mercedes-amg-petronas-formula-one-team/', 'The Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS Formula One Team is the official racing team of Mercedes-AMG, competing in the FIA Formula One World Championship. Based in the United Kingdom, the team operates technology centers in Brackley and Brixworth and employs over 1,000 people focused on designing, developing, and racing their Formula One cars.

With a history dating back to 1954, the team re-entered Formula One as a factory team in 2010 and has since achieved remarkable success, winning seven consecutive double Drivers'' and Constructors'' Championships from 2014 to 2020, and an eighth Constructors'' Championship in 2021. The team develops high-performance racing cars powered by advanced hybrid engines and combines expertise in aerodynamics, powertrain engineering, and race strategy to compete in over 20 Grands Prix each season.

Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS is co-owned by Mercedes-Benz Group, Ineos, and team principal Toto Wolff. Known as the "Silver Arrows," the team emphasizes teamwork, innovation, and precision engineering, making it a leading force in modern Formula One racing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '7', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/070c7c2a-8f63-4a2a-9557-ceda2cdae22c.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'mbgp/Mercedes-AMGF1', null), ('1712', 'GSK', 'GSK Plc', 'https://www.gsk.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gsk/', 'GSK plc (GlaxoSmithKline) is a British multinational biopharmaceutical company based in London, established in 2000 from the merger of Glaxo Wellcome and SmithKline Beecham. With a workforce of around 70,000, GSK operates globally, featuring research and development centers in the United States, Belgium, China, and the UK.

The company focuses on discovering, developing, and manufacturing pharmaceutical medicines and vaccines. GSK develops treatments for various conditions, including respiratory diseases, cancer, and infectious diseases like HIV. It has pioneered over 15 vaccines, particularly in respiratory and immunological areas. GSK also has a strong presence in dermatology and oncology, bolstered by strategic acquisitions. The company is committed to innovative science, investing in research to improve health outcomes through personalized medicine approaches.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/106e94d8-0af2-4961-9650-faac44c42ea1.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'gsk/Pharma', null), ('1713', 'Oracle Red Bull Racing', 'Red Bull Racing Ltd', 'https://www.redbullracing.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/red-bull-racing/', 'Red Bull Racing is a prominent Formula One team owned by Red Bull GmbH, operating under a British license since acquiring Jaguar Racing in 2004. The team is led by Christian Horner, who became the youngest F1 team principal at his appointment. Red Bull Technology serves as the technical division, focusing on the design and development of F1 cars and innovations.

The team competes in Formula One with a strong emphasis on car development, race strategy, and driver management. It has established key technical partnerships with engine suppliers, including Renault and Honda, and currently develops its power units through Red Bull Powertrains. Under the guidance of design chief Adrian Newey, Red Bull Racing has produced aerodynamically advanced cars that have achieved significant success, including multiple championships from 2010 to 2013 and a resurgence in recent years with driver Max Verstappen. The team also collaborates with its sister team, Racing Bulls, to develop new driving talent.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '18', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e8ed9b2e-d906-405e-abc3-85738f476a8a.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'workday', 'redbulltechnology/RB_Racing', null), ('1714', 'Kaluza', ' Kaluza Ltd', 'https://www.kaluza.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kaluza/', 'Kaluza is a London-based energy software company that specializes in a real-time cloud platform designed for the energy sector. It offers software-as-a-service (SaaS) technology that helps major energy suppliers modernize their operations, reduce costs, and improve customer engagement. Kaluza’s platform supports innovations like smart electric vehicle (EV) charging and low-carbon technologies, contributing to decarbonization and a more flexible energy system.

The company provides a live data platform that automates core operations for energy utilities, along with tools for optimizing energy flows and revolutionizing billing processes. Kaluza is a B Corp-certified business with a global presence, operating in the UK, Australia, Portugal, and the United States, and serving millions of customers through its energy supplier clients. As part of the OVO Group, Kaluza is recognized for its technological innovation and commitment to sustainability.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '28', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e66b68e4-51f1-4072-936a-d093f4c080e5.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1715', 'Metro Bank', 'METRO BANK PLC', 'https://www.metrobankonline.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/metro-bank-uk-', 'Metro Bank is an independent UK bank that began operations in 2010 and is headquartered in London. Founded by Vernon Hill and Anthony Thomson, it has emerged as a significant challenger to traditional banks in the UK. The bank focuses on enhancing customer experience and has expanded its branch network across the country.

Metro Bank offers a comprehensive range of financial services for individuals and businesses. Its offerings include various savings and current accounts, personal and business loans, credit cards, foreign currency accounts, and payment solutions. The bank also provides private banking services, online and mobile banking for easy account management, and safe deposit boxes for secure storage. With a diverse customer base, Metro Bank serves individuals, small and medium-sized enterprises, and larger corporate clients, ensuring accessibility through its branches and digital platforms.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b3d65a49-9247-4817-b326-18a99de983cb.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'avature', 'metrobank', null), ('1716', 'Marks and Spencer', 'Marks and Spencer Group Plc', 'https://corporate.marksandspencer.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/marks-and-spencer', 'Marks and Spencer (M&S) is a prominent British multinational retailer founded in 1884. Headquartered in London, the company specializes in clothing, beauty products, home goods, and luxury food items. M&S operates nearly 1,500 stores across 62 countries and is a member of the FTSE 100 Index.

Originally starting as a market stall, M&S has grown significantly over the years, emphasizing quality British products and excellent customer service. The retailer offers a wide range of apparel for men, women, and children, along with beauty products and accessories. M&S is particularly known for its luxury food items, including fresh, frozen, and packaged goods, and it provides an online food delivery service through a partnership with Ocado. Additionally, M&S features various home goods to cater to diverse customer needs.

M&S targets quality-conscious consumers who appreciate British heritage and premium offerings. The company adapts to modern retail trends by serving customers through both physical stores and online platforms.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '333', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/443c9098-491d-403e-b103-e6d4fa83548c.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'marksandspencer/MSCareers', null), ('1718', 'Harrods', 'Harrods Ltd', 'https://www.harrods.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/harrods', null, 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '111', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f40effc2-f791-4017-bd9c-607e6d91a79f.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'Harrods_External1', null), ('1719', 'Sophos', 'SOPHOS LIMITED', 'https://www.sophos.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sophos', 'Sophos is a British cybersecurity company founded in 1985 in Oxford, UK. Headquartered in Abingdon, it has grown into a global leader in AI-driven cybersecurity, serving over 600,000 customers worldwide, including more than 30,000 organizations that utilize its Managed Detection and Response (MDR) services.

The company offers a wide range of cybersecurity products and services to protect against various cyber threats, including malware, ransomware, and phishing. Key offerings include endpoint security, network security, email protection, cloud security, and encryption. All solutions are managed through Sophos Central, a unified cloud-based platform that provides centralized administration and visibility across multiple environments. Sophos emphasizes adaptive defenses that predict and prevent emerging threats, processing vast amounts of security data daily to ensure rapid threat detection and mitigation. The company is recognized for its innovation and reliability, delivering scalable and user-friendly cybersecurity solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '9', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8f647c9b-7301-4ba5-b676-2438b6c4cc51.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'lever', 'sophos', null), ('1720', 'Tortoise Media', 'TORTOISE MEDIA LTD', 'https://www.tortoisemedia.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tortoisemedia', 'We''re not about breaking news, but what''s driving it.   Not the news as it happens, but when it''s ready. We want to open up journalism, and give everyone a seat at the table. To create a system of organised listening where you can come and tell us what you think.   Every week we hold ThinkIns, which are at the heart of what we do. A ThinkIn is a forum for civilised disagreement where our members and partners participate in a live, unscripted conversation in our newsroom in order to inform our point of view.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f94651ee-b6d3-4f68-918e-e415219f37b8.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1721', 'ENSEK', 'ENSEK Ltd', 'https://ensek.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ensek', 'ENSEK is a technology company based in Nottingham that specializes in digital transformation solutions for the energy sector. It offers a cloud-native SaaS platform designed to enhance the operations of retail energy suppliers. This platform covers the entire customer lifecycle, including onboarding for residential, SME, and industrial energy consumers, and integrates key functions such as quoting, billing, and revenue assurance.

The company''s product suite includes the Ignition platform, which automates up to 98% of processes, significantly reducing operational costs. ENSEK also recently launched products like the Industry Pricing Engine and Tickd, the UK’s first fully digital energy comparison site for businesses. With a customer base managing over 20 million meter points and more than £2 billion in energy supplier revenue, ENSEK has expanded into international markets, including Benelux and Australia. The company emphasizes innovation and security, supporting renewable adoption and regulatory compliance while ensuring robust information security for its enterprise customers.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/78cbef04-3e5c-4a0f-a29a-1de1c81fb0a1.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('1722', 'Fortinet', 'Fortinet UK Ltd', 'https://www.fortinet.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fortinet', 'Fortinet is a global cybersecurity company founded in 2000 by brothers Ken and Michael Xie, with its headquarters in Sunnyvale, California. The company specializes in integrated and automated security solutions that protect enterprises, service providers, and government organizations from cyber threats. Its flagship product, FortiGate, is a next-generation firewall that combines multiple security functions into a single platform.

The Fortinet product portfolio includes FortiGate Next-Generation Firewalls, FortiGuard Security Services, FortiAnalyzer, FortiManager, and FortiSandbox, addressing a wide range of cybersecurity needs such as threat protection, secure SD-WAN, and advanced threat detection. Fortinet serves a diverse customer base across various industries, including retail, healthcare, finance, education, and government, providing scalable security solutions tailored to different operational environments.

Since going public in 2009, Fortinet has experienced significant growth, achieving a market capitalization of over $75 billion and annual revenues nearing $6 billion. The company is recognized for its innovation in cybersecurity technologies and holds a leading market share in unified threat management and network security hardware.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/fed17c0f-da34-48ca-8e52-5ef657075e0f.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'fortinet', null), ('1723', 'CityFibre', 'CityFibre Holdings Ltd', 'https://cityfibre.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cityfibre', 'CityFibre is an independent telecommunications network provider in the UK, specializing in gigabit-capable full-fibre-to-the-premises (FTTP) broadband. As the third-largest network provider in the country, CityFibre aims to enhance high-speed internet access, particularly in underserved areas and "second-cities." The company is headquartered in London and is co-owned by Antin Infrastructure Partners, Goldman Sachs Asset Management, Mubadala Investment Company, and Interogo Holding.

CityFibre designs, builds, and operates digital infrastructure, delivering fiber optic network services to various sectors, including enterprise, public sector organizations, and mobile network operators. Its full fibre network offers broadband speeds up to 5.5 Gbps, significantly faster and more reliable than traditional broadband options. The company operates a wholesale model, allowing over 35 internet service providers to utilize its network, providing customers with a variety of service options.

Committed to environmental responsibility, CityFibre operates as a B-Corporation and is focused on reducing its carbon footprint through sustainable practices and power-efficient technology. The company aims to decrease its carbon emissions by an estimated 40% over the next five years.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3cf2f87c-a05f-454e-a320-4779abab01ee.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'cityfibre', null), ('1724', 'Octopus Energy', 'Octopus Energy Limited', 'https://octopus.energy/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/octopusenergy', 'Octopus Energy is a British renewable energy company founded in 2015 by Greg Jackson and Stuart Jackson. It has quickly grown to become one of the largest energy suppliers in the UK and globally, serving over 9 million customers across nine countries, including the UK, Germany, the USA, and Japan. The company focuses on providing 100% renewable electricity and gas, along with innovative pricing models that promote energy consumption during times of abundant renewable supply.

The company operates on a technology platform called Kraken, which supports various operational functions like billing and customer relationship management. Octopus Energy is also a significant investor in renewable energy assets across Europe, valued at billions of pounds. Its commitment to fair pricing and outstanding customer service has attracted a diverse customer base, contributing to its rapid growth. Recognized for its innovation, Octopus Energy has been featured in TIME Magazine’s ‘100 Most Influential Companies’ and is backed by major global investors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b5b78c71-2122-4b63-a902-851e986ccb6b.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'lever', 'octoenergy', null), ('1725', 'Meta', 'Facebook UK Ltd', 'https://meta.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/meta', 'Meta, formerly known as Facebook, is a prominent global technology company that specializes in social media, digital services, and virtual reality experiences. Founded in 2004 by Mark Zuckerberg and his Harvard roommates, Meta has grown to become the largest social media platform, boasting over 3 billion monthly active users. Its core products include Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, and Oculus VR, each offering unique features for connecting and communicating.

The company rebranded to Meta in 2021 to emphasize its focus on building the metaverse, a virtual shared space for real-time interaction through virtual and augmented reality technologies. Meta aims to create an interconnected online environment that allows seamless movement of digital assets and personalized interactions. Additionally, Meta provides business tools such as advertising platforms and e-commerce solutions to help companies engage with customers effectively. With headquarters in Menlo Park, California, Meta employs over 100,000 people worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d97a3da9-f90f-4e28-b2ff-df752f6b68dc.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'meta', null), ('1726', 'Goldman Sachs', 'Goldman Sachs International', 'https://goldmansachs.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/goldman-sachs', 'Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. is a prominent global investment banking, securities, and investment management firm based in New York City. Founded in 1869, it has grown from a small commercial paper business into a key player in the financial services industry, serving a wide range of clients including corporations, governments, and individuals. The firm operates through four main divisions: Investment Banking, Global Markets, Asset Management, and Consumer and Wealth Management.

Goldman Sachs provides various services such as advising on mergers and acquisitions, underwriting securities, and managing assets worth approximately $1.6 trillion. Its consumer banking division, Marcus by Goldman Sachs, offers digital banking services including personal loans and savings accounts. The firm is also known for its innovative products, including the co-development of the Apple Card. Goldman Sachs is committed to sustainability and social impact, with initiatives focused on promoting racial equity and supporting small businesses.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '135', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/64c01ab4-81f8-4fe1-993a-ddf9fbcae11a.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'goldmansachs', 'goldmansachs', null), ('1727', 'Amazon', 'Amazon UK Services Ltd', 'https://amazon.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/amazon', 'Amazon is a multinational technology company founded by Jeff Bezos in 1994, originally as an online bookstore. It has since evolved into a leading global e-commerce platform, offering a vast array of products and services, including electronics, clothing, and media.The company operates the world''s largest online marketplace and provides Amazon Web Services (AWS), a prominent cloud computing service. Amazon also offers Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA) for third-party sellers, a subscription service called Amazon Prime with various benefits, and a range of smart home devices featuring its virtual assistant, Alexa. Amazon serves a diverse customer base, including individual consumers, small businesses, large enterprises, and developers, making it a significant player in multiple sectors.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '260', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/7a7c7fe3-0def-46b9-8ace-d94fa0edbaee.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'amazon', 'amazon', null), ('1728', 'Google DeepMind', 'DeepMind Technologies Limited', 'https://deepmind.google', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/googledeepmind', 'Google DeepMind is a British artificial intelligence company and research laboratory founded in 2010. Acquired by Google in 2014, it merged with Google AI''s Google Brain division in April 2023. Headquartered in London, DeepMind has research centers in the United States, Canada, France, Germany, and Switzerland.

The company focuses on developing advanced AI technologies to "solve intelligence" by integrating machine learning and systems neuroscience. DeepMind is known for its reinforcement learning techniques, which allow AI to learn from raw data. One of its most notable achievements is AlphaGo, an AI program that defeated world champion Lee Sedol in the game of Go in 2016. Beyond gaming, DeepMind applies its AI technologies in healthcare, collaborating with the NHS to create tools for medical diagnostics and patient care, as well as exploring applications in scientific research and energy efficiency. 

DeepMind''s core offerings include reinforcement learning algorithms, neural networks, and AI-powered applications across various industries. With a team of around 700 employees, the company is recognized for its contributions to AI research and development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '27', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e3ba5fa9-39b1-4284-b52f-e3211fc7589f.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'deepmind', null), ('1729', 'Samsung Electronics', 'Samsung Electronics (UK) Limited', 'https://samsung.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/samsung-electronics', 'Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. is a South Korean multinational corporation established in 1969 as part of the Samsung Group. Headquartered in South Korea, it has become a global leader in technology and consumer electronics, known for its innovative products and extensive portfolio.

The company offers a wide range of products, including smartphones, tablets, televisions, home appliances, and audio-visual equipment. It is also a major player in the semiconductor industry, producing memory chips and providing foundry services. Additionally, Samsung manufactures display panels, telecommunications equipment, and IT solutions, along with smart devices and IoT technologies. The Galaxy smartphone series has been particularly successful, contributing significantly to the company''s revenue.

Samsung targets a diverse customer base, including individual consumers, businesses, and telecommunications companies. Its products are marketed worldwide, with a strong presence in various regions, emphasizing innovation and quality to meet the needs of tech-savvy users and corporate clients.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5a3b8162-890e-428e-b1df-102233a4697b.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'samsungelectronics', null), ('1730', 'BAE Systems', 'BAE Systems plc', 'https://www.baesystems.com/en', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bae-systems', 'BAE Systems is a prominent British multinational defense, security, and aerospace company, established in 1999 through the merger of British Aerospace and Marconi Electronic Systems. Headquartered in London, it ranks among the world''s largest defense contractors, offering a diverse portfolio that includes military aircraft, naval vessels, missiles, avionics, and land systems.

The company designs, develops, and manufactures a variety of defense and aerospace products. This includes military aircraft like the Eurofighter Typhoon and Harrier jet, naval vessels such as submarines for the British Royal Navy, and advanced missile systems. BAE Systems also specializes in avionics, land systems, and provides space technology and cybersecurity solutions through its subsidiaries. It serves government and military customers worldwide, including the British Ministry of Defence and allied armed forces, and collaborates with major aerospace firms like Lockheed Martin and Boeing. With a strong commitment to innovation, BAE Systems continues to enhance defense technology while supporting national security interests.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '269', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c9e9611d-e92a-4966-aecf-d2c097210e91.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'bamboohr', 'baesystems', null), ('1731', 'Scarlet', 'Scarlet Global Holdings Ltd', 'https://scarlet.cc', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/scarlet-comply/', 'Scarlet is an independent certifying organization focused on regulatory compliance for medical software and devices. It is designated as an EU Notified Body under Regulation (EU) 2017/745 and a UK Approved Body under UK Medical Devices Regulations. Scarlet specializes in the safe and compliant deployment of software-as-a-medical-device (SaMD) and AI-driven healthcare technologies.  The company offers regulatory certification services for EU MDR and UKCA/CE marking, as well as compliance support through ISO 13485 certification for quality management systems in medical device manufacturing. Scarlet also provides guidance on intellectual property, ensuring clients adhere to strict usage policies for certification marks.  As Europe''s only Notified Body dedicated exclusively to software and AI medical devices, Scarlet streamlines certification processes and enforces rigorous compliance standards. Its clients include developers of medical software and AI technologies seeking regulatory approval in the EU and UK, enabling them to deliver compliant software updates, particularly for life-saving technologies.', 'The company will sponsor any candidate they''re very excited about. Sponsorship can be offered for all roles.', '4', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b6fc6399-417f-45f0-b6b5-c4e839958d61.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/scarlet', null), ('1732', 'Apple', 'Apple Europe Limited', 'https://apple.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/apple', 'Apple Inc. is a prominent American multinational technology company based in Cupertino, California. Founded in 1976 by Steve Jobs, Steve Wozniak, and Ronald Wayne, Apple initially focused on personal computers, launching the Apple I and the successful Apple II. Over the years, the company expanded its offerings to include a wide range of consumer electronics.

Apple''s product lineup features well-known devices such as the Macintosh personal computer, iPod, iPhone, and iPad. The company also develops software and services, including macOS, iOS, the iTunes Store, the App Store, iCloud, Apple Music, and Apple Pay. These offerings enhance the user experience and contribute significantly to Apple''s revenue.

With a diverse customer base that includes individual consumers, educational institutions, and enterprises, Apple maintains a strong retail presence through its Apple Store chain and online platforms. The company is recognized for its focus on user-friendly design and innovation, making it one of the most valuable technology companies in the world. Under the leadership of Tim Cook, Apple continues to grow and diversify into new product categories.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '85', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ebff1868-bded-4318-a791-663d2d8b677b.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'apple', null), ('1733', 'Google', 'Google (UK) Limited', 'https://google.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/google', 'Google, founded on September 4, 1998, by Larry Page and Sergey Brin, is a leading global technology company known for its powerful web-based search engine, Google Search. The company aims to organize the world''s information and make it universally accessible and useful. As a subsidiary of Alphabet Inc. since 2015, Google holds a significant share of the global desktop search market and processes billions of search queries each day.

Google offers a wide range of products and services across various technology sectors. Its core product, Google Search, delivers fast and relevant results. Other offerings include Google Ads for advertising, Gmail for email, Google Workspace for productivity, Google Maps for navigation, and the Chrome web browser. Additionally, Google develops the Android mobile operating system, owns YouTube, and provides cloud computing services through Google Cloud. The company also engages in hardware development and AI research, contributing to its extensive ecosystem that supports individual users, businesses, and content creators worldwide.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '1', '113', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/92084892-0276-41d6-b89e-4d1c026533b8.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'google', 'google', null), ('1734', 'Aon', 'Aon UK Limited', 'https://www.aon.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/aon', 'Aon is a global professional services firm that specializes in risk, reinsurance, retirement, and health solutions. Founded in 1982 through the merger of Ryan Insurance Group and Combined International Corporation, Aon has grown to employ over 66,000 people across 120 countries. The company''s name, derived from a Gaelic word meaning "one," reflects its unified approach to client service.

