With a history dating back to 1828, WTW has evolved through strategic mergers, becoming a leading advisory and solutions firm that combines industry knowledge with advanced technology to improve business performance globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8a46506c-74ba-4802-82fc-81f16f692617.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'wtw', null), ('1737', 'Lloyds Banking Group', 'Lloyds Bank plc', 'https://www.lloydsbankinggroup.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lloyds-banking-group', 'Lloyds Banking Group is one of the largest financial services organizations in the UK, with a history that dates back to 1765. Headquartered in London, the Group serves around 30 million customers and employs approximately 65,000 people. It was formed in 2009 through the acquisition of Halifax Bank of Scotland (HBOS) by Lloyds TSB.

The Group offers a wide range of services, including retail banking, commercial banking, and insurance. In retail banking, it provides personal banking services such as current accounts, savings accounts, mortgages, and credit cards. For businesses, Lloyds offers lending, asset finance, and treasury services. It is also a significant provider of insurance products, including life, home, and car insurance. Additionally, Lloyds Banking Group has a strong presence in digital banking, having introduced the UK''s first online cash machine and continuing to offer extensive online and mobile banking services.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '173', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/68d3002e-1e5e-422e-b48c-4e4ef26fbae0.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'workday', 'LBG_Careers', null), ('1738', 'Diageo', 'Diageo plc', 'https://www.diageo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/diageo', 'Diageo plc is a British multinational alcoholic beverage company based in London, formed in 1997 from the merger of Guinness and Grand Metropolitan. It is a global leader in the beverage industry, known for its extensive portfolio of spirits and beer brands. Diageo produces about 40% of all Scotch whisky worldwide and operates from 132 sites globally.

The company owns over 24 Scotch whisky brands, including Johnnie Walker and J&B, as well as major spirits like Smirnoff vodka, Baileys Irish Cream, and Captain Morgan rum. Diageo also produces Guinness, one of the most recognized stout beers. Recently, it has expanded into the non-alcoholic spirits market with acquisitions like Seedlip and Ritual Zero Proof. Diageo emphasizes sustainability and operational efficiency, focusing on its core alcoholic beverage business while adapting to changing consumer preferences through e-commerce and innovation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/21fc3471-2a0c-4c19-930c-9036b70e75b2.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'workday', 'Diageo_Careers', null), ('1739', 'Sainsbury''s', 'J Sainsbury Plc', 'https://www.sainsburys.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sainsburys', 'Sainsbury''s, officially known as J Sainsbury plc, is one of the largest supermarket chains in the United Kingdom, founded in 1869 by John James Sainsbury and his wife Mary Ann. The company began as a small dairy shop in London and has since grown into a major national retailer, becoming the largest grocery retailer in the UK by 1962. Headquartered in London, Sainsbury''s is recognized for its product quality, customer service, and strong tradition of employee ownership.

Sainsbury''s operates a network of supermarkets and convenience stores throughout the UK, offering a wide range of grocery products, including fresh produce, packaged foods, wines, and household essentials. The company has a history of innovation, having introduced self-service shopping in the 1920s and home delivery services early on. In 2016, Sainsbury''s expanded its offerings by acquiring Argos, allowing it to provide a broader range of products, including general merchandise and electronics, through both physical stores and online channels.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/32be5b5c-b02c-4b52-9f21-6c35849b61ee.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('1740', 'Serco', 'Serco Ltd', 'https://www.serco.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/serco', 'Serco is a global provider of public services, operating in over 20 countries with a workforce of more than 50,000 employees. Founded in 1929, the company specializes in delivering critical support services to governments across various sectors, including defense, justice, migration, space, health, transport, and customer services.Serco''s core capabilities encompass service design and advisory, complex program management, systems integration and engineering, asset and facilities management, and case management. The company generates significant revenue by managing military facilities, operating prisons and immigration centers, running transport networks, providing health support, and offering satellite operations. With a strong presence in the UK, North America, Asia Pacific, and the Middle East, Serco partners with government agencies to address complex challenges in public service delivery.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/63970b5e-0807-41a9-9c28