ServiceNow serves a diverse range of industries, such as government, healthcare, telecommunications, and financial services. It has established strategic partnerships with companies like Celonis and NVIDIA to enhance its automation and AI capabilities. Since going public in 2012, ServiceNow has become a Fortune 500 company, recognized for its innovative approach to IT service management and enterprise-wide workflow automation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '23', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5e512644-c4af-4d46-936c-9ef5bd3f2e33.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'servicenow', null), ('1758', 'Wellcome Sanger Institute', 'Genome Research Limited', 'https://www.sanger.ac.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wellcome-sanger-institute', 'The Wellcome Sanger Institute is a prominent UK-based non-profit research institute focused on genomics and genetics. Established in 1992 by the Wellcome Trust, it played a key role in the Human Genome Project, contributing significantly to the first draft of the human genome sequence. Located on the Wellcome Genome Campus near Cambridge, the institute employs around 900 staff and conducts research in areas such as cancer, human genetics, and microbial genomics.

The institute operates one of the largest DNA sequencing facilities globally, having sequenced over 46.6 petabases of DNA and RNA. It engages in foundational research to explore the genomes of various life forms, aiming to address critical questions related to health and disease. The Wellcome Sanger Institute is dedicated to open access, making its genomic data publicly available to enhance global research efforts. It also supports translational research, training programs, and collaborations with academic, healthcare, and industry partners to foster innovation and improve public health outcomes.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/aa6b796c-71fe-4202-b4b8-ff3398a27676.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'bamboohr', 'wellcome', null), ('1759', 'Zepz', 'WorldRemit Ltd', 'https://zepzpay.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zepzpay', 'Zepz is a digital remittances company that specializes in fast and affordable international money transfers. It operates through its well-known brands, WorldRemit and Sendwave, serving customers in 50 markets and facilitating transfers to over 130 countries, with a strong emphasis on Africa and Asia. The company processes more than $1.3 billion in monthly send volumes and supports over 5,000 transfer routes, acquiring around 100,000 new customers each month.

Zepz''s core service is its digital money transfer platform, which allows customers to send funds online quickly and securely. A notable feature is its focus on transfers to mobile money accounts, enabling recipients to access funds easily without traditional banking. The company prioritizes customer experience, offering a mobile app for quick transactions, payment tracking, and transaction history. With a commitment to fair pricing and flexibility, Zepz aims to reduce remittance costs for low-income consumers while fostering sustainable growth in the digital payments sector.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/cd2d2df1-2023-46a8-a683-3d6cc69bc25e.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1760', 'IBM', 'IBM UK Ltd', 'https://www.ibm.com/uk-en', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ibm', 'IBM, or International Business Machines Corporation, is a prominent American multinational technology company based in Armonk, New York. Established in 1911, IBM has played a significant role in the evolution of computing and information technology. The company is known for its pioneering contributions, including the introduction of the System/360 mainframe computers, which set the standard for business and scientific applications.

IBM offers a wide range of products and services, including mainframe computers, servers, storage systems, operating systems, enterprise software, and cloud-based solutions. The company also provides IT consulting, technology services, artificial intelligence, data analytics, and cybersecurity. With a strong focus on research and development, IBM operates 19 research facilities worldwide, exploring advanced technologies such as quantum computing and blockchain.

Serving a diverse clientele that includes large enterprises, governments, and scientific institutions, IBM targets various industries, including finance, healthcare, manufacturing, and telecommunications. The company is committed to helping clients enhance operational efficiency and innovate through advanced IT solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '85', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e017195e-af4d-4958-b778-c4a668cf527f.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('1761', 'Zoopla', 'Zoopla Ltd', 'https://www.zoopla.co.uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zoopla', 'Zoopla is a UK-based online property platform founded in 2007 and headquartered in London. It serves as a real estate matchmaking service, connecting property buyers and renters with realtors and sellers across the UK. Launched in 2008, Zoopla has grown rapidly, attracting over 40 million users monthly and establishing itself as one of the leading property portals in the country.

The platform offers a wide range of services, including property listings for sale and rent, detailed property information, and tools for realtors to market their properties. Users can access valuable data such as sold house prices, current value estimates, and area trends to make informed decisions. Zoopla operates a transactional model that facilitates direct interactions between buyers, renters, and real estate professionals, enhancing the property search experience with rich, data-driven insights.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/dc65960d-a0eb-49f0-8a09-957661d72da6.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('1762', 'Booking.com', 'Booking.com Limited', 'https://booking.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/booking.com', 'Booking.com is a prominent global digital travel company based in Amsterdam, Netherlands. Founded in 1996, it has grown from a small startup into the world’s largest accommodation booking platform. As part of Booking Holdings Inc., the company employs over 17,000 people across 198 offices in 70 countries, providing services in more than 40 languages.

