The company serves various sectors, including science research facilities, educational buildings, and residential co-living developments. Scotch Partners emphasizes a collaborative culture and a problem-solving approach, aiming to create high-performing buildings that contribute to a sustainable future. Their expertise in acoustics enhances building performance and occupant comfort, while their comprehensive design consultancy supports a wide range of building types.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/c383cc65-75cd-4b89-986d-5de03a66b0fe.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'scotch', null), ('2007', 'Motion Applied', 'Motion Applied Limited', 'https://www.motionapplied.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/motionapplied', 'Motion Applied, officially known as McLaren Applied Limited, is a private limited company based in Woking, Surrey, England. Established in 1988, it specializes in advanced engineering and manufacturing, particularly in the automotive sector. The company operates under the SIC code 29320, which pertains to the manufacture of parts and accessories for motor vehicles.

With a history of name changes reflecting its growth, Motion Applied has evolved from McLaren Applied Technologies Limited to McLaren Electronic Systems Limited. This evolution highlights its focus on high-performance engineering solutions, including advanced electronics and data analytics. The company''s strong connection to McLaren suggests a commitment to innovation and precision in engineering.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/cf19b7c7-71cd-4b42-ba0a-32720de1c886.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'applied', null), ('2008', 'Sierra', 'Sierra Technologies Ltd', 'https://sierra.ai', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sierra', 'Sierra is a conversational AI company founded in 2023 by Bret Taylor and Clay Bavor. The company focuses on helping businesses create personalized AI agents to improve customer service and brand interaction. Since its public launch in early 2024, Sierra has attracted enterprise clients like WeightWatchers, Sonos, and SiriusXM, showcasing its effectiveness for businesses with high-volume customer support needs.

Sierra''s platform features two main components: AgentOS, which allows companies to build and manage AI agents, and Experience Manager, which provides tools for designing branded conversational experiences and monitoring agent performance. The AI agents are trained on specific company data and can perform various tasks, such as updating CRM entries and managing orders. Sierra emphasizes security and compliance, ensuring customer data is protected and used appropriately. The company operates from multiple locations, including New York and San Francisco, and has achieved a valuation of $4.5 billion within its first year.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '34', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/530c3fe6-ff25-4e4a-b48f-c3ef8d5d934f.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'ashby', 'https://api.ashbyhq.com/posting-api/job-board/sierra', null), ('2009', 'Artic', 'Trunk Works Ltd trading as Artic', 'https://artic.works', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/useartic', 'Manufacturing for the built world is hard. Artic is here to bring you certainty and control. Use one system to reduce risk and drive efficiency across production, quality and site delivery.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3fbc29c9-61a0-4b31-9461-0d6c3d3f3518.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2010', 'PEP Health', 'PEP Health', 'https://pephealth.ai', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pep-health', 'PEP Health is a healthcare company dedicated to enhancing patient experiences through its patient-centric platform. The company addresses communication challenges in healthcare by enabling patients to document their health journeys, manage their health data, and share information with clinicians and researchers. 

At the core of PEP Health''s offerings is the Patient Engagement Platform (PEP), developed by Liquid State. This platform utilizes advanced AI and natural language processing to gather and analyze real-time patient feedback from various online sources. It generates a proprietary PEP Score that reflects the quality of patient experiences across over 350,000 healthcare facilities in the US. PEP Health provides real-time insights, continuous monitoring, and actionable data to hospitals, physician clinics, and payers, helping them improve care quality and patient satisfaction. 

Headquartered in Brisbane, Australia, PEP Health operates with a team of about 40 employees and focuses on empowering patients to enhance health outcomes globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f9a7971a-d305-4315-9ed5-8699cad4ab5c.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'pep', null), ('2011', 'Centre for Energy Equality', 'Centre for Energy Equality', 'https://cee-uk.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/centre-for-energy-equality', 'The Centre for Energy Equality (CEE) is a UK-based social enterprise committed to ensuring equal access to safe, affordable, and sustainable energy for all communities. Founded in 2021, CEE focuses on identifying and implementing practical solutions that promote energy equality, particularly during the low-carbon energy transition. The organization combines expertise and extensive networks to support initiatives that help individuals and communities access sustainable energy.

CEE offers consulting services in engineering and environmental aspects of energy equality. It leads innovative projects, such as the Solar Battery Hub in Nigeria, which develops solar-powered battery-swapping stations as an alternative to diesel generators. This initiative targets sectors like small and medium enterprises, agriculture, healthcare, and education, aiming to reduce reliance on fossil fuels and enhance energy access.

The company collaborates with a diverse range of organizations across public, private, and community sectors to promote energy equality. CEE''s mission emphasizes inclusivity and gender equality in energy access, contributing to climate goals and social justice through its initiatives and partnerships.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b3afac62-c916-4caa-a8ee-ccea20dc24c3.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2012', 'Essendi', 'Essendi UK Hotels 1 Limited', 'https://www.essendi.com/en', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/accor-invest', 'Essendi is a prominent European hotel owner and operator, specializing in the economy and midscale segments. Originally spun off from the Accor group in 2017 as AccorInvest, the company rebranded in 2025 to reflect its commitment to responsible hospitality. As of the end of 2024, Essendi''s portfolio includes 576 hotels across 24 countries, valued at approximately €7.8 billion, and employs around 20,000 people.The company operates a hybrid economic model that integrates operational performance with real estate asset management. This approach allows Essendi to optimize hotel value while achieving strong financial results, reporting revenues of €4.0 billion and an EBITDA of €656 million in 2024. Essendi manages hotels under well-known brands such as ibis, Novotel, and Mercure, focusing on creating sustainable and vibrant hospitality experiences for guests and local communities. The company emphasizes ESG criteria as a core part of its strategy, aiming to contribute to a more sustainable hotel industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/53dfbff5-a615-4fdd-bf5d-221f401827fe.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('2013', 'Smythson of Bond Street', 'Frank Smythson Limited', 'https://www.smythson.com/uk/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/smythson', 'Smythson of Bond Street is a prestigious British luxury brand founded in 1887 by Frank Smythson. Known for its exquisite craftsmanship, the company specializes in high-quality stationery and leather goods, blending functionality with elegant design. Smythson is famous for innovations like the "Panama Notebook" and its unique "featherweight" paper, which transformed portable writing. The brand''s signature "floppy leather" binding has remained consistent since the 1890s.

The product range includes luxury stationery, leather-bound diaries, bespoke address books, and a variety of leather goods such as handbags, briefcases, and pens. Smythson is recognized for its distinctive light blue paper, a hallmark of its notebooks and diaries. With a rich heritage of serving an elite clientele, including European royalty and celebrities, the brand has received multiple Royal Warrants, underscoring its esteemed status. Smythson operates internationally with locations in the UK, US, and France, and collaborates with contemporary artists to stay relevant in the luxury market.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e34a7aa4-38bf-4e2f-bd09-82228674d739.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('2014', 'Roblox', 'Roblox UK Limited', 'https://www.roblox.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/roblox', 'Roblox Corporation is an American technology company founded in 2004 by David Baszucki and Erik Cassel, with its headquarters in San Mateo, California. The company is renowned for developing Roblox, a popular online platform and game creation system launched in 2006. This platform allows users to design, share, and play games created by others, fostering a vibrant user-generated content ecosystem.

Roblox''s core offerings include Roblox Studio, a free game development suite that enables users to create immersive 3D experiences, and the Roblox Platform, where users can engage in multiplayer gaming and social interactions. The platform features a virtual currency called Robux, which supports in-game purchases and a monetization program known as Developer Exchange (DevEx) that allows developers to convert Robux into real-world currency. With over 71.5 million average daily active users and a strong focus on community safety, Roblox caters to a diverse demographic, primarily targeting children and teenagers while also appealing to users of all ages interested in gaming and creative expression.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '2', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/111e6c36-a298-4dfa-a8d1-60efbd71b5e1.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('2015', 'Stellantis', 'Stellantis UK Limited', 'https://www.stellantis.com/en', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/stellantis', 'Stellantis is a multinational automotive manufacturing corporation formed in 2021 from the merger of the French PSA Group and Fiat Chrysler Automobiles (FCA). Headquartered in Hoofddorp, Netherlands, Stellantis is one of the world’s largest automakers, employing around 300,000 people and operating manufacturing facilities in over 30 countries. The company serves customers in more than 130 markets globally.

Stellantis manages a diverse portfolio of 14 automotive brands, including Abarth, Alfa Romeo, Chrysler, Jeep, and Peugeot, covering a wide range of vehicles from luxury cars to commercial trucks. The company is focused on sustainable mobility solutions, including electrification, autonomous driving, and connected vehicles, as part of its strategic plan "Dare Forward 2030." Stellantis also offers mobility services through Free2Move and Leasys, along with aftermarket support via Mopar, enhancing its commitment to innovation and customer service in the automotive industry.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ffc1e972-dd62-443d-9800-c97627165013.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('2016', 'The Harkalm Group', 'The Harkalm Group Ltd', 'https://www.harkalm.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/theharkalmgroup', 'The Harkalm Group Ltd is a UK-based commercial property investment and development company established in 2020. With over 25 years of experience, the company specializes in the retail, education, food store, and roadside sectors. They focus on acquiring, asset managing, and investing in properties across the UK, employing a streamlined approach to enhance the value of both vacant and tenanted properties.

The Harkalm Group excels in several areas, including high street properties, where they redevelop vacant buildings into vibrant commercial spaces. They are also leaders in roadside developments, creating high-quality Drive-Thru and Drive-To units in collaboration with top operators. In the food sector, they develop supermarkets tailored to specific occupier needs, ensuring modern retail environments. Additionally, they acquire and develop properties for educational use, aiming to create inspiring learning spaces that meet community and environmental requirements. The company operates from its registered office in London and is dedicated to delivering value and innovation in property investment and development.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6b1c8d93-e731-4535-9ef5-0efc4f10d3f3.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('2017', 'poolside', 'Poolside AI Ltd', 'https://www.poolside.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/poolsideai', 'Poolside is a French startup focused on developing advanced artificial intelligence software to enhance and automate software development processes. Founded in July 2023 by Jason Warner and Eiso Kant, the company specializes in creating proprietary large language models and AI systems that understand and manage computer code, prioritizing security, privacy, and efficiency.

The company offers a full-stack generative AI coding platform that includes foundation models, an AI coding assistant, customizable enterprise AI solutions, and API access. Their tools help developers automate routine tasks, generate and optimize code, and create complex software systems. Poolside has formed a strategic partnership with Amazon Web Services (AWS) to provide secure and scalable AI solutions for software development.

With significant funding and a valuation of $3 billion, Poolside targets enterprises and software development teams looking to improve their coding workflows through reliable AI solutions. The company''s leadership brings extensive expertise in AI and software development, positioning Poolside as a key player in the generative AI landscape for software engineering.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '11', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/8df436dc-f485-4fdd-bf3f-c88f2ab0dc00.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('2018', 'Lime', 'Lime Technology Limited', 'https://www.li.me/en-gb', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/limebike', 'Lime, officially known as Neutron Holdings, Inc., is a leading provider of shared electric micromobility solutions. Founded in 2017 and based in San Francisco, California, Lime operates the world''s largest fleet of electric scooters, bikes, and mopeds across over 280 cities in nearly 30 countries. The company aims to create a future of shared, affordable, and carbon-free transportation.

Lime''s offerings include electric scooters, electric bikes branded as Lime-E, and electric mopeds available in select markets. The company also launched LimePod, a car-sharing service featuring small electric vehicles. Users can easily locate and unlock these vehicles through Lime''s app, which also supports seamless payment and customer service options. Lime''s mission is to reduce car dependency and promote eco-friendly travel, having powered over 250 million rides and replaced approximately 60 million car trips globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/5b009f9d-310a-4aea-a1a3-eb9461faeffb.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'ashby', 'Lime', null), ('2019', 'Fractile', 'Fractile Ltd', 'https://www.fractile.ai', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fractile', 'Fractile is a UK-based semiconductor company focused on designing advanced AI chips for datacenters. The company utilizes an innovative in-memory compute (IMC) architecture that closely integrates processing and memory, enhancing speed and reducing power consumption. Their technology combines RISC-V processor technology with SRAM memory, allowing computations to occur directly within memory components. This design aims to improve performance and energy efficiency significantly.

Fractile is actively developing multiple chip designs and is also working on reference designs for full rack systems tailored for cloud datacenters. Their chips are optimized for AI inference, claiming to run large language models up to 100 times faster and at 10 times lower cost than current GPU solutions, while providing up to 20 times better performance per watt. The company has secured $15 million in seed funding from notable investors, highlighting confidence in its innovative technology and market potential. Teams are based in London and Bristol, UK.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '40', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/b58735c6-6f15-4619-9349-50c9aaca19b4.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', 'greenhouse', 'fractile', null), ('2020', 'Carrier', 'Carrier Solutions UK Ltd', 'https://www.carrier.com/carrier/en/worldwide/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carrier', 'Carrier is a global leader in heating, ventilation, air conditioning (HVAC), and refrigeration solutions, founded in 1915 by Willis Carrier and a team of engineers. Willis Carrier is known for inventing modern air conditioning in 1902, which laid the foundation for the HVAC industry. The company has a rich history of innovation and has expanded its operations internationally through mergers and acquisitions.

Carrier offers a wide range of products and services for residential, commercial, and industrial customers. Its portfolio includes residential HVAC systems like air conditioners, furnaces, heat pumps, and air purifiers. For commercial clients, Carrier provides large-scale HVAC solutions and refrigeration systems. The company also specializes in industrial refrigeration and process cooling equipment, focusing on energy efficiency and advanced climate control technologies. Additionally, Carrier supports its products with installation, maintenance, and repair services, ensuring customer satisfaction and comfort.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/e6441645-fb57-4c69-a8a3-7f72deeaef47.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'jobs', null), ('2023', 'CUR8', 'CUR8 Earth Limited', 'https://www.cur8.earth', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cur8earth', 'CUR8 is a London-based company founded in 2022 that specializes in carbon removal intelligence and sustainability consultancy services. Led by CEO Marta Krupinska, the team of 31 professionals focuses on helping businesses develop and implement effective environmental strategies to reduce their carbon footprints.

