.  Our team of engineers and designers have the ability to programme our system to meet the clients creative needs. We work directly with artists to convert their music into spatial audio so that it is ready for live performance in 3D.Feedback from clients and artists is unwaveringly positive. The DJ Viken Arman said it was "by far the best stage ever made" and Brazilian DJ Reple raved that it was "definitely the most special show I''ve ever done so far. Closing this stage was a dream come true."  A Festival goer "I think this is the best live experience I''ve ever had in my life."Polygon is growing- fast.  We are exploring partnerships around the globe to see where we can take Polygon next.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/63f4751d-80fe-417e-80af-591987e92593.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('2036', 'ROLLER', 'ROLLER Networks LTD', 'https://www.roller.software', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/roller', 'ROLLER is a cloud-based venue management software company that serves attractions, entertainment, and leisure venues globally. Founded in 2011 by brothers Luke and Mark Finn, ROLLER is headquartered in Austin, Texas, and has a strong presence in Australia. The company employs around 68 staff in the U.S. and approximately 130 employees worldwide. ROLLER has raised over $78 million in funding, including $50 million in late 2023.

