Their product range includes custom screens, feeders, vibrating centrifuges, scraper conveyors, and big bag dischargers, designed to handle challenging bulk materials with minimal spillage and dust. Don Valley Engineering serves industries such as quarrying, iron and steel, mineral processing, power generation, and construction. They are known for their skilled design capabilities, project management expertise, and commitment to delivering durable equipment along with comprehensive after-sales support, including parts supply and servicing.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/539f4ddc-46cc-407f-8bad-7f040d602e54.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('2114', 'Level Zero Health', 'Level Zero Health', 'https://www.levelzerohealth.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/level-zero-health', 'Level Zero Health is a female-founded biotech and medical device company established in 2023 by CEO Ula Rustamova and CTO Irene Jia. The company is focused on developing the first remote and continuous hormone monitoring device, utilizing advanced DNA-based biosensors that are worn on the skin. This innovative wearable biosensor platform continuously measures hormone levels through interstitial fluid, providing real-time updates that correlate with traditional blood readings.

The technology aims to enhance reproductive health management and monitor hormone-related conditions by enabling immediate treatment adjustments. Level Zero Health''s device is designed to be minimally invasive, creating a new market category similar to continuous glucose monitors. The company is backed by a strong clinical advisory board and has secured significant funding to support regulatory approvals, research and development, and team expansion in the UK and US. Their target customers include clinicians, pharmaceutical companies, fertility clinics, and wellness users seeking actionable hormone insights.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/fd273624-6b00-439e-88b3-cc55a454b285.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'lever', 'level-zero-health', null), ('2115', 'SimplyPhi', 'PHI PROPERTY ACQUISITIONS LIMITED', 'https://www.simplyphi.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/simplyphi', 'SimplyPhi is a UK-based company dedicated to addressing the affordable housing crisis. They collaborate with local authorities, housing associations, and public sector bodies to source, acquire, and renovate homes for vulnerable households. Their mission is to provide safe, warm, and affordable homes, streamlining the complex process of affordable housing delivery through technology and funding expertise.

The company offers services such as property sourcing, acquisition management, and renovation oversight, utilizing proprietary software platforms—SimplyFind and Iris. These tools enhance property identification and management, allowing clients to filter searches based on various criteria like property age and energy performance. SimplyPhi also manages public sector grants and raises private capital through flexible investment models, ensuring long-term stability for local authorities and residents.

