UCR''s Plasma Electrolytic Oxidation (PEO) ceramics offer significant market potential across energy, aerospace, automotive, hydrogen production, and industrial sectors due to their durability, heat resistance, and efficiency-enhancing properties. With growing demand for renewable energy, electric vehicles, and hydrogen infrastructure, UCR''s ceramics are positioned to capture a share of these multi-billion-dollar markets by improving performance and reducing costs. UCR is collaborating with the Henry Royce Institute on material resilience, following their publication, "Degradation in structural materials for net zero. A landscaping exercise".

UCR''s technology enables decarbonisation across industries with minimal impact while improving profitability.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/80857130-4b78-405c-9320-1392250b4b17.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'smartrecruiters', 'ucr', null), ('2304', '1GLOBAL', '1GLOBAL Operations (UK) Limited', 'https://www.1global.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/1global', '1GLOBAL is an international telecommunications company that specializes in specialty telecom services, particularly eSIM technology and global connectivity. Founded in 2022 by Hakan Koç and Pyrros Koussios, the company has quickly established itself as a GSMA-certified Mobile Virtual Network Operator (MVNO) in nine countries, with operations regulated in 42 countries and coverage in over 190 countries.

The company offers a wide range of telecommunications products and services, including eSIM solutions, IoT connectivity, business roaming, and financial compliance services. 1GLOBAL''s unique global core network supports voice, data, and SMS services, allowing enterprises to manage their communications seamlessly under a single contract. With a dedicated network operations center in Lisbon, Portugal, the company ensures high service quality and reliability, boasting a network availability of 99.9%. 1GLOBAL serves various customers, including global enterprises, financial institutions, IoT device manufacturers, and tech companies, providing them with secure and scalable communication solutions.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ca5a3596-5c35-4ecd-836a-240121e34003.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-07 12:26:12.201+00', 'workable', '1global', null), ('2305', 'Ambue', 'Ambue Ltd', 'https://www.ambue.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ambue', 'Ambue is a UK-based tech startup founded in 2020, located in Thame, Oxfordshire. The company specializes in software solutions that assist Registered Social Landlords (RSLs) in achieving government Net Zero targets and enhancing energy efficiency in their housing stock. Ambue offers a digital platform that automates the retrofit process for social housing, covering survey, analysis, design, and specification phases. Their technology utilizes LiDAR scanning and 3D digital Building Information Modeling (BIM) to gather comprehensive data in a single survey, minimizing the need for multiple site visits.

The platform provides detailed insights into each property''s building safety, quality, and sustainability, along with cost/benefit analyses for various retrofit measures. It supports compliance with the Quality Assured PAS 2035 guidance, helping landlords improve Energy Performance Certificate (EPC) ratings and Standard Assessment Procedure (SAP) scores. Ambue''s services are designed for social housing providers, enabling them to efficiently decarbonize their housing portfolios and contribute to climate change mitigation efforts.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/ed529ec4-14d5-4abe-a9e8-273c86e4349c.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2306', 'Blue Light Card', 'Blue Light Card Limited', 'https://www.bluelightcard.co.uk/en', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/blue-light-card', 'Blue Light Card is a UK-based company founded in 2008 and headquartered in Leicester. It serves the "Blue Light" community, which includes emergency services, NHS staff, social care workers, armed forces personnel, and teachers. The company operates a membership-based discount marketplace that provides access to over 15,000 discounts from various partner brands, both online and in physical stores.

Members can enjoy savings across a wide range of categories, including retail, travel, insurance, entertainment, dining, and holidays. The Blue Light Card app and website offer a virtual card for easy access to these offers, along with exclusive deals, free tickets, and unique experiences like sporting events and concerts. Eligible individuals can join by verifying their status and paying a membership fee of £4.99 for two years of access. 

Blue Light Card is committed to supporting public service workers and educators, providing them with valuable benefits through a straightforward membership model and a user-friendly digital platform.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/320389c3-4072-47f0-8ee9-c63894dae573.png', 'true', 'Medium-sized company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2307', 'Cohesity', 'Cohesity International UK Limited', 'https://www.cohesity.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cohesity', 'Cohesity, Inc. is an American information technology company based in San Jose, California, with additional offices in India and Ireland. Founded in June 2013 by Mohit Aron, Cohesity specializes in simplifying data management and protection for enterprises.

The company offers a converged secondary storage platform and a range of software solutions that help IT professionals backup, manage, and analyze data across various systems and cloud environments. Their product lineup includes DataProtect for backup and recovery, DataHawk for data security and governance, and FortKnox, a SaaS-based air-gapped data protection service. Cohesity''s platform supports multiple virtual environments and databases, as well as major cloud providers.

Cohesity serves various industries, including financial services, healthcare, and government, focusing on protecting critical enterprise data. Their solutions encompass backup and recovery, disaster recovery, long-term retention, and data security, among others. The leadership team includes founder Mohit Aron and CEO Sanjay Poonen, who guide the company''s growth in data management and cybersecurity.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f153ca10-ab85-4c7b-a6de-86f8ca4f6dcc.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2308', 'Daihatsu Infinearth', 'Daihatsu Infinearth (Europe) Ltd.', 'https://www.d-infi.com/en/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/daihatsu-infinearth-europe', 'DAIHATSU INFINEARTH (EUROPE) LTD. is the European branch of DAIHATSU INFINEARTH MFG. CO., LTD. Previously known as DAIHATU DIESEL, in May 2025 our group changed our name, combing "Infinity" and "Earth" to showcase our core ideals of environmental sustainability and sustainable business. Through creativity and flexible thinking, we look to enrich lives with technology through low environmental impact fuels and electrification.  INFINEARTH: Driving progress, to enrich society.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/d40f40ac-6287-49f4-ad35-dbb55abe6bbb.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:01.557015+00', null, null, null), ('2309', 'Plain', 'Not Just Tickets Ltd', 'https://www.plain.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/plainsupport', 'Plain is an AI-powered customer support platform tailored for engineering-heavy B2B teams. It consolidates various support channels like Slack, Teams, and Discord into a single, intuitive interface, allowing teams to provide scalable support with enterprise-grade security compliance, including GDPR and SOC2 Type II.

The platform integrates live product data into support workflows, enabling agents to access real-time customer information such as subscription status and usage metrics directly within the support interface. Key features include a unified support inbox, AI-driven workflow automation, collaboration tools for internal communication, and deep integrations with tools like Slack, Linear, Stripe, and Jira. Plain also offers advanced reporting and analytics to track key performance metrics, ensuring teams can prioritize their work effectively.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '8', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/feb55e44-ac73-4a18-8d18-e2ef22bceb51.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', null, null, null), ('2310', 'du Boulay Projects', 'du Boulay Projects Ltd', 'https://duboulay.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/du-boulay-projects-limited', 'du Boulay Projects is a main contractor with over 50 years of experience, specializing in the hospitality, commercial fit-out, and refurbishment sectors. Based in the Royal Victoria Patriotic Building in Wandsworth, London, the company has a strong reputation for delivering high-end fit-outs for restaurants, bars, hotels, offices, casinos, airport lounges, and retail units across the UK and Europe.

The company offers a range of services, including commercial fit-out and refurbishment, interior construction, and structural and decorative work. They focus on high-quality finishes and craftsmanship, employing skilled tradesmen experienced in materials like hardwood, marble, and architectural metalwork. du Boulay Projects collaborates closely with leading design and architectural practices, often resulting in award-shortlisted projects. With a dedicated team, they handle complex projects in challenging environments, ensuring exceptional results for their clients.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/df3b842e-6cb2-4726-86a2-5f123b1fb578.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', null, null, null), ('2311', 'ZoomInfo', 'ZoomInfo UK LTD', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zoominfo', 'ZoomInfo Technologies Inc. is a prominent American software and data company based in Vancouver, Washington. Originally founded as DiscoverOrg in 2007, it rebranded to ZoomInfo in 2019 after acquiring Zoom Information, Inc. The company specializes in providing business intelligence and go-to-market intelligence solutions for sales, marketing, operations, and recruiting teams.

ZoomInfo offers a cloud-based platform that aggregates detailed profiles of individuals and companies, delivering a comprehensive view of organizations. Its core product is the go-to-market intelligence platform, which integrates data, analytics, and AI-driven insights. Key offerings include RevOS, a modern operating system for revenue professionals, and ZoomInfo Copilot, an AI-powered assistant that helps sales teams optimize their efforts. With over 15,000 customers and approximately 202,000 paid users, ZoomInfo is dedicated to enhancing business growth through accurate B2B data and advanced analytics.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f2d914ba-1c0e-4b3e-a118-5af02a6da560.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:04.042781+00', 'greenhouse', 'zoominfo', null), ('2312', 'Justified Studio', 'Justified Studio LTD', 'https://justified.studio/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/justifiedstudio', 'Justified Studio is a full-service creative agency based in Oldham, Greater Manchester, with a presence in London. Founded in 2019, the agency specializes in strategy, design, and technology, focusing on supporting purpose-driven organizations that aim for social and environmental progress. The team is dedicated to transparency, authenticity, and activism, aligning their work with values that address climate change and social impact.

The founders, Joshua Ogden, Luke Patton, and William Whiting, bring extensive experience in creative direction and design, having collaborated with notable clients such as the United Nations, Google, and FIFA. Justified Studio offers a range of services, including creative strategy, visual identity design, technology solutions for storytelling, and consulting for startups and established organizations. They also run Justified Ventures, which accelerates early-stage businesses through their expertise in strategy and design. The agency is committed to helping clients amplify their authentic brand stories and drive positive change globally.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/f922ede6-05b8-4491-8f0b-a76ffa7af555.png', 'true', 'Small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('2313', 'Kodamai', 'Kodamai Limited', 'https://www.kodamai.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kodamai', 'Kodamai is transforming the digital economy with its Proprietary AI-driven Platform for orchestrating AI agents to autonomously learn, collaborate, and manage complex tasks by blending neurosymbolic-AI with customer data and large language models. Reflecting recent insights from Lux Capital, Kodamai addresses challenges such as AI imperfection at scale, the gap between research and enterprise adoption, and the importance of user experience and workflow integration over model differentiation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/00f5234b-67a2-476e-8141-7106c382fb7e.png', 'true', 'Very small company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('2314', 'OSRL', 'OSRL (Oil Spill Response Limited)', 'https://www.osrl.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/oil-spill-response-ltd', 'OSRL (Oil Spill Response Ltd) is the largest industry-funded cooperative focused on oil spill preparedness and response. Established in 1984, it is owned by 44 leading global oil and gas companies dedicated to environmental responsibility. With over 40 years of experience, OSRL operates from 13 strategic locations worldwide and employs nearly 300 professionals, including oil industry experts and environmental scientists.

The organization collaborates with its members and industry stakeholders to enhance global oil spill response capabilities. OSRL provides a comprehensive range of services, including rapid spill response, contingency planning, modeling and sensitivity mapping, equipment hire, and personnel support. It also offers specialized wildlife response services and advanced subsea well intervention capabilities. OSRL is committed to training and exercises, ensuring that its members are prepared for potential spill scenarios. With a strong global presence, OSRL is recognized for its integrated solutions that minimize the environmental impact of oil spills.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/eae45b86-ba9b-40fc-9c77-749c9f94727a.png', 'true', 'Large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('2317', 'Cisco', 'Cisco International Limited', 'https://www.cisco.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cisco', 'Cisco Systems, founded in 1984 by Leonard Bosack and Sandy Lerner, is a global leader in networking hardware and technology solutions. Based in San Jose, California, Cisco has significantly influenced modern internet infrastructure by providing essential products that enable secure and reliable communication for businesses and organizations worldwide.

The company offers a wide range of networking technologies, including routers, switches, and wireless systems, which are vital for enterprise and service provider networks. Cisco also provides advanced data center products, cybersecurity solutions, and collaboration tools like WebEx and Cisco Jabber. Additionally, its Internet of Things (IoT) platforms help organizations collect and analyze real-time data to enhance operational efficiency. Cisco serves a diverse clientele, including small businesses, large enterprises, government agencies, and educational institutions, supporting critical infrastructure across various industries. With annual revenues exceeding $53 billion as of 2024, Cisco remains a leader in networking technology and digital transformation.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6c62abe9-a109-40a7-b153-a946788688e7.png', 'true', 'Very large company', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', 'workday', 'Cisco_Careers', null), ('2318', 'Alkimi', 'Alchemy Exchange Ltd', 'https://www.alkimi.org', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/alkimi-exchange', 'Alkimi Exchange Ltd is a pioneering company based in the City of London, United Kingdom, recognized as the world’s first decentralized advertising exchange. The company aims to enhance the programmatic advertising industry by promoting a fair value exchange among advertisers, publishers, and users. Alkimi''s platform is built on a custom layer 2 scaling solution using the Ethereum blockchain, which ensures complete transparency, low transaction fees, and scalability.Alkimi offers a decentralized ad exchange that connects advertisers and publishers in real-time, improving the efficiency and economic viability of advertising. The company also focuses on the tokenization of digital ads, providing a transparent ledger for validating transactions. With a commitment to sustainability, Alkimi''s platform reduces energy consumption and carbon emissions compared to traditional advertising technologies. The company operates internationally, serving clients in various countries and fostering an ethical and inclusive advertising ecosystem.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/35f5df64-4613-4fea-9121-c50282d66947.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2319', 'Anesi Advisors', 'ANESI ADVISORS', 'https://anesiadvisors.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/anesi-advisors', 'Anesi Advisors is a boutique investment and M&A advisory firm based in London. The company specializes in serving small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and lower mid-market business owners, particularly focusing on founder-led companies. Anesi Advisors aims to connect with entrepreneurs to help them achieve optimal outcomes when selling their businesses.The firm provides merger and acquisition advisory services, guiding business owners through the complexities of selling or merging their companies. Anesi Advisors emphasizes personalized service and close collaboration with clients, often working with high-growth companies in the technology and healthcare sectors. Incorporated in November 2023, Anesi Advisors is a micro-sized private limited company with fewer than 10 employees.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/3133f59d-c1be-4436-a76e-d1a1cb0f322e.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2320', 'Aubury’s', 'Aubury and Associates Limited', 'https://www.auburys.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/auburys-associates', 'Aubury''s are the trusted supplier for clients in the UK and abroad with over 35 years'' experience in a huge range of gallery, exhibition and specialist museum services. Our services include Exhibitions, Fairs & Custom Stands, Renovations, Gallery Services, Design Services, Display Furniture, Electrics & Lighting, and AV & Graphics.We''re a family business of experienced gallery, exhibition and event specialists, supported by a highly-skilled and carefully selected workshop team. Call or email us to find out how we can help you.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/6be716fb-dbdc-4897-958c-56c02e84ab22.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:00.376782+00', null, null, null), ('2321', 'IonOpticks', 'Ion Opticks UK Ltd', 'https://ionopticks.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ionopticks', 'IonOpticks is an Australian biotechnology company based in Melbourne, established in 2017. The company specializes in developing and manufacturing advanced chromatography columns for liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry (LC-MS), focusing on proteomics research. IonOpticks has quickly become a global leader in high-performance nanoflow chromatography solutions that improve the sensitivity, accuracy, and throughput of mass spectrometry analyses.The flagship product line, the Aurora Series®, including the Generation 4 Aurora Series®, is designed to enhance mass spectrometry sensitivity and throughput. These chromatography columns are utilized in various applications, such as advanced proteomics and phosphoproteomics, allowing scientists and clinicians to achieve deeper insights in their analyses. IonOpticks also offers application notes and technical support to optimize the performance of their products with different mass spectrometry platforms.The company serves a diverse global research community, including pharmaceutical companies, academic institutions, and industry laboratories. IonOpticks is committed to innovation and quality, with a dedicated research and development team focused on expanding their product offerings and maintaining high standards in chromatography and proteomics.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/32a0dfa4-5f3e-40bd-b1c0-263338fd6236.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('2322', 'J.D. Power', 'J.D Power UK Limited', 'https://europe.jdpower.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jd-power-and-associates', 'J.D. Power is an American data analytics and consumer intelligence company founded in 1968 by James David Power III. It specializes in collecting and analyzing big data through consumer surveys to provide insights that help companies enhance their products and services. Initially focused on the automotive industry, J.D. Power pioneered customer satisfaction and quality studies, establishing standards like the U.S. Automotive Customer Satisfaction Index and the Initial Quality Study.The company conducts independent syndicated studies and market research across various sectors, including automotive, food, computers, and retail. Its research methodology involves gathering consumer feedback on product quality, customer satisfaction, and dealer experiences. J.D. Power''s products include syndicated studies and awards programs, which are widely recognized and utilized by manufacturers and service providers to promote quality and customer satisfaction. The company has expanded globally, with offices in several countries, and continues to help clients improve their offerings and brand reputation through its authoritative insights.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/22d5f41d-36da-4a84-badc-9433b9159a6f.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', 'bamboohr', 'autovista', null), ('2323', 'Reltio', 'Reltio UK Limited', 'https://www.reltio.com/eng-gb/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/reltio-inc', 'Reltio is a cloud-native software-as-a-service (SaaS) company that specializes in modern Master Data Management (MDM) solutions. Founded in 2011 by Manish Sood, Reltio focuses on addressing data fragmentation in large organizations by providing a platform that unifies, cleanses, enriches, and mobilizes enterprise data. Headquartered in Redwood Shores, California, the company employs over 400 people and serves Global 2000 enterprises across various industries.Reltio''s MDM platform integrates data from multiple sources to create a trusted data foundation, enabling real-time delivery to applications and analytics systems. The platform is agile and scalable, designed to adapt to fast-paced business environments. Reltio also offers industry-specific "velocity packs" for sectors like Life Sciences and Healthcare, which include prepackaged configurations to streamline MDM implementations. The company is recognized as a leader in the MDM space, with a customer base that includes many of the largest global companies in life sciences, healthcare, hospitality, and luxury goods.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '6', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/38fcc27c-dbf6-42cb-a641-22a4a34555b3.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:03.25189+00', 'greenhouse', 'reltio', null), ('2324', 'Mouthfull Food Trading Co.', 'The Mouthfull Trading Company', 'https://www.mouthfullfood.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mouthfull-food-trading-co', 'A white label food manufacturer for the hospitality, catering and public sectors. We help hospitality business save time, reduce costs and ensure consistency with our professional manufacturing food solution.We have a modern, BRC start-intermediate accredited production facility in west London that can produce over 30 tonnes of food a week. We specialise in curries, stews, pasta sauces, soups, sauces, marinades and dressings. Our current supply base includes casual dining restaurants, food to go, cafes, pub groups, sandwich/sushi manufacturers, butchers, holiday parks and fast food restaurants.We work across price points required and can work to brief or create dishes with our in house NPD team.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/company_icons/435e31f0-dd93-4021-9fc7-d0b6b4016159.png', 'true', null, '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', '2026-03-03 15:44:02.529791+00', null, null, null), ('2325', 'Triton Restoration', 'Triton Restoration Limited', 'https://www.tritonrestoration.co.uk', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/triton-restoration', 'Triton Restoration is a specialist restoration contractor founded in 1989, focusing on external façade restoration and the refurbishment of historic buildings in London, Greater London, and South East England. The company is known for its expertise in complex restoration projects, having worked on notable landmarks such as the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and Lancaster House. Triton Restoration is committed to client satisfaction and quality craftsmanship, supported by a skilled team of masons and restorers.The company offers a range of services, including principal contractor roles, external façade restoration, project management, and consultancy related to restoration and conservation. Triton Restoration works with traditional materials like natural stone and terracotta, employing sensitive techniques that respect the architectural integrity of heritage buildings. Their clientele includes government bodies, heritage organizations, and architects, reflecting their strong presence in the preservation of historic sites. Triton Restoration holds several accreditations, emphasizing quality management, environmental responsibility, and a commitment to health and safety.', 'The company is a licensed sponsor.', '4', '0', 'https://jbuikhbssecxhfunkaol.supabase.co/storage/